(1443, 4, '2009-10-23 09:23:28', '2009-10-23 07:23:28', '<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>10.23.09</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>Paris. Street Style. </em><em><span style="color: #888888;">Week #6. Post 3.</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;">There are some outfits that are just not meant for everyone. No matter how much we gawk and loathe over something, it may just not be right. </span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;">For example, our street style lady of the day. I love this. Love it. Very chic, yet funky, original and well-put together. The lines, the curves and the proportions work perfectly. This woman knows how to work unique shapes and lines and make them work like you never thought they could. </span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;">Yet, if I tried putting ruffles and imitation croc skin leggings together, I would look like one. hot. mess... (That is one is for you B.)</span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;">To our bead lady, merci beaucoup.</span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;">Bon weekend tous. </span></span></p>\