(1466, 4, '2009-10-26 15:50:33', '2009-10-26 14:50:33', '<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>10.26.09</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>Paris. Street Style. </em><em><span style="color: #888888;">Week #7. Post 1.</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #000000;">There are some trends I dislike. Some I understand. Some I love. I wonder sometimes if the influence of a trend is eventually inevitable? And I don''t mean a 100% influence, it could be just 10% influence...but is it inevitable? In one form or another, it may just be. </span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #000000;">Manon. Manon is a perfect example someone who wears a trend. Ripped tights and/or leggings were something of a ''big thing'' here in Paris back in the Spring. I was not a huge fan, however I did find myself, without even realizing it, wearing black tights-socks with jeans which were partially ripped. The runs were apart of my ''hard-knock'' style I was feeling for the day. So, was I influenced? </span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #000000;">I would say, surely. </span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #000000;">Besides the trends, Manon is an awesome character of a woman who mixes and matches trends, styles, times and passions. This is why she caught our eye. Not for ripped tights and cut-offs, but for an all original tee, one-feather earring and layer of black stone necklaces. </span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;">So, the appreciation for today. Originality and a fantastic melange. Merci pour le melange. </span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;">____________</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Below: <span style="color: #000000;">MANON GINGOLD</span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #999999;">Seen:<span style="color: #000000;">Jardin Tuileres</span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Photographer:</span> Valentina Frugiuele</span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Wearing:</span> The t-shirt is an ode to<a href="http://joydivision.homestead.com/" target="_blank">Joy Division</a> (English rock band formed in 1976 &amp; broken in 1980 when lead singer committed suicide), the jacket is BelAir, shorts and tights/leggings are self made... she re-invented old jeans and finished off the tights. The bag is vintage, the layered necklaces are a mix of her grandma and mums jewlery plus a piece from <a href="http://www.hm.com/" target="_blank">H&amp;M</a> (oh how the old and new world''s collide), the one feather earring is from a street vendor in <a href="http://www.unionsquarenyc.org/" target="_blank">NYC''s Union SQ</a>.</span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Choices From the Boutique: <a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/leigh-amp-luca-cashmere-scarf.html" target="_blank">Leigh &amp; Luca cashmere &amp; silk scarf</a>, <a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/world-landmarks-acrylic-ring-set-white.html" target="_blank">Plastique* white acrylic world landmark ring set</a> &amp; <a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/lisa-levine-awaken-the-hunt-brass.html" target="_blank">Lisa Levine''s Saber necklace</a>. </em></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_1468" align="aligncenter" width="420" caption="Paris Street Style. Manon."]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1468" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/10/26/paris-street-style-the-tights/manon-paris-streer-style/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1468 " title="Manon-Paris-Street-Style" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/Manon-Paris-Streer-Style.jpg" alt="Paris Street Style. Manon. " width="420" height="820" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1469" align="alignleft" width="240" caption="Leigh &amp; Luca Cashmere Scarf"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1469" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/10/26/paris-street-style-the-tights/leigh-and-luca-cashmere-scarf-2/" target="_blank"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1469      " title="leigh-and-luca-cashmere-scarf" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/leigh-and-luca-cashmere-scarf1-300x300.jpg" alt="Leigh &amp; Luca Cashmere Scarf" width="240" height="240" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1470" align="alignright" width="240" caption="Plastique* World Landmarks Acrylic Ring Set"]<a href="http://www.icuinparis.com" target="_blank"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1470 " title="plastique-acrylic-set-of-rings" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/plastique-acrylic-set-of-rings-300x300.jpg" alt="Plastique* World Landmarks Acrylic Ring Set" width="240" height="240" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-size: small;">\n</span></span>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1472" align="aligncenter" width="300" caption="Lisa Levine Saber Necklace"]<a href="http://www.icuinparis.com" target="_blank"><img class="size-full wp-image-1472 " title="lisa-levine-saber-necklace" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/lisa-levine-saber-necklace1.jpg" alt="Lisa Levine Saber Necklace" width="300" height="300" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><em> </em></span></em></span></em></p>\n<em><em> </em></em>\n\n<em><em> </em></em>\n\n<em><em> </em></em>\n\n<em><em> </em></em>\n\n<em><em> </em></em>\n\n<em><em> </em></em>\n\n<em><em> </em></em>\n\n<em><em> </em></em>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1467" align="aligncenter" width="395" caption="Manon &amp; the feather. Paris Street Style."]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1467" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/10/26/paris-street-style-the-tights/feather-and-tights-paris-street-style/"><img class="size-large wp-image-1467  " title="feather-and-tights-paris-street-style" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/feather-and-tights-paris-street-style-617x1024.jpg" alt="Manon &amp; the feather. Paris Street Style." width="395" height="655" /></a>[/caption]\n\n</em></em>', 'Paris Street Style &amp; The Tights. ', 'Paris Street style is what we love here. This is the real independent fashion and unique style. This is why we opened the boutique; for creative, unique and independent style and fashion. Paris street style is an amazing place to find this creativity on a daily basis. This is why we bring our camera everywhere because the streets of paris are filled. Manon. Today''s street style lady. ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'paris-street-style-the-tights', '', '', '2009-10-26 15:50:33', '2009-10-26 14:50:33', '', 0, 'https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/?p=1466', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1483, 4, '2009-10-28 16:33:20', '2009-10-28 15:33:20', '<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>10.28.09</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>Paris. Street Style. </em><em><span style="color: #888888;">Week #7. Post 2.</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">Shapes. Geometrics. Curves &amp; curvatures. There is an amazing exhibit right now at the </span><a href="http://www.musee-orsay.fr/fr/collections/histoire-des-collections/arts-decoratifs.html" target="_blank"><span style="color: #000000;">Muse d''Orsay on Art Nouveau</span></a><span style="color: #000000;">. Really very inspiring. I have literally entered a curvature state of mind...</span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">Not to get off topic...shapes, geometrics, lines, patterns. This is what makes fashion, style, beauty. The way you wear a dress can change the way the curves of your body take form. With a simple cinch at the waist or the placement of a seam-line you are able to manipulate shapes &amp; sizes. </span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;"><span style="color: #999999;"><em>Without lines fashion would be lost.</em></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">So, today we pay hommage to Natalie. Wearing simply black. Normally this to me is a bit boring, but take note to the shapes...the texture of her sweater &amp; the way it frames...bringing your eye to her mid-line where she tied a rope belt to cinch and create more shape in the dress. The necklace is well chosen. A statement piece on a simple template. Not too much and just enough to take notice. The sunglasses as the only color. Vintage. Love them. And the ring. Simple, clean, relative to the necklace but not matching.</span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #808080;">Font appel aux sens plus qu''a la raison...</span><em><span style="color: #808080;">Appealing more to sense than reason.</span></em></span></em></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;">____________</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Below: </span><span style="color: #999999;">NATALIE</span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #999999;">Seen:<span style="color: #000000;">Jardin Tuileres</span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Photographer:</span> Valentina Frugiuele</span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Wearing:</span> <a href="http://www.hm.com/" target="_blank">H&amp;M</a> dress, vintage shoes, <a href="http://www.fiorella.fi/index.htm" target="_blank">Fiorellas</a> sweater, <a href="http://rubell.wordpress.com/2009/04/28/my-vintage-sunglasses/" target="_blank">Rg (vintage)</a> sunglasses, the necklace is from one of my favorite boutiques in NYC,<a href="http://www.oaknyc.com/" target="_blank">OAK</a> &amp; a <a href="http://www.marcjacobs.com/" target="_blank">Marc Jacobs</a> ring</span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><em><span style="color: #999999;">Choices From the Boutique: <span style="color: #000000;"><a title="leigh and luca, icuinparis.com" href="http://www.icuinparis.com/white-cotton-scarf-with-embroidery.html" target="_blank">Leigh &amp; Luca hand embroidered designer scarf</a>, <a title="tracy matthews, skull necklace, icuinparis.com" href="http://www.icuinparis.com/silver-skull-black-diamond.html" target="_blank">Tracy Matthews oxidized silver &amp; black diamond necklace</a> &amp; <a title="anna beck, icuinparis.com" href="http://www.icuinparis.com/catalogsearch/result/?q=anna+beck" target="_blank">Anna Beck hand crafted silver and 14k gold cocktail ring</a>. </span></span></em></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;">&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_1485" align="aligncenter" width="420" caption="Natalie. Paris and the Curvature street style."]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1485" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/10/28/paris-street-style-balls-of-jewelry/natali