]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1484" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/10/28/paris-street-style-balls-of-jewelry/natalie-parist-street-style/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1484  " title="Natalie-Parist-Street-Style" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/Natalie-Parist-Street-Style.jpg" alt="Natalie. Black but shapely Street Style." width="420" height="825" /></a>[/caption]', 'Paris Street Style. Balls of Jewelry.', 'Paris Street style. Natalie is our style victim of the day and a perfect example of simple lines made to be creative and unique. We love street style because it is where we can find the reason why you wear what you wear and why. We love that. Street style is our opportunity to pay hommage to the real fashionistas of this world and find out what they know about the best boutiques and indie designers of the world. ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'paris-street-style-balls-of-jewelry', '', '', '2009-10-28 16:33:20', '2009-10-28 15:33:20', '', 0, 'https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/?p=1483', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1498, 4, '2009-10-30 18:26:02', '2009-10-30 17:26:02', '<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>10.30.09</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>Paris. Street Style. </em><em><span style="color: #888888;">Week #7. Post 3.</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #000000;">Everyday we leave our home with no idea of what will happen. Our days can be what we make them, but there is always a moment, a second, an hour that is out of our control. Sometimes that second changes your life. Sometimes that hour is everything we were looking for. </span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #000000;">You never know.</span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">This week I came across three ladies. Their style is not eccentric, but I would define it as unique, original &amp; thought-provoking. I wanted to know more about them. After I stopped them, I found a story to each one. </span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">Grandmother'' scarf, vintage bag, designer friends, and designer. I had no idea I would stop these women who were so relevant to what I do for this business. We search for independent designers everyday, but we don''t always meet them face to face. </span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;"><span style="color: #000000;">So, to our trio &amp; their stories. Happy vendredi. </span></span></span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;">Bon weekend tous. Oh yeah, &amp; happy halloween.</span></span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;">____________</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Below (left to right): <span style="color: #000000;">SARAH, MARIA &amp; NATALIA</span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #999999;">Seen: <span style="color: #000000;">Rue Raspail</span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Photographer:</span> Christan Summers</span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Wearing: <span style="color: #999999;">From left to right:</span><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;"> SARA: Jeans from <a href="http://www.nudiejeans.com/start" target="_blank">Nudie</a>, Grey shirt from <a href="http://shop.hm.com/" target="_blank">H&amp;M</a>, shoes from <a href="http://shop.hm.com/" target="_blank">H&amp;M</a>. &amp; jacket froma swedish store called <a href="http://www.carlings.no/" target="_blank">Carlings</a>. Bag, vintage. <span style="color: #000000;">"I love vintage bags, they look so much better then the new ones." </span>Scarf from a swedish store <a href="http://indiska.com/" target="_blank">Indiska</a>. </span></span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;">MARIA: Wool scarf was her Grandmother''s...vintage yet perfect for this season''s love of chunky and wool scarves. Clothes from random vintage boutiques as well.<span style="color: #999999;"> <span style="color: #000000;">"I like wearing vintage stuff such as my bag and my scarf because they add a personal feeling to the outfit."</span><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></span></span></span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;">NATALIA: Is in fact a designer with a studio in Edinburg, Scotland. Her brand is <a href="http://www.misslin.co.uk/" target="_blank">Natalia Misslin Designs</a> &amp; she designs bridal wear, jewelry, &amp; in fact she designed and created the jacket she was wearing. You may visit her site <a href="http://www.misslin.co.uk/" target="_blank">HERE</a> to view her designs. </span></span></span></span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padd