(1550, 4, '2009-11-04 18:30:59', '2009-11-04 17:30:59', '<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>11.04.09</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>Paris.<span style="color: #ff0000;"> </span>Street Style. </em><em><span style="color: #888888;">Week #8. Post 2. </span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;">People from home often ask me what one of my favorite parts of Paris is. There are many, of course, but I always think of things that I cannot necessarily have at home. One thing in particular being men who dress like Drischel (street style man pour le jour). That of course is not a insult to my Boston boys...yet, we all know many of them would only be caught dead in a light violet sweater and scarf from mom. </span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;">European men dress well. And very well when they wear </span><a href="http://www.finsbury-shoes.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #000000;">Finsbury chaussures</span></a><span style="color: #000000;">. Of course great bone structure doesn''t hurt and the french accent to match...but we won''t go there. </span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;">There is a different point of view here on the way people express them self through fashion. </span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;">And on that note, our street style of the day, Drischel &amp; Ornella. A shy yet beautiful couple. A man who wears his style oh so well and a woman who dresses in a feminine yet comfortable manner. I would however love to have seen a bit more accessories, but you can''t have it all. </span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;">Merci encore  ces deux couples. </span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><a href="www.cinsummer.com" target="_blank"></a>____________</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Below: <span style="color: #000000;">DRISCHEL &amp; ORNELLA</span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Seen:<span style="color: #000000;"><a href="http://www.parismarais.com/" target="_blank">Le Marais</a></span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Photographer:</span> Christan Summers</span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">He''s Wearing: <span style="color: #000000;"><a href="http://www.finsbury-shoes.com/" target="_blank">Finsbury</a> shoes, <a href="http://www.smalto.com/accueil.php?langage=gb" target="_blank">Smalto</a> Belt, <a href="http://www.massimodutti.com/" target="_blank">Massimo Dutti </a>Sweater and a scarf from mum. ''sigh''. </span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">She''s Wearing: <span style="color: #000000;">Clothing and leather jacket from small boutiques around Paris &amp; London &amp; her bag is from <a href="http://www.monsoon.co.uk/page/acchome" target="_blank">Accessorize</a>. </span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Choices From the Boutique:</span> <a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/philip-crangi-geometric-silver-cuff-links.html" target="_blank">Giles &amp; Brother silver geometric cuff links </a>, <a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/lisa-levine-soft-leather-and-silver-chain-headbands.html" target="_blank">Lisa Levine Falling Rain earrings</a> &amp; <a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/lisa-levine-waterfall-chain-earrings.html" target="_blank">Lisa Levine silver and leather headband.</a></span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<em><em> </em></em>\n\n<em><em> </em></em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1551" align="aligncenter" width="420" caption="Paris Street Style. One beautiful couple."]<a rel="