/a-different-kind-of-street-style-paris/time-track/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1589  " title="time-track" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/time-track.jpg" alt="Time Track" width="480" height="694" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1590" align="aligncenter" width="600" caption="eyes."]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1590" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/06/a-different-kind-of-street-style-paris/the-eye/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1590  " title="the-eye" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/the-eye.jpg" alt="eyes." width="600" height="399" /></a>[/caption]\n\n</em></em>\n\n<em><span style="font-style: normal;"> </span></em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em> </em></p>\n<em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1591" align="aligncenter" width="600" caption="Can you see what I see?"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1591" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/06/a-different-kind-of-street-style-paris/can-u-see-it/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1591  " title="can-u-see-it)" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/can-u-see-it.jpg" alt="Can you see what I see?" width="600" height="367" /></a>[/caption]\n\n</em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em> </em></p>\n<em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1592" align="aligncenter" width="540" caption="3 blind men. "]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1592" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/06/a-different-kind-of-street-style-paris/3-blind-men/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1592  " title="3-blind-men" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/3-blind-men.jpg" alt="3 blind men. " width="540" height="359" /></a>[/caption]\n\n</em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em> </em></p>\n<em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1601" align="aligncenter" width="540" caption="les cles."]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1601" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/06/a-different-kind-of-street-style-paris/keys/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1601  " title="keys" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/keys.jpg" alt="les cles." width="540" height="347" /></a>[/caption]\n\n</em>\n\n<em><em>\n</em></em>', 'A Different Kind of Street Style. Paris.', 'Today I wanted to do something different. So far I have posted ''street style'' as people. Fashion. Accessories. Yes, of course this what ''street style'' has been defined as, however, there is also a different kind of street style in Paris. This particular street style I don''t believe is given enough credit.\n\nIt is an art which has fed my inspiration and the inspiration of many other.\n\nStreet art. Our street style of the day. The artists are unknown. Anonymous. This is an underground society of artists that are truly talented and who have done this for years. Sometimes I wonder how many layers of art are under the one image I capture? Can you imagine? Hundreds, if not thousands...depending upon the age of the wall I suppose. ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-different-kind-of-street-style-paris', '', '', '2009-11-06 17:42:49', '2009-11-06 16:42:49', '', 0, 'https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/?p=1586', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1605, 4, '2009-11-09 11:47:21', '2009-11-09 10:47:21', '<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>11.06.09</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>Paris.<span style="color: #ff0000;"> </span>Street Style. </em><em><span style="color: #888888;">Week #9. Post 1.</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #000000;">It'' s true you know. It is the little things that count. The small details, the bursts of color, the unobtrusive. </span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #000000;">Every person has a different idea of how to accessorize them self. Of course. To each his/her own. And always, it''s the details, the fine lines, that catch my eye. Hand-stitched buttons, brooches, safety pins, layered vintage necklaces, laces. Laces. </span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #000000;">Stella and her red laces. I like details because people who create details are often those who love to get dressed, love to accessorize, care to wear what they wear. Does that makes sense? </span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #000000;"> Karin and her leopard. Monique and her maroon. Some details are less obvious than others. Some are made just for an accent, to make a contrast and/or a statement. It is fantastic how one detail can change an entire outfit. </span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Hence, our love for accessories. </em></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #000000;">So, to our three detailed ladies of the day. Bon lundi tous. </span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;">____________</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Below:<span style="color: #000000;">STELLA, KARIN, MONIQUE</span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Seen: <span style="color: #000000;">Blvd Raspail</span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Photographer:</span> Christan Summers</span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Wearing (from left to right): <span style="color: #000000;">STELLA:</span> <span style="color: #000000;"><a href="http://www.brunobanani.de/" target="_blank">Bruno Banani </a> eyeglasses, <a href="http://www.zara.com/" target="_blank">Zara</a> studded jacket &amp; her red laces were found in a fabric store in Iceland (where she is from). KARIN: Vintage bag, vintage shoes, leopard leggings from <a href="http://www.hm.com/" target="_blank">H&amp;M</a> and shoes are <a href="h