eah-Paris-Street-style" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/Woo-Yeah-Paris-Street-style.jpg" alt="Paris Street Style. Woo Yeah. " width="510" height="659" /></a>[/caption]\n\n</em></em>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;"> </span></span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<em><em> </em></em>\n\n<em><em> </em></em>\n\n<em><em> </em></em>\n\n<em><em> </em></em>\n\n<em><em> </em></em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><em> </em></em></p>\n<em><em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1630" align="aligncenter" width="420" caption="Woo Yeah and his Special Bag. "]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1630" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/11/paris-street-style-he-is-fabulous/paris-street-style-beads-and-bags/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1630   " title="paris-street-style-beads-and-bags" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/paris-street-style-beads-and-bags.jpg" alt="Woo Yeah and his Bag. " width="420" height="721" /></a>[/caption]\n\n</em></em>', 'Paris Street style. He is Fabulous.', 'A word related to so many different instances, people, places, etc. Descriptive to the max and filled with any amount of emotion you want to say it with. Like this one: Woo Yeah is Fabulous.\n\nThat''s not one you see everyday.\n\nThe point exactly. Woo yeah,  yes, that is his name and a man who I wish you all could have spoken to as well. Energy, life, excitement and his ''special bag from Korea.''', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'paris-street-style-he-is-fabulous', '', '', '2009-11-11 19:17:48', '2009-11-11 18:17:48', '', 0, 'https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/?p=1628', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1641, 4, '2009-11-13 20:21:39', '2009-11-13 19:21:39', '<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>11.13.09</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>Paris.<span style="color: #ff0000;"> </span>Street Style. </em><em><span style="color: #888888;">Week #9. Post 3. </span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #000000;">I just realized it is Friday the 13th. I should probably post about black cats or something, but since I just remembered, that''s not going to happen. Instead I wanted to post images from the mini tour I gave today for my wonderful visitors from back home.</span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #000000;">A different view of Paris. Or a view of sorts, my view. I love this city for the fashion, bien sur, but as I posted last week, the inspiration is everywhere. It lies within the statues, monuments, windows, house boats on the Seine, the cars (for you B), the people, the people, the people. </span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #000000;">We of course paid a visit to the Tower and I couldn''t help myself to be fascinated with the men selling the infamous illegal trinkets. I even watched a tourist have their prized 2" Eiffel Tower taken from them by the Paris Police. The police yelled at them for buying and of course the sellers were no where to be found! Amazing how they disappear in an instant and reappear just as fast. </span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #000000;">It''s a culture, it is a way of life. New York City has the same. It fascinates me.</span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #000000;">So, street style of the day, something a bit out of the box, but an inspiration. </span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"> </span></em></p>\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1642" align="aligncenter" width="420" caption="A little play with photo-shop"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1642" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/13/paris-the-art-of-the-real/eiffel-the-birds/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1642   " title="eiffel-&amp;-the-birds" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/eiffel-the-birds.jpg" alt="I couldn''t help myself with playing with photoshop." width="420" height="631" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1648" align="aligncenter" width="360" caption="The man and his watches. "]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1648" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/13/paris-the-art-of-the-real/the-man-and-his-watches/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1648  " title="the-man-and-his-watches" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/the-man-and-his-watches.jpg" alt="The man and his watches. " width="360" height="541" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<em><span style="font-style: normal;">\n</span></em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1643" align="aligncenter" 