(1691, 4, '2009-11-18 20:44:13', '2009-11-18 19:44:13', '<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>11.18.09</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>Paris.<span style="color: #ff0000;"> </span>Street Style. </em><em><span style="color: #888888;">Week #10. Post 2.</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">This is the story of a lady and her stole. Not many times do you hear that, but you read it here. Segolene is her name and of course her style is one that I could not walk past without snapping. </span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">I find Paris to be an interesting city when it comes to color. There is a commonality, a color palette which is followed and loved here. Black. Navy blue. Grey. This is the norm. I am in no way saying their is a lack of creativity, not at all, there is just an appreciation for the simple creative. The chic, the sexy, the ''I look fantastic without even trying.'' </span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">I write this because when I see a women who does not necessarily follow that color palette and she still carries herself with an heir of confidence, I gravitate. I gravitated to Segolene. Actually, I ran after her...her style is the ind I LOVE to post. It is why I search for street style.</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">Fantastic in vintage finds and small boutique purchases, Segolene &amp; her stole. Our street style lady of the day. </span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #000000;">Merci beaucoup Segolene. </span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #000000;">____________</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Below: <span style="color: #000000;">SEGOLENE</span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Seen:<span style="color: #000000;">Boulevard Saint Germain</span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Photographer:</span> Christan Summers</span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Wearing: <span style="color: #000000;">Vintage fur cap and stole found in one of Paris''s sought after vintage shops...dan le Marais, vintage shoes and the small chain necklace is a gift.</span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #999999;">Choices From the Boutique: <span style="color: #000000;"><a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/gorjana-black-diamond-and-14k-solid-gold-neckla14.html" target="_blank">Gorjana black diamond necklace</a>, <a href="https://www.cinsummer.com/#/shop/product/feature031" target="_blank">ebb.and.pflow two-toned stud earrings</a> &amp; <a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/linda-levinson-snake-necklace.html" target="_blank">Linda Levinson snake and turquoise wrap necklace</a>.</span></span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_1693" align="aligncenter" width="360" caption="Paris street style. Segolene."]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1693" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/18/paris-street-style-the-lady-the-stole/segolene-paris-street-style-and-the-hat/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1693  " title="segolene-paris-street-style-and-the-hat" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/segolene-paris-street-style-and-the-hat.jpg" alt="Paris street style. Original." width="360" height="541" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em> </em></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_1692" align="aligncenter" width="360" caption="Our Lady &amp; The Stole"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1692" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/18/paris-street-style-the-lady-the-stole/segolene-paris-street-style/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1692  " title="segolene-paris-street-style" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/segolene-paris-street-style.jpg" alt="Our Lady &amp; The Stole" width="360" height="638" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1695" align="alignleft" width="230" caption="Gorjana Black Diamond Necklace"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1695" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/18/paris-street-style-the-lady-the-stole/gorjana-black-diamond-necklace-model/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1695    " title="Gorjana-black-diamond-necklace-model" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/Gorjana-black-diamond-necklace-model.jpg" alt="Gorjana Black Diamond Necklace" width="230" height="266" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1698" align="alignleft" width="270" caption="Linda Levinson Necklace"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1698" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/18/paris-street-style-the-lady-the-stole/linda-levinson-necklace/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1698  " title="linda-levinson-necklace" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/linda-levinson-necklace-300x258.jpg" alt="Linda Levinson Necklace" width="270" height="232" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1704" align="alignleft" width="219" caption="ebb.and.pflow two-toned studs"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1704" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/18/paris-street-style-the-lady-the-stole/ebbandpflow-en-lightning-two-toned-stud-earrings-2/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1704  " title="ebbandpflow-en-lightning-two-toned-stud-earrings" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/ebbandpflow-en-lightning-two-toned-stud-earrings1-243x300.jpg" alt="ebb.and.pflow two-toned studs" width="219" height="270" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1694" align="aligncenter" width="360" caption="Segolene&#39;s Vintage Shoes"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1694" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/18/paris-street-style-the-lady-the-stole/segolene-paris-street-style-and-the-fur/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1694  " title="segolene-paris-street-style-and-the-fur" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/segolene-paris-street-style-and-the-fur.jpg" alt="Segolene''s Vintage Shoes" width="360" height="563" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center;">------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>', 'Paris Street Style. The lady &amp; the Stole. ', 'This is the story of a lady and her stole. Not many times do you hear that, but you read it here. Segolene is her name and of course her style is one that I could not walk past without snapping.\n\nI find Paris to be an interesting city when it comes to color. There is a commonality, a color palette which is followed and loved here. Black. Navy blue. Grey. This is the norm. I am in no way saying their is a lack of creativity, not at all, there is just an appreciation for the simple creative. The chic, the sexy, the ''I look fantastic without even trying.''\n\nI write this because when I see a women who does not necessarily follow that color palette and she still carries herself with an heir of confidence, I gravitate. I gravitated to Segolene. Actually, I ran after her...her style is the ind I LOVE to post. It is why I search for street style.\n', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'paris-street-style-the-lady-the-stole', '', '', '2009-11-18 20:44:13', '2009-11-18 19:44:13', '', 0, 'https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/?p=1691', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1710, 4, '2009-11-20 17:48:54', '2009-11-20 16:48:54', '<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>11.20.09</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>Paris.<span style="color: #ff0000;"> </span>Street Style. </em><em><span style="color: #888888;">Week #10. Post 3. </span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">Today I was waiting for the light to change at a cross walk just next to St. Michel and my eyes were all of a sudden captured by a handful of silver. </span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">I looked, and it wasn''t just one handful, it was two plus chains, plus leather pants, plus lightning red leather ''space men'' boots. Oh, plus a cap full of tiny circle pins. The man. The incredible vision of pure funk, looked to be in his 40''s. </span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">I don''t know anything more than that because he vanished in the crowd and I had no ''real'' camera to run after him with and in a desperate attempt to catch a glimpse, I snapped a picture with my blackberry. I know, kind of sad, but I felt it was ever so necessary. </span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #000000;">____________</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Below:<span style="color: #000000;">Paris &amp; Bangkok funk. Anonymous.</span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Seen:<span style="color: #000000;">St. Michel, Paris &amp; Chatuchak Market, Bangkok. </span></span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Photographer:</span> Christan Summers</span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Wearing: <span style="color: #000000;">A lot</span>. </span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"> </span></em></p>\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em> </em></p>\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1711" align="aligncenter" width="480" caption="Full of funk. "]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1711" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/20/paris-bangkok-this-is-unusual-street-style/paris-man-on-the-street/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1711  " title="paris-man-on-the-street" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/paris-man-on-the-street.jpg" alt="Full of funk. " width="480" height="437" /></a>[/caption]\n\n</em>\n<p style="text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">So, here</span><span style="color: #888888;"> you are</span>. My street man and his array of funk. Literally, if I had been able to catch him today, I know I would have found him wearing just an array of surprises. However, in light of the situation, I remembered photos I have hidden away...waiting for the right time to un-surface. </em></p>\n<p style="text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;"><em>Bangkok street style. Pictures taken when I was there last year living and working on my collaborative jewelry collection. My design partner and I found these two in the <a href="http://www.bangkok.com/shopping-market/popular-markets.html" target="_blank">JJ Market</a> (AMAZING market!!!) and even though I was not blogging then, and had no reason to take their picture, I still asked if they would stop a moment and allow me to gawk.</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;"><em>We gawked. They stood. And check out all that they have on. It is unbelievable! This man is wearing solid ivory rings on each and every finger, beaded bracelets and necklaces for the both of them, stone rings upon stones necklaces and even the bags are covered in color, trinkets, and mirrors.</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;"><em>I am still shocked looking at the picture of these two. This is jewelry and accessories at one of the most exaggerated levels I have ever seen. </em></p>\n<p style="text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;"><em>Feast your eyes. You may feel the same. </em></p>\n<p style="text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;"><em>Happy Friday everyone. </em></p>\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em> </em></p>\n<em> </em>\n\n<em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1712" align="aligncenter" width="360" caption="Bangkok. Street Style. "]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1712" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/20/paris-bangkok-this-is-unusual-street-style/bankgkok-street-style-jewelry/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1712  " title="bankgkok-street-style-jewelry" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/bankgkok-street-style-jewelry.jpg" alt="Bangkok. Street Style. " width="360" height="516" /></a>[/caption]\n\n</em>\n\n<em><span style="font-style: normal;"> </span></em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em> </em></p>\n<em> </em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1713" align="aligncenter" width="360" caption="That&#39;s a lot of color."]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1713" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/20/paris-bangkok-this-is-unusual-street-style/bangkok-street-style-ladyboy/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1713   " title="bangkok-street-style-ladyboy" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/bangkok-street-style-ladyboy.jpg" alt="Lady or LadyBoy? Who cares. This is fantastic. " width="360" height="604" /></a>[/caption]\n\n</em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em> </em></p>\n<em> </em>\n\n<em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1715" align="aligncenter" width="360" caption="The Ivory Rings. Bangkok Street style."]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1715" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/20/paris-bangkok-this-is-unusual-street-style/bangkok-street-style-ivory-rings/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1715  " title="Bangkok-street-style-ivory-rings" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/Bangkok-street-style-ivory-rings.jpg" alt="The Ivory Rings. Bangkok Street style." width="360" height="542" /></a>[/caption]\n\n</em>', 'Paris. Bangkok. This is unusual street style. ', 'Bangkok street style. Pictures taken when I was there last year living and working on my collaborative jewelry collection. My design partner and I found these two in the JJ Market (AMAZING market!!!) and even though I was not blogging then, and had no reason to take their picture, I still asked if they would stop a moment and allow me to gawk.\n\nWe gawked. They stood. And check out all that they have on. It is unbelievable! This man is wearing solid ivory rings on each and every finger, beaded bracelets and necklaces for the both of them, stone rings upon stones necklaces and even the bags are covered in color, trinkets, and mirrors.\nI am still shocked looking at the picture of these two. This is jewelry and accessories at one of the most exaggerated levels I have ever seen.\n\nFeast your eyes. You may feel the same.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'paris-bangkok-this-is-unusual-street-style', '', '', '2009-11-20 17:48:54', '2009-11-20 16:48:54', '', 0, 'https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/?p=1710', 0, 'post', '', 0),
