(1764, 4, '2009-11-25 11:35:41', '2009-11-25 10:35:41', '<em>11.24.09</em>\n\n<em>This is Magic. United Artists. </em>\n\n<em><a href="http://www.wmagazine.com/" target="_blank">W Magazine United Artists Cover Shoot</a>. </em>\n\n<em>Stated as a magazine about photography. </em><em><span style="color: #888888;">I have always loved W Magazine for that reason and this month especially. The December issue focuses on the unison of artists from all different sectors; dancers, actors, models, theatre, singers &amp; songwriters.</span></em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">Inspirational and groundbreaking was the ultimate goal for the United Artists photo shoot.Photographers <a href="http://www.airdeparis.com/inezvin.htm" target="_blank">Ines Van Lamsweerde &amp; Vinoodh Matadin</a> captured each individual in an element all their own, focusing on parts of their behavior, body &amp; movements which ''the naked eye'' may not normally recognize. </span></em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">Fashion Director Alex White styled each artist in the three different Armani collections; <span style="color: #888888;"><a href="http://www.giorgioarmani.com/index.html" target="_blank">Armani Priv</a>, <a href="http://www.emporioarmani.com/index.asp?tskay=2FA4E164" target="_blank">Emporio Armani</a> and <a href="http://www.giorgioarmani.com/index.html" target="_blank">Armani Collection</a>.<a href="http://www.wmagazine.com/w/bios/dennis_freedman/search?contributorName=Dennis%20Freedman" target="_blank">Dennis Freedman</a> W Magazine Creative Director &amp;<a href="http://forums.thefashionspot.com/f71/alexandra-white-fashion-director-w-magazine-64677.html" target="_blank">Alex White</a> Fashion Director styled and directed the shoot. </span></span></em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;">Below,<a href="http://www.wmagazine.com/video?videoID=50837582001" target="_blank">the exclusive video</a> from the <a href="http://www.airdeparis.com/inezvin.htm" target="_blank">Inez van Lamsweerde &amp; Vinoodh Matadin</a> portfolio </span><span style="color: #000000;"><a style="font: normal normal normal 12px/normal Georgia; text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.meredithmonk.org/" target="_blank">starring Susie Bick, Hugh Dancy, Peter Sarsgaard, Meredith Monk</a>.</span></em></span></span></em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></em></span></span></em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1806" align="aligncenter" width="318" caption="Susie Bick for Artists Unite. W Magazine."]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1806" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/25/united-artists-w-magazine-paris-street-style/w-magazine-united-artists-december-2009-issue/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1806  " title="W-Magazine-United-Artists-December-2009-issue" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/W-Magazine-United-Artists-December-2009-issue.jpg" alt="Susis Bick for Artists Unite. W Magazine." width="318" height="440" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;">\n</span> </span></em></span></span></em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><span style="font-style: normal;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="486" height="412" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="name" value="flashObj" /><param name="bgcolor" value="#FFFFFF" /><param name="flashvars" value="videoId=50837582001&amp;linkBaseURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wmagazine.com%2Fvideo%3FvideoID%3D50837582001&amp;playerId=1571664582&amp;viewerSecureGatewayURL=https://console.brightcove.com/services/amfgateway&amp;servicesURL=http://services.brightcove.com/services&amp;cdnURL=http://admin.brightcove.com&amp;domain=embed&amp;autoStart=false&amp;" /><param name="src" value="http://c.brightcove.com/services/viewer/federated_f8/1571664582" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="486" height="412" src="http://c.brightcove.com/services/viewer/federated_f8/1571664582" flashvars="videoId=50837582001&amp;linkBaseURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wmagazine.com%2Fvideo%3FvideoID%3D50837582001&amp;playerId=1571664582&amp;viewerSecureGatewayURL=https://console.brightcove.com/services/amfgateway&amp;servicesURL=http://services.brightcove.com/services&amp;cdnURL=http://admin.brightcove.com&amp;domain=embed&amp;autoStart=false&amp;" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" name="flashObj"> </embed></object></span></em>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em>With this video, I found it the perfect time to post about Mark. An artist, a photographer, a fellow blogger, a very cool individual. I spotted him and his friends (who I will post later this week!) in the Marais. I loved them. So, of course I approached them. Little did I know Mark carries quite the resum as a photographer, artist &amp; graphic designer. Residing in Geneva, only in Paris only for the weekend, so I''m glad I caught him. </em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em>Surely a man to look out for. His <a href="http://www.esprit-tzp.com/goodbye.htm" target="_blank">website</a> speaks graphic artist, photographer, graffiti man. </em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em>So, although I am not W magazine and I don''t have Alex White or Dennis Freedman on my side, capturing Mark''s photo and speaking to him and his freinds was definitely a grande dose of inspiration and ground breaking talent for my day.</em></span>\n\n<em>It just proves the fact, you never know who may run into on the street...</em>\n\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #000000;">____________</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Below: </span><span style="color: #999999;">MARK REMUND</span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Seen: </span><span style="color: #000000;">Le Marais</span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Photographer:</span> <a style="color: #333333; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: none;" href="http://laurenceguenoun.fr/" target="_blank">C</a>hristan Summers</span></em></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #999999;">Wearing: Brass knuckle necklace, <a href="http://www.famousape.net/index.htm" target="_blank">Faumous Ape</a> (store in Geneva); T-shirt, <a href="http://www.sixpack.fr/" target="_blank">Sixpack.fr</a> (fantastic tees!); Belt bought from an indie designer in Geneva, bag is from <a href="http://americanapparel.net/" target="_blank">American Apparel</a>. </span></span></em></span></em></p>\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em> </em></span>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em> </em></p>\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1771" align="aligncenter" width="384" caption="Mark. Paris Street Style."]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1771" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/25/united-artists-w-magazine-paris-street-style/mark-paris-street-style/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1771  " title="Mark-Paris-street-style" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/Mark-Paris-street-style.jpg" alt="Mark. Paris Street Style." width="384" height="631" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1772" align="aligncenter" width="360" caption="Mark. Brass Knuckle Necklace. "]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1772" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/25/united-artists-w-magazine-paris-street-style/mark-brass-knuckle-necklace/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1772  " title="Mark-Brass-knuckle-necklace" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/Mark-Brass-knuckle-necklace.jpg" alt="Mark. Brass Knuckle Necklace. " width="360" height="380" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1773" align="alignleft" width="190" caption="Giles &amp; Brother Brass Necklace"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1773" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/25/united-artists-w-magazine-paris-street-style/g-b-brass-nkl-2/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1773   " title="g&amp;-b-brass-nkl" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/g-b-brass-nkl-237x300.jpg" alt="Giles &amp; Brother Brass Necklace" width="190" height="240" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1775" align="alignright" width="210" caption="Tracy Matthews black diamond nkl"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1775" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/25/united-artists-w-magazine-paris-street-style/tracy-matthews-skull-necklace-2/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1775   " title="tracy-matthews-skull-necklace" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/tracy-matthews-skull-necklace-300x300.jpg" alt="Tracy Matthews black diamond nkl" width="210" height="210" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1774" align="aligncenter" width="240" caption="Giles &amp; Brother Brass Rings"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1774" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/25/united-artists-w-magazine-paris-street-style/giles-and-brother-brass-rings-2/" target="_blank"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1774    " title="giles-and-brother-brass-rings" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/giles-and-brother-brass-rings-300x282.jpg" alt="Giles &amp; Brother Brass Rings" width="240" height="226" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<span style="color: #999999;">Above, choices from the boutique:</span> <a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/philip-crangi-brass-rr-pick-necklace.html" target="_blank">Giles &amp; Brother brass ''railroad pick'' necklace</a>, <a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/philip-crangi-brass-rings.html" target="_blank">Giles &amp; Brother brass ''railroad pick'' rings</a> &amp; <a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/tracy-matthews-oxidized-silver-and-black-diamond-necklace.html" target="_blank">Tracy Matthews oxidized silver and black diamond necklace UNISEX</a>.\n\nBelow: <span style="color: #888888;">A portrait of Mark from his </span><a href="http://esprit1220.skyrock.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #000000;">blog</span></a><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">.</span> </span>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-1778" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/25/united-artists-w-magazine-paris-street-style/mark-blog-portrait/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1778  aligncenter" title="Mark-blog-Portrait" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/Mark-blog-Portrait.jpg" alt="Mark. Portrait from his blog. " /></a></p>\n\n\n<em>***View more images from the W Magazine photo shoot <a href="http://www.wmagazine.com/fashion/2009/12/armani_artists#slide=1" target="_blank">HERE</a>.</em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</em></p>', 'United Artists. W Magazine. Paris Street Style.', 'Stated as a magazine about photography. I have always loved W Magazine for that reason and this month especially.  The December issue focuses on the unison of artists from all different sectors; dancers, actors, models, theatre, singers & songwriters.\nInspirational and groundbreaking was the ultimate goal for the United Artists photo shoot. Photographers Ines Van Lamsweerde & Vinoodh Matadin captured each individual in an element all their own, focusing on parts of their behavior, body & movements which ''the naked eye'' may not normally recognize.\nFashion Director Alex White styled each artist in the three different Armani collections; Armani Priv, Emporio Armani and Armani Collection. Dennis Freedman W Magazine Creative Director & Alex White Fashion Director styled and directed the shoot.\nBelow, the exclusive video from the Inez van Lamsweerde & Vinoodh Matadin portfolio starring Hugh Dancy, Peter Sarsgaard, Meredith Monk.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'united-artists-w-magazine-paris-street-style', '', '', '2009-11-25 11:35:41', '2009-11-25 10:35:41', '', 0, 'https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/?p=1764', 0, 'post', '', 0);
