(1810, 4, '2009-11-27 18:43:42', '2009-11-27 17:43:42', '<em>11.27.09</em>\n\n<em>Paris. Street Style. <span style="color: #888888;">Week #10. Post 3.</span></em>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em>Street style is an art which can be defined in so many different ways. Fashion, graffiti, photography, stencils, stickers, flyers, people, people, people. </em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em>As you have seen in past posts, street art is quite the inspiration for me. I think of it as <span style="color: #000000;">a</span><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"> form of art which has life</span>.</span> Always changing, re-forming, metamorphosing. One day a mural will occupy the entire side of a building, and the next day it is gone. Something new has taken its place, or the space is empty, stripped with chemicals to clean. </em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em>A subject that surely encourages controversy...right vs. wrong. Fair enough, some street art is really ugly, therefore in my mind, unnecessary. However, to lighten the subject of controversy I found a video on <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fHGbJ_SbTcQ&amp;feature=fvw" target="_blank">YouTube</a> of a young gentlemen in Manhattan, he goes by Aakash Nihalani; illustrating a form of street art I have never seen, therefore it sparked my interest. </em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em><em><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fHGbJ_SbTcQ&amp;feature=fvw" target="_blank">Aakash Nihalani: Cuban (Street Art)</a></em></em></span>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="425" height="344" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/fHGbJ_SbTcQ&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="425" height="344" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/fHGbJ_SbTcQ&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"> </embed></object>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em>As for our street style ladies &amp; gents of the day, they are friend''s of Mark, our Wednesday street style man. A group of artists who carry and express their own flair of creativity....a different style from the masses as well as each other. Something you don''t find too often.</em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;">Happy Friday everyone et bon weekend. </span></em></span>\n\n<p style="padding-left: 180px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"> </span></em></p>\n<em>____________</em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">Below: <span style="color: #000000;">LONG MURPAY</span></span></em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">Seen:</span> Le Marais</em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">Photographer:</span> Christan Summers</em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">Wearing: Clothes and accessories from <span style="color: #000000;">his</span><span style="color: #000000;"> online store,</span> <a href="http://www.zipia.net/" target="_blank">Zipia.net</a> a store you must check out. Serious low prices, affordable clothing and accessories, fashion from Korea and beyond. I love that I ran into him, I already bought a pair of gloves from the shop! </span></em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1812" align="aligncenter" width="360" caption="Attitude. Paris. Street Style. Love this. "]<a title="Paris Street Style, Men''s style, Men''s fashion" rel="www.icuinparis.com/blog" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?attachment_id=1812" target="_blank"><img class="size-full wp-image-1812    " title="Paris-street-style-fashion-from-Korea" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/Paris-street-style-fashion-from-Korea.jpg" alt="Attitude. Paris. Street Style. Love this. " width="360" height="841" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1813" align="aligncenter" width="360" caption="Love the Scarf &amp; the Watch. "]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1813" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/27/a-treat-from-geneva-new-york-street-art-paris-street-style/paris-street-style-love-this-look/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1813   " title="paris-street-style-love-this-look" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/paris-street-style-love-this-look.jpg" alt="Love the Scarf &amp; the Watch. " width="360" height="559" /></a>[/caption]\n\n____________\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><em>Below: <span style="color: #000000;">TRYSTAN &amp; ANAS</span></em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><em>Seen: <span style="color: #000000;">Le Marais</span></em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><em>Photographer: <span style="color: #000000;">Christan Summers</span></em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><em>Wearing: Trystan is wearing a ''New Yorker'' t-shirt and a mix of clothing and accessories from H&amp;M as well as small boutique shops in and around Paris &amp; Geneva. Anas''s bracelets and necklaces are a mix of gifts from friends and pieces she has bought herself. She told me she never takes them off, always wears them as a memory, a sentiment. </em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><em>Which is exactly why I have an entire <a href="www.cinsummer.com" target="_blank">boutique</a> full of jewelry and accessories. </em></span>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1814" align="aligncenter" width="350" caption="Paris Street Style. Trystan &amp; Anais."]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1814" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/27/a-treat-from-geneva-new-york-street-art-paris-street-style/paris-street-style-trystan-and-anais/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1814 " title="Paris-Street-style-Trystan-and-Anais" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/Paris-Street-style-Trystan-and-Anais.jpg" alt="Paris Street Style. Trystan &amp; Anais." width="350" height="686" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1811" align="aligncenter" width="350" caption="Trystan &amp; Anais. Piercings. Eyes. "]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1811" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/27/a-treat-from-geneva-new-york-street-art-paris-street-style/up-close-paris-street-style-white-hair-and-pretty-eyes/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1811 " title="Trystan &amp; Anais Paris Street Style" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/up-close-paris-street-style-white-hair-and-pretty-eyes.jpg" alt="Trystan &amp; Anais. Piercings. Eyes. " width="350" height="438" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1815" align="aligncenter" width="350" caption="Anais &amp; her melange of bracelets. "]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1815" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/27/a-treat-from-geneva-new-york-street-art-paris-street-style/anais-paris-street-style-the-bracelets/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1815 " title="Anais-Paris-Street-Style-The-bracelets" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/Anais-Paris-Street-Style-The-bracelets.jpg" alt="Anais &amp; her melange of bracelets. " width="350" height="493" /></a>[/caption]\n\n____________\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><em>Below:<span style="color: #000000;">ANGIE</span></em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><em>Seen:<span style="color: #000000;">Le Marais</span></em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><em>Photographer:<span style="color: #000000;">Christan Summers</span></em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><em>Wearing: <span style="color: #000000;">"Trash" Hat is from a street vendor in Geneva; their label is called "Trash", T-shirt is from <a href="http://www.mango.cat/paises.htm" target="_blank">Mango</a> &amp; the pacifier necklace...Angie bought the pacifier in the pharmacy and strung it as a necklace. Love it. </span></em></span>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1820" align="aligncenter" width="344" caption="Angie &amp; her pacifier necklace. "]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1820" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/27/a-treat-from-geneva-new-york-street-art-paris-street-style/angie-paris-street-style-and-the-pacifer-necklace/"><img class="size-large wp-image-1820  " title="Angie-Paris-Street-style-and-the-pacifer-necklace" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/Angie-Paris-Street-style-and-the-pacifer-necklace-491x1024.jpg" alt="Angie &amp; her pacifier necklace. " width="344" height="717" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1821" align="aligncenter" width="350" caption="Angie. Paris Street Style. The &#39;Trash&#39; hat."]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1821" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/27/a-treat-from-geneva-new-york-street-art-paris-street-style/street-funk-paris-trash-hat/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1821 " title="Street-funk-paris-Trash-Hat" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/Street-funk-paris-Trash-Hat.jpg" alt="Angie. Paris Street Style. The ''Trash'' hat." width="350" height="520" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center;">------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>', 'A Treat from Geneva. New York Street Art. Paris Street Style.', '11.18.09\n\nParis. Street Style. Week #10. Post 3.\n\nStreet style is an art which can be defined in so many different ways. Fashion, graffiti, photography, stencils, stickers, flyers, people, people, people.\n\nAs you have seen in past posts, street art is quite the inspiration for me. I think of it as a form of art which has life. Always changing, re-forming, metamorphosing. One day a mural will occupy the entire side of a building, and the next day it is gone. Something new has taken its place, or the space is empty, stripped with chemicals to clean.\n\nA subject that surely encourages controversy...right vs. wrong. Fair enough, some street art is really ugly, therefore in my mind, unnecessary. However, to lighten the subject of controversy I found a video on YouTube of a young gentlemen in Manhattan, he goes by Aakash Nihalani; illustrating a form of street art I have never seen, therefore it sparked my interest.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-treat-from-geneva-new-york-street-art-paris-street-style', '', '', '2009-11-27 18:43:42', '2009-11-27 17:43:42', '', 0, 'https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/?p=1810', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1849, 4, '2009-11-30 17:48:33', '2009-11-30 16:48:33', '<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;">11.30.09</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;">Paris. Street Style.<span style="color: #888888;">Week #11. Post 4.</span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">One of the best parts of working in this industry are the people I am able to meet. Last summer while I was making the transition from Boston to Paris a young women named </span><a href="http://shamila.com/flash.html" target="_blank"><span style="color: #999999;">Shamila Jiwa</span></a><span style="color: #000000;"> found me thanks to this blog. </span></span></span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">An independent designer with a heart of gold, really. An amazing woman. We met the first time in Paris when she was on her way to</span> <a href="http://themoment.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/11/20/wanderlust-istanbul/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #808080;">Istanbul, Turkey</span></a><span style="color: #000000;"> for an intensive training in goldsmith. (Side note:</span><span style="color: #808080;"> </span><a href="https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/?page_id=1607" target="_blank"><span style="color: #808080;">Vogue will launch an edition in Turkey March 2010</span></a><span style="color: #000000;">)</span></span></span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">This past weekend for the first time since we met, Shamila was back in Paris, this time on her way to exhibit at the</span> <a href="http://www.eastlondondesignshow.co.uk/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #808080;">East London Design Show</span></a>. <span style="color: #000000;">We sat down to have lunch and caf and I was able to get a sneak peak at the new collection...as well as capture a few pieces for the new store!</span></span></span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">To view Shamila''s collection click </span><a href="http://shamila.com/flash.html" target="_blank"><span style="color: #808080;">HERE</span></a></span></span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;">____________</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;">Below:<span style="color: #000000;">SHAMILA JIWA</span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;">Seen:</span> LINE 7 METRO LE PELETIER</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;">Photographer:</span> Christan Summers</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;">Wearing:<span style="color: #000000;">The jacket is <a href="http://www.marcjacobs.com/" target="_blank">Marc by Marc Jacobs</a>, the red scarf is a gift from her mother, the red booties were from NYC: Juno NYC, the tunic is<a href="http://www.bananarepublic.com/" target="_blank">Banana Republic</a>,the leggings are <a href="http://www.anthropologie.com/anthro/index.jsp" target="_blank">Anthropologie</a>,the fingerless gloves are <a href="http://www.zara.com/" target="_blank">Zara</a>, the jewels are <a href="http://shamila.com/flash.html" target="_blank">Shamila</a> &amp; the bag is <a href="http://www.orlakiely.com/" target="_blank">Orla Kiely</a>.</span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></span></span></span></p>\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;"> </span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;"> </span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;"> </span>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1850" align="aligncenter" width="350" caption="Shamila."]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1850" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/30/shamila-a-turkish-delight-paris-street-style/shamila-paris-street-style/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1850  " title="shamila paris street style" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/shamila-paris-street-style.jpg" alt="Shamila. A Phenomenal Jewelry Designer!" width="350" height="617" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">Shamila is one of the most passionate designers I have ever met and her stories while designing and creating this collection in Turkey are awe inspiring, to say the least.</span> <span style="color: #808080;">" I returned to Turkey this Summer because I wanted to leap into creating jewelry that was a collaborative effort between some exquisite createurs and myself. In this creative endeavor we are all peers, and each day I carry a piece of their story into my own experience, which are ultimately woven into my designs.</span></span></span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;">Shamila''s inspiration comes in many forms; however, for this collection in particular something was different.</span><span style="color: #808080;"> </span><span style="color: #808080;">"I did not want to be limited by technique but rather challenged in discovering the infinite depth of my creative possibilities." </span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;"> </span><span style="color: #000000;">The result of this challenge is breathtaking. The stones she chooses by hand (self-taught gemologist) are outstanding. Grade AAA. Which simply means perfection.</span></span></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_1851" align="aligncenter" width="350" caption="Shamila. Lokum Lale Rings."]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1851" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/30/shamila-a-turkish-delight-paris-street-style/shamila-and-the-gorgeous-rings/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1851    " title="shamila and the gorgeous rings" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/shamila-and-the-gorgeous-rings.jpg" alt="Shamila. Lokum Lale Rings." width="350" height="526" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1852" align="aligncenter" width="350" caption="Shamila. Lokum Lale Rings."]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1852" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/30/shamila-a-turkish-delight-paris-street-style/shamilas-rings-paris-street-style/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1852 " title="shamila''s rings paris street style" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/shamilas-rings-paris-street-style.jpg" alt="Lokum Lale Rings &amp; red shoes. " width="350" height="488" /></a>[/caption]\n\nThe rings above are from the Lokum Lale collection, designed and inspired from Shamila''s work in Turkey. The ring on her left hand (light blue) is a swiss blue topaz stone perfectly cut to form the shape of a spider web. I kid you not. This ring is stunning. The stone is alone on a solid silver (or gold band), custom made, and so definitely on my wish list!\n\n<span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;">The pieces I bought for the </span><a href="www.cinsummer.com" target="_blank"><span style="color: #808080;">boutique</span></a><span style="color: #000000;"> consist of two rings similar to this one; one ring with a Lavender amethyst and the other also a swiss blue topaz yet carved to another shape. </span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;">Below Shamila is wearing two pieces from her signature collection; the necklace features oodles of fine, faceted labradorite briolletes and the custom earrings, also labradorite.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #999999;">\n</span>\n\n<span style="color: #999999;"> </span>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1855" align="aligncenter" width="350" caption="Shamila. Custom Labradorite Necklace &amp; Earrings"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1855" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/30/shamila-a-turkish-delight-paris-street-style/shamila-fine-jewelry-paris-street-style/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1855 " title="shamila fine jewelry paris street style" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/shamila-fine-jewelry-paris-street-style-.jpg" alt="Shamila. Custom Labradorite Necklace &amp; Earrings" width="350" height="526" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<span style="color: #000000;">Fantastic way to spend a rainy afternoon in Paris. Merci Shamila. I wish you all the luck in London.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;">To view more of Shamila''s work, click </span><a href="http://shamila.com/flash.html" target="_blank"><span style="color: #808080;">HERE</span></a><span style="color: #808080;">.</span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;">Seeing Shamila of course reminded me of the fashion spread in W Magazine, Sep 2008 edition.</span>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1874" align="aligncenter" width="469" caption="W MAGAZINE ISTANBUL"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-1874" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/30/shamila-a-turkish-delight-paris-street-style/w-magazine-istanbul-2/"><img class="size-full wp-image-1874" title="W MAGAZINE ISTANBUL" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/W-MAGAZINE-ISTANBUL-1.jpg" alt="W MAGAZINE ISTANBUL" width="469" height="352" /></a>[/caption]\n\nCredit: W Magazine\n\n<span style="font-style: normal;"><span style="color: #000000; font: normal normal normal 11px/normal georgia, ''times new roman'', times, serif;">Photographed by </span><a style="color: #5985a0; text-decoration: none; font-family: ''Trebuchet MS''; font-weight: bold; font: normal normal bold 11px/normal ''trebuchet ms'', corbel, ''lucida grande'', sans-serif;" onclick="s_objectID=&quot;http://www.wmagazine.com/w/bios/mert_alas_and_marcus_piggott/search?contributorName=Mert%20Alas%2_1&quot;;return this.s_oc?this.s_oc(e):true" href="http://www.wmagazine.com/w/bios/mert_alas_and_marcus_piggott/search?contributorName=Mert%20Alas%20and%20Marcus%20Piggott">Mert Alas and Marcus Piggott</a> </span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000; font: normal normal normal 11px/normal georgia, ''times new roman'', times, serif;">Styled by </span><a style="color: #5985a0; text-decoration: none; font-family: ''Trebuchet MS''; font-weight: bold; font: normal normal bold 11px/normal ''trebuchet ms'', corbel, ''lucida grande'', sans-serif;" onclick="s_objectID=&quot;http://www.wmagazine.com/w/bios/alex_white/search?contributorName=Alex%20White_1&quot;;return this.s_oc?this.s_oc(e):true" href="http://www.wmagazine.com/w/bios/alex_white/search?contributorName=Alex%20White">Alex White</a>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;">The trend of Turkey''s inspiration and quality craftsmanship has been spreading through the mainstream fashion scene as well. The picture above was for a spread in W Magazine September 2008 Edition.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;">Interesting. Their has been a major trend in fashion houses changing their markets to India, Turkey and China. Markets that have been touched before but not heavily focused on. For example, the first <a href="http://www.vogue.fr/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #808080;">Vogue</span></a> Turkey will drop March 2010. So, we shall see what happens. </span></span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;"> To learn a bit more on the rise of the Fashion sector is Istanbul &amp; to watch the W Magazine video from the Istanbul shoot click</span> <a href="https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/?page_id=1607" target="_blank"><span style="color: #808080;">HERE</span></a><span style="color: #808080;"> </span></span>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; text-align: center; padding: 0px;"></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; text-align: center; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #888888;">------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</span></span></span></p>', 'Shamila. A Turkish Delight. Paris Street Style.', 'One of the best parts of working in this industry are the people I am able to meet. Last summer while I was making the transition from Boston to Paris a young women named Shamila Jiwa found me thanks to this blog. An independent designer with a heart of gold, really. An amazing woman. We met the first time in Paris when she was on her way to Istanbul, Turkey for an intensive training in goldsmith. The result of her training is breathtaking. The stones she chooses by hand (self-taught gemologist) are outstanding. This past weekend for the first time since we met, Shamila was back in Paris, this time on her way to exhibit at the East London Design Show. We sat down to have lunch and caf and I was able to get a sneak peak at the new collection...as well as capture a few pieces for the new store!', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'shamila-a-turkish-delight-paris-street-style', '', '', '2009-11-30 17:48:33', '2009-11-30 16:48:33', '', 0, 'https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/?p=1849', 0, 'post', '', 2),
