(1960, 5, '2009-12-04 00:28:27', '2009-12-03 23:28:27', '<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;"><em>12.04.09</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;"><em>Paris. Street Style.<span style="color: #888888;">Week #11. Post 3.</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;">Today is something a little different. We have a guest blogger, <a href="https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/?p=1664" target="_blank">Erin Kim</a> who I met at <a href="http://www.paris-sorbonne.fr/en/" target="_blank">La Sorbonne</a> and since then has been gracing us with her wonderful presence on <a href="https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/?p=1733" target="_blank">various photo shoots</a>.</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;">A fellow American living in Paris with an insider view on all those inspirational and creative. Today she is introducing us to Amandine, a fashion design student in Paris, an independent jewelry designer, and a good friend. An over all fantastically unique and talented young woman.</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">________________</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">Below: </span><span style="color: #000000;">AMANDINE</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">Seen:</span> 15th Arrondissement</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">Photographer:</span> Erin Kim</em></p>\n<em>Amandine is a fashion design student in Paris, an independent jewelry designer, and a good friend. I have known her ever since she was a foreign exchange student at my high school in the USA, and even then she was very artistically inclined with a keen eye for details and color schemes. We''ve been able to keep in touch these past years, and it is so strange to see her familiar face again in Paris. </em>\n\n<em>Being in Paris, I took this opportunity to photograph her style and work. This is not the typical "street style" post of a random, stylish/chic person that steps into your life for just three minutes; this is more or less a profile of a great friend with an unique, creative vision &amp; style that I''ve gotten to see first-hand for years. Here''s a small look into her world:</em>\n\n<em>\n</em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">Wearing:</span></em><em> <span style="color: #000000;">Black overcoat from </span><a href="http://www.mango.com/paises.htm" target="_blank"><span style="color: #000000;">MANGO</span></a><span style="color: #000000;">, red and green silk scarves are from </span><a href="http://www.ellen-decoration.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;">Ellen</span><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></span></a><span style="color: #000000;">(a small fabric store in Troyes, France), black sweater is </span><a href="http://www.sudexpress.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;">Sud</span><span style="color: #000000;">Express</span></span></a><span style="color: #000000;">, grey shirt is from </span><a href="http://www.zara.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #000000;">Zara</span></a><span style="color: #000000;">, jeans are </span><a href="http://www.calvinkleininc.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #000000;">Calvin Klein</span></a><span style="color: #000000;">, shoes are </span><a href="http://www.janetandjanet.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;">Janet&amp;</span><span style="color: #999999;"><span style="color: #000000;">J</span><span style="color: #000000;">anet</span></span></span></a><span style="color: #000000;">, earrings are all handmade by Amandine herself.</span></em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1962" align="aligncenter" width="415" caption="Amandine&#39;s red silk scarf"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1736.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-1962  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1736-768x1024.jpg" alt="Amandine''s red silk scarf" width="415" height="553" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1964" align="aligncenter" width="369" caption="Red silk scarf &amp; matching lipstick."]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Amandine2.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-1964  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Amandine2-768x1024.jpg" alt="Red silk scarf &amp; matching lipstick. " width="369" height="491" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1965" align="aligncenter" width="369" caption="flower &amp; butterfly motif"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Amandine5.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-1965  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Amandine5-768x1024.jpg" alt="flower &amp; butterfly motif" width="369" height="491" /></a>[/caption]\n\nOn inspiration: "I tend to use flower and butterfly motifs for my jewelry. I just really admire flowers--to me, they are the most extraordinary things in nature. They are so well-constructed, and everything about them is perfect. The architecture, the symmetry, the scent, the colors, the patterns and motifs are all in harmony with each other, and I find inspiration in that sort of perfection. Butterflies do that for me too--you can hardly believe that so many colors exist. Some butterflies are almost transparent, some resemble leaves, some resemble the colorful tapestries you see hanging in museums. It looks like they were all designed by somebody; you can hardly believe it''s just nature."\n\n[caption id="attachment_1970" align="aligncenter" width="491" caption="Deciding how to accessorize..."]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1673.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-1970  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1673-1024x768.jpg" alt="Deciding how to accessorize..." width="491" height="369" /></a>[/caption]\n\nOn Music: "Every time I work, I listen to music. Always. When I really need to focus, I listen to classical music but for the most part, I listen to everything--pop, jazz, classic rock, etc. For me, music has to age a bit like wine. I always enjoy music more when it has aged a bit, because there is always a sense of nostalgia."\n\n[caption id="attachment_1967" align="aligncenter" width="369" caption="Green silk and beaded earrings. "]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Amandine6.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-1967  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Amandine6-768x1024.jpg" alt="Green silk and beaded earrings. " width="369" height="491" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1968" align="aligncenter" width="331" caption="Green silk scarf and hand-made beaded earrings"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Amandine7.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-1968  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Amandine7-591x1024.jpg" alt="Green silk scarf and hand-made beaded earrings" width="331" height="574" /></a>[/caption]\n\nOn jewelry: "I always look everywhere for pieces for my jewelry, and I keep everything. I find scraps of metal from garage sales, beads from discount stores and decorations from flea markets and craft stores that I can use. Once I have everything, I am completely free to make whatever I want. Making jewelry is really just a way to express myself outside of work for my design classes."\n\n[caption id="attachment_1966" align="aligncenter" width="491" caption="Scraps of metal transformed into beautiful earrings"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Amandine4.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-1966  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Amandine4-1024x837.jpg" alt="Scraps of metal transformed into beautiful earrings" width="491" height="402" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1973" align="aligncenter" width="415" caption="Paris from her window. "]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Amandine11.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-1973  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Amandine11-768x1024.jpg" alt="Paris from her window. " width="415" height="553" /></a>[/caption]\n\nOn Paris: "My favorite arrondissement in Paris is the 6th. It might sound clich but the cafs, buildings and streets evoke the "Paris" that American film-directors try to capture in their movies. I am pretty sure that this arrondissement is where many directors shoot their movies. And of course, many of my friends and loved ones live there."\n<p style="text-align: center;">----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>', 'Venus in Red.', 'Today is something a little different. We have a guest blogger, Erin Kim who has been gracing us with her wonderful presence on various photo shoots & good ole'' working days.\n\nA fellow American living in Paris with an insider view on all those inspirational and creative. Today she is introducing us to Amandine, a fashion design student in Paris, an independent jewelry designer, and a good friend. An all over fantastically unique and talented young woman.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'venus-in-red', '', '', '2009-12-04 00:28:27', '2009-12-03 23:28:27', '', 0, 'https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/?p=1960', 0, 'post', '', 0);
