(2038, 4, '2009-12-07 00:40:26', '2009-12-06 23:40:26', '<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>12.07.09</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><a href="http://www.behemothofmoscow.com/" target="_blank">Behemoth Of Moscow.</a> </span>Paris Photo Shoot.</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><a href="http://www.dewaldbrand.com" target="_blank">Dewald Brand</a>, creative director &amp; owner of Behemoth Of Moscow.Photographer, clothing designer, traveler, friend. The man has a mind with ideas which are changing trends. Literally, fresh off the plane from his latest business/design trip in India I knew there would be a photo shoot and I couldn''t wait to help produce it.</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;">This past weekend, we bombarded <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/jarellano/3067303733/" target="_blank">le Mtro Barbs Rouchechouart</a> (maybe not the <em>best</em> idea) and shot a few pieces from the Winter 2010 Collection. Unfortunately, time was a cut a bit short due to the presence of a few Parisian metro police who informed us a permit would be necessary in order to continue our shoot. Well, we had no permit. Shut down. The tragedy of it all.</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;">Luckily, time granted us enough to shoot some amazing shots.</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">________________</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">Below: </span><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;"><a href="http://www.behemothofmoscow.com/" target="_blank">Behemoth Of Moscow</a> Winter 2010 mini Collection</span></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">Shot:</span> </em><em><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/jarellano/3067303733/" target="_blank">L</a><span style="font-style: normal;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/jarellano/3067303733/" target="_blank">e Mtro Barbs Rouchechouart</a></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">Photographer:</span> </em><em><a href="http://www.dewaldbrand.com" target="_blank">Dewald Brand</a></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">Stylist:</span> Christan Summers</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">Creative Direction:</span> DV &amp; C.dawg</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><em>Model: </em><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Talat Barghouti</em></span></span></p>\nThe <a href="http://www.behemothofmoscow.com/" target="_blank">Behemoth Of Moscow</a> man.\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;">''A smooth-like-butter, witty-ass, fast-talking, vodka-drinking, chess-playing, pistol-bearing, caviar-eating, cat-like beast without any regard for reality let alone those in it. Sophistication and class emanate with the swing and swagger of his bowtie as he be on his own mission, in his own world, on his own path.''</p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2041" align="aligncenter" width="603" caption="Behemoth 2010 Winter Collection"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2041" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/07/behemoth-of-moscow-escalation/behemoth-of-moscow-mini-winter-10/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2041  " title="behemoth of moscow mini winter 10" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/behemoth-of-moscow-mini-winter-10.jpg" alt="Behemoth 2010 Winter Collection (mini)" width="603" height="402" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2042" align="aligncenter" width="601" caption="Behemoth &amp; Talat"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2042" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/07/behemoth-of-moscow-escalation/behemoth-of-moscow-winter-10-collection/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2042  " title="behemoth of moscow  winter 10 collection" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/behemoth-of-moscow-winter-10-collection.jpg" alt="Behemoth &amp; Talat" width="601" height="403" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">On The Creator''s Mind:</span> Travel. Life. People.Chilling, kicking it. Listening to that vintage skool flavour by each her or his own. Snapping shutters from South Africa, to wherever, then round to here, back to there.Filling with knowledge along the way.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2043" align="aligncenter" width="491" caption="Who&#39;s that lady in the purple hat?"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2043" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/07/behemoth-of-moscow-escalation/purple-teal-styling/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2043  " title="purple teal styling" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/purple-teal-styling.jpg" alt="Who''s that lady in the purple hat?" width="491" height="329" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">Soon after the shot above was taken, we were asked by the metro police to close shop. However, we figured we could a shoot a couple more images on our way out. The short series below is from that quick shoot. </span></span>\n<div id="_mcePaste" style="position: absolute; left: -10000px; top: 1745px; width: 1px; height: 1px; overflow-x: hidden; overflow-y: hidden;">Occasional beat making, occasional tree hugging, occasional snow waxing., always hungry.</div>\n\n[caption id="" align="aligncenter" width="517" caption="Escalation"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2039" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/07/behemoth-of-moscow-escalation/escalation/"><img class="   " style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="escalation" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/escalation-1024x374.jpg" alt="Behemoth Of Moscow Escalation" width="517" height="189" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="" align="aligncenter" width="327" caption="Pink Behemoth"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2040" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/07/behemoth-of-moscow-escalation/dv-behemoth-2/"><img class="  " style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px none initial;" title="DV behemoth 2" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DV-behemoth-2.jpg" alt="Pink Behemoth" width="327" height="504" /></a>[/caption]\n\nThis shoot I missed. I wish I could have seen this in real life. Check out what is on that ironing board...\n\n[caption id="attachment_2044" align="aligncenter" width="491" caption="Unknown functions of an Ironing board"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2044" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/07/behemoth-of-moscow-escalation/the-behemoth-set-up/"><img class="size-large wp-image-2044   " title="the behemoth set up" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/the-behemoth-set-up-1024x654.jpg" alt="Unknown functions of the Ironing board" width="491" height="314" /></a>[/caption]\n\nCooking eggs on a glass stand heated by a candle, toasting his eggs on the iron. Any body have anything to say about that one?\n\n[caption id="attachment_2049" align="aligncenter" width="600" caption="Behemoth cooking school"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2049" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/07/behemoth-of-moscow-escalation/behemoth-of-moscow-toast-on-the-iron/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2049 " title="behemoth of moscow toast on the iron" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/behemoth-of-moscow-toast-on-the-iron.jpg" alt="Behemoth cooking school" width="600" height="399" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2048" align="aligncenter" width="601" caption="The Behemoth"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2048" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/07/behemoth-of-moscow-escalation/the-behemoth-2/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2048  " style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="the behemoth" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/the-behemoth1.jpg" alt="The Behemoth" width="601" height="401" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2050" align="aligncenter" width="600" caption="Behemoth instrumental"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2050" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/07/behemoth-of-moscow-escalation/behemoth-instrumental/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2050 " title="behemoth instrumental" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/behemoth-instrumental.jpg" alt="Behemoth instrumental" width="600" height="401" /></a>[/caption]\n\nFor more information on where to buy and to view other designs from the collection go to the Behemoth Of Moscow <a href="http://www.behemothofmoscow.com/" target="_blank">Website</a>.\n<p style="text-align: center;">____________________________________________________________________________________________</p>', 'Behemoth of Moscow. Escalation.', 'Behemoth Of Moscow. International clothing company for the contemporary urbanite. The man who appreciates the value of curves in life. Dewald Brand, photographer and designer. ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'behemoth-of-moscow-escalation', '', '', '2009-12-07 00:40:26', '2009-12-06 23:40:26', '', 0, 'https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/?p=2038', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(2074, 5, '2009-12-08 23:29:02', '2009-12-08 22:29:02', '<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;"><em>12.08.09<span style="color: #888888;"> Week #12. Post 2.</span>\n</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"> Madeleine Vionnet:</span></em><em> Puriste de la Mode</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;">Again, today we have the pleasure of handing the keyboard to Ms. Erin Kim, guest blogger and museum spy. A visit to Les Art Decoratifs this past weekend was all she needed to mention for me to ask her again to join us for a post. An amazing exhibit currently in Paris and although cameras are not allowed, Erin braved the museum security and snapped a few for you and us.</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;">Not to mention a beautifully written &amp; articulated post.</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;">Thank you Erin!</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">________________</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">Below: <span style="color: #000000;"><a href="http://www.lesartsdecoratifs.fr" target="_blank">Les Arts Dcoratifs</a></span><span style="color: #000000;">\n<span style="color: #808080;"> </span></span></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #808080;">Seen</span>: 107, rue de Rivoli, 75001 Paris\n24 juin 2009-31 janvier 2010\n</span></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #888888;">Exhibition Design</span>: <a href="http://www.andreeputman.fr/index.html" target="_blank">Andre Putman</a>\n<em> </em></span></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">Photographer &amp; Author:</span></em><em> <span style="color: #000000;">Erin Kim</span></em></span></span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madeleine_Vionnet" target="_blank">Madeleine Vionnet</a> is considered to be an "artist of fashion as Picasso is to painting"--precisely because of her commitment to her own aesthetic vision, and her career-long journey in perfecting her style. Her vision was the unaltered female form, a garment that served only as a second-skin that flowed in harmony with the woman''s body, rather than restricting it within a single shape.</p>\nThe most inspiring thing about Madeleine Vionnet--and I''m sure Chanel, Balenciaga, Valentino would agree with me--is that she was first and foremost an artist. Her creativity fed from the artistic traditions that preceded her, and the artistic movements that was taking shape during her lifetime. She combined classical Grecian ideals of perfect proportion, balance and simplicity with the avant-garde, exotic and sensual tastes of the 1920s.\n\nHowever, as a couturier, she took utmost consideration of the three-dimensional female body; in a way, she transformed the womens body into something of a work of art in itself. And why hide something so beautiful? Thus, she removed all the restricting hooks, linings, shackles, buttons and zippers of corsets and created the dress that was the closest thing in nature to a womans body.\n\nPS: These photos were taken while I was dodging security guards, so these photos are not as clear as I''d like them to be. I was caught and reprimanded numerous times but I kept sneaking a few photos becausethe dresses were just too beautiful!\n\n[caption id="attachment_2075" align="aligncenter" width="430" caption="Madeleine Vionnet: Puriste de la Mode"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1928.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2075  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1928-1024x768.jpg" alt="Madeleine Vionnet: Puriste de la Mode" width="430" height="323" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2085" align="aligncenter" width="387" caption="&quot;proportion, balance, movement, truth&quot;"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1906.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2085   " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1906-768x1024.jpg" alt="&quot;proportion, balance, movement, truth&quot;" width="387" height="516" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2083" align="aligncenter" width="369" caption="Ornamentation fit to the form"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1644.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2083  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1644-768x1024.jpg" alt="Ornamentation fit to the form" width="369" height="491" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2081" align="aligncenter" width="387" caption="Structured evening dresses"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1642.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2081   " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1642-768x1024.jpg" alt="Structured evening dresses" width="387" height="516" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2082" align="aligncenter" width="369" caption="Structured evening gown, Moroccan crpe"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1643.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2082  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1643-768x1024.jpg" alt="Structured evening gown, Moroccan crpe" width="369" height="491" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2099" align="aligncenter" width="369" caption="Her 1930s creations"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1912.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2099  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1912-768x1024.jpg" alt="Her 1930s creations" width="369" height="491" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2089" align="aligncenter" width="369" caption="My favorite. "]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1630.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2089  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1630-768x1024.jpg" alt="My favorite. " width="369" height="491" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2112" align="aligncenter" width="491" caption="&quot;Effets de matires&quot;"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1898.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2112  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN1898-1024x768.jpg" alt="Madeleine Vionnet" width="491" height="369" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center;">__________________________________________________________________________________________</p>', 'Madeleine Vionnet: An Architect of Fashion', 'Madeleine Vionnet is considered to be an "artist of fashion as Picasso is to painting"--precisely because of her commitment to her own aesthetic vision, and her career-long journey in perfecting her style. Her vision was the unaltered female form, a garment that served only as a second-skin that flowed in harmony with the woman''s body, rather than restricting it within a single shape.\n\nHowever, as a couturier, she took utmost consideration of the three-dimensional female body; in a way, she transformed the womens body into something of a work of art in itself. And why hide something so beautiful? Thus, she  removed all the restricting hooks, linings, shackles, buttons and zippers of corsets and created the dress that was the closest thing in nature to a womans body.\n\nPS: These photos were taken while I was dodging security guards. I was caught and reprimanded numerous times but I kept sneaking a few photos becausethe dresses were just too beautiful!', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'madeleine-vionnet-an-architect-of-fashion', '', '', '2009-12-08 23:29:02', '2009-12-08 22:29:02', '', 0, 'https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/?p=2074', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2181, 4, '2009-12-10 17:01:13', '2009-12-10 16:01:13', '<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>12.10.09<span style="color: #888888;"> Week #12. Post 3.</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;">Vogue Art December Issue.</span> Grace Coddington and a Lady Gaga experience. </em></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;">After Erin''s post on Wednesday on <a href="https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/?p=2074" target="_blank">Madeleine Vionnet</a> and the </span><span style="color: #000000;"><a href="http://www.lesartsdecoratifs.fr/" target="_blank">Les Arts Dcoratifs</a></span><span style="color: #000000;"><a href="http://www.lesartsdecoratifs.fr/" target="_blank"> </a><span style="font-style: normal;">exhibition, it made me think of another inspiring woman, and one who is still with us today. </span></span></em></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grace_Coddington" target="_blank">Grace Coddington</a>. <span style="font-style: normal;">A woman in</span></span><span style="font-style: normal;"><span style="color: #000000;"> fashion for more than 30 years who started as a model, grew to be creative director for <a href="http://www.vogue.co.uk/" target="_blank">British Vogue </a>for 19 years, then moved in ''88 to work at <a href="http://www.vogue.com" target="_blank">U.S Vogue</a> with Anna Wintour. </span></span></em></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="font-style: normal;"><span style="color: #000000;">At 62, Coddington, still lives up to her reputation for transforming photographic spreads into narratives and her latest creation for the Vogue December Art Issue is a perfect example. Working along side photographer, <a href="http://www.pbs.org/wnet/americanmasters/episodes/annie-leibovitz/life-through-a-lens/16/" target="_blank">Annie Leibovitz</a>, the two established a modern day </span></span><span style="color: #000000;">Hansel &amp; Gretel, <span style="font-style: normal;">starring <a href="http://www.ladygaga.com/news/default.aspx" target="_blank">Lady Gaga</a> &amp; <a href="http://www.supermodels.nl/lilycole" target="_blank">Lily Cole</a>. The pairing is a unique one and the set and shots are truly notable. </span></span></em></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;">Below, a behind the scenes video of the shoot courtesy of Vogue, images from the spread, as well as Coddington over the years.</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; text-align: center; padding: 0px;"><span style="line-height: 16px; font-size: medium;">________________</span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; text-align: center; padding: 0px;"><span style="line-height: 16px; font-size: medium;">\n</span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; text-align: center; padding: 0px;"><span style="line-height: 16px; font-size: medium;">THE ARTS ISSUE. VOGUE DECEMBER 2009</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object id="flashObj" classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="404" height="436" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="bgcolor" value="#FFFFFF" /><param name="flashVars" value="videoId=49818578001&amp;linkBaseURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.vogue.com%2Finclude%2Fvogue%2Fvoguediaries%2F2009_December_Arts_Issue%2Fplayer.html&amp;playerID=8558003001&amp;domain=embed&amp;" /><param name="base" value="http://admin.brightcove.com" /><param name="seamlesstabbing" value="false" /><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="swLiveConnect" value="true" /><param name="allowScriptAccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://c.brightcove.com/services/viewer/federated_f9/8558003001?isVid=1&amp;publisherID=1568114478" /><param name="name" value="flashObj" /><param name="flashvars" value="videoId=49818578001&amp;linkBaseURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.vogue.com%2Finclude%2Fvogue%2Fvoguediaries%2F2009_December_Arts_Issue%2Fplayer.html&amp;playerID=8558003001&amp;domain=embed&amp;" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed id="flashObj" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="404" height="436" src="http://c.brightcove.com/services/viewer/federated_f9/8558003001?isVid=1&amp;publisherID=1568114478" name="flashObj" allowscriptaccess="always" swliveconnect="true" allowfullscreen="true" seamlesstabbing="false" base="http://admin.brightcove.com" flashvars="videoId=49818578001&amp;linkBaseURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.vogue.com%2Finclude%2Fvogue%2Fvoguediaries%2F2009_December_Arts_Issue%2Fplayer.html&amp;playerID=8558003001&amp;domain=embed&amp;" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> </embed></object>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2182" align="aligncenter" width="502" caption="Lady Gaga &amp; Lily Cole. Hansel &amp; Gretel"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2182" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/10/grace-coddington-vogue-lady-gaga/lady-gaga-hansel-gretel-vogue-us-december-2009/"><img class="size-large wp-image-2182   " title="lady-gaga-hansel-gretel-vogue-us-december-2009" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/lady-gaga-hansel-gretel-vogue-us-december-2009-1024x695.jpg" alt="Lady Gaga &amp; Lily Cole. Hansel &amp; Gretel" width="502" height="340" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2183" align="aligncenter" width="500" caption="Into the Oven"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2183" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/10/grace-coddington-vogue-lady-gaga/lady-gaga-and-lily-cole-for-vogue-december-issue/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2183 " title="lady gaga and lily cole for Vogue december issue" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/lady-gaga-and-lily-cole-for-Vogue-december-issue.jpg" alt="Into the Oven" width="500" height="346" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2184" align="aligncenter" width="580" caption="Hansel &amp; Gretel following the breadcrumbs"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2184" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/10/grace-coddington-vogue-lady-gaga/lily-cole-for-vogue-hansel-and-gretel-december-issue-2009/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2184 " title="lily-cole-for-Vogue-hansel-and-gretel-december-issue-2009" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/lily-cole-for-Vogue-hansel-and-gretel-december-issue-2009.jpg" alt="Hansel &amp; Gretel following the breadcrumbs" width="580" height="400" /></a>[/caption]\n\nThis I just find incredible. After producing shoots of my own, I can now imagine the amount of work which it takes to create the set, vibe and emotion of these images. The lighting, make-up, costumes, direction...the patience. People who are able to realize work like this of course have a large team, but the final result is something extremely inspiring.\n\n<em><span style="color: #808080;">Below:</span></em> Grace Coddington during her period of modeling, on the cover of British Vogue, 1962.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2185" align="aligncenter" width="370" caption="Grace Coddington. British Vogue 1962"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2185" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/10/grace-coddington-vogue-lady-gaga/british_vogue_august_1962__grace_coddington__carapetian/"><img class="size-large wp-image-2185    " title="british_vogue_august_1962__grace_coddington__carapetian" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/british_vogue_august_1962__grace_coddington__carapetian-756x1024.jpg" alt="Grace Coddington. British Vogue 1962" width="370" height="502" /></a>[/caption]\n\nAnd Grace Coddington now...still gracious, catching &amp; confident.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2186" align="aligncenter" width="506" caption="Grace Coddington on her move to Vogue US"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2186" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/10/grace-coddington-vogue-lady-gaga/grace-coddington-quotes/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2186 " title="grace-coddington-quotes" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/grace-coddington-quotes.jpg" alt="Grace Coddington on her move to Vogue US" width="506" height="349" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2187" align="aligncenter" width="506" caption="Grace Coddington"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2187" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/10/grace-coddington-vogue-lady-gaga/grace-coddington/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2187 " title="grace coddington" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/grace-coddington-.jpg" alt="Grace Coddington" width="506" height="349" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center;">__________________________________________________________________________________</p>', 'Grace Coddington, Vogue &amp; Lady Gaga. ', 'Grace Coddington. A woman in fashion for more than 30 years who started as a model, grew to be creative director for British Vogue for 19 years, then moved in ''88 to work at U.S Vogue with Anna Wintour.\n\nAt 62, Coddington, famous for transforming photographic spreads into narratives and her latest creation for the December Art Issue for Vogue is a perfect example of that. Working along side photographer, Annie Leibovitz, the two established a modern day Hansel & Gretel, starring Lady Gaga & Lily Cole. The pairing is a unique one and the set and shots are truly notable. ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'grace-coddington-vogue-lady-gaga', '', '', '2009-12-10 17:01:13', '2009-12-10 16:01:13', '', 0, 'https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/?p=2181', 0, 'post', '', 0);
