(2281, 5, '2009-12-16 00:19:43', '2009-12-15 23:19:43', '<div>\n<div>12.16.09</div>\n<div>Paris. Street Style. <span style="color: #888888">Week #13. Post 2</span></div>\n<div>Post &amp; Photography by, Erin Kim</div>\n<div>\n\nThere are many reasons why students all over the world do not dress up for school. Some schools enforce a uniform dress-code, yet most are just too tired, too hungover, too broke or too lazy. But honest to god, I haven''t seen anyone in Paris wearing a university-logo sweatshirt, a Northface or Uggboots; they are just as tired, hungover, exhausted and broke as any other student in America but they are determined to look good regardless.\n<p style="text-align: center"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center">BELOW: Sarah</p>\n<p style="text-align: center">SEEN: Boulevard Edgar Quinet, Cimetire du Montparnasse\nSCHOOL: La Sorbonne\nSTUDYING: Public Relations, Communication\nSarah, in various vintage finds from stores along Rue St. Denis in Paris (by <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Les_Halles" target="_blank">Forum Les Halles</a>)\nGlasses are from <a href="http://www.burberry.com" target="_self">Burberry</a> , Bag is from <a href="http://www.bensherman.com" target="_blank">Ben Sherman</a>, Scarf is <a href="http://www.etam.com" target="_blank">Etam</a>, Jeans are <a href="http://eu.levi.com/fr_FR/index.html">Levis</a></p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n\n[caption id="attachment_2303" align="aligncenter" width="377" caption="Sarah"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Sarah21.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2303  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Sarah21-768x1024.jpg" alt="Sarah" width="377" height="502" /></a>[/caption]\n\n</div>\n\n[caption id="attachment_2284" align="aligncenter" width="451" caption="Shoes: a thrift-store treasure"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Sarah1.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2284   " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Sarah1-1024x768.jpg" alt="Sarah" width="451" height="339" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center">BELOW: La\nSEEN: 15th Arrondissement, apartment\nSCHOOL: Lyce Duperre ESAA\nSTUDYING: Fashion Design\nThis is La: complete with red lipstick, a fur stole, and lastly, a denim shirt stolen from her father''s closet!\nFur stole &amp; hat is from <a href="http://www.hm.com/fr/">H&amp;M</a>, tote bag is from a stand in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quartier_Pigalle" target="_blank">Pigalle</a></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2288" align="aligncenter" width="369" caption="La"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Lea2.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2288  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Lea2-768x1024.jpg" alt="La" width="369" height="491" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2291" align="aligncenter" width="365" caption="La"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Lea.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2291  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Lea-651x1024.jpg" alt="La" width="365" height="574" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center">BELOW: Aedan\nSEEN: Chartres, 96 km from Paris\nSCHOOL: abroad\nAedan is a bit of a mystery man; I don''t have any other information about him except for his name &amp;\nthat I am inlove with his shoes.</p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2292" align="aligncenter" width="290" caption="Aedan"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Aedan.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2292  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Aedan-519x1024.jpg" alt="Aedan" width="290" height="574" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center">BELOW: Marc\nSEEN: 11th Arrondissement, Foyer\nSCHOOL: Lyce Bouffon\nSTUDYING: "Math and Science."\nMarc is a 17 year old student in Paris--I wish the boys dressed as well as he did while I was in high school.\nGlasses are <a href="http://www.facconnable.com/" target="_blank">Faonnable</a>, Shoes are <a href="http://www.ralphlauren.com/home/index.jsp?direct" target="_blank">Ralph Lauren</a>\nThe sweater and pants are from various trips to the <a href="http://www.parispuces.com/" target="_blank">Puces de Saint-Ouen</a> fleamarkets</p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2294" align="aligncenter" width="395" caption="Marc"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Marc.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2294  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Marc-617x1024.jpg" alt="Marc" width="395" height="655" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2296" align="aligncenter" width="328" caption="Marc &amp; his tortoise-shell, horn-rimmed glasses"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Marc3.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2296    " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Marc3-916x1024.jpg" alt="Marc" width="328" height="367" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center">BELOW: Sharon\nSEEN: Seine River\nSCHOOL: Abroad\nSTUDYING: Art History\nSharon is on a Seine river boat cruise on Bateaux Parisiens, wearing a silk green kimono, and also a fur stole from H&amp;M.\nThe kimono, shoes and jewelry were all found combing through various flea markets and vintage stores throughout Paris.</p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2313" align="aligncenter" width="338" caption="Sharon&#39;s green red kimono is a vintage find"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN2005.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2313   " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN2005-417x1024.jpg" alt="Sharon" width="338" height="830" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center">BELOW: James</p>\n<p style="text-align: center">SEEN: Rue de Charonne, Alexandre Dumas Metro\nSCHOOL: Paris Graduate School of Management\nSTUDYING: Finance\nJames, on his way home from school after a long day:\nJacket &amp; Shoes are from christmas markets in Munich, Germany\nJeans are <a href="http://www.calvinklein.com" target="_blank">Calvin Klein</a>, shirt is <a href="http://www.ralphlauren.com/home/index.jsp?direct" target="_blank">Polo</a>,Black sweater is Men''s <a href="http://www.zara.com/" target="_blank">Zara</a></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2330" align="aligncenter" width="344" caption="James"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN2070.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2330   " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/DSCN2070-768x1024.jpg" alt="James" width="344" height="458" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center">____________________________________________________________________________________________</p>', 'Student street style in Paris ', 'There are many reasons why students all over the world do not dress up for school. Some schools enforce a uniform dress-code, yet most are just too tired, too hungover, too broke or too lazy. But honest to god, I haven''t seen anyone in Paris wearing a university-logo sweatshirt, a Northface or Uggboots; they are just as tired, hungover, exhausted and broke as any other student in America but they are determined to look good regardless.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'you-only-live-once-you-might-as-well-look-good-doing-it', '', '', '2009-12-16 00:19:43', '2009-12-15 23:19:43', '', 0, 'https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/?p=2281', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2397, 4, '2009-12-18 00:46:07', '2009-12-17 23:46:07', '12.18.09\n\nI C U - In Paris. <span style="color: #888888;">Week #13. Post 3.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;">This is a quick one. Not for any other reason than I am exhausted from getting this show together for Saturday. I am very excited. Our first show in Paris, inside a very funky scooter shop, Free Scoot which is directly behind the Notre Dame of all places. Fantastic.</span></span></span>\n\nA vente prive as well as a celebration of our new store, under a new name, fresh ideas, jewelry, and minds.\n\n<a href="http://www.icuinparis.com" target="_blank">I C U - In Paris</a>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;">If your in in the neighborhood, or you know of anyone who is, e-mail us! We would love to see you or them!</span></span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></span></span>\n\n[caption id="attachment_2424" align="aligncenter" width="720" caption="I C U - In Paris"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2424" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/18/a-change-has-come-now-a-vente-privee-to-celebrate/invit2-2/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2424  " title="INVIT2" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/INVIT21.jpg" alt="I C U - In Paris" width="720" height="514" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></span></span>\n\nThese are the cards we will offer people at the show...posted for those who cannot grace us with your presence.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2403" align="aligncenter" width="459" caption="David Tishbi Moonstone Ring"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2403" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/18/a-change-has-come-now-a-vente-privee-to-celebrate/i-c-u-4x6-postcard-face-1/"><img class="size-large wp-imag