(2431, 4, '2009-12-22 22:36:27', '2009-12-22 21:36:27', '<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;">12.22.09</p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;">Joyeux Nol. Happy Holidays. Break time!<span style="color: #888888;">Week #14. Post 1.</span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #000000;">(Small discrepancy with the blog...since we changed the name &amp; url the pictures are not displaying properly. This will be fixed asap).</span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #000000;">Okay, so late update here, but the show over the weekend went very well. We are all quite exhausted and ready for a small break... a good thing indeed. Thank you to all who weathered the Paris cold and came to shop, look, talk and network. Really. Loved the presence we had. </span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">So now, it''s time to relax, tranquil, repose. But before I do, I wanted to post a couple images from a shoot I styled the weekend before last. Again, for Dewald Brand''s clothing line, </span><a href="http://www.behemothofmoscow.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #000000;">Behemoth of Moscow</span></a><span style="color: #000000;">. A fantastic juxtaposition of the cool collected man and the laid-back, guitar-player. </span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">However, before I post those pics, </span><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?s=shamila" target="_blank"><span style="color: #000000;">Shamila</span></a><span style="color: #000000;">, jewelry designer and friend asked me to post about Samantha Zaza. She is a friend of Shamila and sincerely an incredible artist. Zaza recently entered into an illustration competition and each artist was asked to submit their own shoe design to </span><span style="color: #000000;"><a href=" http://www.fluevog.com/code/fc_finalists.php">Fluevog</a>.</span><span style="color: #000000;"> The contest was for an ad promotion for their own shoe design and the drawing below is the design which Zaza submitted for her Mini Zaza shoe. Fantastic. </span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">Unfortunately, we all just missed the deadline to vote for this incredible artistry, however please do take a minute to check out her site. Really, this young woman has a real talent. Check out her website </span><a href="http://www.szaza.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #000000;">HERE</span></a><span style="color: #000000;">. </span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"> </span></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2433" align="aligncenter" width="180" caption="Fluevog Shoes Illustration Competition"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2433" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/22/time-for-a-small-break/zara-samantha/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2433 " title="Zaza-samantha" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Zara-samantha.jpg" alt="Fluevog Shoes Illustration Competiton" width="180" height="180" /></a>[/caption]\n\nSome examples of Samantha Zaza''s work...more on her <a href="http://www.szaza.com/" target="_blank">website</a>.\n\nFrom the <a href="http://www.szaza.com/awpd01.htm" target="_blank">Angry Woman in Party Dresses</a> Collection:\n\n[caption id="attachment_2455" align="aligncenter" width="400" caption="Angry Woman in Party Dresses"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2455" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/22/time-for-a-small-break/awpd_09_001-1/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2455" title="awpd_09_001-1" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/awpd_09_001-1.jpg" alt="awpd_09_001-1" width="400" height="400" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2456" align="aligncenter" width="400" caption="Angry Woman in Party Dresses"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2456" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/22/time-for-a-small-break/aw02/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2456" title="aw02" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/aw02.jpg" alt="Angry Woman in Party Dresses" width="400" height="400" /></a>[/caption]\n\nFrom the <a href="http://www.szaza.com/lpd01.htm" target="_blank">Les Petits Dsirs</a> collection:\n\n[caption id="attachment_2449" align="aligncenter" width="400" caption="Les Petits Dsirs"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2449" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/22/time-for-a-small-break/lpd07_09/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2449" title="lpd07_09" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/lpd07_09.jpg" alt="Les Petits Dsirs" width="400" height="400" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2450" align="aligncenter" width="400" caption="Les Petits Dsirs"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2450" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/22/time-for-a-small-break/lpd07_06/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2450" title="lpd07_06" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/lpd07_06.jpg" alt="Les Petits Dsirs" width="400" height="400" /></a>[/caption]\n\nAnd from the <a href="http://www.szaza.com/draw01.htm" target="_blank">Sketch book</a>:\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-2451" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/22/time-for-a-small-break/lmoly03-004/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2451 aligncenter" title="LMoly03-004" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/LMoly03-004.jpg" alt="From the Sketch Book" width="509" height="400" /></a></p>\n<a rel="attachment wp-att-2452" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/22/time-for-a-small-break/lmoly03-022/"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2452" title="LMoly03-022" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/LMoly03-022.jpg" alt="LMoly03-022" width="509" height="400" /></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-2453" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/22/time-for-a-small-break/migraine01/"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2453" title="migraine01" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/migraine01.jpg" alt="migraine01" width="509" height="400" /></a>\n\n<a rel="attachment wp-att-2454" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/22/time-for-a-small-break/lmoly03-032/"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2454" title="LMoly03-032" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/LMoly03-032.jpg" alt="LMoly03-032" width="509" height="400" /></a>\n\nAnd now the pics from Behemoth of Moscow photoshoot.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2434" align="aligncenter" width="604" caption="Behemoth Of Moscow"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2434" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/22/time-for-a-small-break/behemoth-of-moscow-1/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2434" title="behemoth-of-moscow-1" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/behemoth-of-moscow-1.jpg" alt="Behemoth Of Moscow" width="604" height="604" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2435" align="aligncenter" width="604" caption="Behemoth Of Moscow"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2435" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/22/time-for-a-small-break/behemoth-of-moscow-3/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2435" title="behemoth-of-moscow-3" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/behemoth-of-moscow-3.jpg" alt="Behemoth Of Moscow" width="604" height="414" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2436" align="aligncenter" width="604" caption="Behemoth of Moscow T-Shirt &amp; Jacket"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2436" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/22/time-for-a-small-break/behemoth-of-moscow-2/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2436" title="behemoth-of-moscow-2" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/behemoth-of-moscow-2.jpg" alt="Behemoth of Moscow T-Shirt &amp; Jacket" width="604" height="414" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2437" align="aligncenter" width="604" caption="Behemoth of Moscow Flanel Hoodie"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2437" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/22/time-for-a-small-break/behemoth-of-moscow-4/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2437" title="behemoth-of-moscow-4" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/behemoth-of-moscow-4.jpg" alt="Behemoth of Moscow Flanel Hoodie" width="604" height="414" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2438" align="aligncenter" width="604" caption="Behemoth of Moscow. Purple Man. "]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2438" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/22/time-for-a-small-break/behemoth-of-moscow-6/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2438" title="behemoth-of-moscow-6" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/behemoth-of-moscow-6.jpg" alt="Behemoth of Moscow. Purple Man. " width="604" height="414" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2439" align="aligncenter" width="604" caption="Behemoth of Moscow. Love this shot. "]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2439" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/12/22/time-for-a-small-break/behemoth-of-moscow-5/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2439" title="behemoth-of-moscow-5" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/behemoth-of-moscow-5.jpg" alt="Behemoth of Moscow. Love this shot. " width="604" height="414" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center;">__________________________________________________________________________________________</p>', 'Time for a small break.', 'Okay, so late update here, but the show over the weekend went very well. We are all quite exhausted and ready for a small break... a good thing indeed. Thank you to all who weathered the Paris cold and came to shop, look, talk and network. Really. Loved the presence we had.\n\nSo now, it''s time to relax, tranquil, repose. But before I do, I wanted to post a couple images from a shoot I styled the weekend before last. Again, for Dewald Brand''s clothing line, Behemoth of Moscow. A fantastic juxtaposition of the cool collected man and the laid-back, guitar-player.\n\nBut before I post the pics, Shamila, jewelry designer and friend asked me to post about a friend''s illustration competition. It is a drawing in order to win the space of an advertisement for the company, they sell shoes. You can vote until the end of day today. Here is the link: FLUEVOG and below is the picture to be voted for...\n\n', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'time-for-a-small-break', '', '', '2009-12-22 22:36:27', '2009-12-22 21:36:27', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=2431', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2469, 4, '2010-01-03 14:27:06', '2010-01-03 13:27:06', '1.04.10\n\nTo the New Year! Christmas in Paris. Lights, lights &amp; more lights. <span style="color: #888888;">Week #14. Post 1.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;">I hope you all had a wonderful holiday season. Its so funny, the holidays sometimes cause such a frenzy in people, you feel like you need another holiday after this one. Honestly, I saw more than three disputes in Paris! People get so worked up over buying presents, seeing family, getting to places in time, cooking, eating, drinking, gaining weight, losing weight...eh, yay, yay. It can be quite exhausting!</span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;">However, at the same time there is always the beautiful, pleasant, loving side of the holidays. Connecting with friends and family, offering gifts you know will bring a smile, watching silly Christmas movies (Polar Express is amazing by the way!), and my favorite, seeing all the Christmas lights and decorations throughout the city.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">I was lucky enough to have my mom visit. The first time in France in forty years and her French was spot on! Fantastic. She brought along her camera of course, being a photographer for quite some time I could not wait to share some of her images with all of you. </span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">Paris. Christmas. The lights. The people. The Gypsy tricksters. All apart of a Holiday week...along with a couple extra kilos. </span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">Happy New Year everyone. Bonne Anne. May all your wishes, thoughts, goals and dreams persevere in 2010. </span></span>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">________________</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">Below: </span><span style="color: #000000;">Paris</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">Photographer:</span> Julia Summers</em></p>\n\nHotel De Ville just to your right, a temporary skating rink; although a bit bizarre in it''s placement, it is quite the popular activity to do for those who stay in Paris for the holidays.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2471" align="aligncenter" width="600" caption="Hotel De Ville Skating Rink"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2471" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/03/bonne-annee-a-paris-christmas/hotel-de-ville-skating/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2471" title="hotel de ville skating" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/hotel-de-ville-skating.jpg" alt="Hotel De Ville Skating Rink" width="600" height="402" /></a>[/caption]\n\nI love this one. This one is a landmark which stays year-round and perfect for the little ones who can''t yet skate.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2472" align="aligncenter" width="600" caption="Carousel"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2472" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/03/bonne-annee-a-paris-christmas/carousel-hotel-de-ville/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2472" title="carousel hotel de ville" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/carousel-hotel-de-ville.jpg" alt="Carousel" width="600" height="458" /></a>[/caption]\n\nAnd a little closer...\n\n[caption id="attachment_2473" align="aligncenter" width="420" caption="Round-a-Bout"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2473" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/03/bonne-annee-a-paris-christmas/round-a-bout/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2473 " title="round-a-bout" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/round-a-bout.jpg" alt="Round-a-Bout" width="420" height="627" /></a>[/caption]\n\nHard to catch this one...there were lights decorating the facade of Hotel De Ville. Flashing, sparkling. It looked just magical.\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"> </span>\n\n[caption id="attachment_2470" align="aligncenter" width="378" caption="Hotel De Ville. Christmas Trees and lots of Lights. "]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2470" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/03/bonne-annee-a-paris-christmas/hotel-de-ville-and-the-lights/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2470  " title="hotel de ville and the lights" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/hotel-de-ville-and-the-lights.jpg" alt="Hotel De Ville. Christmas Trees and lots of Lights. " width="378" height="564" /></a>[/caption]\n\nAnother hard one to capture, but this could not be missed. Un upside Christmas tree smiling through the windows of Hotel De Ville.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2474" align="aligncenter" width="336" caption="The Upside down Christmas Tree"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2474" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/03/bonne-annee-a-paris-christmas/upside-christmas/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2474  " title="upside christmas" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/upside-christmas.jpg" alt="The Upside down Christmas Tree" width="336" height="433" /></a>[/caption]\n\nAhhh...<a href="http://www.bhv.fr/" target="_blank">BHV</a>. The mecca of a shopping center in the heart of Paris. The shopping rush was in full swing as we admired the lights. Flashing, blinking colors of blue, green, purple, magenta, yellow, red, orange. A full rainbow spectrum and to top it off <em>Noel</em> in fluorescent lights above the entrance.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2475" align="aligncenter" width="540" caption="BHV &amp; The LIGHTS!"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2475" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/03/bonne-annee-a-paris-christmas/bhv-lights/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2475 " title="BHV lights" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/BHV-lights.jpg" alt="BHV &amp; The LIGHTS!" width="540" height="362" /></a>[/caption]\n\nAnd it didn''t end upon entrance. Welcoming you from one of the many BHV doors, our lovely sequined mannequin standing under a rainfall of fluorescence.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2476" align="aligncenter" width="420" caption="BHV &amp; More Lights Inside"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2476" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/03/bonne-annee-a-paris-christmas/paris-manneiquin-bhv/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2476 " title="paris manneiquin BHV" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/paris-manneiquin-BHV.jpg" alt="BHV &amp; More Lights Inside" width="420" height="627" /></a>[/caption]\n\nOnto <a href="http://www.notredamedeparis.fr/" target="_blank">Notre Dame</a>. Something a bit more natural and calming. We walked through the cathedral, basking in its immense structure and overwhelming amount of lit candles. No electricity necessary here.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2477" align="aligncenter" width="540" caption="Notre Dame Lights"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2477" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/03/bonne-annee-a-paris-christmas/notre-dame-candles/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2477 " title="notre dame candles" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/notre-dame-candles.jpg" alt="Notre Dame Lights" width="540" height="362" /></a>[/caption]\n\nA landmark in Paris. The Gypsies. Surround the most popular monuments and ask, well beg for your money. I can never tell how real their character is. How crippled they really are and how badly they do need my money. Well, my mom being my mom asked this particular Gypsy if she could take her picture, for a couple euros in return she obliged. I welcome you to create your own perception of her character by the look in her eyes...(check out the moon to the right of her).\n\n[caption id="attachment_2487" align="aligncenter" width="384" caption="Notre Dame Gypsy"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2487" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/03/bonne-annee-a-paris-christmas/notrre-dame-trickster/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2487  " title="Notre Dame Trickster" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/notrre-dame-trickster.jpg" alt="Notre Dame Gypsy" width="384" height="574" /></a>[/caption]\n\nNotre Dame to the right, gorgeous moon to the left, felt like a scene from an old movie.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2479" align="aligncenter" width="384" caption="Paris Moon"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2479" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/03/bonne-annee-a-paris-christmas/paris-lune/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2479  " title="paris lune" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/paris-lune.jpg" alt="Paris Moon" width="384" height="574" /></a>[/caption]\n\nAnd of course, something for the sustainability conscience in all of us. Why cut down a tree when you can make a Christmas out of plastic bottles?\n\n[caption id="attachment_2480" align="aligncenter" width="378" caption="The Plastic Bottle Christmas Tree"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2480" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/03/bonne-annee-a-paris-christmas/plastic-bottle-christmas-tree/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2480  " title="plastic bottle christmas tree" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/plastic-bottle-christmas-tree.jpg" alt="The Plastic Bottle Christmas Tree" width="378" height="564" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center;">______________________________________________________________________________</p>', 'Bonne Anne! A Paris Christmas.', 'Paris Christmas. Hotel De ville is a spectacular scene at this time of year. Lights everywhere, skating rink, carousel, lights, lights and more lights. The square looks magical, the people, well people are always ind of crazy for holidays but I must say, Christmas in Paris is just beautiful. Well done to the Parisians. ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bonne-annee-a-paris-christmas', '', '', '2010-01-03 14:27:06', '2010-01-03 13:27:06', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=2469', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2514, 4, '2010-01-05 21:41:53', '2010-01-05 20:41:53', '<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>1.06.10</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em> </em><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;">The Naked Truth. </span></em><em>Week #14. Post 2.</em></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">Okay, so I may be written off from the rest of the fashion industry after this post, but I feel it is one of those not-to-be-ignored subject. My attention was first struck when I read the article on the <a href="http://nymag.com/" target="_blank">New York Magazine</a> web page: </span><a href="http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2010/01/does_a_naked_unretouched_super.html?imw=Y&amp;f=most-viewed-24h5" target="_blank"><span style="color: #808080;">"Does a Naked, Unretouched Super Model Promote Positive Body Image?"</span></a><span style="color: #808080;">. </span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">Down under, in Australia, the campaign run by the </span><a href="http://www.thebutterflyfoundation.org.au/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #808080;">Butterfly Foundation</span></a><span style="color: #000000;"> against photo retouching lands on the cover of Marie Claire, with supermodel, <a href="http://www.jenniferhawkins.com.au/" target="_blank">Jennifer Hawkins</a> posing naked, un-retouched. You may ask, as I did, okay, but she is a supermodel! Of course they used her as an example not to re-touch. Yes, I agree, and the question is why are we supposed to feel better about seeing a supermodel, naked and un-retouched? Well, Julie Parker, the Butterfly Foundation''s general manager has your answer (and why they did not use a "regular" shaped woman:</span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; text-align: center; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;">"The thing is unfortunately it doesn''t make the same point, because Jennifer sells magazines and she creates awareness. If Marie Claire had chosen to put on their cover an ordinary women, say myself or a friend of yours, it would not have created the awareness it does."</span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; text-align: left; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">I bring this subject to a post because I just received images from a photo shoot I did during October. The model is absolutely beautiful, naturally. She honestly does not need to be re-touched, but we re-touch because this is now considered to be a necessity, perfection, un-real has to be had.</span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; text-align: left; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">This is exactly what the <a href="http://www.thebutterflyfoundation.org.au/" target="_blank">Butterfly Foundation</a> is trying to make a point of. It is a waste of time to compare to women in magazines because they are not real. Believe me, I know. I''ve watched a woman transformed before my eyes with a whole bunch of clicks from a mouse. </span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; text-align: left; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">So, here is Ellen. A naturally striking model I worked with in October along side Photographer <a href="http://www.kendrarae.com/" target="_blank">Kendra Rae</a>, Make-up Artist Eva and Assistant Stylist (and beloved guest blogger!), Erin Kim.</span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; text-align: left; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">I''ll show you some shots which are un-touched, then the shots which are touched to perfection. </span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">________________</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">Below: <span style="color: #000000;">I C U - In Paris &amp; Kenda Rae</span></span><span style="color: #000000;"> Photo Shoot</span></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">Photographer:</span> <a href="http://www.kendrarae.com/" target="_blank">Kendra Rae</a></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #808080;">Make-up Artist:</span> Eva</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #808080;">Stylist &amp; Creative Director:</span> <a href="http://shownd.com/csummers" target="_blank">Christan Summers</a></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em><span style="color: #808080;">Assistant Stylist:</span> <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?s=erin+kim" target="_blank">Erin Kim</a></em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><em>\n</em></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;">First shot. The lighting is off, Ellen is cold and the picture is not zoomed or cropped.</p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2530" align="aligncenter" width="446" caption="Ellen Un-touched"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2530" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/05/the-naked-truth-un-touched-vs-re-touched-models/kendra-ras-and-icuinparis-tuileres-garden-paris-3-2/"><img class="size-large wp-image-2530" title="kendra rae and icuinparis tuileres garden paris 3" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/kendra-ras-and-icuinparis-tuileres-garden-paris-31-744x1024.jpg" alt="kendra rae and icuinparis tuileres garden paris 3" width="446" height="614" /></a>[/caption]\n\nThis was a sight. We were working to get a shot on the carousel when the machine operator started it with no warning. Ellen, half-naked and freezing could not get off the ride until it stopped, so we went with it. Bare feet and cold lips. Un-touched.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2531" align="aligncenter" width="409" caption="Ellen Un-touched"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2531" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/05/the-naked-truth-un-touched-vs-re-touched-models/kendra-and-icuinparis-3/"><img class="size-large wp-image-2531 " title="Kendra and Icuinparis" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/Kendra-and-Icuinparis2-682x1024.jpg" alt="Ellen Un-touched" width="409" height="614" /></a>[/caption]\n\nHere you can really see the difference, especially in how cold Ellen was when we were shooting. She is blue! ey!\n\n[caption id="attachment_2532" align="aligncenter" width="574" caption="Ellen Re-touched Vs. Un-touched"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2532" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/05/the-naked-truth-un-touched-vs-re-touched-models/ellen-touched-vs-untouched/"><img class="size-large wp-image-2532  " title="ellen-touched-vs-untouched" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/ellen-touched-vs-untouched-1024x635.jpg" alt="Ellen Touched Vs. Un-touched" width="574" height="356" /></a>[/caption]\n\nNow, lightly re-touched...\n\n[caption id="attachment_2516" align="aligncenter" width="432" caption="Carousel"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2516" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/05/the-naked-truth-un-touched-vs-re-touched-models/kendrae-rae-and-icuinparis-tuileres-garden-paris/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2516  " title="kendrae rae and icuinparis tuileres garden paris" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/kendrae-rae-and-icuinparis-tuileres-garden-paris.jpg" alt="Carousel" width="432" height="498" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; display: block; padding: 0px;"><span style="color: #888888;"><em> </em></span></p>\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\nNow, re-touched to perfection...\n\n[caption id="attachment_2521" align="aligncenter" width="480" caption="Lisa Levine Earrings"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2521" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/05/the-naked-truth-un-touched-vs-re-touched-models/lisa-levine-on-ellen/"><img class="size-full wp-image-2521 " title="lisa levine on ellen" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/lisa-levine-on-ellen.jpg" alt="Lisa Levine Earrings" width="480" height="535" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2522" align="aligncenter" width="491" caption="Ellen &amp; the Eiffel"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2522" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/05/the-naked-truth-un-touched-vs-re-touched-models/kendrarae1/"><img class="size-large wp-image-2522  " title="KENDRARAE1" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/KENDRARAE1-1024x682.jpg" alt="Ellen &amp; the Eiffel" width="491" height="327" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2523" align="aligncenter" width="368" caption="Ellen &amp; The Eiffel 2"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2523" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/05/the-naked-truth-un-touched-vs-re-touched-models/kendrarae2/"><img class="size-large wp-image-2523  " title="KENDRARAE2" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/KENDRARAE2-682x1024.jpg" alt="Ellen &amp; The Eiffel 2" width="368" height="553" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2524" align="aligncenter" width="382" caption="Bohemian Chic. Ellen wears Lisa Levine Leather &amp; Silver Chain Headband"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2524" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/05/the-naked-truth-un-touched-vs-re-touched-models/kendrarae4/"><img class="size-large wp-image-2524  " title="KENDRARAE4" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/KENDRARAE4-682x1024.jpg" alt="Bohemian Chic" width="382" height="574" /></a>[/caption]\n\nThis is the winner. Ellen is wearing Zhen U.N. gold and citrine earrings and Any NY 24k gold and silver gradient necklace from the <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/" target="_blank">boutique</a>.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2525" align="aligncenter" width="398" caption="Ellen is wearing Zhen U.N. gold &amp; Citrine Earrings &amp; Any NY 24k Gold &amp; Silver Necklace"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-2525" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/05/the-naked-truth-un-touched-vs-re-touched-models/kendrarae3/"><img class="size-large wp-image-2525    " title="KENDRARAE3" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/KENDRARAE3-682x1024.jpg" alt="Zhen U.N. &amp; Any NY " width="398" height="597" /></a>[/caption]\n\nSo, in conclusion, by showing this comparison I am not trying to take away from the talents of models or photographers or the beauty of these shots. I honestly believe 75% of the time photographers do not need to re-touch, but again it is now a industry must.\n\nTrust me, I''ve tried to use "un-perfect" images and I''m told by customers and colleagues the pictures are working against me. I wonder sometimes, what happened to the natural beauty? The real? The comfortable, un-loathing comparison? Because no matter what, most woman compare.\n\nI found this <a href="http://www.theage.com.au/lifestyle/wellbeing/body-image-foundation-defends-nude-jennifer-hawkins-cover-20100104-lox9.html?autostart=1" target="_blank">video interview</a> with Julie Parker on the magazine article and why they used Jennifer Hawkins as their un-touched subject. I like what they are doing especially as the efforts of fighting against eating disorders and the un-real ''perfect'' continue.\n<p style="text-align: center;">____________________________________________________________________________________</p>', 'The Naked Truth. Un-Touched Vs. Re-Touched Models.', 'Okay, so I may be written off from the rest of the fashion industry after this post, but I feel it is one of those not-to-be-ignored subject. My attention was first struck when I read the article on the New York Magazine web page: "Does a Naked, Unretouched Super Model Promote Positive Body Image?".\n\nI bring this subject to a post because I just received images from a photo shoot I did during October. The model is absolutely beautiful, naturally. She honestly does not need to be re-touched, but we re-touch because this is now considered to be a necessity, perfection, un-real has to be had.\n\nSo, here is Ellen. A naturally striking model I worked with in October along side Photographer Kendra Rae, Make-up Artist Eva and Assistant Stylist (and beloved guest blogger!), Erin Kim.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-naked-truth-un-touched-vs-re-touched-models', '', '', '2010-01-05 21:41:53', '2010-01-05 20:41:53', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=2514', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2566, 4, '2010-01-08 09:42:55', '2010-01-08 08:42:55', '<em>1.08.10</em>\n\n<em> </em><em>India &amp; The Sought After Strategy.<span style="color: #888888;">Week #14. Post 3.</span></em>\n\nI subscribe to a blog called the <a href="http://www.businessoffashion.com/" target="_blank">Business Of Fashion</a> and everyday on the metro my thoughts are filled with fashion business and economy news. Really, <a href="http://www.businessoffashion.com/about/imran-amed-editor-london" target="_blank">Imran Amed</a> has an amazing pulse on fashion news and updates.\n\nThis morning I was launched into the land of India and what luxury retailers are desperately seeking to find in order to reach correctly and strategically to the market. A subject which hits a familiar spot simply because I have traveled to India in order to work with jewelry artisans and it is true, the market is not always easy to define nor simple to work within as a Westerner.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2567" align="aligncenter" width="500" caption="Luxury Retailers Targeting India"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/Targeting-India-luxury-market.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2567" title="Targeting-India-luxury-market" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/Targeting-India-luxury-market.jpg" alt="Luxury Retailers Targeting India" width="500" height="328" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\nRetailers are learning the necessity to localise marketing plans and strategies. The size and range of dialects, religions, cultural norms and styles have to be understood and specially targeted in order for any retailer to have success in the Indian market. Here is a video I pulled from <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8iPTeGS0JyU&amp;feature=related" target="_blank">YouTube</a> which talks about the potential of India as manufacturers as well as the fact India will be the next ''hub'' for luxury retail companies.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="425" height="344" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/8iPTeGS0JyU&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="425" height="344" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/8iPTeGS0JyU&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"> </embed></object>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">On a personal note, I feel some what protective of the market and the idea of luxury retailers eyeing India as the next ''big buck''. India is one of the most beautiful places I have ever seen in my life. The thought the Western luxury market influencing India makes me feel a bit nostalgic, but at the same time we live in a globalized economy and if marketing is done respectfully it can be a benefit for everyone.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2568" align="aligncenter" width="388" caption="The Contrast. Is it a conflict?"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/India-luxury-market.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2568" title="India-luxury-market" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/India-luxury-market.jpg" alt="The Contrast. Is it a conflict?" width="388" height="388" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: left;">On a positive note, the people of India are not to be underestimated. Retailers have to learn how to remain sensitive to the vast cultures, people and religions India houses. If retailers are able to do this (which is their biggest challenge), then the people of India will respond. However, if they do not take the time to educate them self on the people, their efforts will be lost.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Below are some images I took from my last trip to Jaipur, India. I worked with a small jewelry shop, Vishnu Gems run by two men named Jai and Titu, they work harder than any people I have ever met.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The best part, their shop is within a market for farmers and directly outside their front door are endless rows of fresh fruits, vegetables, spices and of course the neighboring monkeys who ever-so desperately try to steal what they can. A fantastic scene.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Below:</em> Pictures from inside Vishnu Gems. Boxes stacked full of semi-precious stones, walls decorated with jewelry and counter cases which display the most beautiful precious stones and designs.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2569" align="aligncenter" width="408" caption="Vishnu Gem Shop"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/the-shop.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2569 " title="the-shop" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/the-shop-680x1024.jpg" alt="Vishnu Gems " width="408" height="614" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<em>Below: </em>The men of the shop hard at work. That is Titu on the phone and Jai (the two owners) standing behind the counter weighing jewelry... oh and grapes.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2570" align="aligncenter" width="560" caption="Hard At Work"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/hard-at-work.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2570 " title="hard-at-work" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/hard-at-work.jpg" alt="" width="560" height="372" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<em>Below: </em>A typical style for jewelry in India, I still find these stones incredible. All tourmaline, hand-drilled, hand-strung.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2577" align="aligncenter" width="367" caption="Multi-colored Tourmaline Necklace"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/necklace-made-of-tourmaline.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2577  " title="necklace-made-of-tourmaline" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/necklace-made-of-tourmaline-680x1024.jpg" alt="" width="367" height="553" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<em>Below:</em> Mukesh (I can never remember the name of the guy eating the grapes), and Deepak.\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2571" align="aligncenter" width="408" caption="The Boys of the Shop"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/the-boys.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2571 " title="the-boys" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/the-boys-680x1024.jpg" alt="The Boys of the Shop" width="408" height="614" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<em>Below:</em> My partner in all motor bike rides (crazy!) and shop visits, Bharat.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2576" align="aligncenter" width="408" caption="Bharat"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/partner-and-crime-Bharat.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2576 " title="partner-in-crime-Bharat" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/partner-and-crime-Bharat-680x1024.jpg" alt="" width="408" height="614" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<em> Below: </em>The view of the market outside Vishnu Gems shop.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2572" align="aligncenter" width="640" caption="The Famer&#39;s Marketplace Outside the Shop&#39;s Door"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/the-marketplace.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2572 " title="the-marketplace" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/the-marketplace.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="426" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<em>Below: </em>And the roaming monkeys...\n\n[caption id="attachment_2575" align="aligncenter" width="560" caption="And The Monkeys"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/monkeys-on-the-roof.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2575 " title="monkeys-on-the-roof" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/monkeys-on-the-roof.jpg" alt="" width="560" height="372" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<em>Below: </em>And my favorite. Papu. Everyday I arrive and Papu would be there. Smiling, happy, ready for another day of selling and fighting off the monkeys.\n\n[caption id="attachment_2573" align="aligncenter" width="560" caption="My Favorite. Papu"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/papu.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2573 " title="papu" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/papu.jpg" alt="" width="560" height="372" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center;">_____________________________________________________________________________________________</p>', 'India &amp; The Sought After Strategy.', '1.08.10\n\nIndia & The Sought After Strategy. Week #14. Post 3.\n\nI subscribe to a blog called the Business Of Fashion and everyday on the metro my thoughts are filled with fashion business and economy news. Really, Imran Amed has an amazing pulse on fashion news and updates.\n\nThis morning I was launched into the land of India and what luxury retailers are desperately seeking to find in order to reach correctly and strategically to the market.\n\nPosted is a video talking about the luxury retailers efforts into India as well as an insider''s look at the smaller retailers...pictures from my last trip to Jaipur, India...\n\n', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'india-the-sought-after-strategy', '', '', '2010-01-08 09:42:55', '2010-01-08 08:42:55', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=2566', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2594, 4, '2010-01-10 18:59:21', '2010-01-10 17:59:21', '<em>1.11.10</em>\n\n<em> </em><em>What Feeds You? An I C U - In Paris Exclusive Video.<span style="color: #888888;">Week #15. Post 1.</span></em>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;">Recently, we sat down with Parisian film maker, Laetitia Gadan Karmaly for an intimate interview. The idea, the main question: what feeds you? What inspires you? </span>\n\nJewelry &amp; Accessories assist in the formation of identities, hence our love for them.   The idea for this video, and others to come is about talking with people (some of them customers) and finding how and why they are inspired by jewelry, accessories and fashion.\n\nHow do you express your self and why?\n\n<em>________________</em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #808080;">Below:</span><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/" target="_blank"> What feeds you? I C U  In Paris Exclusive Video</a></em>\n\n<em><em><span style="color: #808080;">Interviewed</span></em><span style="color: #808080;">:</span> <a href="http://laetitiagadan.blogspot.com/" target="_blank">Laetitia Gadan Karmaly </a></em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #808080;">Film Maker:</span> <a href="http://brunoferreira.com" target="_blank">Bruno Ferreria</a></em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #808080;">Creative Director &amp; Interviewer:</span> <a href="http://shownd.com/csummers" target="_blank">Christan Summers</a></em>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><em>\n</em></span>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="425" height="344" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/Qhw5gJrMsg0&amp;hl=en&amp;fs=1" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="425" height="344" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/Qhw5gJrMsg0&amp;hl=en&amp;fs=1" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"></embed></object>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">_____________________________________________________________________________</p>', 'What Feeds You? An I C U  In Paris Exclusive Video', '1.11.10\n\nWhat Feeds You? An I C U - In Paris Exclusive Video. Week #15. Post 1.\n\nRecently, we sat down with Parisian film maker, Laetitia Gadan Karmaly for an intimate interview. The idea, the main question: what feeds you? What inspires you?\n\nJewelry & Accessories assist in the formation of identities, hence our love for them. The idea for this video, and others to come is about talking with people (some of them customers) and finding how and why they are inspired by jewelry, accessories and fashion.\n\nHow do you express your self and why?\n\nVideo please....', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'what-feeds-you-an-i-c-u-in-paris-exclusive-video', '', '', '2010-01-10 18:59:21', '2010-01-10 17:59:21', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=2594', 0, 'post', '', 0);
