(2607, 4, '2010-01-12 22:50:20', '2010-01-12 21:50:20', '<em>1.13.10</em>\n\n<em> </em><em>The Death of Bunny Munro.<span style="color: #888888;">Week #15. Post 2.</span></em>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;">Nick Cave. A creatively renaissance Australian man; musician, songwriter, author, screenwriter, and occasional film actor. For this round, we are getting him on his author side; <a href="http://www.thedeathofbunnymunro.com/index.html" target="_blank">The Death Of Bunny Munro</a> released in September 2009 swept the reviews with awe and praise. </span></span></em></span>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;">\n<img class="aligncenter" title="the-death-of-bunny-monro-by-nick-cave" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/the-death-of-bunny-monroe-by-nick-cave.jpg" alt="" width="297" height="430" /></span></span></em></span></p>\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;">The<a href="http://www.rollingstone.com/rockdaily/index.php/2009/09/17/nick-cave-says-dark-novel-bunny-munro-inspired-by-avril-lavigne-and-kylie-minogues-hot-pants/" target="_blank">Rolling Stone </a>online news wrote; </span>"The Death of Bunny Munro is awash in sex, violence and sleaze, a bleakly hilarious trip through the sordid life of a traveling salesman. Like most people youd meet in a Nick Cave song, Bunny is a disturbing character. He cheats on his wife until she commits suicide, then he takes his nine-year-old son on the road, selling beauty products and trying to hustle the customers. He has depraved fantasies about Minogue as well as Avril Lavinge. Bunnys obsessed with sex, Cave says. Yet hes not actually that good at it."</span></em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">Not the book to read to your kids, however notable. <a href="http://www.nick-cave.com/" target="_blank">Nick Cave </a> is surely a man of interest and one who has learned to express his thoughts and emotions very successfully through creative and media. This is his second novel, which was initially a screenplay for John Hillcoat, who Cave wrote<em>The Proposition</em> for. </span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">Hillcoat wanted a story about a traveling salesmen, so Cave interviewed some of them. Slowly, a story began to unfold as these salesman revealed the "''underworld'' they live in: drug-taking, alcohol-drinking, womanizing." The results turned into this novel which was written while on the road with his band, the<a href="http://www.nickcaveandthebadseeds.com/" target="_blank">Bad Seeds.</a></span></span>\n\n[caption id="" align="aligncenter" width="434" caption="Nick Cave, the author of Bunny Munro"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/Bunny_Munro_Nick_Cave.jpg"><img title="Bunny_Munro_Nick_Cave" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/Bunny_Munro_Nick_Cave.jpg" alt="Bunny_Munro_Nick_Cave" width="434" height="335" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;">Well, tonight in Paris there is an event for the book which was organized by,<a href="http://www.plateformag.com/VERNISSAGE-CONCERTS-Sur-la-route.html?lang=fr" target="_blank">PLATEFORM Magazine</a> (founded by photographer and friend, <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/23/photo-shoot-i-c-u-in-paris/" target="_blank">Laurence Geunoun</a>) and<a href="http://editions.flammarion.com/Home_Departements.cfm?levelCode=litterature" target="_blank">FLAMMARION</a> (French publication site and store). </span></span></em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;">For the release of Nick Cave''s, Death of Bunny Munro, PLATEFORM Magazine organized a competition on the theme:"On the road to Bunny Munro" and asked photographers / artists to send aseries of 15 pictures / creations and find excerpts from the story of Bunny Munro in order to create their own illustrative story line of the book. </span></span></em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;">The winner will receive: an exhibition, a publication in PLATEFORM Mag, autographed books, prints, T-shirts WHO "I Love Rock''n''Roll"</span></span></em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;">So tonight, the winner will be unveiled. </span></span></em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;">We shall be there and will do our best to bring as much material back with us to share for Friday''s post. </span></span></em></span>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/PLATEFORM-INVITE-BUNNY-MONROE-NICK-CAVE.jpg" target="_blank">\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2610" title="PLATEFORM-INVITE-BUNNY-MONROE-NICK-CAVE" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/PLATEFORM-INVITE-BUNNY-MONROE-NICK-CAVE.jpg" alt="" width="768" height="512" /></a>\n</span></span></em></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/plateform-invite.jpg" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2609" title="plateform-invite" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/plateform-invite.jpg" alt="" width="350" height="249" /></a></span></span></em></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;">___________________________________________________________________</span></span></em></span></p>', 'The Death Of Bunny Munro. By, Nick Cave.', 'The Death of Bunny Munro. Week #15. Post 2.\n\nNick Cave. A renaissance of a creative man; an Australian musician, songwriter, author, screenwriter, and occasional film actor. We are getting him on his author side; The Death Of Bunny Munro released in September 2009 swept the reviews with awe and praise.\n\nThe book, the book...apparently it is "awash in sex, violence and sleaze, a bleakly hilarious trip through the sordid life of a traveling salesman." If you know of Nick Cave as a musician, this will make sense.\n\nTonight is an event in Paris created by the collaboration of PLATEFORM Magazine and Flammarion Publication. The winner of a very interesting contest will be unveiled and we will be there...', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-death-of-bunny-monro-by-nick-cave', '', '', '2010-01-12 22:50:20', '2010-01-12 21:50:20', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=2607', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2626, 4, '2010-01-14 22:17:49', '2010-01-14 21:17:49', '<em>1.15.10</em>\n\n<em> </em><em>The result of Bunny Munro. Il est Mort.<span style="color: #888888;">Week #15. Post 3.</span></em>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;">Wednesday we told you we were going to visit the <a href="http://www.plateformag.com/" target="_blank">PLATEFORM Magazine</a> &amp; <a href="http://editions.flammarion.com/Home_Departements.cfm?levelCode=litterature">Flammarion Publication</a> event to celebrate the winner of the Nick Cave, Bunny Munro contest. </span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;">Here is what we thought, filmed, shot...</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">The vernissage at <a href="http://www.labellevilloise.com/" target="_blank">La Bellevilloise</a> hosted by Plateform Magazine was a collection of artistic talent with independent musicians, photographs &amp; artwork all lending to the scene. </span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">However, the focal point of the entire event was the story of <a href="http://www.nick-cave.com/" target="_blank">The Death of Bunny Munro</a> by <a href="http://www.nick-cave.com/" target="_blank">Nick Cave</a> and the photographs to illustrate the agonizing road that Bunny Munro embarks on with his son. </span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Text by <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?s=erin+kim" target="_blank">Erin Kim</a></em></span></span>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="445" height="364" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/nGGbgZDRYRo&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;border=1" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="445" height="364" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/nGGbgZDRYRo&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;border=1" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"> </embed></object>\n\n[caption id="attachment_2634" align="aligncenter" width="600" caption="Finalist&#39;s submission - from the illustration category"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/plateform-magazine-and-nick-cave-bunny-monro.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2634" title="plateform-magazine-and-nick-cave-bunny-monro" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/plateform-magazine-and-nick-cave-bunny-monro.jpg" alt="Finalist''s submission - from the illustration category" width="600" height="450" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2635" align="aligncenter" width="600" caption="Submissions from the winner of the Photography category"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nick-cave-1.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2635" title="nick-cave-1" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nick-cave-1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="795" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2636" align="aligncenter" width="600" caption="Finalist&#39;s Submission"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nick-cave-3.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2636" title="nick-cave-3" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nick-cave-3.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="450" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2637" align="aligncenter" width="600" caption="Images from the winner of the contest: Name, Unknown. "]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/plateform-magazine-for-nick-cave-contest.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2637" title="plateform-magazine-for-nick-cave-contest" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/plateform-magazine-for-nick-cave-contest.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="450" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<em> </em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_2633" align="aligncenter" width="600" caption="Solas Band for Plateform Magazine &amp; The Nick Cave Exhibit"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/solas-paris-band-for-plateform-magazine.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2633" title="solas-paris-band-for-plateform-magazine" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/solas-paris-band-for-plateform-magazine.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="450" /></a>[/caption]\n\nPhotos by, <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?s=erin+kim" target="_blank">Erin Kim</a>. Video by, <a href="http://shownd.com/csummers" target="_blank">Christan Summers</a>.\n\nAnd below is a music video we found for <a href="http://www.myspace.com/solaslegroupe" target="_blank">Solas</a>, one of the bands who played Wednesday night. The quality of the sound on the ipod video camera is not superb so I figured we could give the band a little more justice with this here.\n\nThis video is really, very cool. The camera they used is fantastic!\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="400" height="300" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=6878932&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=1&amp;show_byline=1&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=&amp;fullscreen=1" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="400" height="300" src="http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=6878932&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=1&amp;show_byline=1&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=&amp;fullscreen=1" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"> </embed></object>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://vimeo.com/6878932">SOLAS band, Perdu le Nord</a> from <a href="http://vimeo.com/user1158336">Alta Media Productions</a> on <a href="http://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">_______________________________________________________________________</p>', 'Bunny Munro. Il est Mort. PLATEFORM Magazine.', '1.15.10\n\nThe result of Bunny Monro. Il est Mort. Week #15. Post 3.\n\nWednesday we told you we were going to visit the PLATEFORM Magazine & Flammarion Publication event to celebrate the winner of the Nick Cave, Bunny Monro contest.\n\nHere is what we thought, filmed, shot...', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bunny-monro-il-est-mort-plateform-magazine', '', '', '2010-01-14 22:17:49', '2010-01-14 21:17:49', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=2626', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2652, 4, '2010-01-17 21:01:01', '2010-01-17 20:01:01', '<em>1.18.10</em>\n\n<em> </em><em>Paris Street Style. Live with Clmence.<span style="color: #888888;">Week #16. Post 1.</span></em>\n\nClmence. Our wonderful Parisian street style victim of the day.\n\nThe short clip below was filmed with an ipod video camera...oh the strides technology has taken. Clmence speaks to us in French and we provide translations slides after.\n\nA young woman who loves the classic with a little masculine edge. Clmenceprefers to be comfortable when walking through Paris, and as an art student with her portfolio on her side,<a href="http://www.christianlouboutin.com/" target="_blank">Louboutins</a> are just not practical. Adores<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Columbo_(TV_series)" target="_blank">Columbo</a>, rocks a beaded bracelet her mom hand-made illustrating <a href="http://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/La_Joconde" target="_blank">La Joconde</a>, speaks beautiful French &amp; on top of it all, was kind enough to stop and speak with us. Fantastic.\n\nMerci Clmence.\n\n<em><span style="font-style: normal;">\n</span></em>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="520" height="300" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/Xk_ptSnXr4E&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;border=1" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="520" height="300" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/Xk_ptSnXr4E&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;border=1" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"></embed></object>', 'Paris Street Style. Le Vido &amp; Clmence.', '1.18.10\n\nParis Street Style. Live with Clmence. Week #16. Post 1.\n\nClmence. Our wonderful Parisian street style victim of the day.\n\nThe short clip below was filmed with an ipod video camera...oh the strides technology has taken. Clmence speaks to us in French and we provide translations slides after.\n\nA young woman who loves the classic with a little masculine edge. Clmence prefers to be comfortable when walking through Paris, and as an art student with her portfolio on her side, Louboutins are just not practical. Adores Columbo, rocks a beaded bracelet her mom hand-made illustrating La Joconde, speaks beautiful French & on top of it all, was kind enough to stop and speak with us. Fantastic.\n\nMerci Clmence. ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'paris-street-style-le-video-clemence', '', '', '2010-01-17 21:01:01', '2010-01-17 20:01:01', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=2652', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2868, 4, '2010-01-27 10:56:14', '2010-01-27 09:56:14', '<em>1.27.10</em>\n\n<em> </em><em>Paris. Trade shows. <a href="http://www.pretparis.com/" target="_blank">Prt  Porter</a>.<span style="color: #888888;">Week #17. Post 2.</span></em>\n\nThis past weekend was the beginning of a 4-day fashion explosion in Paris. Trade show time in Paris is always a site for sore eyes. From up and coming designers, to those who have been in the business for years, this is a trade show you want to be a vendor at.\n\nHuge halls of clothing, jewelry, sneakers, accessories, bags, shoes, belts, etc, etc. Its a fashion lover''s dream and a wallet''s worst nightmare (trust me, wholesale minimums prices are no joke).\n\nThe <a href="http://www.pretparis.com/" target="_blank">Prt  Porter</a> event consists of sub-categorized exhibit halls:<a href="http://www.pretparis.com/en/shibuya">Shibuya</a>,<a href="http://www.pretparis.com/en/the-box">The Box</a>, <a href="http://www.pretparis.com/en/atmospheres">Atmosphre''s</a>, <a href="http://www.pretparis.com/en/so-ethic">So Ethic</a>, <a href="http://www.pretparis.com/en/univers2">Creative By</a>, <a href="http://www.pretparis.com/en/so-magic">Go Magic</a>, <a href="http://www.pretparis.com/en/so-easy">Go Easy</a>, <a href="http://www.pretparis.com/en/so-shop">So Shop</a>.\n\nOverwhelming, and of course awe-inspiring, we brought along our lovely ipod video camera to show a peak of what this all looks like from the inside. Mind you, there are 7 different halls (as in HUGE spaces) for vendors. We did not get to all of them, but we did get to enough.\n\nAs for buying new pieces for the store, we were definitely successful and cannot wait to share with you the new designs when the store is finally complete!\n<p style="text-align: center;">_____________________________</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #0000ee;"><span><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> </span></span></span></span></p>\n<span style="color: #0000ee;"><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></span>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="560" height="340" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/hdyiyurf8XE&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="560" height="340" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/hdyiyurf8XE&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"> </embed></object>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">_____________________________</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<em> </em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_2870" align="aligncenter" width="471" caption="Sneakers from a vendor at &#39;Shibuya&#39;"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/shibuya.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2870" title="shibuya" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/shibuya.jpg" alt="" width="471" height="272" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2871" align="aligncenter" width="471" caption="Runway show "]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/defile.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2871" title="defile" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/defile.jpg" alt="" width="471" height="272" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_2872" align="aligncenter" width="470" caption="So Ethic Invite"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/072722100-1256651521_so_ethic.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2872" title="072722100-1256651521_so_ethic" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/072722100-1256651521_so_ethic.jpg" alt="" width="470" height="314" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center;">__________________________________________________</p>', 'Prt  Porter &amp; 7 Halls full of Accessories.', '1.27.10\n\nParis. Trade shows. Prt  Porter. Week #17. Post 2.\n\nThis past weekend was the beginning of a 4-day fashion explosion in Paris. Trade show time in Paris is always a site for sore eyes. From up and coming designers, to those who have been in the business for years, this is a trade show you want to be a vendor at.\n\nThe Prt  Porter event consists of sub-categorized exhibit halls: Shibuya, The Box, Atmosphre''s, So Ethic, Creative By, Go Magic, Go Easy, So Shop.\n\nOverwhelming, and of course awe-inspiring, we brought along our lovely ipod video camera to show a peak of what this all looks like from the inside.\n\nClick on the I C U - In Paris link or picture to view the Blog and Video.\n', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'pret-a-porter-7-halls-full-of-accessories', '', '', '2010-01-27 10:56:14', '2010-01-27 09:56:14', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=2868', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2881, 4, '2010-01-29 11:30:16', '2010-01-29 10:30:16', '<em>1.29.10</em>\n\n<em> </em><em>A new found designer love.Week #17. Post 3.</em>\n\n<em><span style="font-style: normal;">It is official. Love has struck. It is beautiful, shiny, perfectly polished and oh so sensually shaped. No, I am not talking about a man. Yes, I am talking about jewelry...I know, strange. But seriously, these designers are amazing. Talent which I love to discover, women who I love to see working, striving, succeeding. </span></em>\n\n<em><span style="font-style: normal;">I stumbled upon both of them at <a href="http://www.premiere-classe.com/" target="_blank">Premiere Classe </a>on Monday and of course wanted to give them some extra praise here, on the blog. </span></em>\n\nSo below, it brings me pleasure to present designers, <a href="http://www.gavang.com/" target="_blank">Gavang</a> and <a href="http://www.nathaliedmitrovic.com/index.php?" target="_blank">Nathalie Dmitrovic</a>.\n\n<strong><a href="http://www.gavang.com/" target="_blank">Gavang</a></strong>\n\nEstablished in 2005 by designer Tai-Kutirat Meesaiyati, the Gavang design house resides in Bangkok and creates designs for both jewelry and interior merchandise. When I first spotted their booth I was drawn in by the smooth, perfect lines and shapes of the rings. Really, magnificent craftsmanship and design.\n\n<em><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/gavang.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2882" title="gavang" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/gavang.jpg" alt="" width="467" height="419" /></a></em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/gavang-ring.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2883" title="gavang-ring" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/gavang-ring.jpg" alt="" width="350" height="524" /></a>\n</em></p>\n<em><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/gavang-model.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2884" title="gavang-model" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/gavang-model.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></em>\n\n<em><a style="text-decoration: none;" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/icuinparis-gavang-rings.jpg"><br style="text-decoration: underline;" /><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2885" title="icuinparis-gavang-rings" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/icuinparis-gavang-rings.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="781" /></a></em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_2895" align="aligncenter" width="400" caption="Gavang Designer &amp; Design Director. "]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/gavang-designer.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2895 " title="gavang-designer" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/gavang-designer.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="400" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<a href="http://www.nathaliedmitrovic.com/index.php?" target="_blank"><strong>Nathalie Dmitrovic</strong></a>\n\nI just love. Nathalie divides her collections into 5 categories:<em> <a href="http://www.nathaliedmitrovic.com/index.php?page=AccueilCollection&amp;page_secondaire=53" target="_blank">Elegance</a></em><span style="color: #888888;"><em>, <a href="http://www.nathaliedmitrovic.com/index.php?page=AccueilCollection&amp;page_secondaire=50" target="_blank">Les Merveilles</a>, <a href="http://www.nathaliedmitrovic.com/index.php?page=AccueilCollection&amp;page_secondaire=51" target="_blank">Les Precieuses</a>,</em></span><span style="color: #888888;"><em> <a href="http://www.nathaliedmitrovic.com/index.php?page=AccueilCollection&amp;page_secondaire=49" target="_blank">Pure</a></em></span><span style="color: #888888;"><em>, &amp; <a href="http://www.nathaliedmitrovic.com/index.php?page=AccueilCollection&amp;page_secondaire=52" target="_blank">Vermeil</a>. <span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;">And after viewing pieces from each collection </span></span></em><span style="color: #000000;">it is clear this woman has an art and crafts-hand which speaks true to her collection names. </span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">This is what I call unique, designer jewelry.</span></span>\n\n<em>Below: From <a href="http://www.nathaliedmitrovic.com/index.php?page=AccueilCollection&amp;page_secondaire=50">LES MERVEILLES</a> Collection, Tahitian Pearls and perfectly polished silver. </em>\n\n<em><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nathalie-dmitrovic-les-merveilles_2715.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2886" title="nathalie-dmitrovic-les-merveilles_2715" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nathalie-dmitrovic-les-merveilles_2715.jpg" alt="" width="416" height="520" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nathalie-dmitrovic-les-merveilles_2716.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2887" title="nathalie-dmitrovic-les-merveilles_2716" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nathalie-dmitrovic-les-merveilles_2716.jpg" alt="" width="416" height="520" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nathalie-dmitrovic-merveilles.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2888" title="nathalie-dmitrovic-merveilles" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nathalie-dmitrovic-merveilles.jpg" alt="" width="416" height="520" /></a></em>\n\n<em>Below: From the </em><a href="http://www.nathaliedmitrovic.com/index.php?page=AccueilCollection&amp;page_secondaire=51"><em>LES PRECIEUSES</em></a><em> collection. Sapphires and rubies embedded into pure silver. </em>\n\n<em><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nathalie-dmitrovic-les-precieuses_2728.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2889" title="nathalie-dmitrovic-les-precieuses_2728" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nathalie-dmitrovic-les-precieuses_2728.jpg" alt="" width="433" height="520" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nathalie-dmitrovic-les-precieuses_2736.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2890" title="nathalie-dmitrovic-les-precieuses_2736" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nathalie-dmitrovic-les-precieuses_2736.jpg" alt="" width="433" height="520" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nathalie-dmitrovic-les-precieuses_2753.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2891" title="nathalie-dmitrovic-les-precieuses_2753" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nathalie-dmitrovic-les-precieuses_2753.jpg" alt="" width="433" height="520" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nathalie-dmitrovic-pure.jpg"></a></em>\n\n<em>Below: From the </em><a href="http://www.nathaliedmitrovic.com/index.php?page=AccueilCollection&amp;page_secondaire=49"><em>PURE</em></a><em> collection. It is what it reads; pure silver, pure design,perfectly shaped, polished, shined and presented. </em>\n\n<em><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nathalie-dmitrovic-pure_2746.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2894" title="nathalie-dmitrovic-pure_2746" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nathalie-dmitrovic-pure_2746.jpg" alt="" width="433" height="520" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nathalie-dmitrovic-pure_2709.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2893" title="nathalie-dmitrovic-pure_2709" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nathalie-dmitrovic-pure_2709.jpg" alt="" width="416" height="520" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nathalie-dmitrovic-pure.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2892" title="nathalie-dmitrovic-pure" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/nathalie-dmitrovic-pure.jpg" alt="" width="433" height="520" /></a>\n</em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_2897" align="aligncenter" width="250" caption="Designer, Nathalie Dmitrovic"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/photonathalie-dmitrovic.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2897" title="photonathalie-dmitrovic" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/photonathalie-dmitrovic.jpg" alt="Nathalie Dmitrovic" width="250" height="348" /></a>[/caption]', 'Designer Love', '1.29.10\n\nA new found designer love. Week #17. Post 3.\n\nIt is official. Love has struck. It is beautiful, shiny, perfectly polished and oh so sensually shaped. No, I am not talking about a man. Yes, I am talking about jewelry...I know, strange. But seriously, these designers are amazing. Talent which I love to discover, women who I love to see working, striving, succeeding.\n\nI stumbled upon both of them at Premiere Classe on Monday and of course wanted to give them some extra praise here, on the blog.\n\nSo below, it brings me pleasure to present designers, Gavang and Nathalie Dmitrovic.\n\nClick on the I C U - In Paris The Blog link to view pictures. ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'designer-love', '', '', '2010-01-29 11:30:16', '2010-01-29 10:30:16', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=2881', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2901, 4, '2010-02-01 09:57:16', '2010-02-01 08:57:16', '<em>2.01.10</em>\n\n<em> </em><em>Street Style. The Gentlemen. </em><em><span style="color: #888888;">Week #18. Post 1.</span></em>\n\nParis street style caught again with our ''trusty'' ipod video camera. This time we have caught two gentlemen, Johannes (from Munich) visiting Eliakim (Parisian) who gives us a great tip on vintage shopping in Paris... he told us ''the young, cool Parisians'' don''t shop at designer stores and spend hundreds at Ralph Lauren, they flock to vintage shops, and specifically one,<a href="http://espacekiliwatch.fr/" target="_blank">Kiliwatch</a>.\n<p style="text-align: center;">_______________________________________</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="560" height="340" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/4th9Xxo8u6Q&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="560" height="340" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/4th9Xxo8u6Q&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"></embed></object>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">______________________________________</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/kiliwatch2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2904" title="kiliwatch2" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/kiliwatch2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a>\n\n<em>Kiliwatch</em>\n\n<em>64 rue Tiquetonne, 2 me arr (mtro Etienne Marcel)</em>\n\n<em>ouvert du lundi au samedi de 10h  19h30</em>\n\n<em><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/kiliwatch.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2905" title="kiliwatch" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/kiliwatch.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="572" /></a>\n</em>', 'Paris Street Style Video. The Gentlemen.', '2.01.10\n\nStreet Style. The Gentlemen. Week #18. Post 1.\n\nParis street style caught again with our ''trusty'' ipod video camera. This time we have caught two gentlemen, Johannes (from Munich) visiting Eliakim (Parisian) who gives us a great tip on vintage shopping in Paris... he told us ''the young, cool Parisians'' don''t shop at designer stores and spend hundreds at Ralph Lauren, they flock to vintage shops, and specifically one, Kiliwatch.\n\nTo view video and pictures click on the picture or I C U - In Paris The Blog.\n', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'paris-street-style-video-the-gentlemen', '', '', '2010-02-01 09:57:16', '2010-02-01 08:57:16', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=2901', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2911, 4, '2010-02-03 11:58:56', '2010-02-03 10:58:56', '<em>2.03.10</em>\n\n<em> </em><em>The BJOP. Union Franaise de la Bijouterie, Joaillerie, Orfvrerie, Des Pierres &amp; Des Perles. </em><em><span style="color: #888888;">Week #18. Post 2.</span></em>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">A personal venture. I am currently taking courses at the Louvre''s BJOP school for design. One day per week, all day we learn the basis for designing jewelry. This is the first course within three, so everything is about the shapes, colors, dimensions and 3-D. </span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/bjop-paris-gems.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2914" title="bjop-paris-gems" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/bjop-paris-gems.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="300" /></a>\n</span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">Some of the students in the class are working in the field of design already, designing within houses who produce jewelry for Dior...yeah, no biggie. They are in the course just to continue refining their talents. </span></span>\n\nBelow, a few pictures from the school and of course, a small video.\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">__________________________________</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="560" height="340" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/kraSLd3JRi4&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="560" height="340" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/kraSLd3JRi4&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"> </embed></object>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">_________________________________________</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2912" align="aligncenter" width="250" caption="The Facade of the School."]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/bjop-paris-building.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2912" title="bjop-paris-building" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/bjop-paris-building.jpg" alt="" width="250" height="198" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2913" align="aligncenter" width="250" caption="Metal-smithing"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/bjop-metalsmith-paris.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2913" title="bjop-metalsmith-paris" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/bjop-metalsmith-paris.jpg" alt="" width="250" height="231" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/bjop-paris-gems.jpg"></a>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">\n</span></em>', 'The BJOP. Not just any design course.', '2.03.10\n\nThe BJOP. Union Franaise de la Bijouterie, Joaillerie, Orfvrerie, Des Pierres & Des Perles. Week #18. Post 2.\n\nA personal venture. I am currently taking courses at the Louvre''s BJOP school for design. One day per week, all day we learn the basis for designing jewelry. This is the first course within three, so everything is about the shapes, colors, dimensions and 3-D.\n\nClick on the I C U - In Paris The Blog link or Avatar to view pictures & video.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-bjop-not-just-any-design-course', '', '', '2010-02-03 11:58:56', '2010-02-03 10:58:56', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=2911', 0, 'post', '', 12),
(2923, 4, '2010-02-05 11:00:16', '2010-02-05 10:00:16', '<em>2.03.10</em>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><em>Samantha Zaza. Fluevog Shoe Design Competition.</em></span><em> Week #18. Post 3.</em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;">So back in December I posted about <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?s=samantha+zaza" target="_blank">Samantha Zaza</a>,an exceptional artist and dear friend of my friend &amp; jewelry designer, <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/30/shamila-a-turkish-delight-paris-street-style/" target="_blank">Shamila</a>.Samantha has re-entered into the <a href="http://www.fluevog.com/code/fc_finalists.php" target="_blank">Fluevog Shoe Design Competition</a>, and this time you have the time to vote for her! (last time we posted passed the deadline).</span></span></em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;">Below, a small note from Samantha, </span></span></em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #808080;"><em>Last time, despite all our efforts, we lost by a mere 1% Let''s not lose this time! </em></span><span style="color: #808080;"><em> </em></span></span></span>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">Winning the Fluevog Competition means my art would get published over 250,000 times internationally something every illustrator dreams of. Please get everyone you know to join in friends, family, strangers use every email account you have to vote. I need as many as I can get.</span>\n\n</em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">Thank you so much!\nSamantha</span></em>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;">You have the opportunity to vote for Samantha EVERY DAY until NOON on Feb 8th: </span><span style="color: #000000;"><a href="http://www.fluevog.com/code/fc_finalists.php" target="_blank">http://www.fluevog.com/code/fc_finalists.php</a>. Below is Samantha''s submission. </span></span></span>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"><a href="http://www.fluevog.com/code/fc_finalists.php"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2924" title="szaza-fluevog" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/szaza-fluevog.jpg" alt="" width="401" height="401" /></a>\n</span></span></span></p>\n<span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;">Below, some images from Samantha''s website/portfolio. Not to be voted on, just here for a pleasurable view. </span></span></span>\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/zaza_poppiessamantha-zaza.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2926" title="zaza_poppiessamantha-zaza" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/zaza_poppiessamantha-zaza.jpg" alt="" width="523" height="400" /></a>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/samantha-zaza1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2925" title="samantha-zaza1" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/samantha-zaza1.jpg" alt="" width="651" height="262" /></a></span></span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/samantha-zaza2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2927" title="samantha-zaza2" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/samantha-zaza2.jpg" alt="" width="649" height="282" /></a></span></span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/samantha-zaza-01.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2928" title="samantha-zaza-01" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/samantha-zaza-01.jpg" alt="" width="509" height="400" /></a></span></span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/samantha-zaza4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2929" title="samantha-zaza4" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/samantha-zaza4.jpg" alt="" width="509" height="400" /></a></span></span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/samantha-zaza3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2930" title="samantha-zaza3" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/samantha-zaza3.jpg" alt="" width="509" height="400" /></a></span></span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;">And Ms. Zaza herself...who also has a great blog about life in Istanbul and well, <em><span style="color: #808080;">"the adventures of a compulsive sketcher in Istanbul." <span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;">The blog is called <a href="http://harikaszaza.blogspot.com/" target="_blank">Harika</a>.</span></span></span></em></span></span></span>\n\n[caption id="attachment_2931" align="aligncenter" width="200" caption="Samantha Zaza"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/samantha-zaza-pic.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2931" title="samantha-zaza-pic" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/samantha-zaza-pic.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="176" /></a>[/caption]', 'My, what fabulous shoes you have!', '2.03.10\n\nSamantha Zaza. Fluevog Shoe Design Competition. Week #18. Post 3.\n\nSo back in December I posted about Samantha Zaza, an exceptional artist and dear friend of my friend & jewelry designer, Shamila. Samantha has re-entered into the Fluevog Shoe Design Competition, and this time you have the time to vote for her! (last time we posted passed the deadline).\n\nBelow, a small note from Samantha...\n\nTo view Samantha''s design submission and note to all viewers please click on the I C U - In Paris The Blog link and/or picture. ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'my-what-fabulous-shoes-you-have', '', '', '2010-02-05 11:00:16', '2010-02-05 10:00:16', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=2923', 0, 'post', '', 6);
