(2939, 4, '2010-02-08 11:48:19', '2010-02-08 10:48:19', '<em>2.08.10</em>\n\n<em>Sex! Love! Valentine''s Day!</em><em> <span style="color: #888888;">Week #19. Post 1.</span></em>\n\nSo, as of Thursday, I will be Boston-bound. Quick trip home, very excited to touch down &amp; of course I have gotten myself involved in an event for the boutique.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://boldfacers.com/index.cfm"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2952" title="Sex-boldfacers" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/Sex-boldfacers1.jpg" alt="" width="292" height="290" /></a></p>\n<span style="color: #000000;"> <a href="http://boldfacers.com/index.cfm" target="_blank">Boldfacers.com</a> (a site that you should know about if you already do not) is a place to find the...<em>"Next Big Things. Each week, you''ll meet up-and-coming chefs, fashion designers, authors, rockers, artists and yoga instructors. There might be a meter maid-turned-poet, plumber or philanthropist. With fire in the belly, a heart packed with passion, they excel. They express. They contribute. Put simply, they make Boston tick. Just like you.We call them<strong>BOLDFACERS</strong>."</em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;">Every week is a new profile. A video interview is your introduction to the Boldfacer of the week and of course a text interview to follow if you wish to read on. This past week was Misty Kalkofe, bartender specialist and lover of cocktails. </span></span></em></span>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #808080;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;"><a href="http://boldfacers.com/index.cfm"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-2941" title="boldfacers" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/boldfacers-1024x551.jpg" alt="" width="574" height="309" /></a></span></span></em></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #808080;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;">And of course, the option to view all the past Boldfacers, categorized into different profiles for business, art, fashion, entrepreneur, etc. </span></span></em></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://boldfacers.com/index.cfm"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-2940" title="boldfacers homepage" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/boldfacers-homepage-1024x649.jpg" alt="" width="574" height="363" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Established and operated by <a href="http://boldfacers.com/index.cfm?page=aboutus" target="_blank">Lisa Pierpont</a>, a role model of mine and friend (not to mention, 3-time Emmy award winner), Boldfacers has quickly become one of the most tapped into info channels for what and who is happening in Boston. So, of course when I told Lisa I was coming home for a visit and she asked me to participate in their next Boldfacers pop-up store, I couldn''t refuse.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Friday, February 12th from 6-11 pm for your last minute Valentine''s Day gifts! A sex, love, jewelry, aphrodisiac pop-up store....I don''t know how I get myself mixed up in these ;)</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Location:</span></p>\n<a href="http://boldfacers.com/index.cfm" target="_blank">Boldfacers Studio</a>\n\n15 Channel Center Street\n\nFort Point Channel\n\n617-428-0500\n\nInfo@Boldfacers.com\n\nWe''ll be bringing some of the following pieces, so if you are looking for some beautiful Valentine''s Day gifts don''t miss you chance to buy before Boston does!\n\n<em>Below: <a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/designer-necklaces.html" target="_blank">Sonya Renee Double-sided Love Emblem Necklace</a></em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/designer-necklaces.html"><img class="size-full wp-image-2943  aligncenter" title="sonya-renee-love-emblem-nkl" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/sonya-renee-love-emblem-nkl.jpg" alt="Sonya Renee Love Emblem Necklace" width="607" height="301" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Below: <a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/designerrings.html" target="_blank">Rose Quartz Silver ''Flower'' Ring, Hand made from India.</a></em></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/designerrings.html"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-2944" title="India-rose-quartz-ring" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/India-rose-quartz-ring-1024x512.jpg" alt="" width="491" height="246" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Below: <a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/designerrings.html" target="_blank">Shamila Swiss Blue Topaz &amp; Silver Artisan Ring</a>. Check out the shape of that HAND-CARVED swiss blue topaz!</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/designerrings.html"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2946" title="Shamila swiss blue topaz artisan ring" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/Shamila-swiss-blue-topaz-artisan-ring-.jpg" alt="" width="448" height="233" /></a>\n</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">And we can''t forget about the gentlemen.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Below:<a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/philip-crangi-nut-amp-bolt-brass-cuff-links.html" target="_blank"> Giles &amp; Brother brass nut&amp;bolt cuff links.</a></em></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/philip-crangi-nut-amp-bolt-brass-cuff-links.html"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2947" title="giles and brother men''s brass cuff links" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/giles-and-brother-mens-brass-cuff-links.jpg" alt="" width="504" height="336" /></a></em></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Below: <a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/philip-crangi-brass-rings.html" target="_blank">Giles &amp; Brother Brass Men''s Rings</a></em></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/philip-crangi-brass-rings.html"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2948" title="giles and brother brass men''s rings" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/giles-and-brother-brass-mens-rings.jpg" alt="" width="576" height="383" /></a></em></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Below: <a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/philip-crangi-brass-and-copper-ring-necklace.html" target="_blank">Giles &amp; Brother Brass &amp; Copper Rings Men''s Necklace</a></em></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/philip-crangi-brass-and-copper-ring-necklace.html"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2949" title="giles and brother men''s brass and copper necklace" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/giles-and-brother-mens-brass-and-copper-necklace.jpg" alt="" width="504" height="415" /></a></em></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">To Shop styles from the boutique <em><a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/" target="_blank">CLICK HERE.</a></em></p>', 'A Sex Pop-up Shop? Hmm.', '2.08.10\n\nSex! Love! Valentine''s Day! Week #19. Post 1.\n\nSo, as of Thursday, I will be Boston-bound. Quick trip home, very excited to touch down & of course I have gotten myself involved in an event for the boutique. Boldfacers, the most tapped into info channels for what and who is happening in Boston is hosting their next pop-up store dedicated to Valentine''s Day.\n\nFriday, February 12th from 6-11 pm for your last minute Valentine''s Day gifts! A sex, love, jewelry, aphrodisiac pop-up store....I don''t know how I get myself mixed up in these ;)\n\nClick on I C U - In Paris The Blog link and/or picture to view event details and images.\n', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-sex-pop-up-shop-hmm', '', '', '2010-02-08 11:48:19', '2010-02-08 10:48:19', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=2939', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2958, 4, '2010-02-12 15:32:40', '2010-02-12 14:32:40', '<em>2.12.10</em>\n\n<em>Alexander McQueen. Week #19. Post 3.</em>\n\n<em><span style="font-style: normal;">Last night I found out about Alexander McQueen. What an incredible loss this is. McQueen has always been an icon to me for his ability to push the buttons, show the fashion world something different, something out of the box while keeping it all strikingly beautiful. </span></em>\n\nI''m not a reporter, I''m just a lover of all that is unique and Mr. McQueen was creating something that was going to change the art of fashion. It is just terrible he did not see that as well.\n\nI''ve posted one of the last videos from his women''s fashion week runway show. Plus a two short video from a fashion press in London.\n<p style="text-align: center;">_________________________</p>\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/alexander-mcqueen.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2973" title="alexander-mcqueen" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/alexander-mcqueen.jpg" alt="" width="398" height="400" /></a>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">_________________________</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="560" height="340" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/6dMd_Xw3n34&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="560" height="340" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/6dMd_Xw3n34&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"> </embed></object>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">_________________________</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="560" height="340" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/t-k7UirWf5s&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="560" height="340" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/t-k7UirWf5s&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"> </embed></object>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">_________________________</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="425" height="344" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/pUvFTc2mlNY&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="425" height="344" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/pUvFTc2mlNY&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"></embed></object>', 'Alexander McQueen. A small tribute.', '2.12.10\n\nAlexander McQueen. Week #19. Post 3.\n\nLast night I found out about Alexander McQueen. What a sad story and a huge loss to the fashion world. McQueen has always been on e of my favorites for his ability to push the buttons, show the fashion world something different, something out of the box but beautiful.\n\nI''m not a reporter, I''m just a lover of all that is unique and Mr. McQueen was creating something that was going to change the art of fashion. It is just terrible he did not see that as well. Not much to write other than McQueen will be missed dearly in and out of the fashion world.\n\nI''ve posted one of the last videos from his women''s fashion week runway show. Plus a two short video from a fashion press in London.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'alexander-mcqueen-a-small-tribute', '', '', '2010-02-12 15:32:40', '2010-02-12 14:32:40', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=2958', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2980, 4, '2010-02-15 16:15:47', '2010-02-15 15:15:47', '<em>2.15.10</em>\n\n<em>BJOP #2. Week #20. Post 1.</em>\n\n<em><span style="font-style: normal;">BJOP. The personal venture continues and so does the challenge to create dimension, 3D and diamonds!</span></em>\n\n<em><span style="font-style: normal;">I will miss this week''s class, and the following video was from last week, so I''m hoping not to be too far behind after I return to Paris!</span></em>\n\n<em><span style="font-style: normal;">But here you are, a small clip from the results of our painting course. Creating the dimension of stones and learning the concept of colors and light. </span></em>\n\n<em>\n</em>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="560" height="340" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/YtzZ_-3WKyE&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="560" height="340" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/YtzZ_-3WKyE&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"></embed></object>', 'BJOP. #2. A Diamond Dimension.', '2.15.10\n\nBJOP #2. Week #20. Post 1.\n\nBJOP. The personal venture continues and so does the challenge to create dimension, 3D and diamonds!\n\nI will miss this week''s class, and the following video was from last week, so I''m hoping not to be too far behind after I return to Paris!\n\nBut here you are, a small clip from the results of our painting course. Creating the dimension of stones and learning the concept of colors and light. ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bjop-2-a-diamond-dimension', '', '', '2010-02-15 16:15:47', '2010-02-15 15:15:47', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=2980', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(3007, 5, '2010-02-17 13:41:48', '2010-02-17 12:41:48', '<em>2.17.10</em>\n\n<em>I C U - Brooklyn Style. Week #20. Post 2.</em>\n\nI am so happy to write that <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?s=erin+kim" target="_blank">Erin Kim</a>, our wonderful assistant stylist and freelance blogger is back again! This time, she is writing us from the East Coast, where she has returned to school, friends &amp; family. But lucky us, she is still sharing what she sees and who she knows.\n\nBelow, you will find two stories, two people, two incredibly creative minds and passions who surely are going to make a difference wherever their passions and careers may find them.\n\nErin''s text starts here.\n\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Daniel Silverstein &amp; Danielle Brock:</strong></span>\n\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong> </strong></span>\nJust a few days after landing at JFK in New York City, I ventured over to Brooklyn to see two long-time friends. What happens when you put two immensely creative &amp; funky people together in an apartment in Brooklyn? You get one fantastic looking place and a giant, bottomless wardrobe.\nDaniel is currently a designer &amp; student at the <a href="http://www.fitnyc.edu" target="_blank">Fashion Institute of Technology</a>.\nDanielle manages production of events and handles public relations and press outreach for <a href="http://flavorpill.com/newyork" target="_blank">Flavorpill</a> (whose blog is <a href="http://flavorwire.com" target="_blank">Flavorwire</a>), an online guide to music, arts, and cultural events in the city (as well as London, Miami, etc.)\n\n<strong>Dan Silverstein speaks about his style:</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n"<em>i would say my style is young and urban but always sophisticated. i like to look like a classic almost preppy young man, but always with a twist: a badass ring, gold earrings, my neatly parted hair shaved on the side or fresh kicks. these days i am also into a russian inspiration, my friend Amanda calls it "russian appeal</em>."\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2998" align="aligncenter" width="473" caption="jeans, slip covers for the couch and pillows made by Daniel"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSCN3219.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2998   " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSCN3219-768x1024.jpg" alt="" width="473" height="631" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2999" align="aligncenter" width="498" caption="rings for gentlemen, handmade in Milan. "]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSCN3225.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2999   " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSCN3225-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="498" height="374" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<strong>Danielle Brock on her style:</strong>\n\n"<em>style is somewhere between Audrey Hepburn and Edie Sedgwick. Classic, but a little grunge-y. And earrings, of course. Very inspired by Swedish and Danish style right now - there''s a effortless beauty and elegance to the way they dress, yet it''s imbued with harder elements of grunge rock, sportswear, asymmetry, and architectural features, that I absolutely love</em>."\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2983" align="aligncenter" width="512" caption="Danielle wearing D. Silver&#39;s own dress"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6272.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2983  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6272-1024x680.jpg" alt="" width="512" height="340" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2992" align="aligncenter" width="520" caption="vintage earrings from Woodstock fleamarket"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6367.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2992    " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6367-1024x680.jpg" alt="" width="520" height="363" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_3000" align="aligncenter" width="524" caption="Danielle wearing D. Silver&#39;s custom-made dress. "]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSCN3230.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-3000    " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSCN3230-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="524" height="404" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<strong>Climbing up to the rooftop overlooking Brooklyn &amp; Manhattan:</strong>\n<div>\n\n[caption id="attachment_3002" align="aligncenter" width="483" caption="a spy? a runaway? an expert thief? albeit a very well-dressed one"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSCN3241.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-3002  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSCN3241-768x1024.jpg" alt="" width="483" height="643" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<strong>Dan on Brooklyn:</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n"<em>My favorite thing about Brooklyn is that it is not Manhattan. With all the charm and bustle of New York City proper, it is still outside the madness that is in the central city. On weekends I prefer not to leave, if I don''t need to. The attitude here is relaxed, and there are families and friendly people here, it''s nice</em>.<em>"</em>\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\n[caption id="attachment_2984" align="aligncenter" width="523" caption="Dan on his rooftop in Brooklyn, with Manhattan in the distance"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6284.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2984    " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6284-1024x680.jpg" alt="" width="523" height="347" /></a>[/caption]\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\n[caption id="attachment_2985" align="aligncenter" width="523" caption="Dan on his rooftop in Brooklyn"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6289.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2985    " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6289-1024x680.jpg" alt="" width="523" height="347" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<strong>Danielle on Brooklyn:</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n"<em>It''s quiet and there are trees! and no skyscrapers! our neighborhood is very community oriented and you can walk just about anywhere in Park Slope from our apartment. It reminds me of living in Italy, where everything was quaint and nearby and picturesque and the woman who sold vegetables next to my apartment knew me. Living in Brooklyn (versus Manhattan) has the same feeling to it, only now it''s a bunch of hipsters at the local coffee shops that know me, instead of an old Italian woman</em>."\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\n[caption id="attachment_2987" align="aligncenter" width="514" caption="Danielle in her Miu Mius from Milan, sweater made by Daniel Silverstein"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6304.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2987  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6304-816x1024.jpg" alt="" width="514" height="645" /></a>[/caption]\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\n[caption id="attachment_2988" align="aligncenter" width="505" caption="Miu Mius from Corso Como 10 in Milan"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6315-1.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2988     " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6315-1-1024x680.jpg" alt="" width="505" height="338" /></a>[/caption]\n\nThis is Danielle''s secret to having such a unique sense of style: traveling &amp; collecting beautiful clothes and jewelry from flea markets, customizing with everyday items (spray paint!), and of course--having a dear friend who designs, sews, knits, cuts &amp; styles hair...\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\n[caption id="attachment_3023" align="aligncenter" width="523" caption="changing into yet another outfit; corset made by D. Silver"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSCN3249.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-3023    " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSCN3249-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="523" height="392" /></a>[/caption]\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\n[caption id="attachment_3003" align="aligncenter" width="498" caption="Tattoo done by Ian Babb from Murder Ink in Queens"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSCN3246.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-3003   " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSCN3246-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="498" height="374" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<strong>Danielle on her style influences:</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n"<em>Music. I''m attached to my headphones. Bob Dylan, The Strokes, Fever Ray, Phoenix, Passion Pit, Apes and Androids, The Drums, The Shoes, Yeasayer, The XX, Dirty Projectors, jj, The Knife, Thieves Like Us, Joy Division, New Order, Lyyke Li, M83, Memory Tapes - some of my favorites. My music influences everything - how I dress, how I feel, and how I work.\nI also get really excited about art. Some times I can''t breathe when I talk about Duchamp,Boccioni, Picasso, Hirst, Manet, de Chirico...And as a note, sharks are fantastic."\n</em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_2990" align="aligncenter" width="428" caption="pure class, in a classic men&#39;s dress shirt and vintage pearls from her grandmother"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6336.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2990  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6336-680x1024.jpg" alt="" width="428" height="645" /></a>[/caption]\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\n[caption id="attachment_2991" align="aligncenter" width="517" caption="vintage snake ring and a ring by Marc Jacobs"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6361.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2991   " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6361-1024x680.jpg" alt="" width="517" height="343" /></a>[/caption]\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\n[caption id="attachment_2993" align="aligncenter" width="428" caption="their wardrobes are just bottomless "]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6387.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2993  " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6387-680x1024.jpg" alt="" width="428" height="645" /></a>[/caption]\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_2997" align="aligncenter" width="498" caption="bowling shoes painted gold by Boris @ St. Marks."]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6397.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2997   " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6397-1024x680.jpg" alt="" width="498" height="330" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<strong>Daniel on his designs:</strong>\n<em>"Well, to say something about work, it is always changing, as a designer i like to focus on details of a greater picture. my current design philosophy is, "age is beauty, aged is beautiful." this means that i want to look at the things people consider damaged, broken or ugly, and interoperate them as beautiful, or to extend the thought process into production, i like to use old and esteemed techniques to create these things. After school i would like to work in designer pricepoint/luxury fashion and eventually start my own design firm with the idea that the process of design is far reaching past just clothing, but it is about branding a lifestyle, which i hope to do."</em>\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\n[caption id="attachment_2996" align="aligncenter" width="476" caption="friendship &amp; mutual inspiration"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6404.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-2996 " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/DSC_6404-680x1024.jpg" alt="" width="476" height="717" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<em>\n</em>\n\nThank you Dan &amp; Danielle.\n\n</div>', 'I C U - Brooklyn Style.', '2.17.10\n\nI C U - Brooklyn Style. Week #20. Post 2.\n\nI am so happy to write that Erin Kim, our wonderful assistant stylist and freelance blogger is back again! This time, she is writing us from the East Coast, where she has returned to school, friends &amp; family. But lucky us, she is still sharing what she sees and who she knows.\n\nBelow, you will find two stories, two people, two incredibly creative minds and passions who surely are going to make a difference wherever their passions and careers may find them.\n\nErin''s text starts here... PLEASE CLICK ON I C U - In Paris LINK OR IMAGE TO VIEW POST &amp; PICTURES', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'i-c-u-brooklyn-style', '', '', '2010-02-17 13:41:48', '2010-02-17 12:41:48', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3007', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(3074, 4, '2010-02-19 19:34:42', '2010-02-19 18:34:42', '<em>2.19.10</em>\n\n<em>I C U  NYC. Puma &amp; Kehinde Wiley take over Deitch Project in SoHo. <span style="color: #888888;">Week #20. Post 3.</span></em>\n\n<em>NYC</em>. February 17th, 2010. <a href="http://www.puma.com/us/en/pindex.jsp;jsessionid=AC1F55B20CE089AD11BE4EE6617FAA5D.tomcat2" target="_blank">PUMA</a> commissioned the talented portraitist,<a href="http://www.kehindewiley.com/" target="_blank">Kehinde Wiley</a>, in creating a series of larger-than-life portraits of professional African soccer players to participate in this years World Cup. Featuring soccer stars such as; Samuel Etoo (Cameroon) John Mensah (Ghana) and Emmanuel Eboue (ivory Coast) exchanging greetings, done in Kehinde Wileys unique fashion of superimposing masculine identities against feminine backdrop.\n\n[caption id="attachment_3091" align="aligncenter" width="570" caption="Mr. Kehinde Wiley "]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-22.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-3091" title="puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-22" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-22.jpg" alt="" width="570" height="430" /></a>[/caption]\n\nThe exhibition entitled,Legends of Unity, highlights Africa Unity Kit initiative by <a href="http://www.puma.com/us/en/pindex.jsp;jsessionid=AC1F55B20CE089AD11BE4EE6617FAA5D.tomcat2" target="_blank">PUMA</a> which is currently underway. The idea: Soccer <em>ou futb</em><em>ol</em>, has always been a common love &amp; passion for and through the trials and tribulations our world undergoes, we strive to find a moment''s peace under a commonality of talent and appreciation.\n\nThe launch party introduced the exhibition which will continue to be held at the <a href="http://www.deitch.com/" target="_blank">Deitch Project in SoHo</a> with live music wonderfully provided by<a href="http://zozoafrobeat.com/" target="_blank">Zozo Afrobeat</a>. The gallery was packed full of individuals from every corner in Manhattan. The style was amazing, really. The ambiance was fresh and funky and the drinks were free. Not much more you can ask for.\n\nPictures below from the party (pardon the quality, iphone was the only means of image-capturing for the night).\n\n**Certain pictures credited to FreshnessMag.com**\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-40.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3089" title="puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-40" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-40.jpg" alt="" width="570" height="430" /></a>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-13.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3075" title="puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-13" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-13.jpg" alt="" width="570" height="430" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Below: </em>The Deitch Project''s space and an event on its way to being fabulous.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-42.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3090" title="puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-42" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-42.jpg" alt="" width="570" height="430" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-nyc-event-and-unity-exhibition.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3076" title="puma nyc event and unity exhibition" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-nyc-event-and-unity-exhibition.jpg" alt="" width="570" height="430" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Below: </em>Kehinde Wiley''s PUMA commissioned portraits. Oil paint. Amazing.</p>\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-event-nyc-fashion-week.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3077" title="puma event nyc fashion week" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-event-nyc-fashion-week.jpg" alt="" width="570" height="500" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-nyc-fashion-week-exhibit.jpg"></a>\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-nyc-fashion-week-exhibit.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3078" title="puma nyc fashion week exhibit" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-nyc-fashion-week-exhibit.jpg" alt="" width="570" height="500" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-17.jpg"></a>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Below: </em>Kehinde Wiley''s bio, which was plastered onto the wall.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/Puma-Kehinde-Wiley.-Legends-of-Unity.-NYC-wiley.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3092" title="Puma &amp; Kehinde Wiley. Legends of Unity. NYC wiley" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/Puma-Kehinde-Wiley.-Legends-of-Unity.-NYC-wiley.jpg" alt="" width="480" height="640" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Below: </em>A view from a above.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-17.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3079" title="puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-17" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-17.jpg" alt="" width="570" height="430" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Below: </em>Deitch Gallery entrance and lower level. Open bar to the right, Wiley wall paper to the left and limited edition PUMA shirts over head.</p>\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-19.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3080" title="puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-19" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-19.jpg" alt="" width="570" height="430" /></a>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Below: </em>Kehinde Wiley''s signature portrait back-drops. Here, transformed into the exhibit wall paper.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-20.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3081" title="puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-20" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-kehinde-wiley-legends-of-unity-20.jpg" alt="" width="570" height="430" /></a>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Below:</em> Zozo AfroBeat Kickin up the party.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/Puma-Kehinde-Wiley.-Legends-of-Unity.-NYC-and-zoz-afrobeat.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-3082 aligncenter" title="Puma &amp; Kehinde Wiley. Legends of Unity. NYC and zozo afrobeat" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/Puma-Kehinde-Wiley.-Legends-of-Unity.-NYC-and-zoz-afrobeat.jpg" alt="" width="512" height="384" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Below: </em>A view of the crowd under an array of vintage &amp; special edition Puma t-shirts and jerseys.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/Puma-Kehinde-Wiley.-Legends-of-Unity.-NYC-the-scene.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3083" title="Puma &amp; Kehinde Wiley. Legends of Unity. NYC the scene" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/Puma-Kehinde-Wiley.-Legends-of-Unity.-NYC-the-scene.jpg" alt="" width="560" height="420" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Below: </em>Movie stations to view World Cup player''s interviews and point of view on soccer and it''s influence.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/Puma-Kehinde-Wiley.-Legends-of-Unity.-NYC-movie-stations.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3084" title="Puma &amp; Kehinde Wiley. Legends of Unity. NYC movie stations" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/Puma-Kehinde-Wiley.-Legends-of-Unity.-NYC-movie-stations.jpg" alt="" width="560" height="420" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Below: </em>Now just some fun shots of awesome style and dancing...</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/Puma-Kehinde-Wiley.-Legends-of-Unity.-NYC-fashion-week-nyc.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3085" title="Puma &amp; Kehinde Wiley. Legends of Unity. NYC fashion week nyc" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/Puma-Kehinde-Wiley.-Legends-of-Unity.-NYC-fashion-week-nyc.jpg" alt="" width="480" height="640" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Below: </em>These shoes belonged to one handsome lady..if you catch the drift you will understand the supreme awe we had for her.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/Puma-Kehinde-Wiley.-Legends-of-Unity.-NYC-the-shoes.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3086" title="Puma &amp; Kehinde Wiley. Legends of Unity. NYC the shoes" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/Puma-Kehinde-Wiley.-Legends-of-Unity.-NYC-the-shoes.jpg" alt="" width="480" height="416" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Below: </em>The dancing then began.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/Puma-Kehinde-Wiley.-Legends-of-Unity.-NYC.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3087" title="Puma &amp; Kehinde Wiley. Legends of Unity. NYC" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/Puma-Kehinde-Wiley.-Legends-of-Unity.-NYC.jpg" alt="" width="480" height="640" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-nyc-event-.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3093" title="puma nyc event" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/puma-nyc-event-.jpg" alt="" width="420" height="560" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/Puma-Kehinde-Wiley.-Legends-of-Unity.-NYC2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3088" title="Puma &amp; Kehinde Wiley. Legends of Unity. NYC2" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/Puma-Kehinde-Wiley.-Legends-of-Unity.-NYC2.jpg" alt="" width="420" height="560" /></a></p>\n<strong>Deitch Projects</strong>\n\n18 Wooster Street |<a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?oe=utf-8&amp;client=firefox-a&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;q=18+Wooster+Street+New+York+NY&amp;fb=1&amp;gl=us&amp;hnear=&amp;cid=0,0,9811866743216537918&amp;ei=irJ9S6nvOoeVtgfT6tmwBQ&amp;ved=0CAoQnwIwAA&amp;hq=18+Wooster+Street+New+York+NY&amp;ll=40.721827,-74.003134&amp;spn=0.010034,0.022724&amp;t=h&amp;z=16&amp;iwloc=A" target="_blank">MAP</a>\nNew York, NY 10013\nTEL #: +1-212-941-9475\n\n<strong>Exhibition Date:</strong> February 18th - February 20th (Saturday)', 'Puma &amp; Kehinde Wiley. Legends of Unity. NYC.', '2.19.10\n\nI C U  NYC. Puma & Kehinde 