(3148, 5, '2010-03-29 09:12:51', '2010-03-29 07:12:51', '<em>3.29.10</em>\n\n<em>Viviane Sassen. A new depth of Fashion Photography.</em><em> <span style="color: #888888;">Week #25. Post 1.</span></em>\n\nGuest Blogger Erin Kim. This is really beautifully written, thank you Erin.\n\n<a href="http://www.vivianesassen.com" target="_blank">Viviane Sassen</a> is a freelance photographer, who has done work for various fashion publications and advertisements, such as Vogue (FR), Purple and Re-Magazine. Yet her photographs for fashion publications seem to go beyond the immediate subject matter of eye-catching garments and style.\n\nNearly all her images--both commissioned, and personal work--evoke a sense of nostalgia; perhaps it is a search to recapture the senses she experienced during her childhood in Kenya. For her series Ultraviolet and Flamboya, she travels to Uganda, Tanzania, Kenya, Zambia and Ghana to capture portraits that not just describe the people, but also the complexities of African societies in which they live.\n\nHer images of people from her travels all throughout the African continent are vivid, mysterious and multifaceted.\n\nHer work is being exhibited at the <a href="http://www.danzigerprojects.com/" target="_blank">Danziger Projects</a> at 534 West 24th Street New York, New York 10011 from March 4th 2010-April 10th 2010 (by appointment only).\n\nCommissioned Work:\n\n[caption id="attachment_3214" align="aligncenter" width="345" caption="(c) Viviane Sassen"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/fashion1.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-3214" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/fashion1.jpg" alt="" width="345" height="450" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_3215" align="aligncenter" width="345" caption="(c) Viviane Sassen"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/fashion2.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-3215" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/fashion2.jpg" alt="" width="345" height="450" /></a>[/caption]\n\nHer aesthetic also informs the way in which she photographs and captures fashion and beauty, thus creating images of fashion that have much more depth than one''s average fashion editorial shot.\n\nFashion photography, after all, requires artists for its existence; the best fashion photography will need artists with an aesthetic that is informed by a variety of sources.<strong> </strong>In Viviane Sassen''s case, it is the beauty that she reveres in the countries and the people within Africa.\n\n[caption id="attachment_3216" align="aligncenter" width="353" caption="(c) Viviane Sassen"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/fashion3.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-3216" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/fashion3.jpg" alt="" width="353" height="450" /></a>[/caption]\n\nSome photos from her Ultraviolet series: currently on display at Danziger Projects in NYC\n\n[caption id="attachment_3219" align="aligncenter" width="357" caption="DNA (c) Viviane Sassen"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/dna.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-3219" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/dna.jpg" alt="" width="357" height="450" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_3208" align="aligncenter" width="360" caption="Totem (c) Viviane Sassen"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/uv08.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-3208" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/uv08.jpg" alt="" width="360" height="450" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_3210" align="aligncenter" width="361" caption="Elvis (c) Viviane Sassen"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Elvis.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-3210" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Elvis.jpg" alt="" width="361" height="450" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_3209" align="aligncenter" width="360" caption="Anansi (c) Viviane Sassen"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/uv15.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-3209" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/uv15.jpg" alt="" width="360" height="450" /></a>[/caption]\n\nSome photos from her Flamboya series: currently on display at Danziger projects in NYC\n\n[caption id="attachment_3212" align="aligncenter" width="361" caption="Traveller (c) Viviane Sassen"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/traveller.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-3212" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/traveller.jpg" alt="" width="361" height="450" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_3211" align="aligncenter" width="558" caption="Sister (c) Viviane Sassen"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/sister.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-3211" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/sister.jpg" alt="" width="558" height="450" /></a>[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_3207" align="aligncenter" width="560" caption="Spring of the Nile. (c) Viviane Sassen"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/fl12.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-3207" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/fl12.jpg" alt="" width="560" height="450" /></a>[/caption]\n\nView more of her work on <a href="http://www.vivianesassen.com" target="_blank">www.vivianesassen.com</a>.', 'Viviane Sassen: A new depth of Fashion Photography', '3.29.10\n\nViviane Sassen. A new depth of Fashion Photography. Week #25. Post 1.\n\nViviane Sassen is a freelance photographer, who has done work for various fashion publications and advertisements, such as Vogue (FR), Purple and Re-Magazine. Yet her photographs for fashion publications seem to go beyond the immediate subject matter of eye-catching garments and style.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'viviane-sassen-a-new-depth-of-fashion-photography', '', '', '2010-03-29 09:12:51', '2010-03-29 07:12:51', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3148', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(3152, 4, '2010-03-22 08:30:54', '2010-03-22 07:30:54', '<em>3.22.10</em>\n\n<em>Scan Life, NYC fashion week &amp; Norma Karmali .</em><em> <span style="color: #888888;">Week #24. Post 1.</span></em>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;">Although the video is a bit late to be published, the idea is still fresh out of the box. <a href="http://atlantis.scanlife.com/" target="_blank">Scan Life</a> - a new tech phenomenon which has the potential to sweep through just about every industry imaginable. </span>\n\nIt did make it to Fashion Week 2010 in NYC, with help from <a href="http://www.normakamalicollection.com/shared/html/NK_NEWHOME1.html" target="_blank">Norma Kamali</a> and her gallery of designs.\n\nNYC Fashion Week - Scan Life &amp; Norma Kamali. Changing the fashion industry one bar code at a time. This is innovative fashion.\n\n<a style="text-decoration: none;" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/norma-kamali-logo.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-3153" title="norma kamali logo" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/norma-kamali-logo-300x42.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="42" /></a>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Norma-kamail-NYC-fashion-week-gallery.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-3154  aligncenter" title="Norma kamail NYC fashion week gallery" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Norma-kamail-NYC-fashion-week-gallery.jpg" alt="" width="312" height="416" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="425" height="344" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/_XRT-ZdTPj8&amp;hl=en&amp;fs=1" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="425" height="344" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/_XRT-ZdTPj8&amp;hl=en&amp;fs=1" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"></embed></object>', 'Scan Life. The new fashion phenomenon. ', 'NYC Fashion Week - Scan Life & Norma Kamali. Changing the fashion industry one bar code at a time. This is innovative fashion. ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'scan-life-the-new-fashion-phenomenon', '', '', '2010-03-22 08:30:54', '2010-03-22 07:30:54', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3152', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(3160, 4, '2010-03-23 08:02:39', '2010-03-23 07:02:39', '<em>3.23.10</em>\n\n<em>NYC fashion week - wasn''t all about the runway glam .</em><em> <span style="color: #888888;">Week #24. Post 2.</span></em>\n\nNYC - Fashion Week 2010 is not all about the runway.\n\nArt &amp; talent is everywhere, and sometime all it takes is a stroll through the park to find it and record it.   I C U caught this particular artist, hand drawing huge designs on the side walk with a heavy clay powder.\n\nPretty funky for just a stroll in the park.\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="425" height="344" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/7PfEyEnQrnE&amp;hl=en&amp;fs=1" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="425" height="344" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/7PfEyEnQrnE&amp;hl=en&amp;fs=1" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"></embed></object>', 'NYC - ICU Street Art. ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'nyc-icu-street-art', '', '', '2010-03-23 08:02:39', '2010-03-23 07:02:39', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3160', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(3164, 4, '2010-03-25 00:26:31', '2010-03-24 23:26:31', '<em>3.24.10</em>\n\n<em>I C U  Styles the Cover for Paris Magazine.</em><em> <span style="color: #888888;">Week #24. Post 3.</span></em>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">What a day, what a day. A beautiful one indeed and I''m not just talking sunshine in Paris. </span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #000000;">Today was the shoot for <a href="http://www.theparismagazine.com/" target="_blank">Paris Magazine</a> - a publication here in Paris, all in English that writes about the best of the city, the worst of the city, funky people, places to go, things to do, etc, etc. If and when you come to Paris, find this magazine in the (kiosques) news stands, it is definitely a fantastic resource.</span></span>\n\nI was asked to style the shoot for today which will be on May/June''s cover issue. The idea: Spring, Paris...light, flowers, sunshine...Paris.\n\nPhotographer, <a href="http://laurenceguenoun.com/" target="_blank">Laurence Guenoun</a> (who we have worked with before for <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/23/photo-shoot-i-c-u-in-paris/" target="_blank">jewelry shoots</a>) - she is outstanding. Model Dasha - who we have also worked with, and the wonderfully charming Nicolas, for the make-up.\n\nBelow, a few photos from the set-up and also a few sneak-peaks of the post-production.\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/icu-in-paris-paris-magazine-photo-shoot1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3167" title="icu in paris - paris magazine photo shoot" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/icu-in-paris-paris-magazine-photo-shoot1.jpg" alt="" width="384" height="578" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Make-up.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/icu-in-paris-paris-magazine-photo-shoot62.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3171" title="icu in paris - paris magazine photo shoot6" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/icu-in-paris-paris-magazine-photo-shoot62.jpg" alt="" width="480" height="319" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Laurence, her assistant &amp; William, the editor &amp; founder of <a href="http://www.theparismagazine.com" target="_blank">Paris Magazine</a>.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/icu-in-paris-paris-magazine-photo-shoot9.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3172" title="icu in paris - paris magazine photo shoot9" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/icu-in-paris-paris-magazine-photo-shoot9.jpg" alt="" width="480" height="722" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Test shooting. Light is not right just yet...</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/icu-in-paris-paris-magazine-photo-shoot03.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3173" title="icu in paris - paris magazine photo shoot03" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/icu-in-paris-paris-magazine-photo-shoot03.jpg" alt="" width="480" height="722" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/icu-in-paris-paris-magazine-photo-shoot01.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3174" title="icu in paris - paris magazine photo shoot01" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/icu-in-paris-paris-magazine-photo-shoot01.jpg" alt="" width="480" height="722" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/2icu-in-paris-paris-magazine-photo-shoot5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3175" title="2icu in paris - paris magazine photo shoot5" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/2icu-in-paris-paris-magazine-photo-shoot5.jpg" alt="" width="480" height="722" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Pre-production/post production</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Of course, of course, we accessorized with only jewelry from<a href="http://www.icuinparis.com" target="_blank">I C U</a> &amp; clothes from the good old stylist closest of Paris. Dasha is wearing<a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/sonya-renee-moonstone-necklace.html" target="_blank">Sonya Renee''s moonstone necklace</a> - as a bracelet,<a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/gorjana-green-sapphire-and-solid-18k-gold-neckla18.html" target="_blank">Gorjana green sapphire chain necklace</a> &amp;<a href="http://www.cinsummer.org/zhen-un-solid-18k-gold-and-gold-citri18.html" target="_blank">Zhen U.N. citrine &amp; 18k gold earrings.</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/icu-in-paris-paris-magazine-photo-shoot2.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-3176  aligncenter" title="icu in paris - paris magazine photo shoot2" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/icu-in-paris-paris-magazine-photo-shoot2-701x1024.jpg" alt="" width="491" height="717" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/icu-in-paris-for-paris-magazine-photo-shoot03.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3177" title="icu in paris for - paris magazine photo shoot03" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/icu-in-paris-for-paris-magazine-photo-shoot03.jpg" alt="icu in paris - paris magazine photo shoot." width="400" height="599" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/icu-in-paris-paris-magazine-photo-shoot3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-3178" title="icu in paris - paris magazine photo shoot3" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/icu-in-paris-paris-magazine-photo-shoot3-683x1024.jpg" alt="" width="491" height="737" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">And more to come...bientt</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>', 'Paris Magazine - I C U Cover Shoot', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'paris-magazine-i-c-u-cover-shoot', '', '', '2010-03-25 00:26:31', '2010-03-24 23:26:31', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3164', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(3184, 4, '2010-03-25 13:12:52', '2010-03-25 12:12:52', '<em>3.25.10</em>\n\n<em>I C U - In Boston &amp; 5spr. A sale for every woman''s dream.</em><em> <span style="color: #888888;">W</span><span style="color: #888888;">eek #24. Post 4.</span></em>\n\nIt''s the kind of sale we all dream about getting an invitation to. Champagne cocktails mixed by Hypnotic, gift bags (which no matter, always remind me of when I was five &amp; at b-day parties), prices you will surely not find anywhere else, a beautiful day, a gorgeous space...all presented by the ladies of 5spr and some of Boston''s best boutiques.\n\nAmong the crowd were:<a href="http://www.stilinc.com/">Stil</a>,<a href="http://www.habitshop.com/">Habit</a>,<a href="http://stylecarrot.com/2010/01/07/shopping-trip-portobello-road/" target="_blank">Portobello Road</a>,<a href="http://stylecarrot.com/2010/03/09/deal-alert-the-velvet-fly/" target="_blank">Velvet Fly</a>,<a href="http://www.dailycandy.com/boston/article/74206/Flock-Boutique-Opens" target="_blank">Flock</a>, and<a href="http://stylecarrot.com/2010/03/18/deal-alert-sample-sale-in-fort-point/www.frenchdressinglingerie.com" target="_blank">French Dressing</a>. Other vendors, such as<a href="http://stylecarrot.com/2010/03/18/deal-alert-sample-sale-in-fort-point/ww.bryceorganics.com/" target="_blank">Bryce Skin Care</a> ,<a href="http://www.fabricadabra.us/">Fabricadabra</a> and yours truly - I C U.\n<p style="text-align: center;">The Lofts @319.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/icu-and-5spr-warehouse-sale-event-boston3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3185" title="icu and 5spr warehouse sale event - boston3" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/icu-and-5spr-warehouse-sale-event-boston3.jpg" alt="" width="336" height="448" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-co