(3318, 4, '2010-04-08 13:39:08', '2010-04-08 11:39:08', '<em>4.07.10</em>\n\n<em>MOMENT: Latvia Gives it''s Art Students A Stage to Stand On.</em><em> Week #26. Post 2.</em>\n\nThe origin of MOMENT was started in 2006, when the first event [MOMENT] was realized by people who wanted to create a celebratory event for art, fashion and music out of the same components of art, fashion and music...does that make sense?\n\nThis of course depends on your own perception of art''s value, but these individuals see the components in a similar manner, that is why they decide to come together and create one unified event to celebrate it all.\n\nBut simply:\n\n<strong>Themission and amibition is the promotion of the new Baltic fashion and world artists and their ideas to a higher local and international levels.</strong>\n\nThere is so much to write about this event because it is absolutely an amazing idea put into serious action...I however will only highlight a few things with hopes you will check out the site on your own.\n\nBrought to you by the Artists of the <a href="http://lma.lv/eng/index.php" target="_blank">Art Academy of Latvia</a>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Moment-latvia-fashion-and-arts-week.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3319" title="Moment latvia fashion and arts week" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Moment-latvia-fashion-and-arts-week.jpg" alt="" width="394" height="576" /></a></em></p>\n<strong>Opening night: April 7th, 2010 the event will run until the 1oth.</strong>\n\nA couple highlights -\n\n<a href="http://www.mammu.lv/" target="_blank">MAMMU</a>\n\n"MAMMU is a new project, which has been brought to life by creative people, who want to change the society for good with help of fashion and design.Its goal is to support single mothers in Latvia by generating new work places and letting these women work from home or any other place, and give supplement to their family budget. The first MAMMU creation is a scarf collection made by fashion designer Liva Kauke-Saule. 7 out of 8 models in the photo session are single mothers and fathers. Project MAMMU will be presented for the first time during<a href="http://www.moment.com.lv/" target="_blank">[MOMENT]</a> week and this is the first time that such a social project is actualized in Latvia." (text taken directly from the MAMMU site).\n\n<a href="http://www.moment.com.lv/week/participants/fashion-designers/the-wave-of-90ties" target="_blank">Latvian Fashion in the 90''s</a>\n\nA fashion flashback  its an exposition that reveals how fashion used to be before 10 years and what was up-to date at that time. Can you imagine how funky this expo will be??\n\n<a href="http://www.moment.com.lv/week/participants/fashion-designers/heidi-ackerman-ca" target="_blank">Canadian Heidi Ackerman</a>\n\nDuring [MOMENT]week Heidi will present her latest spring/summer collection construct(this), which reflects artists obsession with architecture, futurism and abstraction.Visit her blog here:<a onclick="pageTracker._trackPageview(''/outgoing/flightheidiackerman.blogspot.com?referer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.moment.com.lv%2Fweek%2Fparticipants'');" href="http://flightheidiackerman.blogspot.com/">flightheidiackerman.blogspot.com</a>\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/heidi1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3320" title="heidi1" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/heidi1.jpg" alt="" width="460" height="331" /></a>\n\n<a href="http://www.vinils.lv/index_old.php" target="_blank">Nils Vinlis</a>\n\nPhotographer Nils Vilnis started to take photos right after graduating from high school, when he learned for himself how to take creative photos  read literature, studied works of other photographers etc. Right now Nils is working for magazines like Pastaiga, Klubs, Podium Art, and collaborates with different advertising agencies. His specialisation  fashion and advertising photography. His works will be seen during [MOMENT]week.More information:<a onclick="pageTracker._trackPageview(''/outgoing/www.vinils.lv/?referer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.moment.com.lv%2Fweek%2Fparticipants'');" href="http://www.vinils.lv/">www.vinils.lv</a>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Photography-by-Nils-Vilnis-4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3322" title="Photography-by-Nils-Vilnis-4" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Photography-by-Nils-Vilnis-4.jpg" alt="" width="480" height="384" /></a></p>\n\n<table border="0" width="480">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/nils-vilnis.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3323" title="nils vilnis" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/nils-vilnis.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="500" /></a>\n\nLearn, read and view more on the MOMENT official homepage: http://www.moment.com.lv/week/\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/moment_week_logo.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3324" title="moment_week_logo" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/moment_week_logo.jpg" alt="" width="409" height="100" /></a>', 'MOMENT: Latvia&#039;s Alternate Fashion &amp; Arts Week', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'moment-latvias-alternate-fashion-arts-week', '', '', '2010-04-08 13:39:08', '2010-04-08 11:39:08', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3318', 0, 'post', '', 0),
