(3419, 4, '2010-04-24 11:21:10', '2010-04-24 09:21:10', '<em>4.24.10</em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #ff00ff;"><a href="http://www.sophie-mhabille.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff00ff;">Sophie Mhabille.</span></a></span> Red Pumps &amp; Animal Prints. This is Spring in Paris. </em><em><span style="color: #808080;">Week #28. Post 4.</span></em>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;">Ah yes. You know the feeling. It''s Spring. The sun is shining, windows are open, music playing...If you live in a city, you especially know what I''m talking about. The parks start to bloom, trees in blossom, flower scents carry through crisp air. </span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;">Feeling a bit more creative and funky in your choice of style...takin off the layers today... </span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;">Which leads me to Mlle. Sophie...the young lady has a talent of mixing luxury fashion with contemporary/affordable. </span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;"> Back again and this time in Andr red pumps and leopard animal print courtesy of Mr. Vuitton.</span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/paris-street-style-in-the-spring-sophie-mhabille1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3423" title="paris street style in the spring sophie mhabille" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/paris-street-style-in-the-spring-sophie-mhabille1.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="823" /></a></span></span>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;">Tee-shirt : <a href="http://www.zara.com/" target="_blank">Zara</a>, jupe : <a href="http://www.comptoirdescotonniers.com/" target="_blank">Comptoir des Cotonniers</a>, ceinture : <a href="http://www.hm.com/" target="_blank">H&amp;M</a>, tole : <a href="http://www.louisvuitton.com/" target="_blank">Louis Vuitton</a>, escarpins : <a href="http://www.andre.fr/" target="_blank">Andr</a>, sac : <a href="http://www.chanel.com/" target="_blank">Chanel</a></span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #ff00ff;">T-Shirt: </span><a href="http://www.zara.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff00ff;">Zara</span></a><span style="color: #ff00ff;">, Skirt: </span><a href="http://www.comptoirdescotonniers.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff00ff;">Comptoir des Cotonniers</span></a><span style="color: #ff00ff;">, Belt: </span><a href="http://www.hm.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff00ff;">H&amp;M</span></a><span style="color: #ff00ff;">, Scarf: </span><a href="http://www.louisvuitton.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff00ff;">Loui Vuitton</span></a><span style="color: #ff00ff;">, Red Pumps: </span><a href="http://www.andre.fr/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff00ff;">Andr</span></a><span style="color: #ff00ff;">, Purse: </span><a href="http://www.chanel.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff00ff;">Chanel</span></a></span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/paris-street-style-animal-print-sophie-mhabille.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3420" title="paris street style animal print  sophie mhabille" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/paris-street-style-animal-print-sophie-mhabille.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;">La fameuse tole lopard, (celle qui se cache dabord dans le sac, puis qui fait son apparition!) est inspire par <a href="http://www.welovesprouse.com/" target="_blank">Stephen Sprouse</a> pour <a href="http://www.louisvuitton.com/" target="_blank">Louis Vuitton</a>, un best seller de la Maison, dite chaque saisons dans des coloris diffrents.</span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #808080;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #ff00ff;">The famous leopard scarf (one which hides in the bag and then makes its appearance when right!). The scarf is inspired by </span><a href="http://www.welovesprouse.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff00ff;">Stephen Sprouse</span></a><span style="color: #ff00ff;"> for </span><a href="http://www.louisvuitton.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff00ff;">Louis Vuitton</span></a><span style="color: #ff00ff;">, a best seller at the Vuitton house, and customized in color for each season. </span></span></span></p>\n<em><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/paris-street-style-red-pumps-sphie-mhabille.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3422" title="paris street style red pumps sophie mhabille" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/paris-street-style-red-pumps-sphie-mhabille.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="267" /></a></em>\n\nTo see from Sophie and other fantastic Paris street style pics go to:<em> <span style="color: #ff00ff;"><a href="http://www.sophie-mhabille.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff00ff;">www.sophiemhabille.com</span></a></span></em>', 'Spring in Paris is not Spring in Paris sans Red Pumps. ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'spring-in-paris-is-not-spring-in-paris-sans-red-pumps', '', '', '2010-04-24 11:21:10', '2010-04-24 09:21:10', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3419', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(3512, 4, '2010-04-29 14:33:00', '2010-04-29 12:33:00', '<em>4.29.10</em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #ff00ff;"><a href="http://sophie-mhabille.com/index.php" target="_blank">Sophie Mhabille</a></span></em><em>. I Want... everything that is on this t-shirt ;) Week #29. Post 2.</em>\n\n<em>\n</em>\n\n<em><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/sophie-mhabille-paris-street-style.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3513" title="sophie mhabille paris street style" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/sophie-mhabille-paris-street-style.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></em>\n\n<em><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/sophie-mhabille-paris-street-style-spring-style.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3514" title="sophie mhabille paris street style spring style" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/sophie-mhabille-paris-street-style-spring-style.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></em>\n\n<em><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/sophie-mhabille-paris-street-tee-shirt.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3515" title="sophie mhabille paris street tee-shirt" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/sophie-mhabille-paris-street-tee-shirt.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></em>\n\n<em>Ce tee-shirt rsume parfaitement tout ce que je veux. et jen veux des choses, notamment : du chocolat (il me faut ma dose quotidienne de chocolat noir), faire la grasse matine (cest tellement rare), quon me sert dans ses bras (jaime les marques daffection et de tendresse), des cadeaux (oui, comme tout le monde, je crois), un super job (no comment!), un chouette petit copain (est ce que je lai trouv?!), des vacances (je pars dans quelques jours  Barcelone, j en ai tellement besoin), des vtements (toujours), tre aime (ca cest essentiel, impossible de vivre sans Amour), dancer (oui, avec plaisir!)</em>\n\n<span style="color: #ff00ff;">This t-shirt perfectly resembles all of the things I want... and I want things, especially: chocolate (I need my daily dose of dark chocolate), to sleep (which is so rare), someone who takes me in his arms (like public displays of affection and tenderness), presents (yes, like everyone, I think), a super job (no comment!), an adorable boyfriend (is it that I have found him?!), vacation (I''m leaving in a couple days for Barcelona, which I really need to do), clothes (always), to be loved (this is essential, impossible to love without love), and dancing (yes! with pleasure!).</span>\n\n<em>Tee-shirt : <a href="http://www.soniarykiel.fr/" target="_blank">Sonia Rykiel</a>, jupe : <a href="http://www.zara.com/" target="_blank">Zara</a>, casquette et sabots : vintage, sac, lunettes et montre : <a href="http://www.chanel.com/" target="_blank">Chanel</a></em>\n\n<span style="color: #ff00ff;">T-shirt: <a href="http://www.soniarykiel.fr/" target="_blank">Sonia Rykiel</a>, Skirt: <a href="http://www.zara.com/" target="_blank">Zara</a>, Hat &amp; Clogs: Vintage, Bag, Glasses &amp; Watch: <a href="http://www.chanel.com/" target="_blank">Chanel</a></span>\n\n<span style="color: #ff00ff;"><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>To see from Sophie and other fantastic Paris street style pics go</strong><span style="color: #000000;"><strong> to</strong></span></span><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>:</strong></span><strong> </strong><em><a href="http://www.sophie-mhabille.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff00ff;"><strong>www.sophiemhabille.com</strong></span></a></em></span>', 'Je Veux Votre T-Shirt! ;)', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'je-veux-votre-t-shirt', '', '', '2010-04-29 14:33:00', '2010-04-29 12:33:00', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3512', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(3553, 4, '2010-06-02 12:23:51', '2010-06-02 10:23:51', '6.02.10\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">Its been some time... And lots has happened : )</span> Week #30. Post 1.\n\nCrazy how fast time flies when lots and lots is happening. I cannot believe it has been a month since our last blog post! So... even though we would love to catch up on all that has gone down, we will probably just start right back up again. However, there are a couple things that should be mentioned...\n\nOur first magazine cover appearance hit news stands on May 1st! Owner and founder of I C U - In Paris, Christan Summers is also a freelance stylist and styled and directed the shoot for <a href="http://www.theparismagazine.com/" target="_blank">Paris Magazine''s</a> May/June issue. We showed you some of <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/03/25/paris-magazine-i-c-u-cover-shoot/" target="_blank">"the making of" shots</a>, you may notice a couple differences from the first images to the final... but thats what comes with working in the media world.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/paris-cover.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-3554" title="parisMAY2010:PARIS MAGAZINE" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/paris-cover-790x1024.jpg" alt="" width="498" height="645" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\nPhotographer: <a href="http://laurenceguenoun.com/" target="_blank">Laurence Guenoun</a>\n\nCreative Direction: <a href="http://shownd.com/csummers" target="_blank">Christan Summers</a>\n\nModel: Dasha G.\n\nMake-up: Nicolas Petitot\n\nDress: <a href="http://www.americanretro.fr/" target="_blank">American Retro Vintage Collection</a>\n\nJewelry: I C U - In Paris:<a href="http://www.icuinparis.com/eshop" target="_blank">Sonya Renee Moonstone necklace </a>worn as a bracelet.\n\nAnd just a side note: for those English speakers coming to Paris to visit or live <a href="http://www.theparismagazine.com" target="_blank">Paris Magazine</a> is an absolute savior. All that you want to know on the latest happenings, events, discoveries, shopping and people - in English! Sometimes feels nice to understand 100% of what you read ; )', 'I C U - Paris Magazine May/June 2010 Cover Shoot', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'i-c-u-paris-magazine-mayjune-2010-cover-shoot', '', '', '2010-06-02 12:23:51', '2010-06-02 10:23:51', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3553', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(3558, 4, '2010-06-02 13:09:01', '2010-06-02 11:09:01', '6.02.10\n\n<span style="color: #800080;">Paris Magazine June/August 2010 Cover Shoot - Its the Making of...</span> <em>Week #30. Post 2.</em>\n\nCover shoot numro deux. Again, here are the "behind the scenes" images and when the issue hits the news stands we will post the final image here! <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/06/02/i-c-u-paris-magazine-mayjune-2010-cover-shoot/" target="_blank">(View May/June Issue)</a>\n\nThe idea for the issue: <strong><span style="color: #cc99ff;">Summer in Paris!</span></strong> The theme of the issue will be "An Insider''s View" of Paris - and <a href="http://www.theparismagazine.com" target="_blank">Paris Magazine </a>will even provide a handy pocket size map to aide fellow English speakers along their ways.\n\nBelow the shoot in action:\n\nPhotographer: <a href="http://designlab7.com/" target="_blank">Brian Wright</a>\n\nCreative Director: <a href="http://shownd.com/csummers" target="_blank">Christan Summers</a>\n\nMake-up/Hair Artist: <a href="http://tomohiroyamada.sakura.ne.jp/book.html" target="_blank">Tomorhiro Yamada</a>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/paris-magazine-photo-shoot-may-june-2010.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3559" title="paris magazine photo shoot may june 2010" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/paris-magazine-photo-shoot-may-june-2010.jpg" alt="" width="560" height="414" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/paris-magazine-photo-shoot-2010.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3560" title="paris magazine photo shoot 2010" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/paris-magazine-photo-shoot-2010.jpg" alt="" width="560" height="399" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/paris-magazine-making-of-photo-shoot-images-paris-photo-shoot.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-3561" title="paris magazine making of photo shoot images paris photo shoot" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/paris-magazine-making-of-photo-shoot-images-paris-photo-shoot-1024x937.jpg" alt="" width="553" height="506" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/paris-magazine-photo-shoot-may-june-shoot.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3562" title="paris magazine photo shoot may june shoot" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/paris-magazine-photo-shoot-may-june-shoot.jpg" alt="" width="560" height="450" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">And a treat from Mr. Wright  Brian Wright<a href="http://www.designab7.com/">www.designab7.com</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/O5E8837_CREDIT_BRIAN_WRIGHT.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3563" title="_O5E8837_CREDIT_BRIAN_WRIGHT" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/O5E8837_CREDIT_BRIAN_WRIGHT.jpg" alt="" width="473" height="709" /></a></p>', 'Paris Magazine Cover Shoot July/Aug - The Making Of', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'paris-magazine-cover-shoot-julyaug-the-making-of', '', '', '2010-06-02 13:09:01', '2010-06-02 11:09:01', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3558', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(3569, 4, '2010-06-03 14:14:42', '2010-06-03 12:14:42', '6.03.10\n\nA Pop-UP with a lot of Flavor<em>Week #30. Post 3.</em>\n\nLast weekend in Paris we attended a Pop-Up Shop fabulously full of indie designers and creators alike. Sponsored by the likes of <a href=" http://www.jalouse.fr/" target="_blank">Jalouse</a> Magazine, you can imagine the level of <em>fantastic</em> of what the attendees and exhibitors had to offer.\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/pop-up-shop-paris.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3570" title="pop up shop paris" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/pop-up-shop-paris.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="300" /></a>\n\nNow there is not enough time and space this morning for me to write about each designer who exhibited - because they were all inspiring. However, there were two - two that really caught our eye and we hope to be seeing a lot more from them in the future.\n\n<a href="http://www.isnotdeadparis.com/" target="_blank">Is Not Dead</a> - who is not online just yet, but we have a small sneak peak for you from their look book...\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/is-not-dead-look-book-1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-3571" title="is not dead look book 1" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/is-not-dead-look-book-1-721x1024.jpg" alt="" width="455" height="645" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/is-not-dead-paris-clothing1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-3573" title="is not dead paris clothing" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/is-not-dead-paris-clothing1-721x1024.jpg" alt="" width="455" height="645" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads