(3600, 4, '2010-06-22 19:34:55', '2010-06-22 17:34:55', '6.22.10\n\n<em>Fashion''s Top Illustrators - Getting the Attention They Deserve. <span style="color: #888888;">Week #31. Post 2.</span></em>\n\nI receive blog updates from <a href="http://www.refinery29.com/four-illustrators-capture-fashions-finest.php?utm_source=Triggermail&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=R29+-+The+other+It+Bags+of+summer" target="_blank">Refinery 29</a> which I am sure many of you are aware of... if not, you should be! But this morning, they broadcasted something I was so very happy to read which was all about the top fashion illustrator''s of the year. One of them I have been a fan of for quite some time, so it made me super happy to see her getting such great attention!\n<h2 style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://igorandandre.blogspot.com/" target="_blank">aurore de la morinerie</a></h2>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.auroredelamorinerie.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3601" title="fashion-illustration-aurore-de-la-morinerie" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/fashion-illustration-aurore-de-la-morinerie.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">aurore de la morinerie which translates from French to <em>dawn of morinerie.</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Aurore was born in France in ''62 and attended L''cole des Arts Appliqus Duperr in Paris, which is a famous art design school (in fact, the same school one of our street style fashion ladies attends! - watch her video <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/01/17/paris-street-style-le-video-clemence/" target="_blank">HERE</a>).</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Aurore has completed works for Elle, Le MOnde, World of Interiors, and many others. Her techniques include ink and wash painting as well as etching press for monotypes.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">To view more illustrations, visit Aurore''s site <a href="http://www.auroredelamorinerie.com/" target="_blank">HERE</a></p>\n\n<h2 style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://igorandandre.blogspot.com/" target="_blank">Igor + Andr</a></h2>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://igorandandre.blogspot.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3602" title="fashion-illustration-igor-andre" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/fashion-illustration-igor-andre.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://igorandandre.blogspot.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-3608" title="mainsitew" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/mainsitew-1024x316.jpg" alt="" width="614" height="190" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Words from the artist:</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">I''ve always been one for creative projects and art and crafts.\nWhen I was five, I convinced myself that pouring mud onto cardboard was how to make concrete.\nI began drawing as a young child, but it wasn''t until a few years ago when I decided to practice everyday, that I started getting better.\nI would draw some days for 15 hours straight till my hands were swollen shut.\nWhen I was 13, I started my own clothing company and ran it with the help of my friend till I was was in college.\nI studied Photography at Cal Poly SLO, and then later studied Fashion Design at the Academy of Art in San Francisco.\nIve been honored to be able to collaborate with<a href="http://igorandandre.blogspot.com/search/label/Harajuku%20Lovers">Gwen Stefanis Harajuku Lovers</a>,<a href="http://igorandandre.blogspot.com/search/label/Forever21">Forever21</a>,<a href="http://igorandandre.blogspot.com/search/label/Heutchy">Heutchy Shoes</a>,<a href="http://igorandandre.blogspot.com/search/label/Lancome">Lancome</a>, and<a href="http://igorandandre.blogspot.com/search/label/Full%20Fontal%20Fashion">Sundance Channel''s Full Frontal Fashion</a>.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">The artist''s clothing line has since made it to <a href="http://www.forever21.com/" target="_blank">Forever 21</a> where you may buy styles now.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://igorandandre.blogspot.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3609" title="fashionsquadtank21" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/fashionsquadtank21.jpg" alt="" width="715" height="400" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://igorandandre.blogspot.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3610" title="bowlerhattees" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/bowlerhattees.jpg" alt="" width="715" height="400" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://igorandandre.blogspot.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3611" title="alicepointwaeringshirt" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/alicepointwaeringshirt.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="600" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">This is cool... inside view of the studio &amp; work in progress.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="640" height="385" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/zaaV_HmuCc4&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="640" height="385" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/zaaV_HmuCc4&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"> </embed></object>\n<h2 style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://cocopit.biz/" target="_blank">COCO</a></h2>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://cocopit.biz/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3603" title="fashion-illustration-coco-pit" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/fashion-illustration-coco-pit.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Words from the artist:</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">As an illustrator my background gives me a unique insight into fashion. After spending five years studying fine arts in Paris, I worked as a communication consultant for many leading fashion designers....I find inspiration in a wide variety of places. Living between Paris and London I feel at ease with the visual landscapes of both cities. As art and fashion capitals, they are a byword for innovation, creativity and metropolitan edge.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">And check out the artist''s small collection of silk scarf collection: <a href="http://forget-me-not.me/" target="_blank">forget-me-not </a> These are AMAZING!</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">More illustrations by Coco below...</p>\n<a href="http://cocopit.biz/" target="_blank"><img class="size-full wp-image-3604 alignnone" title="02-coco-portfolio-ilustracin-beauty-illustration-" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/02-coco-portfolio-ilustracin-beauty-illustration-.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="440" /></a>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://cocopit.biz/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3605" title="15-perfume-montage-magazine-fashion-coco" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/15-perfume-montage-magazine-fashion-coco.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="440" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://cocopit.biz/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3606" title="17-nylon-usa-magazine-fashion-coco-illustration" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/17-nylon-usa-magazine-fashion-coco-illustration.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="440" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://cocopit.biz/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3607" title="33-alexi-mabille-house-of-flora-invitation-valery-demure-fashion-exhition-london-fashion-week" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/33-alexi-mabille-house-of-flora-invitation-valery-demure-fashion-exhition-london-fashion-week.jpg" alt="" width="396" height="549" /></a></p>', 'Fashion&#039;s Illustrator&#039;s...not just any doodle', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'fashions-illustrators-not-just-any-doodle', '', '', '2010-06-22 19:34:55', '2010-06-22 17:34:55', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3600', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(3618, 4, '2010-06-23 16:34:22', '2010-06-23 14:34:22', '6.23.10\n\n<em>A Shaded View on Fashion Film Festival in collaboration with Vogue Italia.Week #31. Post 3.</em>\n\n<em><span style="font-style: normal;">A winner has been chosen for the <a href="http://www.ashadedviewonfashionfilm.com/program" target="_blank">ASVOFF Milan Film Festival</a>. In collaboration with <a href="http://www.vogue.it/en" target="_blank">Vogue Italia</a>, the theme of the festival was light and the challenge - show the judges what you can do with something un-touchable. </span></em>\n\n<em><span style="font-style: normal;">The Contest Winners: (To view the videos, click on the titles)</span></em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/jaifaim-181504_201x113.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3620" title="jaifaim-181504_201x113" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/jaifaim-181504_201x113.jpg" alt="" width="201" height="113" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><a href="http://www.vogue.it/en/talents/vogue-video-lab/2010/05/asvoff-milano--i-vincitori" target="_blank">J''AI FAIM!</a></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="http://www.vogue.it/en/talents/vogue-video-lab/2010/05/asvoff-milano--i-vincitori" target="_blank">by Miho Kinomura</a></em></p>\nA girl, mysterious and miraculous, who lives only on light. A light that sparkles like icy blue colored crystals, a light that the girl dearly loves. A wonderland inhabited by sweet, strange creatures.<strong>Miho Kinomura</strong> is a Los Angeles based Creative Director/Film Director who works between Japan, Europe, and Los Angeles. After working as a fashion designer, Miho moved to New York and started fashion film production company,<a title="Studio DOG Inc" href="http://www.studiodoginc.com/v2/" target="_blank">Studio D.O.G.INC.</a>\n\nMiho is well-known worldwide networking and photography lover within the advertising industry, and has expanded into music video, where she established a fashion genre. Her collaboration project Tokyo Style Clash "Hot or Not" with UK''s Show studio, led by Nick Knight, was awarded the bronze medal on the<a title="CLIO Awards" href="http://www.clioawards.com/entries/mediums_and_categories.cfm" target="_blank">CLIO Award Innovative Media Apparel</a>/ Fashion Category.\n\n<em>DP: Mitsuaki Koshizuka\nModel: Rina Ohta\nMusic: Kensui Arao</em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><a href="http://www.vogue.it/en/talents/vogue-video-lab/2010/05/asvoff-milano--i-vincitori" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3619" title="william-359611_201x113" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/william-359611_201x113.jpg" alt="" width="201" height="113" /></a><a href="http://www.vogue.it/en/talents/vogue-video-lab/2010/05/asvoff-milano--i-vincitori" target="_blank">WILLIAM RICHARD GREEN</a></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="http://www.vogue.it/en/talents/vogue-video-lab/2010/05/asvoff-milano--i-vincitori" target="_blank">by Zaiba Jabbar</a></em></p>\n<strong>Zaiba Jabbar</strong> is a self-taught filmmaker living in London. After studying graphic design at Central Saint Martin''s, Jabbar has worked in the music video industry since 2006. However, she made the move in 2008 into more fashion-orientated projects and has since worked with clients which include Aquascutum, Mulberry, Levis, Hint Magazine, Spring69, New look, David David, Hermione De Paula, William Richard Green, and Fashion 156.\n\n"The designer and I wanted to create a film using light in constant motion. The Rubber Jacket especially absorbed and displayed the moving pin prick lights beautifully. These grungy outlined glimpses of the model with the moving light and void-like negative space infected the key pieces of the AW10 Collection to create a tectonic and mysterious mood for the film which echoed the heroic and anti-heroic ideas of the collection."\n\n<em>for William Richard Green</em>\n\n<em>Model: Thomas Ashley</em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>To view more videos from the contest visit <a href="http://www.vogue.it/en/talents/vogue-video-lab" target="_blank">Vogue ItaliaVideo Lab</a></em></p>', 'ASVOFF Light Film Festival &amp; Vogue Italia have a winner', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'asvoff-light-film-festival-vogue-italia-have-a-winner', '', '', '2010-06-23 16:34:22', '2010-06-23 14:34:22', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3618', 0, 'post', '', 0),
