(3636, 4, '2010-07-04 17:50:57', '2010-07-04 15:50:57', '7.4.10\n\nAmore. I am Love. This film is not to be missed. <span style="color: #888888;">Week #32. Post 1.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><a href="http://dianepernet.typepad.com/diane/" target="_blank">Diane Pernet of A Shaded View on Fashion</a> was of course at the Paris film festival where <a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/culture/2009/dec/31/first-sight-luca-guadagnino" target="_blank">Luca Guadagnino</a>''s Amore (I am Love) film was debuted. </span>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #888888;">A film which has been in the making for 11 years - Italian in language - cinematography that will knock your socks off - and a love that''s passion you will feel through the screen. Twilda Swinton continues to break barriers and attract a respected following. </span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #888888;"> </span>\n<object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="560" height="340" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/UUXEAhJb_O0&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="560" height="340" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/UUXEAhJb_O0&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"></embed></object>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">This is great too - just getting to know a bit more of the film and what went into the making...</p>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="480" height="385" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/g0X4DZcpz0M&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="480" height="385" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/g0X4DZcpz0M&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"></embed></object>', 'Amore ~ &quot;I just like open windows&quot; ~ Tilda Swinton ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'amore-i-just-like-open-windows-tilda-swinton', '', '', '2010-07-04 17:50:57', '2010-07-04 15:50:57', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3636', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(3648, 6, '2010-08-10 15:48:18', '2010-08-10 13:48:18', '8.10.10. Week#33.Post 1.\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/a-matter-of-taste-600x6042.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-3659" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/a-matter-of-taste-600x6042-298x300.jpg" alt="" width="298" height="300" /></a>\n\nYou''ve never seen food like this before! How amazing is this book on the theme "Food as Fashion". The most improbable that all the tasty accessories of Fulvio Bonavia (you can check his work on his <a href="http://www.fulviobonavia.com/" target="_blank">portfolio</a>) are real! Author by his own hands made models from food for each shot and not with the ubiquitous Photoshop. Pictures excite taste buds and sense of style, a work between Haute couture and Gastronomy.\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">Vous n''aviez encore jamais vu la nourriture comme a! Ce recueil de photographie sur le thme du design culinaire est tout simplement formidable. Le plus apprciable tant que tous les succulents accessoires de Fulvio Bonavia (regardez son travail sur </span><a href="http://www.fulviobonavia.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #888888;">ce site</span></a><span style="color: #888888;">) sont rels! L''auteur les a fabriqu de ses mains,avec de vrais aliments et n''a pas cd  la failit de photoshop. Des photos qui aiguisent les sens, un travail entre Haute couture et gastronomie.</span>\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/a-matter-of-taste-1-600x600.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-3651" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/a-matter-of-taste-1-600x600-300x300.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="300" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/a-matter-of-taste-7-600x594.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-3652" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/a-matter-of-taste-7-600x594-300x297.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="297" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/a-matter-of-taste-by-fulvio-bonavia.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-3653" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/a-matter-of-taste-by-fulvio-bonavia-300x258.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="258" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/fruit-hat-1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-3654" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/fruit-hat-1-300x272.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="272" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/a-matter-of-taste-by-fulvio-bonavia-7.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-3655" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/a-matter-of-taste-by-fulvio-bonavia-7-296x300.jpg" alt="" width="296" height="300" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/a-matter-of-taste-by-fulvio-bonavia-4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-3656" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/a-matter-of-taste-by-fulvio-bonavia-4-300x298.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="298" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/a-matter-of-taste-4-600x600.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-3657" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/a-matter-of-taste-4-600x600-300x300.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="300" /></a>\n\n<a href="http://www.fulviobonavia.com/">\n</a>', 'A Matter of Taste /Le Got du Luxe', 'Fulvio Bonavia: A Matter of Taste.\nGreat pictures on the theme "food as fashion".', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-matter-of-taste-le-gout-du-luxe', '', '', '2010-08-10 15:48:18', '2010-08-10 13:48:18', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3648', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(3670, 6, '2010-08-16 16:52:23', '2010-08-16 14:52:23', '8.16.10. Week#34. Post 1.\n\na bouge chez le Sellier le plus chic ever. Aprs la dpart de JP Gaultier, la nomination de son remplaant Christophe Lemaire (collection automne-hiver 11-12 trs attendue! soyez sur le coup), Herms se lance comme un cheval sauvage  la conqute d''un nouveau public avec le site "<a href="http://www.jaimemoncarre.com" target="_blank">jaimemoncarr"</a> en franais dans le texte, largement relay par leur Fanpage sur Facebook, qui compte plus de 150000" likeurs".\n\nLe photographe Matt Irwin et la styliste Francesca Burns nous offrent un joli reportage photos/vidos sur "l''art de porter son carr", une campagne qui se veut originale pour la nouvelle collection de Bali Barret (D.A soie chez Herms), collection qui sera commercialise en exclu chez Colette (what else?) du 27 septembre au 16 octobre prochain. Comment je sais a? parce que je l''ai lu sur Fashion Daily news, car ce n''est pas le genre d''information que l''on trouve en naviguant sur le susnomm site.\n\nAyant apparemment voulu tre dans la mouvance de Burberry avec son trs russi "<a href="http://artofthetrench.com/" target="_blank">Art of the trench</a>"(un site participatif montrant des gens, beaux a va de soit, mais qui existent pour de vrai, portant l''imper mythique, le tout chapeaut par the <a href="http://thesartorialist.blogspot.com/" target="_blank">Satorialist</a>), Herms se fourvoie quelque peu. En effet, outre la navigation dsastreuse (trop de Flash, tue...), on sent bien que l''ergonomie et les choix graphiques n''ont pas non plus t la grande priorit, peut mieux faire, pour rester polie... Et l, on a envie de dire, pourquoi?\n\nLes photos sont plutt jolies, quoique hyper calibres, on s''encanaille, mais dans la soie, on parle d''Herms quand mme.J''aperois une tte de BB brunes, sur les photos parisiennes et ce qui a l''air d''tre sa copine/groupie/plasticine que sais-je encore?On nous pargne le name dropping, c''est dj a. Mais tu es cool, parce que tu l''as reconnu, toi aussi.\n\nBref, on salue tout de mme la volont d''une grande marque de Luxe de se mettre au 2.0 et d''offrir quelque chose de nouveau, mme si le rsultat n''est qu''une illusion de mdia social. Car, Luxe oblige, il faut savoir contrler son image.\n\na c''tait pour la partie "fille aigrie de ne pas pouvoir mettre 300  dans un carr de tissu".\n\nMaintenant la bte de mode qui sommeille a juste envie de lever les bras en l''air et de laisser chapper un cri hystrique suivit de plusieurs "trop beau! J''en veux trop un!",pour aprs, prendre l''air le plus dtach possible pour aller faire la queue chez Colette, genre je fais a tous les jours.\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em>(English Translation Below the images)</em></span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">\n</span>\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3680" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/carre2-e1281623098624.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="406" /><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3681" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/hermes17-143501c04.jpg" alt="" width="620" height="381" /><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3682" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Image-2.png" alt="" width="576" height="263" /><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Image-6.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3684" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Image-6.png" alt="" width="451" height="450" /></a><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3686" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Image-1.png" alt="" width="755" height="482" />\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">Things are moving for the chicest Saddler ever! After JP Gaultier''s walkout, the appointment of his sucessor Christophe Lemaire (the collection Fall-Winter 11-12 has to be kept in check!), Herms is trying to capture a new market with the lauch of the website "j''aimemoncarr" (I love my carr=scarf), with the help of its fanpage on Facebook, that already counts a total of 150000 fans.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">The photographer Matt Irwin and the stylist Francesca Burns are presenting a nice reportage photos/videos on the "art of knotting your carr", a campaign that claim to be original for the brand new collection of Bali Barret (AD for the silk departement at Herms), that will be sold exclusively chez Colette, Paris (of course, where else?) from the 27 of september to the 16 of october. How do I know all this? well, it''s certainly not from the website aforementioned.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">They seemingly wanted to be in the tendency of Burberry with its cool <a href="http://artofthetrench.com/" target="_blank">"Art of Trench"</a>( a participative website that shows real but of course beautiful people wearing THE trench, mostly shot by <a href="http://thesartorialist.blogspot.com/" target="_blank">The Satorialist</a>), but here Herms is somewhat mistaken. Indeed, beyond the disastrous browsing, it appears that the graphic design and the ergonomics were not the highest priority neither. There''s a margin of improvement, will I say, to stay polite.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">Otherwise, the pictures are pretty good, althought very clean, we are talking about Herms, there. If you look closely, you can glimpse a guy from "<a href="http://www.bbbrunes.fr/" target="_blank">BB brune</a>" (*editor''s note: french rock band). If you recognized him too, you''re as hype as Herms expected you to be!</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">To make a long story short, I would still like to mention the will of a Luxe brand to enter the 2.0 era and to bring something new, even though the outcome turns to be a semblance of social media. A Luxe brand knows how to stay a Luxe brand : control its image.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">Now that the embittered-girl-who-can''t-afford-a-300-piece-of-tissu has talked, here comes the part where the dormant fashionista within me just wants to wave my arms and hystericaly whoop : "I want one, I want one, I want one!"...And afterwards, stay in line in front of Colette the D-day, casual, acting like it''s my everyday life.</span>', 'Herms nous fait une tte au carr!', 'The launch of a new website for Herms: j''aimemoncarr.com', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hermes-nous-fait-une-tete-au-carre', '', '', '2010-08-16 16:52:23', '2010-08-16 14:52:23', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3670', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(3692, 4, '2010-08-13 12:42:44', '2010-08-13 10:42:44', '8.13.10. Week#33. Post 2.\n\nThis is interesting. A creative statement on the rise... which means of course we love it.\n\nAn exclusive world premiere first seen on the <a href="http://www.businessoffashion.com" target="_blank">Business Of Fashion</a> of <a href="http://www.bandofoutsiders.com/" target="_blank">Band of Outsiders</a> Scott Sternberg in Being There, directed by <a href="http://www.businessoffashion.com/tag/debra-scherer" target="_blank">Debra Scherer</a> for The Little Squares. Band of Outsiders is a relatively new clothing label - fresh, modern, not your average polo shirt but flirting on the edge of classic style. He''s got a message and I like it. He is making the effort to introduce a different idea to the fashion/luxury world.\n\nIn the short clip, Mr. Sternberg brings attention to the image of luxury - the pouty model sitting on a car holding a purse ... he asks, "How do you, sort of, express your voice without seeming like you''re rejecting these people who you hold a lot of respect for?"\n\nGood question.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="400" height="300" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=14006162&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=1&amp;show_byline=1&amp;show_portrait=1&amp;color=&amp;fullscreen=1&amp;autoplay=0&amp;loop=0" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="400" height="300" src="http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=14006162&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=1&amp;show_byline=1&amp;show_portrait=1&amp;color=&amp;fullscreen=1&amp;autoplay=0&amp;loop=0" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"></embed></object>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Scott-Sternberg-of-Band-Of-Outsiders-1-500x304.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3696" title="Scott-Sternberg-of-Band-Of-Outsiders-1-500x304" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Scott-Sternberg-of-Band-Of-Outsiders-1-500x304.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="304" /></a>Scott Sternberg at Lego installation at Opening Ceremony | Source: Selectism</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://vimeo.com/14006162">Band of Outsiders'' Scott Sternberg in Being There, by The Little Squares</a> from<a href="http://vimeo.com/user4458305">debra scherer</a> on<a href="http://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.</p>', 'Band of Outsiders... a creative statement.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'band-of-outsiders-a-creative-statement', '', '', '2010-08-13 12:42:44', '2010-08-13 10:42:44', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3692', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(3706, 6, '2010-08-17 17:39:40', '2010-08-17 15:39:40', '8.17.10. Week#34. Post 2.\n\nLe top de la tendance pour la rentre? s''habiller en late fifties/early sixties de la tte au pieds. Ca tombe plutt bien:\n\nLa production de la trs jolie srie aux 17 nominations aux Emmy awards<strong>, "Mad men" </strong>vient d''annoncer une vente aux enchres de vtements et de mobilier ayant servi au tournage. Les robes de la styliste<strong> Janie Bryant</strong>, qui a dj fait ses preuves sur l''excellente srie "<em>Deadwood</em>", portes par les actrices <strong>January Jones</strong> (alias Betty Drapper) et <strong>Christina Hendricks</strong> (Joan Holloway), seront disponibles sur ebay<a href="http://stores.ebay.com/Celebrity-Charity-Auctions__W0QQrtZncQQ_sidZ412705173QQ_trksidZp4634Q2ec0Q2em14?_trksid=p4634.c0.m14.l1513&amp;_pgn=1" target="_blank"></a> . Des meubles provenant de l''agence fictive "<em>Sterling Cooper" </em>comme le bureau de Peggy, typique du design des annes 60, seront galement  enchrir.\n\nLa vente se droulera jusqu''au 22 aot, et l''argent sera revers  l''association "<em>City of Hope</em>" luttant contre le cancer du poumon.\n\n(english version below the images)\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3707" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/080728_madmen1.jpg" alt="" width="490" height="326" />\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3708" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/100722-le-style-mad-men.aspx79980Image.jpg" alt="" width="325" height="442" />\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3709" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/mad-men-0909-02.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="274" />\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3710" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/mad-men-0909-06.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="276" />\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3711" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Mad+Men+4.jpg" alt="" width="243" height="320" />\n\nThe new trend of the fall: to dress up like in the late fifties/early sixties from head to toe. Perfect timing:\n\nThe Production of the 17 Emmy nominated TV show," <strong>Mad men</strong>" just announced the auction of part of the wardrobe and the furniture used on the set. Dresses designed by <strong>Janie Bryant</strong>, who already proved her talent in the amazing show "<em>Deadwood</em>", worn by the actresses <strong>January Jones</strong> (alias Betty Drapper) and <strong>Christina Hendricks</strong> (Joan Holloway) will be available on ebay. Furnitures from the imaginary agency "<em>Sterling Cooper</em>", like Peggy''s desk, typical design from the sixties are going to be on auction too.\n\nThe sale is until august 22 only and all the profits will be revert to the association "<em>City of Hope</em>" against lung cancer.', 'Mad Men on ebay!', 'Wardrobe and furniture from Mad men on ebay', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'mad-men-on-ebay', '', '', '2010-08-17 17:39:40', '2010-08-17 15:39:40', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3706', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(3718, 6, '2010-08-23 18:15:42', '2010-08-23 16:15:42', '8.23.10. Week#35. Post 1.\n\n"<em>Quand je serais mort, je veux un suaire de chez Dior</em>", Boris Vian ne croyait pas si bien dire.\n\nCela va s''appeler <strong>Leonor Funeral Couture</strong> et ce sera la premire ligne consacre exclusivement aux enterrements.\n\nL''ide vient de l''intrigante<strong> Lonor Sherrer</strong>, fille du mythique couturier <strong>Jean-Louis Sherrer</strong> et muse de <strong>Riccardo Tisci</strong>. N''ayant pas trouv de tenue approprie pour assister aux funrailles d''Yves Saint Laurent, elle dcide de lancer une collection adapte pour un tel vnement.\n\n"<em>La mort est devenue banale</em>", clame-t-elle. Son ambitieux projet est de restaurer la dignit, l''lgance et le romantisme autrefois associs aux funrailles et au deuil, mais galement de redonner une signification aux vtements et aux accessoires. Lonor regrette le temps ou la robe d''une veuve tait toujours examine sous toutes ses coutures. La mystrieuse" fille de" est une artiste qui chappe dcidment  toutes les conventions: elle prpare un album de musique de crmonies, pour accompagner le lancement de sa collection.\n\nElle s''inspire d''<strong> Yves Saint Laurent</strong> et de<strong> Claude Montana</strong>. Elle a galement dcid de s''entourer de stylistes diffrents pour chaque saison, le premier  avoir accept tant son trs cher ami <strong>Riccardo Tisci</strong>, avec lequel elle partage sa passion du dark et du gothique. "<em>Je suis absolument amoureux d''elle. Pour moi, elle reprsente la France dans toute sa splendeur: l''lgance l''aristocratie et le ct obscur", </em>dit-il  son propos<em>.</em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">(English version bellow the images)</span></em>\n\n<em><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/leonor_784x02.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3721" title="leonor" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/leonor_784x02.jpg" alt="" width="784" height="1925" /></a><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3722" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/01originals-scherrer-tmagSF.jpg" alt="" width="362" height="521" /><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3723" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/12760-800w.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="1057" /> </em>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">"</span><em><span style="color: #888888;">Quand je serais mort, je veux un suaire de chez Dior</span></em><span style="color: #888888;">" (Dead, I want a Dior''s shroud), Boris Vian did not know just how true he was.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">It''s going to be called </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">Leonor Funeral Couture</span></strong><span style="color: #888888;"> and it will be the first fashion line dedicated exclusively for funerals.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">The idea came to </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">Leonor Scherrer</span></strong><span style="color: #888888;">, the daughter of the legendary couturier Jean-Louis Sherrer and a muse to </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">Riccardo Tisci</span></strong><span style="color: #888888;">, during the funeral of </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">Yves Saint Laurent</span></strong><span style="color: #888888;">. Not having found a suitable dress for the occasion, the French trend-setter decided to launch an ad hoc collection for the friends and family of those dearly departed.</span>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">"</span></em><em><span style="color: #888888;">Death has become banal"</span></em><span style="color: #888888;">, Scherrer claims. Her ambitious project aimes to restore the dignity, elegance and romanticism once associated with funerals. By doing so, she addresses one of the biggest fears within Western civilization: death. Reviving the funeral as an act of love and key cultural ritual is close to her heart, as well as music, which she is currently devoting herself to. She is recording an album for funeral ceremonies, which she plans on releasing later this fall.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">Inspired by </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">Yves Saint Laurent</span></strong><span style="color: #888888;"> and </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">Claude Montana</span></strong><span style="color: #888888;">, Leonor decided to use a different, famous designer to design a certain number of pieces for each season''s collection. The first to accept was in fact </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">Riccardo Tisci</span></strong><span style="color: #888888;">, who shares Scherrer''s passion for the dark and gothic. Tisci, said of Scherrer, "I''m utterly in love with her. For me, she represents France in all ways: elegance, aristocracy and darkness."</span>', 'La mort vous va si bien/Death becomes Her.', 'It''s going to be called Leonor Funeral Couture and it will be the first fashion line dedicated exclusively for funerals.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'la-mort-vous-va-si-biendeath-becomes-her', '', '', '2010-08-23 18:15:42', '2010-08-23 16:15:42', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3718', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(3733, 6, '2010-08-25 17:03:08', '2010-08-25 15:03:08', '8.25.10. Week#35. Post 2.\n\nParis, fin de l''t... Il fait presque froid. J''irais bien faire les boutiques, envie d''un blouson aviateur comme je l''ai vu chez <strong>Burberry</strong>, envie de peau retourne, tout a parce qu''on m''en a beaucoup mis sous le nez dernirement...Sommes nous, enfin, suis-je si influenable? Je suis limite  appeler ma mre pour savoir ce qu''elle a fait de sa veste en mouton avec laquelle elle venait me chercher  l''cole, la honte... et celle  franges, Mam? Allez, tant que j''y suis!\n\n<em>"L''autorit de la mode est tellement absolue qu''elle nous force  tre ridicule sous peine de le paratre"</em>(<strong>J.Sanial Dubay</strong>), a c''est envoy! <em> </em>\n\n<em>"La mode est une forme de laideur si intolrable, qu''il faut en changer tous les six mois"</em>(<strong>Oscar Wilde</strong>), a me rassure. Mr Wilde me rassure souvent:<em>"La mode est ce que l''on porte. Ce qui est dmod, c''est ce que portent les autres"</em>, so true, tiens: rien que dans le mtro ce matin...\n\n<em>"Il est plus facile de copier que de penser, c''est ce que fait la mode"</em>(<strong>Wallace Stevens</strong>) pensez H&amp;M.\n\n<em>"La finalit de la mode, c''est quand mme de finir  poil!"</em>(anonyme),\n\nVous avez compris l''esprit de ce post, voici quelques unes de mes citations favorites.\n\nMaintenant,  vous: en attendant le <strong>lancement </strong>de notre<strong> site </strong>(encore quelques semaines de patience), nous vous proposons de nous envoyer des citations sur le thme de la mode, en commentaire sur ce blog ou sur notre Fan page sur Facebook.<strong> Jouez </strong>avec <strong>ICU in Paris</strong> et <strong>recevez</strong> un code de rduction de <strong>15% </strong>sur le prix total de votre premire commande!\n\nA vos claviers!<strong> Envoyez trois citations de mode parmi vos prfres et recevez un code de rduc de 15% sur notre site! En franais ou en anglais, comme vous voulez.\n</strong>\n\nImportant: s''il vous plait, n''oubliez pas l''auteur de la citation.<strong>\n</strong>\n\n<em>"La vritable intelligence, c''est quand on arrte de citer d''autres personnes",</em> ah, merde.\n\n(English version below the image)\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3735" title="Oscar Wilde" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/OscarWilde.jpg" alt="" width="317" height="450" />\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">Paris, it almost looks like it''s the end of the summer, cold already, want to shop, need to find myself one of those bomber''s jacket, aviator style like Burberry''s, need suede...just because Fashion magazines have been flooding me with that lately...Are we, sorry, am I that ductile? I am that close to call my Mom and ask her if she still has that horrible lambskin vest she was wearing when she picked me up from school...Shame. And what about the one with the fringes, Mom?</span>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">"The authority of Fashion is so total that it forces us to be ridiculous, at the risk of appearing so"</span></em><span style="color: #888888;">(</span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">J.Sanial Dubay</span></strong><span style="color: #888888;">), well said, my friend.</span>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">"Fashion is a form of ugliness so intolerable, than we have to alter it every six months"</span></em><span style="color: #888888;">(</span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">Oscar Wilde)</span></strong><span style="color: #888888;">, I''m relieved. Mr Wilde is often reassuring me : </span><em><span style="color: #888888;">"Fashion is what you''re wearing. Old-fashionned is what the others are wearing"</span></em><span style="color: #888888;">, so true, well, in the metro this morning for instance...</span><span style="color: #888888;"><a title="Click for further information about this quotation" href="http://www.quotationspage.com/quote/5.html"></a></span>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">"It''s easier to copy than to think, that''s what fashion does"</span></em><span style="color: #888888;">(</span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">Wallace Stevens</span></strong><span style="color: #888888;">) think H&amp;M!</span>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">"Fashion is all about eventually becoming naked"</span></em><span style="color: #888888;"> (anonymous).</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">You get the spirit, these are a couple of my favorites fashion quotes.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">Now it''s your turn : soon our </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">website is going to be launched </span></strong><span style="color: #888888;">(a few weeks of patience), we want you to send us comments on this blog or on our Facebook fanpage with your favorite fashion quote. </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">Play </span></strong><span style="color: #888888;">with </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">ICU in Paris </span></strong><span style="color: #888888;">and recieve a discount code of </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">15% </span></strong><span style="color: #888888;">off your first order on our website.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">Get writing!</span><strong><span style="color: #888888;"> Send at least 3 fashion quotes that you like and recieve a discount of 15% off on our website! English or french, whatever. </span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style="color: #888888;">You may write the quotes in the <em>Comments</em> section of the blog or send us your submission via e-mail to: submissions@icuinparis.com</span></strong>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">Important : Make sure you tell us who you quoted!</span>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">"Real smarts begin when you quit quoting other people"...</span></em><span style="color: #888888;"> duh!</span>', 'Parlons peu, Parlons Mode! / Let&#039;s talk about Fashion!', 'Get writing! Send at least 3 fashion quotes that you like and recieve a discount of 15% off on our website!', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'parlons-peu-parlons-mode-lets-talk-about-fashion', '', '', '2010-08-25 17:03:08', '2010-08-25 15:03:08', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3733', 0, 'post', '', 5),
(3746, 6, '2010-08-27 14:38:40', '2010-08-27 12:38:40', '8.27.10. Week#35. Post 3.\n<p style="text-align: center;">Hier, dans le quartier Montorgueil. Du style et de la hype.</p>\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3747" title="stephane" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/stephane.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="746" />\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Stphane, 35 ans, travaille dans la communication</strong>:\n<strong>Top</strong>: Frost Birgens\n<strong>Bottom</strong>: Frost Birgens\n<strong>Shoes</strong>: Frost Birgens\n<strong>Bag</strong>: Frost Birgens\n<strong>Glasses:</strong> Ray ban\n<strong>Cap:</strong> Vintage</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">A la fois classe et casual, Stphane a tout bon! Le mec a mme un tattoo du surfeur d''argent : on adore!</p>\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3748" title="cecile et edouard" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/cecile-et-edouard.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="746" />\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left; padding-left: 330px;"><strong> Ccile, 23, styliste: </strong><strong>Edouard, 22, comedien:</strong>\n<strong> Top</strong>: H&amp;M<strong> Top:</strong> Urban Outfitters\n<strong>Bottom</strong>: The Kooples              <strong>Vest:</strong> APC\n<strong>Shoes:</strong> UGG <strong>Belt</strong>: Nike\n<strong> Bag:</strong> Balenciaga</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Ccile et Edouard, un vrai couple parisien!</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Anne.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3749" title="Anne" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Anne.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="747" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Anne.jpg"></a><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3750" title="Anne detail" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Anne-detail.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="334" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong> Anne, 21, Hairstylist: </strong>\n<strong>Top:</strong> New look\n<strong>Body:</strong> American Apparel\n<strong>Shoes:</strong> Minnetonka\n<strong>Bag:</strong> Mango\n<strong>Jewels:</strong> H&amp;M</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Dans la rue, on ne voit qu''elle. Mention spciale  sa coiffure et au choix des bijoux.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3751" title="Juliette" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Juliette.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="746" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3752" title="Juliette detail" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Juliette-detail.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="746" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Juliette, 24, Styliste:</strong>\n<strong>Top:</strong> H&amp;M\n<strong>Bottom:</strong> Fendi\n<strong>Bag:</strong> Vintage</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Simple mais efficace,Juliette est mutine. On aime: le sac XXL, piqu  sa mre.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3753" title="Benji" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Benji.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="746" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3754" title="benji dtail" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/benji-dtail.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="334" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Benji, 28, Artiste tatoueur:</strong>\n<strong>Top</strong>: Urban outfitters\n<strong>Bottom:</strong> Levi''s\n<strong>Shoes</strong>: Rossignol\n<strong>Cap:</strong> Lafayette homme</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Le mec est simplement styl. Un T-shirt, un jean, un air de Titi parisien et surtout des tattoos hauts en couleurs!</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3755" title="Rose" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Rose.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="746" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3756" title="rose detail" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/rose-detail.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="334" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Rose, 26, artiste:</strong>\n<strong>Top:</strong> vintage\n<strong>Bottom:</strong> DIY\n<strong>Shoes: </strong>vintage\n<strong>Vest:</strong> vintage</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Une trs jolie frimousse, une lumire d''orage dans ses cheveux roux, et un sens d''accommoder le vintage en total look!</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3757" title="Nick" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Nick.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="746" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nick, 28, Tatoueur.</strong>\n<strong>Top:</strong> vintage\n<strong>Bottom:</strong> levi''s\n<strong>Hat:</strong> Vintage</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Encore un tatou, mais dcidment quel style! J''adore la chemise. Nick pose pour nous dans le fameux salon <a href="http://www.artcorptattoo.com/" target="_blank">d''Artcorpus</a> de la rue Greneta.</p>', 'Paris street style', 'paris street style', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'paris-street-style-3', '', '', '2010-08-27 14:38:40', '2010-08-27 12:38:40', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3746', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(3763, 4, '2010-08-27 17:11:52', '2010-08-27 15:11:52', '8.27.10. Week#35. Post 4.\n\nJust a sneak peak into the soon to be ICU world of jewelry and accessories. It has been quite some time we have been working on the new site - gearing up, brainstorming, organizing and creating one big platform for a truly creative and innovative shopping experience.\n\nWith 6 homepage styles to shop from and a submission opportunity for creative professionals, the site is not only a place to find the most unique designs on the market, but also a hub for photographers, bloggers, illustrators, and designers to showcase their products and work.\n\nIn anticipation... a bientt  Septembre.\n\n<span style="color: #888888;"><em>ICU - In Paris Street Style Homepage:</em></span>\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/3RD-STREET-STYLE-HOMEPAGE.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-3777 alignnone" title="3RD STREET STYLE HOMEPAGE" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/3RD-STREET-STYLE-HOMEPAGE-1024x754.jpg" alt="" width="819" height="603" /></a>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #888888;"><em><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-style: normal;">\n</span></span></em></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #888888;"><em>ICU - In Paris Submission Page:</em></span></p>\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/designer-submission-page.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-3779 alignnone" title="designer submission page" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/designer-submission-page-978x1024.jpg" alt="" width="782" height="819" /></a>', 'It&#039;s an ICU - Sneak peek...', 'ICU - In Paris Sneak Peek... Website launch for September 2010', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'its-an-icu-sneak-peek', '', '', '2010-08-27 17:11:52', '2010-08-27 15:11:52', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3763', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(3861, 4, '2010-08-31 19:36:30', '2010-08-31 17:36:30', '8.31.10. Week#36. Post 1.\n\n<a href="http://shop.bjorgjewellery.com/Default.aspx?tabid=129&amp;List=0" target="_blank"><img id="dnn_dnnLOGO_imgLogo" style="border-width: 0px;" src="http://shop.bjorgjewellery.com/Portals/0/Bjorg_images/logo.gif" alt="http://shop.bjorgjewellery.com" /></a> &amp; the Cocoon Saloon.\n\nLovin'' this designer out of Norway. A collection for each inspiration... cocoon saloon, aquatic attic, coopers cave, forest, heartbeat, memento magicka... it goes on.\n\nThe designs are raw and elegant - simple and distraught - classic and unique. Like I said, I''m very much loving them.\n\nPictures please. And <a href="http://shop.bjorgjewellery.com/Default.aspx?tabid=129&amp;List=0" target="_blank">here</a> you can visit the site to see more.\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/2929.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3862" title="bjorg" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/2929.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="600" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/3321.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3863" title="bjorg" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/3321.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="600" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/3497.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3864" title="bjorg" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/3497.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="600" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/3706.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3865" title="bjorg" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/3706.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="600" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/3733.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3866" title="bjorg" src="https://www.ic