(3872, 6, '2010-09-01 18:39:47', '2010-09-01 16:39:47', '<div><script type="text/javascript">// <![CDATA[\n	$(document).ready(function(){\n       $( ''#txt a.lightbox'').lightBox({\n			imageLoading: ''http://www.actualitte.com/style/gfx/loading.gif'',\n			imageBtnClose: ''http://www.actualitte.com/style/gfx/close.gif'',\n			imageBtnPrev: ''http://www.actualitte.com/style/gfx/prev.gif'',\n			imageBtnNext: ''http://www.actualitte.com/style/gfx/next.gif''\n	   });\n\n    });\n// ]]></script><strong> </strong></div>\n<div>9.1.10. Week#36. Post 2.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div><strong>L''artiste plasticien japonais Takashi Murakami  va exposer ses oeuvres dans les appartements royaux du Chteau de  Versailles du 14 septembre au 12 dcembre 2010.</strong></div>\n<div><strong>\n</strong></div>\n<div>Aprs celles de Jeff Koons et de Xavier Veilhan, ce sont les uvres du Japonais Takashi Murakami  qui font frissonner Versailles. A quelques jours de l''inauguration, les voix ne cessent de s''lever: plusieurs associations s''insurgent et ptitionnent contre l''exposition.</div>\n<div>L''association "<a href="http://www.versailles-mon-amour.fr/" target="_blank">Versailles, mon amour</a>" adresse une lettre au ministre de la culture (allez lire, c''est marrant.)</div>\n<div>\n<blockquote>NON! A la provocation de l''art contemporain qui ne  respecte rien.\n\nNon au choc des cultures qui brise l''harmonie: les bandes dessines  de Murakami peuvent (ventuellement) avoir leur place  L''Orangerie  Mais en aucun cas au chteau de Versailles; le chteau n''est pas un  panneau Decaux mais l''un des symboles de notre Histoire et de notre  culture.</blockquote>\n</div>\nUn des points sur lesquels les opposants  l''exposition s''appuient est  le ct trop os de certaines crations comme celles intitules <em> My  lonesome cow boy</em>  et <em>Hiropon</em> .  propos de ces deux  crations prcisment, Anne Brassi de Versailles mon amour s''insurge:  <em>Le petit bonhomme au sexe point dont le jet de sperme forme un  lasso, la petite bonne femme aux gros seins dont le jet de lait forme  une corde  sauter n''ont rien  faire dans les appartements royaux</em> .\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3873" title="Takashi-Murakami" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/Takashi-Murakami-art.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="360" />\n\nD''ailleurs, aux dernires nouvelles et selon le prsident de l''tablissement public du Chteau de Versailles,  Jean-Jacques Aillagon, ces uvres ne feront pas parties de l''exposition.\n\nAlors, d''accord, je suis pas forcment une grande fan d''art contemporain et de la rcente politique de Versailles qui consiste  balancer de l''artiste bankable au vu et au su de pauvres touristes dont le seul dsir, aprs s''tre tap du RER C pour les plus courageux, est de se prendre en photo dans la galerie des glaces. Parce que croyez moi, c''est la seule chose qu''ils veulent. Comme au Louvre, la Joconde. a, et surtout rien d''autre. Le Da Vinci code,  la rigueur...\n\nMais, je m''gare. Ce que je veux dire c''est que, appelez moi candide, mais ce que je recherche dans une exposition, c''est de me prendre une claque quelle qu''elle soit. L, je dis OK.\n\nUn champignon magique dans la chambre du Roi, Bam.\n\nDes marguerites hallucines dans la galerie des glaces, Boum.\n\nUne tartine de doigts en aller-retour, des cools photos de moi les deux pouces levs devant Versailles  mettre sur FB et une occasion de rentabiliser mon pass navigo, voil 3 bonnes raisons d''aller voir cette expo.\n\nA consulter: <a href="http://www.chateauversailles.fr/les-actualites-du-domaine/evenements/evenements/expositions/murakami-versailles" target="_blank">la lettre de l''artiste</a>.\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">(English version below the images</span></em><span style="color: #888888;">)</span>\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3874" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/loadResourceDocu.jpg" alt="" width="579" height="427" />\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3879" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/image-42-380x318.png" alt="" width="380" height="318" />\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3880" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/image-24-380x570.png" alt="" width="380" height="570" />\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3881" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/image-51-380x480.png" alt="" width="380" height="480" />\n\n<strong><span style="color: #888888;">The Japanese artist </span></strong><strong><span style="color: #888888;">Takashi Murakami is going to exhibit his work at Versailles, in the Royal''s appartements from the 14 of september to the 12 of december.</span></strong>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">After Jeff Koons and Xavier Veilhan, here comes Takashi Murakami to make the castle quiver. A few days before the Grand opening, associations are rising up and advertise petitions against the exhibition. The association "</span><a href="http://www.versailles-mon-amour.fr/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #888888;">Versailles,  mon amour</span></a><span style="color: #888888;">" even wrote a letter to the Culture minister.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">They are especially offended by the pornographic side of the following work : </span><em><span style="color: #888888;"> My  lonesome cow boy</span></em><span style="color: #888888;">  and  </span><em><span style="color: #888888;">Hiropon</span></em><span style="color: #888888;"> . Anne Brassier from "versailles mon amour" protests :  </span><em><span style="color: #888888;">the little guy who''s playing with his sperm jet like a lasso and the little girl with big breast who''s playing with her mother''s milk like a skipping rope have nothing to do with the Royal appartements</span></em><span style="color: #888888;"> .</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">Apparently, those works are not even on display</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">So, ok, I''m not a big fan of contemporary art, neither of the new policy of Versailles, that consists in putting on display bankable artist for the poor tourist, who only want to take a picture of the "galerie des glaces", because, believe me, that''s the only thing they want to do.Like in the Louvre, the Joconde. That, and nothing else. The Da Vinci code, at a pinch.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">but, I''m getting off the subject. What I want to say is, call me naive, but, the only thing I''m expecting of an exhibition, is a slap in my face, for whatever reason.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">A giant magic mushroom in the king''s bedroom, bang!</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">Hallucinated daisys in the galerie des glaces, bam!</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">A head spin, cool pics of me, thumbs up in front of the castle and a to secure a return of my transit pass, there are three good reasons to go to see this exhibition.</span>', 'Versailles, amour et Rock&#039;n Roll', 'The Japanese artist Takashi Murakami is going to exhibit his work at Versailles, in the Royal''s appartements from the  14 of september to the 12 of december.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'versailles-amour-et-rockn-roll', '', '', '2010-09-01 18:39:47', '2010-09-01 16:39:47', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3872', 0, 'post', '', 3),
(3889, 4, '2010-09-02 20:25:31', '2010-09-02 18:25:31', '9.2.2010. Week #36. Post 3.\n\n<a href="http://www.plateformag.com/Numero-21.html" target="_blank">PLATEFORM magazine</a>\n\nNous sommes unePLATEFORM.\nUnePLATEFORMen ligne. UnePLATEFORMdexpression. CettePLATEFORMmontre et dmontre que le talent prend beaucoup de formes.\nPLATEFORMnest pas unmagazinede mode.\nPLATEFORMnest pas unmagazinedart.\nPLATEFORMnest pas unmagazinedinformation.\nPLATEFORMest unmagazinepour exposer, sexposer, se raconter et raconter.\nPLATEFORMouvre le regard et souvre aux talents.\nPLATEFORMapporte une double vision sur un thme, un lieu, une motion, une ide.\nPLATEFORMest simplement diffrent parce que la cration prend beaucoup de formes.\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">English Translation: </span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">PLATEFORM magazine</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">We are a PLATEFORM.\nAn online PLATEFORM. A PLATEFORM of expression. This PLATEFORM shows and reveals that talent takes many shapes.\nPLATEFORM isnt a fashion magazine.\nPLATEFORM isnt an art magazine.\nPLATEFORM isnt a media magazine.\nPLATEFORM is a magazine to exhibit, to set forth, to discover oneself and to describe.\nPLATEFORM opens up eyes and is open to talents.\nPLATEFORM gives a dual vision on a subject, a place, an emotion, an idea.\nPLATEFORM is simply different because creation takes many shapes.</span>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://www.plateformag.com/local/cache-vignettes/L400xH283/3609880479_64ba2c3704_o-4018c.png" alt="" width="400" height="283" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter" style="height: 284px; width: 400px;" src="http://www.plateformag.com/local/cache-vignettes/L400xH284/3609879729_0381f5fa80_o-147dd.png" alt="" width="400" height="284" /><img style="height: 284px; width: 400px;" src="http://www.plateformag.com/local/cache-vignettes/L400xH284/3609879391_5e5a95c59c_o-c34cd.png" alt="" width="400" height="284" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img style="height: 283px; width: 400px;" src="http://www.plateformag.com/local/cache-vignettes/L400xH283/3610692958_baf3985a84_o-401ea.png" alt="" width="400" height="283" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n<img class="aligncenter" style="height: 284px; width: 400px;" src="http://www.plateformag.com/local/cache-vignettes/L400xH284/3610692536_6ff077ceea_o-ef7d7.png" alt="" width="400" height="284" /><img class="aligncenter" style="height: 284px; width: 400px;" src="http://www.plateformag.com/local/cache-vignettes/L400xH284/3609880863_d6cde7cbcb_o-43d21.png" alt="" width="400" height="284" /><img src="http://www.plateformag.com/local/cache-vignettes/L400xH283/3609880627_ed4c6e0423_o-36b14.png" alt="" width="400" height="283" /><img class="aligncenter" style="height: 284px; width: 400px;" src="http://www.plateformag.com/local/cache-vignettes/L400xH284/3690622344_4c9f96d9ba_o-de043.png" alt="" width="400" height="284" /><img style="height: 283px; width: 400px;" src="http://www.plateformag.com/local/cache-vignettes/L400xH283/3896074609_be5ef2b402_o-930b5.png" alt="" width="400" height="283" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://www.plateformag.com/local/cache-vignettes/L400xH283/3990408012_ea5571b341_o-1f031.png" alt="" width="400" height="283" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="spip_logos" style="height: 283px; width: 400px;" src="http://www.plateformag.com/local/cache-vignettes/L400xH283/arton55-2ed12.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="283" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n\n\nThis is an online publication which I was lucky enough to learn about grace of <a href="http://laurenceguenoun.com/" target="_self">Laurence Guenoun</a> an incredible photographer (view the ICU &amp; Guenoun photo shoot <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2009/11/23/photo-shoot-i-c-u-in-paris/" target="_blank">HERE</a>) as well as one of the creators/contributors/founders of PLATEFORM magazine. As they have perfectly described on their own, this is a <em><span style="color: #888888;">An online PLATEFORM. A PLATEFORM of expression. This PLATEFORM shows and reveals that talent takes many shapes.</span></em>\n\nCurrently only available on the internet feeding and inspiring the senses quite efficiently - PLATEFORM showcases work from artists, photographers, designers, illustrators... from all around the world and does so without losing the touch of any originality or authenticity.\n\nThe current issue is available to view now - plus all the others which have been published through out the year. Its a simple subscription and maybe a <a href="http://www.facebook.com/plateformag?ref=ts" target="_blank">Facebook like</a> to support the efforts and works of the individuals involved in this awesome creation.\n\nBelow - <a href="http://issuu.com/plateform/docs/issues_n21?mode=embed&amp;layout=http%3A%2F%2Fskin.issuu.com%2Fv%2Flight%2Flayout.xml&amp;showFlipBtn=true" target="_blank">ISSUE 210910</a>\n\n<img src="http://i229.photobucket.com/albums/ee272/candicemimi/21.jpg" border="0" alt="PLATEFORM Magazine" width="640" height="451" />\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.plateformag.com/Numero-21.html" target="_blank">More PLATEFORM magazine here</a></p>', 'PLATEFORM MAGAZINE. Not your average publication.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'plateform-magazine-not-your-average-publication', '', '', '2010-09-02 20:25:31', '2010-09-02 18:25:31', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=3889', 0, 'post', '', 4),
