(4047, 6, '2010-09-21 15:27:41', '2010-09-21 13:27:41', '9.21.2010. Week #39. Post 1.\n\nLe samedi 25 et le dimanche 26 septembre,<a href="http://www.salonduvintage.com/" target="_blank"> le salon du vintage</a> investit l''espace des Blancs Manteaux, 48 rue vieille du temple, dans le IV arrondissement  Paris.\n\nSur une surface deux fois plus importante que la prcdente dition, plus de 8O exposants, marchands et spcialistes du design, de la mode et des accessoires vous accueillent dans cet ancien march couvert, de 10h  19 h ce week end.\n\nPhotos du salon de l''anne prcdente:\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">On saturday 25 and sunday 26 of september," le salon du vintage" is going to take place in "Les Blancs Manteaux", 48 rue vieille du temple, in the IV district in Paris.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">With twice as much area than last year, more than 80 exhibitors, merchants and design/ fashion specialists, this week end in le marais...</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">Last year''s pictures:</span>\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4048" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/salon-vintage-20101.jpg" alt="" width="387" height="558" />\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="size-full wp-image-4049 aligncenter" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/100410103548517285801519.jpg" alt="" width="567" height="379" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4050" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/100410103548517285801523.jpg" alt="" width="512" height="765" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4051" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/phoca_thumb_l_SalonVintagePentax04.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="600" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4052" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/phoca_thumb_l_SalonVintagePentax35.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="600" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>', 'Salon du vintage, this weekend!', 'Le samedi 25 et le dimanche 26 septembre, le salon du vintage investit l''espace des Blancs Manteaux, 48 rue vieille du temple, dans le IV arrondissement  Paris.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'salon-du-vintage-this-week-end', '', '', '2010-09-21 15:27:41', '2010-09-21 13:27:41', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=4047', 0, 'post', '', 3),
(4058, 6, '2010-09-23 19:36:41', '2010-09-23 17:36:41', '9.23.2010. Week #39. Post 2.\n\nPour faire honneur au thme de la semaine,voici une petite slection d''adresses vintages  Paris, par quartier...Allez les filles, on s'' promne !\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">This week is vintage, we tell you. Here you can find a small selection of my favorite vintage shop in Paris, go, girls!</span></em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><span style="color: #888888;">_______________________________________</span></em></p>\n\n<h6 style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="color: #993366;">ANVERS/BARBES/MONTMARTRE</span></strong></h6>\nOn commence par le plus dur: <strong>Guerissol</strong>. Ouais, parce qu''une fois que vous aurez fouill dans le bac des "bonnes affaires" de cette boutique et que vous vous serez fait perfor un tympan par un des vendeurs sourds et muets, vous serez prtes  affronter n''importe quelle autre friperie de Paris. C''est un peu comme un rituel d''initiation. Guerissol, mais pas n''importe lequel. <strong>Guerissol 4</strong>. Les autres, trop hardcrore, trust me.\n\nIci vous trouverez de tout  " peu prs" bas prix. J''annonce tout de suite que les bonnes affaires sont rares, mais c''est l qu''on s''affute l''il...il faut savoir apprendre  chercher, sinon, on va  Killiwatch et c''est plus la peine de lire ce post.\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">Let''s start with the most difficult, </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">Guerissol</span></strong><span style="color: #888888;">. Because, once you''ve been there, you can handle any second hand shop in Paris. It''s loud and dirty.But you have to go, it''s like a hazing. You want to go in </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">Guerissol 4</span></strong><span style="color: #888888;">, the others are too hardcore, croyez-moi.</span></em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">It''s a rag-bag of everything and it''s cheap. I''ll make no secret about it : good deals are pretty rare, but you need to learn how to dig! Otherwise you go to Killiwatch and you stop reading this post.</span></em>\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4059" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/102.jpg" alt="" width="448" height="336" />\n\n&nbsp;\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>17, Boulevard de Rochechouart\n75 009 PARIS. Ouvert 7/7 de 10h  19h.</strong></p>\n\n<h4></h4>\n<p style="text-align: center;">_______________________________________</p>\nUn peu plus loin dans le mme coin, deux boutiques magnifiques. <strong><a href="http://www.mamie-vintage.com/" target="_blank">Mamie</a></strong> et <strong><a href="http://www.mamie-vintage.com/" target="_self">Mamie Blue</a></strong>. L, on ne joue pas dans la mme cour. La slection est trs pointue, les prix aussi. Mamie et Mamie Blue sont les adresses prfres des costumiers, des collectionneurs, stylistes et dnicheurs de bonnes affaires. Sur leurs 3 tages, Mamie et Mamie Blue entassent les fringues, les bijoux, les bibelots et les chaussures, des annes 30  80.\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">In the same street, you''ll find two beautiful shops. </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;"><a href="http://www.mamie-vintage.com/" target="_self">Mamie</a></span></strong><span style="color: #888888;"> and </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;"><a href="http://www.mamie-vintage.com/" target="_self">Mamie Blue</a></span></strong><span style="color: #888888;">. There, we''re not on the same league. The selection is very sharp, prices too. On 3 floors, you''ll find a selection of stunning vintage jewels, costumes, shoes and accessories from the 30''s to the 80''s.</span></em>\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4060" title="mamie" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/mamie.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="364" />\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>73 Rue de Rochechouart\n69 Rue de Rochechouart. 75009</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>lundi et samedi\n15h00 - 20h00</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>du mardi au vendredi\n11h00  13h30\net\n15h00  20h00</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">_______________________________________</span></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">\n</span></strong></p>\nVers Montmartre,"<strong><a href="http://www.tombeesducamion.com/" target="_blank">Tombes du camion</a></strong>" porte bien son nom. Ici, vous trouverez tout plein d''accessoires pour vous et votre intrieur : de la lampe rtro en passant par des boutons, des bracelets, des perles... le propritaire des lieux rcupre les stocks invendus des usines qui ferment ou qui font faillite mais aussi tout ce qui n''a pas trouv preneur et qui fera peut-tre votre bonheur ! Une vraie mine d''or pour les accros de la rcup'' et du vintage.\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">Next to Montmartre, "</span><strong><span style="color: #888888;"><a href="http://www.tombeesducamion.com/" target="_blank">Tombes du camion</a></span></strong><span style="color: #888888;">", (Fell off the back of a lorry) its name fits pretty well. There you can find a lot of accessories for you and your home. The owner picks up dead stocks from factories and also vintage lots. A true gold mine!</span></em>\n<div><strong><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4061" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/tombeeducamion.jpg" alt="" width="320" height="169" />\n</strong></div>\n<div style="text-align: center;"><strong>17 rue Joseph de Maistre</strong></div>\n<div style="text-align: center;"><strong>75018 Paris</strong></div>\n<div style="text-align: center;"><strong>Du lundi au vendredi : de 13h  20h</strong></div>\n<div style="text-align: center;"><strong>Du samedi au dimanche : de 11h  20h</strong></div>\n<div style="text-align: center;"><strong>_______________________________________</strong></div>\n<h6 style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="color: #993366;">BASTILLE/RPUBLIQUE</span></strong></h6>\n<div><strong>\n</strong></div>\n<div><strong> </strong>On commence par <strong>Adm</strong>, boutique sympa, toute petite mais bien range. Bonne adresse pour les chaussures, les bottes en bon tat et les best du moment. Une autre boutique homme en face.</div>\n<div><em>\n</em></div>\n<div><em><span style="color: #888888;">This nice shop </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">Adm</span></strong><span style="color: #888888;"> is very small but clean and tidy. A good place for shoes and boots especially, in good shape. Another shop for men in the same street.</span></em></div>\n<div><em><span style="color: #888888;">\n</span></em></div>\n<div><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4062" title="adom" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/adom.jpg" alt="" width="250" height="165" /></div>\n<div style="text-align: center;"><strong>56 et 35 rue de la Roquette 75011</strong></div>\n<div style="text-align: center;"><strong>Lundi au samedi 11h-20h Dimanche 15h-20h</strong></div>\n<div style="text-align: center;"><strong>_______________________________________</strong></div>\nDans le mme quartier<strong>, Come on Eileen</strong> est une vritable caverne d''Ali Baba spcialise dans les annes 60/70. On ne peut qu''y trouver son bonheur: le sous sol est incroyable et il y en a pour toutes les bourses. Belle slection.\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">I</span></em><em><span style="color: #888888;">n the same neighbourhood, </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">Come on Eileen</span></strong><span style="color: #888888;"> is a true Ali Baba''s cave, specialized in the 60''s/70''s. It''s impossible not to find something that will pleases you. The basement is amazing. beautiful selection.</span></em>\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4063" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/15330110_p.jpg" alt="" width="338" height="450" />\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>16 rue des Taillandiers\n75011 Paris\nDu mardi au vendredi de 11h00  20h30\nLe samedi de 14h00  20h00.</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">_______________________________________</p>\nUne petite nouvelle, difficile  trouver, mais qui vaut le dtour. <strong><a href="http://www.thanxgod.com" target="_blank">Thanx god, I''m a VIP</a></strong>. Elle fait  la fois du vintage et de la fripe, le rayon fripe ntant ouvert que le week-end en sous-sol. Les prix sont raisonnables pour le vintage et ne dpassent pas 5-10 pour les fripes. Rang par couleurs pour le vintage avec des pices exceptionnelles.\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">A new shop, a little hidden, but worth it. </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;"><a href="http://www.thanxgod.com" target="_blank">Thanx god, I''m a VIP</a>.</span></strong><span style="color: #888888;"> There you can find vintage and second-hand. For second-hand, in the basement, it''s only on week ends. Price are reasonnable, with stunning pieces.</span></em>\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4064" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/Thx-god-im-a-vip1.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="300" />\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>12 Rue de Lancry 75010</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>(horaires ??)</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>_______________________________________</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>\n</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Pas trs trs loin de l''autre ct de rpublique, un truc marrant et vintage, pour les nostalgiques des photomatons 4 flashs, 4 grimaces, 4 souvenirs,... la nouvelle boutique <strong>Bonton </strong>a eu la jolie ide d''installer une cabine argentique des annes 60.<em>4 photomatons : 2 </em></p>\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">Not really far, on the other side of rpublique, a funny thing to do, for the most nostalgic of you: the vintage photo booth from the 60''s! let''s meet at the </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">Bonton</span></strong><span style="color: #888888;"> shop!</span>\n</em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em> </em><strong>5 boulevard des filles du calvaire\n75003 paris\n01 42 72 34 69\nLundi au samedi de 10 h  19 h</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">_______________________________________</span></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">\n</span></strong></p>\nUn ovni de boutique, un univers incroyable, vous en prendrez pleins les yeux, mais vous n''y achterez rien (enfin, a dpend de votre bourse), mais vous ne pouvez pas ne pas y aller... je veux parler de <strong>MERCI</strong>... une petite merveille au fond d''une cour, on ose  peine y rentrer.<strong> </strong>\n\nImagin par Marie-France et Bernard Cohen, dj connus comme tant les fondateurs de la marque de vtement pour enfants Bonpoint,<strong> Merci </strong>est un concept philanthropique novateur. Les bnfices raliss dans le magasin seront reverss  un fond de dotation, qui se donne pour mission daider les enfants dfavoriss, notamment sur lle de Madagascar.\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">An incredible and beautiful place to go. </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;">MERCI</span></strong><span style="color: #888888;">\n</span> </em>\n<div>\n<div>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">Bernard and Marie-France Cohen (the couple behind the luxury childrens clothing brand Bonpoint) now introduce the newest Parisian wonderland.The designer corner cradles pieces created especially for the store: all profits are re-funneled into a childrens charity in Madagascar.</span></em>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-4070" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/Merci+Boutique++001-243x300.jpg" alt="" width="243" height="300" />\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/merci-parisian-concept-store-1-600x399.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-4084" title="merci-parisian-concept-store-1-600x399" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/merci-parisian-concept-store-1-600x399-300x199.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="199" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/merci-parisian-concept-store-600x400.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-4085" title="merci-parisian-concept-store-600x400" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/merci-parisian-concept-store-600x400-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>111 boulevard Beaumarchais 75003</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Lundi-Samedi 10h/19h</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">_______________________________________</p>\n\n<h6 style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="color: #993366;">ETIENNE MARCEL</span></strong></h6>\nBon,alors, je fais l''impasse sur <a href="http://espacekiliwatch.fr/" target="_blank">Killiwatch</a>, vous l''aurez compris. Trop cher, trop de bruit, trop de BB brunes, blondes, rousses...\n\nPar contre, une adresse pas trop mal... <a href="http://www.episode.eu/" target="_blank">EPISODE</a> que j''ai en fait dcouvert  Amsterdam l''anne dernire. Le travail est prmach, tout est bien rang, presque trop. Il y a un peu un"effet de masse" qui gche le plaisir de fouiller. Une chemise liberty? chouette, mais 500 chemises liberty... bah, en fait t''en as plus envie. Mais bon, a vaut quand mme le coup d''y passer.\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">A" not so bad" place to go, if you''re in the neighbourhood, a little bit to clean and to tidy, wich, for me, waste the pleasure to dig, but it''s still a good place... </span><strong><span style="color: #888888;"><a href="http://www.episode.eu/" target="_blank">EPISODE</a></span></strong></em><span style="color: #888888;">.</span>\n\n<span style="color: #888888;">\n</span>\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4065" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/Episode1.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="300" />\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10-16 Rue de Tiquetonne 75002</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>lundi 13:00 / 20:00\nmardi-vendredi 11:30/19:30\nSamedi 11:00/20:00</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>_______________________________________</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>\n</strong></p>\nDans la mme rue, pour les amateurs de montres, il y a la petite boutique <strong>"<a href="http://www.chezmaman.fr/en" target="_blank">Chez maman</a></strong><strong>"</strong>, comme a aprs<strong> "chez mamie"</strong>, vous aurez fait toute la famille. De belle pices vintage, casio et autres stars des annes 80.\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">In the same street, for watch amateur, there''s a little shop called "<a href="http://www.chezmaman.fr/en" target="_blank">Chez maman</a>". Nice vintage casio and others pieces from the 80''s.</span></em>\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4066" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/CHEZMAMAN6.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="402" />\n<p style="text-align: center;">4, rue Tiquetonne 75002</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">lundi-samedi 11H/20H</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">_______________________________________</p>\n\n<h6 style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="color: #993366;">LE MARAIS</span></strong></h6>\nDans le marais, une foultitude de bonnes adresse vintages...En voici quelques unes.\n\n<strong><a href="http://www.freepstar.com/" target="_self">Free p'' Star</a></strong>est un classique.Une enseigne/2 boutiques. Mais si je dois vous en conseiller une, a serait plutt la seconde (Verrerie) car l''accueil y est plus chaleureux et le choix beaucoup plus vaste. A noter, ouverte le dimanche jusqu'' tard!\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">In le marais, a lot of good adresses:</span></em>\n\n<em><strong><span style="color: #888888;"><a href="http://www.freepstar.com/" target="_blank">Free p''Star</a></span></strong><span style="color: #888888;"> is a classic. 2 shops, but I prefer the second one (la verrerie). Open on sundays till late!</span></em>\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4067" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/freepstar2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="222" />\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 Rue Sainte Croix de la Bretonnerie 75004</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Lundi-samedi 12h-22h / Dimanche 14h-22h</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>61 Rue de la Verrerie 75004</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Lundi-samedi 11h-21h / Dimanche 14h-21h</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>_______________________________________</strong></p>\nDans le mme secteur, une trs jolie boutique, la friperie <strong>Vintage dsir</strong>, avec de belles pices, surtout pour les sacs et accessoires.\n\n<em><strong><span style="color: #888888;">Vintage dsir</span></strong><span style="color: #888888;"> is a good place for bags and accessories.</span></em>\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4068" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/4.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="320" />\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>32 rue des rosiers 75004</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Lundi-vendredi 11H/22H</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>_______________________________________</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>\n</strong></p>\nUn peu plus loin, plus de fun, avec la boutique<strong> </strong><strong><a href="http://www.poidsnetparis.com/culotte/" target="_blank">Culotte</a></strong>:\n\nCe que vous y trouverez sont principalement des bijoux, accessoires et quelques vtements. Tout est ralis  la main, par la cratrice japonaise de la boutique, Minako Ito ou par d''autres crateurs. Elle chine beaucoup d''objets  partir desquels elle fait ses bijoux. Cest un vrai bonheur de passer ses yeux sur les tagres, il y a tellement de dtails. Allez-y avec du temps devant vous!\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">This shop</span><strong><span style="color: #888888;"> <a href="http://www.poidsnetparis.com/culotte/" target="_blank">Culotte</a></span></strong><span style="color: #888888;"> is a lot of fun! Everything is hand crafted by the designer Minako Ito or by her friend designers. It''s a true pleasure !</span></em>\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/29622977.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-4069" title="29622977" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/29622977-225x300.jpg" alt="" width="225" height="300" /></a>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 rue malher 75004 Paris</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Lundi 13h30-17h</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Mardi-vendredi 12h30-19h</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Dimanche 14h-19h</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>_______________________________________</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>\n</strong></p>\nVoil, alors, on enfile une bonne paire de converse et on arpente les rues de Paris,  la recherche de la perle rare.\n\nSans oublier le salon du Vintage ce week end (voir post prcdent).\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">There you go, now you can shop vintage in Paris! And don''t forget the "Salon du vintage" this week end <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/09/21/salon-du-vintage-this-week-end/" target="_blank">(see last post)</a>.</span></em>\n\n<em>\n</em>\n<div><strong>\n</strong></div>', 'Hot Paris vintage boutique tips!', 'Hot vintage tips!', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hot-vintage-tips', '', '', '2010-09-23 19:36:41', '2010-09-23 17:36:41', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=4058', 0, 'post', '', 3),
(4079, 4, '2010-09-24 14:49:58', '2010-09-24 12:49:58', '9.24.2010. Week #39. Post 3.\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter" title="mod_article1698383_2" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/mod_article1698383_2.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="520" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n\n<h6 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #ff00ff;"><a href="http://evamode.eklablog.com/" target="_blank">Welcome to Chez Eva. </a></span></h6>\n<p style="text-align: center;">I had the pleasure of meeting Eva, obviously the owner of <a href="http://evamode.eklablog.com/" target="_blank">Le Dressing d''Eva</a> at the casting for the <a href="http://www.emoi-emoi.com/" target="_blank">moi-moi</a> photo shoot which ICU styled. Eva was gracious enough to lend us some vintage pieces for the shoot which came out superb and since then I can''t seem to keep my wallet away from her newly opened boutique.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">A connoisseur of vintage and the history behind each piece, Eva will tell you where each piece came from, it''s year, what inspired each designer and how to care for the piece in order to keep its longevity.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">The boutique is adorable. Quaint. Comfortable and has no odor of vintage at all! A small dressing room in the corner and two red plch lounge chairs make you feel as if you are at home rather than a boutique on the side streets of Paris.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">This is a must visit vintage. And plus, you don''t want to miss the ravishing Eva either - she is an unforgettable delight.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n[gallery link="file" columns="2" orderby="rand"]\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/mod_article1698383_2.jpg"></a>\n<p style="text-align: auto;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">And here is Ms. Eva - photo credits for <a href="http://www.emoi-emoi.com/" target="_blank">moi-moi</a>.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">And yes, she is pregnant and close to the end so hurry to the shop before it''s doors close temporarily for the birth of l''enfant </p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/eva-it-mom-emoi-emoi-enceinte-de-7-mois-2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4112" title="eva-it-mom-emoi-emoi-enceinte-de-7-mois-2" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/eva-it-mom-emoi-emoi-enceinte-de-7-mois-2.jpg" alt="" width="515" height="385" /></a><img title="gallery columns=&quot;2&quot; orderby=&quot;rand&quot;" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-includes/js/tinymce/plugins/wpgallery/img/t.gif" alt="" /></p>', 'Ms. Eva, nous t&#039;adorons  ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ms-eva-nous-tadorons-%e2%99%a1', '', '', '2010-09-24 14:49:58', '2010-09-24 12:49:58', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=4079', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(4122, 4, '2010-09-24 16:33:57', '2010-09-24 14:33:57', '9.24.2010. Week #39. Post 4.\n\nIn honor of the week''s theme for Paris Vintage and of course Paris''s <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2010/09/21/salon-du-vintage-this-week-end/" target="_blank">Salon du Vintage</a> this coming weekend, we figured we would take a look back from past street style finds and showcase the best of the best in vintage style. Enjoy \n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Click on Images to see full view.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n[gallery link="file" orderby="rand"]\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>', 'Paris Street Vintage Style ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'paris-street-vintage-style', '', '', '2010-09-24 16:33:57', '2010-09-24 14:33:57', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=4122', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(4149, 6, '2010-09-28 13:51:52', '2010-09-28 11:51:52', '9.28.2010. Week #40. Post 1.\n\nIt''s about Designer Inspiration this week. And what a perfect way to start it off with Mr. Crangi himself - also known as Giles&amp;Brother. In 2008 Crangi was the CFDA<em>Swarovski Award</em> Accessories winner and he has not slowed down since then.\n\nIn the film below, Crangi tells us the story of his brand, his inspirations and explains the secret of his growing success...\n\nCredit for article towards: <a href="http://www.businessoffashion.com/" target="_blank">Business of Fashion blog</a>\n\n<strong><span style="color: #ff9900;">New Crangi pieces available in the </span><span style="color: #ff9900;"><a href="http://www.icuinparis.com/eshop/index.php/newarrivals.html" target="_blank">ICU boutique</a></span><span style="color: #ff9900;"><a href="http://www.icuinparis.com/eshop/index.php/newarrivals.html" target="_blank"> </a>now!</span></strong>\n\n<strong>\n</strong>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="635" height="358" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=14427871&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=1&amp;show_byline=1&amp;show_portrait=1&amp;color=00ADEF&amp;fullscreen=1&amp;autoplay=0&amp;loop=0" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="635" height="358" src="http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=14427871&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=1&amp;show_byline=1&amp;show_portrait=1&amp;color=00ADEF&amp;fullscreen=1&amp;autoplay=0&amp;loop=0" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"></embed></object>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://vimeo.com/14427871">"Our Story"</a> from <a href="http://vimeo.com/user4458305">The Little Squares</a> on <a href="http://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<strong>NEW YORK, United States </strong> I want to own this whole thing,<a href="http://crangifamilyproject.com/" target="_blank">Philip Crangi</a> says  of his popular jewellery brand. Id rather own 100 percent of  something small that 10 percent of something huge. The 2008 CFDA  Swarovski Award for Accessories winner  whose jewellery is both  intensely popular with editors and intensely personal to those who wear  it  takes as much pride in forging his business as he does each golden  amulet. Its more than a job, he says. Its my baby. I want control  over it. I believe in control.\n\nGrowing up in Boca Raton, Florida,  Crangi developed a fascination with the talismanic nature of jewellery,  charms and trinkets. I wanted to find the buried treasure in flea  markets or in the attic, he says. I never did, so I have to make it  myself.\n\nAt the Rhode Island School of Design where  he studied gold- and silversmithing, he hit his groove. I had this kind  of personal success with my senior thesis, he says, which was kind of  groundbreaking for me personally  [but] when I came down to New York  all high from the experience I remember meeting with prominent stylists  and they all said, its so interesting, but we dont really use  jewellery much in photo shoots, which was staggering to me. That was  1993 and I cant imagine editorial now that isnt almost totally based  on accessories. The jewellery market wasnt what it is today.\n\nBut  rather than force the issue in an industry that wasnt ready for him,  Crangi put his unique know-how to work for him in other arenas, doing  restoration work, building custom lighting for interior designers,  designing homewards and collaborating with Japanese artist Mariko Mori.  Basically I got further and further away from jewellery in the 90s. But  I didnt want to compromise. I wanted to do it my way.\n\nIn 1998,  Crangis sister Courtney moved to New York and began running his  business. In 2000, Crangis long-time friend the clothing designer  Steven Alan and Aurora Lopez opened Borealis and invited Crangi to make a  line of jewellery to sell in the Nolita shop. Within months, Crangi  says, it was the top selling thing in the store. We had the perfect  thing at the perfect time  the perfect opportunity. And we decided a  couple months later that we would just go for it, and we just dropped  everything and ran whole-hog into jewellery.\n\nIn 2001, Crangi  properly launched Philip Crangi fine jewellery and discovered a truth  about the business of fashion. Having a great debut collection is not  nearly as hard as having a great sophomore collection, he says. Its  one thing to get in the door and get everyones attention, but then  everyones like, OK, whats next?\n\nThen, Crangi noticed another  hard reality: a wave of copy cat pieces were popping up in stores and,  with a lower price point, were well outselling his hand-forged gold and  silver pieces. He responded with an entry level label of his own,<a href="http://www.gilesandbrother.com/" target="_blank">Giles &amp; Brother</a>, which employed less precious alloys to make costume pieces in the same mold as the signature line.\n\nIt  was immediately a huge success, Crangi says. We were thinking we  would be like a version of Tiffany. There is so much missing in the  world. There is so much I have to make! Giles is such a great  opportunity for it. Ive always kept the Philip Crangi brand very  special. I have Giles so that I get to do what I want to do with Philip  Crangi, or not do anything until I feel it.\n\nHis sister Courtney  has an instinctive feel for business that Crangi trusts. She is able to  make the most radical decisions, from the heart, and every time she  does it has been amazing for us, Crangi says. Like the decision to  leave Barneys for Bergdorfs. That was kind of a radical move and she  just refused to be bullied. Shes a real brinksman.\n\nThe siblings  complement each other and make important decisions as a team, whether on  internet sales or opening a shop in New Yorks Meatpacking District.  Joking about the hokie, mystic sound to his approach, he says, We  wanted to open a store but the opportunity never showed itself, until  one day it did. And I really believe in that, if things are meant to be  theyll be. There is a balance between that and being assertive.\n\nTen  years on Crangi has rigorously maintained the integrity of his brand  and the quality of the product. He continues to enjoy collaborating with  other designers  including Phillip Lim, Vera Wang and, most recently,  Jason Wu. Theres a lot to learn from collaborations depending on how  you do them, he says. Collaborations can be done for a lot of reasons   creatively they are amazing of course, they can be PR driven, they can  be for financial gain obviously. For me, it is really interesting to go  into these other companies to see people who know what they are doing  run a businesscomparing and contrasting. There is always something to  learn.\n\nExplaining the secret to his growing success, he says, We  set a very, very high bar weve been really lucky. Courtney and I have  no business background at all, but we have good instincts, Ive  realized, over time. Especially with knowing what not to do. Thats what  I discovered after winning the fashion fund and winning the Swarovski  award  you are in a shark tank, and there are tons of people swimming  around you trying to get a piece of you  and you look at it, and think,  what am I going to get out of it. I was happy the success came a little  bit later for me, so I had a little bit more experience under my belt  about being taken advantage of.\n\nLooking forward, Crangi says, I  want to make things people want because they want it, not because they  are told they want it. Thats what I want to be doing when I am 75.\n\n<em>Chris Wallace.\n</em>', 'Portrait of inspiration, Philip Crangi.', 'Philip Crangi says jewellery design was his perfect business opportunity', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'portrait-of-inspiration-philip-grangi', '', '', '2010-09-28 13:51:52', '2010-09-28 11:51:52', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=4149', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(4158, 6, '2010-09-29 16:03:31', '2010-09-29 14:03:31', '9.29.2010. Week #40. Post 2.\n\nPerso, j''ai jamais t une tte en maths. Pas vraiment de ma faute, juste que, d''aprs mon prof de seconde, Monsieur Poirot (Big up), j''tais dans une autre logique:\n\n"Vous perdez votre temps  faire des choses fausses, Mademoiselle!". Ce n''est qu''aujourd''hui que je saisis la valeur intrinsque de cette remarque, il fallait tout simplement faire des choses "vraies", pas con, le gars!\n\nAlors, qu''est-ce qui me rconcilie avec la vracit mathmatique des choses? a:\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">I never been such a brainiac, when it comes to maths. Not really my fault, just that, according to my highschool teacher, Monsieur Poirot (fwi: Mister Leek in english), my approach of math logic was different:</span></em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">"You''re wasting your time at doing wrong things, young lady!". It is only today, that I realize the intrasic value of such an advice, I had to do only "right" things, duh!</span></em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">So, what made me up with the truthfulness of mathematics? That:</span></em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">\n</span></em>\n\n<a href="http://www.fashematics.com" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4159" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/logo-2.gif" alt="" width="660" height="101" /></a>\n\nFashematics=des rfrences connues de tous (tl, cinma, icnes de mode) qui s''additionnent pour dcoder les sources d''inspirations des grands couturiers. C''est drle, efficace et surtout, c''est d''une logique implacable! Enjoy:\n\n<em>Fashemati</em><em><span style="color: #888888;">cs= well known benchmarks (tv,movies,fashion icons) that add up to unscrumble the source of inspiration of the greatest fashion designers. It''s fun, effectual and above all, it''s unshakably logical! Voil:</span></em>\n\n<em><span style="color: #888888;">\n</span></em>\n\n<img class="alignce