(5320, 8, '2011-03-31 19:12:16', '2011-03-31 17:12:16', 'You''ve been asking to find out a little bit more about Christan Summers, the woman behind ICU. Well, ask and you shall receive! Here''s a brief interview in which she explains her motives behind ICU, her infatuation with Parisian creativity and what jewelry means to her. Not enough Christan for you? Check back each Monday to see her <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/03/28/christans-pick-of-the-week/" target="_blank">Pick of the Week</a>.\n<p style="text-align: center"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Christan-Summers.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-5323" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Christan-Summers-1024x683.jpg" alt="" width="527" height="351" /></a></p>\n<strong>How did you end up in Paris?</strong>\n\nI''m from Boston, but I''ve always had the desire to live somewhere in Europe. I spent a summer in Spain when I was younger and vowed to come back someday, if not to Spain then somewhere else in this continent. A couple years ago I was living in Bangkok where my design partner and I designed our <a href="http://www.icuinparis.com/catalogsearch/result/?q=ebbandpflow" target="_blank">ebb.and.pflow</a> collection, and that was when I decided to finally make the move. Paris is wonderfully beautiful, and visually just so inspiring. There''s also an incredible sensitivity and respect for creativity, which I''ve never experienced anywhere else, so for business reasons it just made sense to come here.\n\n<strong>Why did you choose to focus your business on jewelry?</strong>\n\nWell, it all starts with fashion. Fashion is a means of expression. Everybody can wear a t-shirt and jeans, but it''s the jewelry you add to it that creates your own identity. It''s the ability that jewelry has to empower you with originality and uniqueness. The accessories you choose to wear-- that''s originality, that''s expression, that''s you.\n\n<strong>And why focus on independent designers?</strong>\n\nBecause independent designers are true to their creativity and true to their passion. There''s a story that goes into each piece, an idea that you can take with you and make your own. So, when you''re wearing something from an independent designer you feel like you''re wearing something more precious, more original, a little more unique. You feel special wearing a piece you know not everyone walking down the street is going to have.\n\n<strong>Obviously icuinparis.com is an online boutique meant for shopping, but what else does ICU stand for?</strong>\n\nI''m a true believer in living life to its fullest. Everything is possible and anything you set your mind to you can do. It''s why I love independent designers, because they''re taking a risk and creating their dream. And through ICU, I want to support that dream, and illustrate to the public they can shop with us to express themselves with originality. ICU: independent, curated, unique. Get out of the norm, wear something original, and don''t be afraid of it.\n\n<strong>What does your style mean to you?</strong>\n\nMy style is how I feel. Every day is different. That''s the beauty of jewelry, no matter what your wearing you can change the look and feel of it-- a statement ring, a stack of bangles, a cluster of brooches or necklaces. I dress comfortably because if I''m not comfortable there''s no point in wearing it. I would describe my style as simple with a little edge, always mixing in some menswear. And you have to feel just a little sexy at all times!\n\nCheck out more of Christan''s style and past adventures, and don''t forget about her pick of the week to see which ICU item she can''t get enough of:\n\n<a href="http://www.ebbandpflowvideo.tumblr.com/" target="_blank">ebb.and.pflow</a>\n\n<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uIoMqTo9y_Q" target="_blank">The opening of the ICU showroom in Boston.</a>\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/03/28/christans-pick-of-the-week/" target="_blank">Christan''s Pick of the Week</a>', 'Find Out More About..... Christan Summers, ICU Founder', 'You''ve been asking to find out a little bit more about Christan Summers, the woman behind ICU.  Well, ask and you shall receive!  Here''s a brief interview in which she explains her motives behind ICU, her infatuation with Parisian creativity and what jewelry means to her.  Not enough Christan for you?  Check back each Monday to see her Pick of the Week.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'find-out-more-about-christan-summers-icu-founder', '', '', '2011-03-31 19:12:16', '2011-03-31 17:12:16', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=5320', 0, 'post', '', 2);
