(6823, 9, '2011-09-02 11:48:49', '2011-09-02 09:48:49', 'ICU''s founder and leader, <strong>Christan Summers</strong>, recently sat down for an interview with Daniel of the blog <strong><a href="http://www.tsnewyork.com/index/icu-in-paris-com-christan-summers" target="_blank">That''s So New York</a></strong>. Now, residing at <strong><a href="http://www.tsnewyork.com/index/icu-in-paris-com-christan-summers" target="_blank">That''s So New York</a></strong>, is the wonderfully thorough interview, structured by a heap of Daniel''s thoughtful questions. Here at the ICU blog we''re giving you just a snippet, so make sure to head over to <strong><a href="http://www.tsnewyork.com/index/icu-in-paris-com-christan-summers" target="_blank">That''s So New York</a></strong> to read everything Christan has to say, from why she started ICU, to life in Paris and what you can expect from her in the future.\n\n<a href="http://www.tsnewyork.com/"><img class="size-full wp-image-6825 aligncenter" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Screen-shot-2011-09-02-at-11.40.35-AM.png" alt="" width="705" height="110" /></a>\n\n<span style="color: #808080"><strong>Whatoriginallylead you to create ICU - IN PARIS.COM?</strong></span>\n\n<span style="color: #808080"><strong> </strong>My mom is a photographer and brought my brother and me on trips all over the world with her, starting from a very young age. My eyes were opened to different cultures, foods, people, mannerisms, clothing, jewelry, colors, shapes,... I could keep going. The point is, I changed because of it and as I got older, my means of expression began to take form through fashion and all of these aesthetic facets I experienced traveling.</span>\n<div><span style="color: #808080">I found myself often searching for unique clothing, jewelry and accessories but I couldnt find anything that I had not already seen previously. There was nothing unique or different. There was nothing that would help me express my individuality; therefore I decided when I was in High School that one day I would open my own boutique and carry designs for people who choose to express their individuality through fashion.</span></div>\n<div><span style="color: #808080">\n</span></div>\n<div><span style="color: #808080"><strong>What would you consider to be<em> unique</em></strong><strong> about ICU - IN PARIS.COM?</strong></span></div>\n<div><span style="color: #808080"><strong> </strong>The most important point is our integrity : Most people/companies that promote independent design pose themselves as a contradiction to high fashion, saying support independent design<strong>INSTEAD</strong> of high fashion. We''re saying support both. Our goal is to integrate independent design into the high fashion world because these designers deserve it. Independent designers have been limited by the label "indie design'' which often implies their work is "crafty" and "just a hobby". This is where ICU comes in, to remove the stigma of "indie design" and showcase the talent and professionalism of these amazing creators.</span></div>\n<div><span style="color: #808080">\n</span></div>\n<div><span style="color: #808080"><strong>What projects are you currently working on? Do you have anything exciting coming up in the near future in terms of the development and expansion of ICU - IN PARIS.COM?</strong><span style="font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif"> </span></span></div>\n<div><span style="color: #808080">We are currently redesigning the site which is a big project and long anticipated, so I cannot wait to take it live! It will be a lot more user friendly and will categorize and organize products and styles in a more effective manner. Since we are going to slowly bring in clothing designers (including one of our own, Ariane Haas!), the interface has to change.</span></div>\n<div style="text-align: center"><span>Hungry for more? <a href="http://www.tsnewyork.com/index/icu-in-paris-com-christan-summers" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline">Click here to read the rest</span> of the interview at <strong>That''s So New York</strong>.</a></span></div>\n<img class="size-full wp-image-6824 aligncenter" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Christan-Summers-ICU-IN-PARIS_COM.jpeg" alt="" width="510" height="734" />\n\n&nbsp;', 'That&#039;s So New York: Interview with Christan Summers', 'ICU''s founder and leader, Christan Summers, recently sat down for an interview with Daniel of the blog That''s So New York.  Now, residing at That''s So New York, is the wonderfully thorough interview, structured by a heap of Daniel''s thoughtful questions.  Here at the ICU blog we''re giving you just a snippet, so make sure to head over to That''s So New York to read everything Christan has to say, from why she started ICU, to life in Paris and what you can expect from her in the future.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'thats-so-new-york-interview-with-christan-summers', '', '', '2011-09-02 11:48:49', '2011-09-02 09:48:49', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=6823', 0, 'post', '', 0),
