(6914, 9, '2011-09-07 12:39:23', '2011-09-07 10:39:23', 'For <a href="http://www.icuinparis.com/" target="_blank">ICU''s</a> second <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/03/23/paris-style-profile-with-laura-g-the-flower-darling/" target="_blank">Style Profile</a> we focused our sartorial eye on Laura W, the Trend Forecaster from Down Under. Sporting a darkly organic style, she brings with her a unique set of global influences from her upbringing in Australia, to her Iranian and French heritage, and now her life as a fashion trend forecaster living in Paris. Read the excerpts below for a quick tease and watch the video to hear Laura''s style philosophies in entirety.\n\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-6925" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/laura-w_1-hands.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="441" /><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-6926" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/laura-w_1-tiled.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="294" /></a>\n\n<strong>Where are you from? </strong>Australia\n\n<strong>What is fashion forecasting? </strong>I assess what''s going on in terms of fashion windows, retail, trends, color and street style. And I also cover fashion weeks.\n\n<strong>Today''s street style? </strong>Street style is quite big now and everyone is going out and about to be seen, and you can see some people overdo it. They''re the ones I don''t like to take pictures of. It''s the people in between, it looks almost like they haven''t thought about what they''ve done, but they''ve creatively and collectively put stuff together.\n\n<strong>How does jewelry play a role in creatively and collectively putting your own style together? </strong>I can wear something really plain and I''ll invest in some really great jewelry. If I have stuff that''s completely unique as well there''s always a story to tell about it. My rings have been passed down, my mom wears a heap of silver jewelry, my grandma wears a heap of silver jewelry. And I''ve got a little but of Iranian in me, so I guess it shows my heritage and that makes me me. You have these things that you absolutely love and you know that if you''ve put a bit of money into it and they''re really quality things that they will last forever. And compliments you do get on things you keep with you, and you wear that piece and it brings you a kind of confidence. You choose pieces that make you who you are.\n\n<strong>Which ICU pieces help make you who you are? </strong> I''m wearing <strong>Coralie de Seynes''<a href="http://www.icuinparis.com/coralie-de-seynes-necklace-licol-grey-leather-silver.html" target="_blank">Grey &amp; Silver Leather Licol Necklace</a></strong> and <strong><a href="http://www.icuinparis.com/coralie-de-seynes-bracelet-mors-grey-leather-gun-metal.html" target="_blank">Grey Leather and Silver Chain Bracelet</a></strong>, and the <strong><a href="http://www.icuinparis.com/unsurcinq-ring-eugenie.html" target="_blank">Eugenie Chain Ring</a></strong> and <strong><a href="http://www.icuinparis.com/unsurcinq-ring-charlotte.html" target="_blank">Charlotte Chain Ring</a></strong> from <strong>Unsurcinq</strong>.\n<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><iframe width="560" height="345" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/yKvzpnu7buQ" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #ff00ff;">\n</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.icuinparis.com/" target="_blank">Click here to shop all ICU jewelry worn by Laura W.</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">In case you missed our first Style Profile with Laura G: Flower Darling, <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/03/23/paris-style-profile-with-laura-g-the-flower-darling/" target="_blank">click here to read the interview and watch the video</a>.</p>', 'Style Profile with Laura W: Trend Forecaster from Down Under', 'For ICU''s second Style Profile we focused our sartorial eye on Laura W, the Trend Forecaster from Down Under.  Sporting a darkly organic style, she brings with her a unique set of global influences from her upbringing in Australia, to her Iranian and French heritage, and now her life as a fashion trend forecaster living in Paris.  Read the excerpts below for a quick tease and watch the video to hear Laura''s style philosophies in entirety.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'style-profile-with-laura-w-trend-forecaster-from-down-under', '', '', '2011-09-07 12:39:23', '2011-09-07 10:39:23', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=6914', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(6939, 4, '2011-09-08 12:04:29', '2011-09-08 10:04:29', 'During a whilrwind trip back to the States, <a title="http://www.icuinparis.com/" href="http://www.icuinparis.com/" target="_blank">ICU</a> Founder <a title="christan summers_icuinparis.com" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/09/02/thats-so-new-york-interview-with-christan-summers/" target="_blank">Christan Summers</a> made sure to squeeze in an hour with the fast rising, celebrity stylist and fashion commentator, <a title="colin t. mcdonald" href="http://www.colintmcdonald.com/" target="_blank">Colin T. Mcdonald</a>.\n\nBeginning his career in the fashion industry in 2003 Colin has worked with influencers such as; Numro, Harper''s Bazaar,Christian Dior, Michael Kors, Simon Carter, Ralph Lauren,LOreal, Hombre, Venus Zine, The Oprah Winfrey Show, NBC and SONY Music. As well as some of the most influential personalities in the world; Michele Obama, Mary Alice Stephenson and Patti Wilson.\n\nThe two sat down over cocktails at Tao in New York and talked fashion shop from Colin''s dance with Michele Obama, his secret to avoiding photo shoot horror and his designer forecast naming fashion''s next biggest independent jewelry designer.\n\nRead the full interview below and be sure to watch out for this man as he continues to break into the world of fashion.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/193046_10150112403997418_640922417_6273400_1094235_o.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-6975" title="colin t. mcdonald_icuinparis.com" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/193046_10150112403997418_640922417_6273400_1094235_o.jpg" alt="colin t. mcdonald_icuinparis.com" width="384" height="576" /></a></p>\n<strong>CS : Introduce yourself: What does the world need to know about you?</strong>\n<strong> </strong>CTM : My name is Colin T. McDonald and Im a fashion stylist, commentator, red-carpet host and consultant here in New York.\n\n<strong>CS : How did you come to be such a sought-after stylist?</strong>\nCTM : Hard work, dedication, passion and adrive to want to be a powerful force within the fashion industry.  I want to do it all and build an empire for myself.  This is just the beginning!\n\n<strong>CS : Whose closet would you raid?</strong>\nCTM : Tom Fords - I think I would raid his closet and him.  Amazing sense of style and very easy on the eyes!\n\n<strong><strong>CS :</strong> What is the most treasured item in your closet?</strong>\nCTM : My red metallic Hugo Boss high-tops!  Kanye West wore them for one of his music videos.   Ive literally had people stop their cars in New York just to ask me who they were designed by.\n\n<strong>CS : Do you have a muse?</strong>\nCTM : My muse is New York City and the interesting people who live in it.  It inspires each and every day I walk out of my studio.\n\n<strong>CS : What are the top 5 magazines you have styled for?</strong>\nCTM :\nHarpers  Bazaar\nNumero\nCulture\nFantastic\nHombre\n\n&nbsp;\n\n[gallery orderby="rand"]\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CS : Share with us one favorite experience</strong>\nCTM : Working with Mary Alice Stephenson on the Oprah Winfrey Show and an exclusive White House shoot featuring Michelle Obama for Harpers Bazaar.  Was very proud to be an American that day!\n\n<strong>CS : How about one horror story?</strong>\n<strong> </strong>CTM : I dont have any story in particular because I always try to be well prepared for anything that could happen on set.  As a stylist, you need to always have a back-up plan and come prepared for the worst happens.\n\n<strong>CS : As cited on your press page, you have had the opportunity to work with Oprah and the Obamas. Indulge us, how was it?</strong>\nCTM : I worked alongside Mary Alice Stephenson, an icon to the world of styling, for both those projects.  Truly amazing experiences and Im so grateful that she asked me help out.  I even got the pleasure to not just shake but get THE Oprah handshake from the queen of daytime talk herself.  I also was fortunate enough to dance with Michelle Obama in the red room of the White House.  Two moments I will never forget for the rest of my life.\n\n<strong>CS : What is your take on the independent designer world?</strong>\nCTM : I support it 100% and encourage other stylists and industry leaders to do so as well.  I love discovering new and up-and-coming designers!\n\n<strong>CS : Which designer(s) do you most wish to pull from ICUINPARIS.COM?</strong>\nCTM : I honestly would like to work with all of them.  It just really depends on the project and if theyre right for it.\n\n<strong>CS : What is your philosophy when it comes to accessorizing?</strong>\nCTM : Over indulge with statement pieces!\n\n<strong>CS : Would you rather work with Sascha Lilic or Rachel Zoe?</strong>\nCTM : Both-Huge fan of his and her work.\n<strong>CS : Why? </strong>\n<strong> </strong>CTM : Sascha-I absolutely admire his work.  Rachel-I love how she has gone beyond styling into design and branding her name.  My ultimate goal!\n\n<strong>CS : Fashion photography vs. fashion videography. Do you have a preference?Which inspires you more deeply?</strong>\nCTM : No preference - both offer its viewer a unique perspective.  Although, videography does make it easier to evoke a feeling to its viewer.\n\n<strong>CS : Lets put your fashion forecasting skills to the test. Who is the next independent designer to take the fashion forum by storm?</strong>\nCTM : Jewelry designer Patricia Brown.  Shes studied with Marc Jacobs and Tom Ford and has that same aesthetic when it comes to design.  Shes also created collections for major fashion empires like Calvin Klein, Banana Republic and Ralph Lauren.  Shes slowly gaining recognition in the press with her own label, and major retailers like Henri Bendels are looking to showcase her.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/250312_10150260355337418_640922417_7380211_1071664_n.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-6944 aligncenter" title="COLIN T. MCDONALD_INTERVIEW_ICUINPARIS.COM" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/250312_10150260355337418_640922417_7380211_1071664_n.jpg" alt="COLIN T. MCDONALD_INTERVIEW_ICUINPARIS.COM" width="350" height="436" /></a>\n<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">View Colin T. McDonald''s portfolio &amp; learn more about this rising personality <a title="colintmcdonald" href="http://www.colintmcdonald.com/" target="_blank">here</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">An ICU - IN PARIS.COM Interview</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a title="icuinparis.com" href="http://www.icuinparis.com/" target="_blank">www.icuinparis.com </a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>\n&nbsp;', 'Sit down with ICU &amp; Celebrity Stylist Colin T. McDonald ', 'During a whilrwind trip back to the States, ICU Founder Christan Summers made sure to squeeze in an hour with the fast rising, celbruty stylist and fashion commentator, Colin T. Mcdonald.\n\nBeginning his career in the fashion industry in 2003 Colin has worked with influencers such as; Numro, Harper''s Bazaar, Christian Dior, Michael Kors, Simon Carter, Ralph Lauren, LOreal, Hombre, Venus Zine, The Oprah Winfrey Show, NBC and SONY Music. As well as some of the most influential personalities in the world; Michele Obama, Mary Alice Stephenson and Patti Wilson.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sit-down-with-icu-celebrity-stylist-colin-t-mcdonald', '', '', '2011-09-08 12:04:29', '2011-09-08 10:04:29', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=6939', 0, 'post', '', 0),
