(6962, 9, '2011-09-13 12:34:56', '2011-09-13 10:34:56', 'ICU is lucky enough to have two very talented and stylish friends amongst its ranks, the lovely Lauras. Hailing all the way from Australia, their name is the same but their styles are quite different, and both have been well documented in ICU''s Style Profiles.\n\nFirst came <a title="paris style profile_icuinparis.com" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/03/23/paris-style-profile-with-laura-g-the-flower-darling/" target="_blank">Laura Geddes: Flower Darling</a>, a lovely fashion illustrator whose drawings are even lovelier. Then came <a title="paris style profile_icuinparis.com" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/09/07/style-profile-with-laura-w-trend-forecaster-from-down-under/" target="_blank">Laura Wassermann: Trend Forecaster from Down Under</a>, the street style photographer that sleighed us with her darkly organic style.\n\nICU has brought the Lauras together for an innovative and exciting collaboration, of which this is the first presentation. The plan is simple: Laura W hits the streets of Paris to capture accessories worn by the sartorially inspired passers by. Laura G then illustrates those photographs, reimagining their surroundings.\n\nBelow, the photo and illustration that was inspired from it and further down, read what inspired the ladies to photograph and draw the images.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/laua-illustrations-photo-icuinparis.com_.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-6985" title="laura-illustrations-photo-icuinparis.com" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/laua-illustrations-photo-icuinparis.com_.jpg" alt="laura-illustrations-photo-icuinparis.com" width="620" height="1000" /></a>\n<blockquote><strong>Laura G''s Illustration Inspiration:</strong></blockquote>\n<blockquote><em>I tried to imagine her in context, and thought of her twirling around the gardens (the scarf and glasses, definitely a dreamer), hence she was in need of a dreamy skirt. Also seeing as she would be twirling, a shoulder bag just wouldn''t work, so a clutch it was (plus with so much pattern and detail around her face her look would be more balanced with some weight in her hand, heavy and detailed). </em><strong>- Laura G, Illustrator</strong></blockquote>\n&nbsp;\n<blockquote><strong>Laura W''s Photo Inspiration:</strong></blockquote>\n<blockquote><em>This girl was pretty much just roaming through the Tuilleries at about Midday on a Sunday looking completely dolled up and smiley and not looking like she was in a hurry to go anywhere - no kidding, it was actually a one of the most perfect scenarios for a street style shot proposal ever! She stood out because she looked really fresh for what felt like a dull, over-cast, mopey Sunday. I''m always envious of people who put a little more effort into this kind of Sunday i''m talking about. <strong>- </strong></em><strong>Laura W, Street Style Photographer </strong></blockquote>\n&nbsp;', 'Paris Street Style + Fashion Illustration = Inspired Inspiration', 'ICU is lucky enough to have two very talented and stylish friends amongst its ranks, the lovely Lauras.  Hailing all the way from Australia, their name is the same but their styles are quite different, and both have been well documented in ICU''s Style Profiles.\n\nFirst came Laura Geddes: Flower Darling, a lovely fashion illustrator whose drawings are even lovelier.  Then came Laura Wassermann: Trend Forecaster from Down Under, the street style photographer that sleighed us with her darkly organic style.\n\nICU has brought the Lauras together for an innovative and exciting collaboration, of which this is the first presentation.  The plan is simple: Laura W hits the streets of Paris to capture accessories worn by the sartorially inspired passers by.  Laura G then illustrates those photographs, reimagining their surroundings.\n', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'an-exclusive-collaboration-of-inspired-inspiration', '', '', '2011-09-13 12:34:56', '2011-09-13 10:34:56', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=6962', 0, 'post', '', 0);
