(6993, 4, '2011-09-14 14:35:59', '2011-09-14 12:35:59', '<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/newsletter-emily-rothschild-medical-usb-locket-story.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-7001" title="newsletter-emily-rothschild-medical-usb-locket-story" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/newsletter-emily-rothschild-medical-usb-locket-story.jpg" alt="emily-rothschild-medical-usb-locket-story" width="650" height="963" /></a></p>', 'Emily Rothschild &amp; The Story Behind the Piece: USB Medical Locket Necklace ', 'For our second installement of the Story Behind the Piece, the ICUINPARIS.COM team spoke with designer, Emily Rothschild of the self-entitled brand, EMILY ROTHSCHILD to learn more about the story and inspiration behind her Medical USB Locket\nNecklace.\n\nA unique piece and fascinating recount of inspiration, learn how and why this one-of-a-kind piece was\ndesigned and created. , ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'emily-rothschild-the-story-behind-the-piece-usb-medical-locket-necklace', '', '', '2011-09-14 14:35:59', '2011-09-14 12:35:59', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=6993', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(7004, 4, '2011-09-15 11:44:28', '2011-09-15 09:44:28', '<div>On a sunny summer day in Paris, the ICU creative team had the pleasure of working with rising fashion stylist, Vanessa Cocchiaro. Originally from Australia and just recently re-locating to Milan, Italy, Vanessa is already making huge strides in the European fashion world. When she contacted ICU for a shoot we were only ecstatic to work alongside her and her team on a shoot for the Italian publication, <a title="http://www.jasmology.com/" href="http://www.jasmology.com/" target="_blank">Jasmology</a>.</div>\n&nbsp;\n<div>Of course, we couldn''t just let this darling lady go without learning more about her so our Director of Public Relations and Marketing, <a title="Christina Zervanos" href="http://twitter.com/#!/CZervanos" target="_blank">Christina Zervanos</a> sat down with Vanessa to learn a bit more...</div>\n&nbsp;\n<div><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Vanessa-webimage.jpg">\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-7008" title="Vanessa-webimage" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Vanessa-webimage.jpg" alt="" width="310" height="262" /></a></div>\n&nbsp;\n<div><strong>CZ:</strong> New to Milan as a stylist, take me through a typical work day for you.</div>\n<div><strong>VC: </strong>As a freelance stylist no matter where in the world there isn''t really a typical day, it is usually chaotic, unexpected, stressful and fun... It constantly changes and you are always running around.Recently, I took on the role as fashion editor of a blog called<a href="http://jasmology.com/" target="_blank">jasmology.com</a> so that has been taking up quite a bit of my time researching stories and going to show rooms and events.</div>\n<div><strong>CZ: </strong>Why the move from Australia to Milan?</div>\n<div><strong>VC:</strong> Both of my parents were born in Italy and moved to Australia when they were very young, so I suppose I have always had an itch to discover my roots and learn the language and Milan being the fashion capital of Italy for me the choice couldn''t have been clearer.</div>\n&nbsp;\n<div><strong>CZ: </strong>Such a move is inspiring not to mention brave; what have the highlights been? And thelowlights?</div>\n<div><strong>CV:</strong> When I moved Milan I didn''t really understand what I was getting myself into. I am quite a strong person but I definitelyhad a naive romantic view of moving to a new place when I didnt know a single word of the language or one single person. It is quite funny now I think about it. Moreover, moving from a county where a I knew a lot of people in the fashion industry to not knowing anyone is something that I struggle with ever day. Though, at the same time each accomplishment is about 1000 times more rewarding then before.I have been in Milan just under a year so i really haven''t even touched the surface and i am really excited to see the highs and lows that will come. You cant have one without the other so you just have to stick at it and enjoy whatever is thrown your way.</div>\n&nbsp;\n<div>So now to answer your question (smiles : )</div>\n<div>The highlights: pizza, pasta, gelato!</div>\n<div>The lowlights: pizza, pasta, gelato!</div>\n<div>(another smile :)</div>\n&nbsp;\n<div><strong>CZ:</strong> Is there a stylist whose aesthetic you emulate or whose work inspires you?</div>\n<div><strong>VC:</strong> I know this is incredibly cliche but I am inspired by everything around me. I have stylists whose work I think is incredibly beautiful but I am not one to emulate another person''swork.</div>\n&nbsp;\n<div><strong>CZ: </strong>Lanvins latest campaign video brought humor to the table which is rare in fashion; whatis your take on the video, and do you think fashion takes itself too seriously?</div>\n<div><strong>VC:</strong> Oh I love this question! The Lanvin video is fantastic, it was such a breath of fresh air.I think I have had a thousand conversations about how I don''t understand why people in fashion take themselves so seriously. It''s just fucking fashion!</div>\n<div>For someone like myself who started from the very bottom I have seen quite a lot and been put through quite a lot, lets just say my last boss was the typical fashion bitch from hell. Incredibly unoriginal. I cant help but laugh about how ridiculous the whole scene is.</div>\n<div>I love my industry, fashion and design are really special elements in society but it should make people happy not make them have breakdowns.My brother is an Intellectual Property lawyer and he lives in Cape Town, South Africa representing the rights of African communities. I watch him and hear his stories and it puts things back into perspective.</div>\n&nbsp;\n<div><strong>CZ: </strong>Daphne Guinness is regularly regarded as a muse for those in the fashion world be itstylists, designers, or journalists; does such a statement hold true for you aswell?</div>\n<div><strong>VC: </strong>I think she is amazing, someone who is not afraid to be themselves and just do whatever thay want to do.The people that pave the way for others are the ones that aren''t influenced by the ''norm''.My most disliked word is ''normal'', who is normal? who dictates what normal is?</div>\n<div>So yes, Daphne Guinness is a muse because she isn''t afraid to do what she wants and in this day and age it is very difficult not to be influenced and caught in that so-called ''norm''.</div>\n&nbsp;\n<div><strong>CZ:</strong> Why do photographers and models want to work with you; what is it that you bring to thetable that makes you so sought-after?</div>\n<div><strong>VC: </strong>I suppose they like my aesthetic and the way I work. It is always a lot of fun when you find people who share a similar vision.</div>\n&nbsp;\n\nClick the image thumbnails below to view samples of Vanessa''s work:\n<div><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/image14-web.jpg">[gallery link="file" orderby="rand"]\n</a>&nbsp;\n\n</div>\n<div><strong>CZ:</strong> What is your take on the independent designer world?</div>\n<div><strong>VC: </strong>Ever since I started in the fashion industry I have wanted to work with independent and emerging designers. I think it is really important to support each other especially in the economy we are in at the moment.I am always looking for new and exciting things and the majority of those things com from the independent designer realm.</div>\n&nbsp;\n<div><strong>CZ: </strong>We at<a title="http://ICUINPARIS.COM/" href="http://ICUINPARIS.COM/" target="_blank">ICUINPARIS.COM</a> have been fortunate enough to collaborate with you on ashoot; which designer(s) did you most enjoy styling with?</div>\n<div><strong>VC: </strong>Firstly, I am in love with the whole ICU team so the pleasure was all mine!Secondly, that is a hard questionbecause designers that ICU stock are so diverse and each have their own unique components. To name one,Astraleye''sstyle is simple, beautiful and mysterious. It adds an enhancing element to an outfit that you cant get from anything else.</div>\n&nbsp;\n<div><strong>CZ: </strong>What is your philosophy when it comes to accessorizing?</div>\n<div><strong>VC: </strong>I think it is my same philosophy as getting dressed in the morning. What ever makes you happy and feel great!</div>\n&nbsp;\n<div><strong>CZ: </strong>In your opinion, what are the key components of a successful shoot?</div>\n<div><strong>VC: </strong>A team that works well together. When all of the facets come together it can be magic but when one things is off it will totally change the dynamic of the team and the result.</div>\n&nbsp;\n<div><strong>CZ: </strong>Besides Milan, Paris, NY and London, which new city do you feel is making a solid footprint as a fashion capital?</div>\n<div><strong>VC:</strong> As a fashion capital it is hard to say, the above four cities have it covered but each different country has their own specific style and I look everywhere for interestingdesigners and street style. Each style changes drastically from place to place so it is really interesting to research what the regional designs and trends are.</div>\n<div>I could rattle off a few places like Berlin, Tokyo, Stockholm but they have been popular for a really long time and aren''treally fresh. So instead...I am dying to go to Tel Aviv andReykjavk. I feel culturally and artisticallythere are and will be incredibly exciting things coming from those places.</div>\n&nbsp;\n<div><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/IMG_9328.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-7018" title="vanessa_cocchiaro-interview" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/IMG_9328.jpg" alt="vanessa_cocchiaro-interview" width="450" height="300" /></a></div>\n<div style="text-align: center;">To view further work from Vanessa visit <a title="http://www.modelmayhem.com/2204627" href="http://www.modelmayhem.com/2204627" target="_blank">HERE</a></div>\n<div style="text-align: center;">Want more from the fashion scene? Read last week''s interview on celebrity stylist, Colin T. McDonald <a title="colin t/ mcdonald and icuinparis.com" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/09/08/sit-down-with-icu-celebrity-stylist-colin-t-mcdonald/" target="_blank">HERE</a></div>\n<div style="text-align: center;">An <a title="http://ICUINPARIS.COM/" href="http://ICUINPARIS.COM/" target="_blank">ICUINPARIS.COM</a> Interview Production.</div>\n<div style="text-align: center;"> <a title="http://ICUINPARIS.COM/" href="http://ICUINPARIS.COM/" target="_blank">ICUINPARIS.COM</a> 2011 All Rights Reserved.</div>', 'VANESSA COCCHIARO: ICU sits down with the rising Milano Stylist', 'On a sunny summer day in Paris, the ICU creative team had the pleasure of working with rising fashion stylist, Vanessa Cocchiaro. Originally from Australia and just recently re-locating to Milan, Italy, Vanessa is already making huge strides in the European fashion world. When she contacted ICU for a shoot we were only ecstatic to work along her side and her team on a shoot for the Italian publication, Jasmology.\n\nOf course, we couldn''t just let this darling lady go without learning more about her so our Director of Public Relations and Marketing, Christina Zervanos sat down with Vanessa to learn a bit more...', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'vanessa-cocchiaro-icu-sits-down-with-the-rising-milano-stylist', '', '', '2011-09-15 11:44:28', '2011-09-15 09:44:28', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=7004', 0, 'post', '', 0),
