inparis.com/grey-diamond-cluster-necklace-161.html" target="_blank">Gorjana''s Black Diamond Pav Necklace</a>.\n\n&nbsp;\n<p style="text-align: center;">Shop the ICU Boutique <a title="icuinparis.com" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/" target="_blank">HERE</a></p>', 'Paris Weekend Forecast: Amethyst Studs and Black Diamond Necklaces', 'Summer has returned for a weekend in Paris and its time to pull out those sweet pastels and pleated skirts for one last bare-legged stroll through the Parisian parks. This weekend its about celebrating the colors of an everlasting style romance, through sweet palettes of rose, burgundy and mustard yellow.\n', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'paris-weekend-forecast-amethyst-studs-and-black-diamond-necklaces', '', '', '2011-09-24 12:25:20', '2011-09-24 10:25:20', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=7074', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(7079, 9, '2011-09-27 15:02:05', '2011-09-27 13:02:05', 'It''s time for the second installment from <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/" target="_blank">ICU''s</a> regular contributors, street style photographer Laura Wassermann and fashion illustrator Laura Geddes. Those of you already in the <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/" target="_blank">ICU</a> universe know these two lovely ladies from their Style Profiles. To see those videos again and jog your memory on their personal styles <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/09/07/style-profile-with-laura-w-trend-forecaster-from-down-under/" target="_blank">click <strong>here</strong> to view Laura Wassermann</a> and <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/03/23/paris-style-profile-with-laura-g-the-flower-darling/" target="_blank"><strong>here</strong> to view Laura Geddes</a>.\n\nFor those of you who are new to this collaboration here''s how it works: Laura W hits the streets of Paris to capture accessories worn by the sartorially inspired passers by, then Laura G illustrates those photographs, reimagining their surroundings.\n\nView the <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/" target="_blank">ICU</a> exclusive street style shot along with its inspired drawing, and read below to find out what these creatives were thinking as they snapped the pic and sketched the jewels.\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/entry2.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-7080" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/entry2.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="801" /></a>\n\n<strong><em>Laura W''s Photo Inspiration:</em></strong>\n\n<em>"It was as though the wearer of this ring whirled her grace 100 meters in front of herself as I watched her walking towards me on a serene street in Le Haute Marais. At first it was the vivid, floor scraping Yves Klein blue skirt that caught my attention. Bit as she approached closer, I realized it was actually more so the gorgeous small accents of pastels and the solid sterling silver that finished her look. I felt like the combination of her selected intrinsic touches are not normally easy to pull off so it was great to capture it."</em>\n\n<strong><em>Laura G''s Illustration Inspiration:</em></strong>\n\n<em>"I took from the picture that she might be a bit away with the fairies, with her glitter nail polish and large crystal ring, so I gave her a pencil... maybe she can put some of her musings down on paper... And I turned the Klein blue into a floral to soften the whole look, since the color and jewelry are such a strong combination."</em>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWant more? Click <strong><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/09/13/an-exclusive-collaboration-of-inspired-inspiration/" target="_blank">here</a></strong> to check out the first photo/drawing combo from Laura Wassermann and Laura Geddes.', 'ICU Exclusive: Paris Street Style &amp; Fashion Illustration', 'It''s time for the second installment from ICU''s regular contributors, street style photographer Laura Wassermann and fashion illustrator Laura Geddes.  Those of you already in the ICU universe know these two lovely ladies from their Style Profiles.  To see those videos again and jog your memory on their personal styles click here to view Laura Wassermann and here to view Laura Geddes.\n\nFor those of you who are new to this collaboration here''s how it works: Laura W hits the streets of Paris to capture accessories worn by the sartorially inspired passers by, then Laura G illustrates those photographs, reimagining their surroundings.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'icu-exclusive-paris-street-style-fashion-illustration', '', '', '2011-09-27 15:02:05', '2011-09-27 13:02:05', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=7079', 0, 'post', '', 0),
