(7169, 9, '2011-10-11 11:26:14', '2011-10-11 09:26:14', '<strong>ICU</strong> contributors <strong>Laura Wassermann</strong> and <strong>Laura Geddes</strong> are back with another amazing collaboration, combining exclusive street style photography from Laura W and Laura G''s beautiful hand drawn illustrations. The process is simple: Laura W scours the streets to photograph the well accessorized women of Paris, then Laura G illustrates those photographs using her own inspiration to creatively reimagine the surrounding style.\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-7170" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/icuinparis-streetstyle-blog3.jpg" alt="icuinparis street style fashion illustration" width="650" height="1456" /></a>\n\n<strong><em>Laura Wassermann''s Photo Inspiration:</em></strong>\n\n"This girl had a witty retro flavor but maintained a very lady-like appeal, a kind of style I feel like you don''t see too often. The contrast of red and white looked great on her and even made me evaluate if I myself could pull off that exact duo of colors together. All in all, she stood out and looked fabulous!"\n\n<strong><em>Laura Geddes'' Photo Inspiration:</em></strong>\n\n"Well, I was thinking 1970s when I saw the photograph, between the loose hair, embroidery and necklace. So I listened to some Franoise Hardy, flipped through some old images of her to get inspired and voil!\n<p style="text-align: center">Click <strong><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?s=laura+fashion+illustration+wassermann&amp;submit.x=0&amp;submit.y=0" target="_blank">here</a> </strong>to view more Street Style &amp; Fashion Illustration collaborations from <strong>Laura Wassermann &amp; Laura Geddes</strong>.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/09/27/icu-exclusive-paris-street-style-fashion-illustration/"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-7171" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/entry2-243x300.jpg" alt="Street Style &amp; Fashion Illustration 2" width="243" height="300" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/09/13/an-exclusive-collaboration-of-inspired-inspiration/"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-7172" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/laura-illustrations-photo-icuinparis-186x300.jpg" alt="street style photography &amp; fashion illustration 1" width="186" height="300" /></a></p>', 'Paris Street Style &amp; Fashion Illustration', 'ICU contributors Laura Wassermann and Laura Geddes are back with another amazing collaboration, combining exclusive street style photography from Laura W and Laura G''s beautiful hand drawn illustrations.  The process is simple: Laura W photographs well accessorized women of Paris, then Laura G illustrates those photographs using her own inspiration to creatively reimagine the surrounding style.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'paris-street-style-fashion-illustration', '', '', '2011-10-11 11:26:14', '2011-10-11 09:26:14', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=7169', 0, 'post', '', 0),
