(7274, 9, '2011-10-25 12:00:21', '2011-10-25 10:00:21', 'In the fourth collaboration from Paris based street style photographer <strong><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/09/07/style-profile-with-laura-w-trend-forecaster-from-down-under/" target="_blank">Laura Wassermann</a></strong> and fashion illustrator <strong><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/03/23/paris-style-profile-with-laura-g-the-flower-darling/" target="_blank">Laura Geddes</a></strong>, the girls tackle chain, animal textures and bright prints. See the look that Laura Wassermann captured on the streets exclusively for <strong>ICU</strong> and how it inspired Laura Geddes'' delicate and beautifully hand drawn illustration. Scroll down to read what the artists were thinking and view more exclusive ICU collaborations.\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/lauras4.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-7278" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/lauras4.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="1456" /></a>\n\n<strong><em>Laura Wassermann''s Photo Inspiration:</em></strong>\n\nI loved the metal gold lining around both of these pieces and that it''s totally okay to have chunky plastics sit right by sleek leather-- it gives a contemporary, edgy finish and despite the sharp and striking red hue of the dress, the accessories still dominated.\n\n<strong><em>Laura Geddes'' Illustration Inspiration:</em></strong>\n\nI was inspired by the colors and the graphic nature of the shot, which for some reason lead me to thinking about bamboo. Hmm... who knows how my mind gets there-- it''s instantaneous!\n\n<strong><em>\n</em></strong>\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/10/11/paris-street-style-fashion-illustration/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-7276" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/thumbnail-2.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="459" /></a>\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/1