(7385, 9, '2011-11-08 11:00:59', '2011-11-08 10:00:59', 'This week finds us with another amazing collaboration from Paris based street style photographer<strong><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/09/07/style-profile-with-laura-w-trend-forecaster-from-down-under/" target="_blank">Laura Wassermann</a></strong> and fashion illustrator<strong><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/03/23/paris-style-profile-with-laura-g-the-flower-darling/" target="_blank">Laura Geddes</a></strong>. From the nails, to the jewelry and the textures behind it all Laura Wassermann''s street style photograph has given way to Laura Geddes'' hand drawn illustration, perfectly balancing sweet and sexy. Scroll down to see what the artists themselves were thinking when they snapped the pic and drew the bunny.\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-7388" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/lauras5.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="994" /></a>\n\n<strong><em>Laura Wassermann''s Photo Inspiration: </em></strong>\n\n<strong><em> </em></strong>"This look is like a perfect dessert. I love the unexpected ingredients; the textures and materials-- the mix of sequins, linen and leather with the delicious gold topping. The flat, clean, contemporary metal cuff is what wraps up the package and it stole my attention before everything else."\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><em>Laura Geddes'' Illustration Inspiration:</em></strong>\n\n"I <em>love</em> bunnies, hence why not see it all the way through? So I went for a fashioned up Playboy bunny, wearing nothing but the jewelry."\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?s=laura+geddes&amp;submit.x=0&amp;submit.y=0"><img class="size-full wp-image-7387 aligncenter" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/jpg" alt="" width="200" height="459" /></a>\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/10/11/paris-street-style-fashion-illustration/"><img class="size-full wp-image-7390 aligncenter" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/thumbnail-2.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="459" /></a>\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/09/27/icu-exclusive-paris-street-style-fashion-illustration/"><img class="size-full wp-image-7389 aligncenter" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/thumbnail-1.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="276" /></a>\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/09/13/an-exclusive-collaboration-of-inspired-inspiration/"><img class="size-full wp-image-7391 aligncenter" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/thumbnail.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="357" /></a>\n\nthe girls tackle chain, animal textures and bright prints. See the look that Laura Wassermann captured on the streets exclusively for<strong>ICU</strong> and how it inspired Laura Geddes'' delicate and beautifully hand drawn illustration. Scroll down to read what the artists were thinking and view more exclusive ICU collaborations.', 'ICU Exclusive: Paris Street Style &amp; Fashion Illustration', 'This week finds us with another amazing collaboration from Paris based street style photographer Laura Wassermann and fashion illustrator Laura Geddes.  From the nails, to the jewelry and the textures behind it all Laura Wassermann''s street style photograph has given way to Laura Geddes'' hand drawn illustration, perfectly balancing sweet and sexy.  Scroll down to see what the artists themselves were thinking when they snapped the pic and drew the bunny.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'icu-exclusive-paris-street-style-fashion-illustration-3', '', '', '2011-11-08 11:00:59', '2011-11-08 10:00:59', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=7385', 0, 'post', '', 0),
