(7457, 9, '2011-11-17 11:09:27', '2011-11-17 10:09:27', '<a href="www.icuinparis.com" target="_blank">ICU</a> first got to know Jael Levi as photographer <a href="http://christiangeisselmann.com/" target="_blank">Christian Geisselmann''s</a> assistant, and we have since come to regard her as an incredibly talented photographer in her own right as well as an arbiter of her own unique style. Though she considers Madrid her home, she dresses with the global influence of her experiences living in New York and now Paris. The <a href="www.icuinparis.com" target="_blank">ICU</a> team recently had the pleasure of sitting down with Jael to find out more about her personal style and creative vision that permeates her photography, videos and multimedia blogs...\n\n-Christina Zervanos, Director of Media &amp; Press Relations, ICUinParis.com\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/Screen-shot-2011-11-17-at-10.15.42-AM.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-7461 aligncenter" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/Screen-shot-2011-11-17-at-10.15.42-AM.png" alt="" width="640" height="432" /></a>\n\n<strong>CZ: </strong>A beautiful photographer yourself, what is it like to serve as an assistant for another amazing photographer (Christian Geisselmann), but with a different aesthetic?\n\n<strong>Jael: </strong>I dont want to sound like a crawler but its great! I had the fortune to run into not only a great photographer but also one of the best people Ive ever known when I was about to give up on finding a job related to photography in ParisHe knows exactly what hes doing, how to get whatever he pictured in his head for the shooting hes got everything under control, always. And most important, in my opinion, he lets you be a part of it. Hes a boss when he has to and a friend when you need him to.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CZ: </strong>You have your hands in a lot of creative outlets (video, photography, journalism); does one inspire you the most? And how to they interact and overlap?\n\n<strong>Jael: </strong>I would say its the image that inspires me doesnt matter if its a picture, a film or writing I develop a whole story around a first still that I picture in my head, it can end up being a photograph, a film or a story I guess they all work together somehow.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CZ: </strong>During a shoot, what is your playlist?\n\n<strong>Jael: </strong>Hard question It depends on what I want to get from who Im photographing or how Im feelingbut according to my iTunes: The Smiths, Frou Frou, Cults, Arcade Fire, Foo Fighters, Tegan &amp; Sara, Deerhunter and The Joy Formidable are on my top 10 right nowSome of them have been there for years now\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CZ: </strong>How has coming from a family of actors, acting teachers and directors affected your career ambitions?\n\n<strong>Jael: </strong>I am very lucky to have my family we were taught that creating and expressing yourself was as important as breathing. My parents never told us what to do or choose If I wanted to play piano they would let me try, even though they knew I would quit the class for something else a month later. I tried acting, but it wasnt my thing so the way they affect my career is by letting me find my way and making my own choices and being my support.\n\n<!-- p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Arial; color: #e04009} -->\n\n<strong>CZ: </strong>What do you want people to gain from your blog <strong><a href="http://sendmepostcards.tumblr.com/" target="_blank">Send me Postcards</a></strong>?\n\n<strong>Jael: </strong><strong><a href="http://sendmepostcards.tumblr.com/" target="_blank">Send me Postcards</a> </strong>is the less serious me I try to show things I like: quotes, videos, personal pictures  I just want people to discover stuff they might not know and make them laugh a little from time to time and of course, to promote my worktumblr is getting really big right now!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CZ: </strong>From Madrid, you have also studied in NY, and now live in Paris. Each city is uniquely different; what do you gain from all of them? Culturally? Stylistically?\n\n<strong>Jael: </strong>Inspiration, fulfillment, confidence they are indeed three different cities. Madrid is my hometown; I had a hard time with the city for a few years. It seemed empty, as if I couldnt gain anything from it Now that Im away Ive realized Madrid is the base of who I am. It does have a lot to bring, I was just blinded with the new. I love the feeling of being far from what I already know and now Ive learned to love the feeling of going back to the well known. Madrid is my family and friends. They are my first influences, who pushed me into willing to know about art, photography, cinema\n\nThen New York changed the way I looked at things, everything was new, different, interesting I met great people from all around the world and a lot of photographers with different points of view. New York gave me a global vision. And of course I took a little bit of the pop art culture and cinema.\n\nParis is another story. Sometimes it feels like home and sometimes the city pushes you away its a hard place to live in. But still when you walk the streets you feel surrounded by history here Ive learned to pay attention to small details. Theres a feeling of yearning around the city, they dont want to let go of the past. So you find yourself on a battlefield between the modern Paris and the remains of the greatest periods of France.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CZ: </strong>You have done some advertisements in Spain; does the knowledge you have as a photographer help you when on the other side of the camera as a model?\n\n<strong>Jael: </strong>Atthat time I wasnt interested in photography at all but at least now I know how it feels to be on the other side as a model.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CZ: </strong>How did you get involved in performing monologue for an event at the Mother''s of Plaza de Mayo in Spain?\n\n<strong>Jael: </strong>I wrote a short text years ago, I think I was around 17 or 18, about the fear of being alone My father was part of a theater cycle called Teatro por la identidad (Theater for the Identity) that was taking place in Madrid in 2005, my writing worked out to be perfect as the voice of the five hundred kids victim to the military dictatorship in Argentina.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CZ: </strong>Tell me about NY and the School of Visual Arts.\n\n<strong>Jael: </strong>For six years now, moving to NY is all Ive wanted to do. The SVA plan is just an undeveloped idea of applying for an MFA in Digital Photography next fall Im still thinking about it. But, Ill make it to NY one day just dont know when.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CZ: </strong>You wear the same series of layered necklaces pretty consistently; do they hold significant importance?\n\n<strong>Jael: </strong>When I moved to Paris my mother gave me the hand of Hamsa (a Jewish symbol), and my father the Star of David, and I wear an anchor too that represents my two best friends. So I have them all close.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CZ: </strong>You''re only allowed to put on one accessory in the morning: what''s it going to be?\n\n<strong>Jael: </strong>Sunglasses, no doubt.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CZ: </strong>Style icon: Nicole Richie or Leigh Lezark?\n\n<strong>Jael: </strong>Long live Leigh Lezark!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CZ: </strong>What is the biggest influence on your daily style?\n\n<strong>Jael: </strong>Mood, hours of sleep mostly I cant say comfort sometimes Im out for hours and I cant keep asking myself <em>why did I decide to wear this or that</em> I wear what I feel like wearing as long as Im dressed in black.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CZ: </strong>Is there one person in your life that you can definitely say has influenced your style?\n\n<strong>Jael: </strong>Theres not one person in particular Bettie Page, Betty Brosmer, Janelle Monae and Jean Seberg: Pin-ups when it comes to hair style and tomboy look for clothing\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CZ: </strong>What is your philosophy when it comes to accessorizing?\n\n<strong>Jael: </strong>Accessories complete the look. Theyre needed!\n\n<a href="http://www.jaellevi.com/"><img class="size-full wp-image-7460 aligncenter" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/jael.jpg" alt="" width="550" height="329" /></a>\n<p style="text-align: center"><a href="http://www.jaellevi.com/" target="_blank">Click to see more of Jael''s photography</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center">Jael''s blogs: <strong><a href="http://greenoverblack.blogspot.com/" target="_blank">green over black</a></strong> &amp; <strong><a href="http://sendmepostcards.tumblr.com/" target="_blank">send me postcards</a></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: center"><strong> </strong></p>\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>\n<div>An<a title="http://ICUINPARIS.COM/" href="http://icuinparis.com/" target="_blank">ICUINPARIS.COM</a> Interview Production.</div>\n<div><a title="http://ICUINPARIS.COM/" href="http://icuinparis.com/" target="_blank">ICUINPARIS.COM</a> 2011 All Rights Reserved.</div>\n</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n<p style="text-align: center">&nbsp;</p>', 'Jael Levi: ICU Exclusive Interview with the Talented Young Photographer', 'ICU first got to know Jael Levi as photographer Christian Geisselmann''s assistant, and we have since come to regard her as an incredibly talented photographer in her own right as well as an arbiter of her own unique style.  Though she considers Madrid her home, she dresses with the global influence of her experiences living in New York and now Paris. The ICU team recently had the pleasure of sitting down with Jael to find out more about her personal style and creative vision that permeates her photography, videos and multimedia blogs...', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'jael-levi-icu-exclusive-interview-with-the-talented-young-photographer', '', '', '2011-11-17 11:09:27', '2011-11-17 10:09:27', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=7457', 0, 'post', '', 0),
