(7495, 9, '2011-11-22 11:13:56', '2011-11-22 10:13:56', 'It''s time for another fabulous and exclusive ICU collaboration from our resident fashion illustrator, Laura Geddes and streel style photographer, Laura Wassermann. Iconographic symbols, tarnished gunmetal silver and deep turquoise stones make for an interesting pairing captured so brilliantly by Laura W on the streets of Paris, and endearingly rendered by Laura G. Scroll down to see what the artists themselves were thinking when they captured these beautiful necklaces.\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/lauras6.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-7497" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/lauras6.jpg" alt="icu fashion illustration" width="650" height="994" /></a>\n\n<em>Laura Wassermann''s Illustration Inspiration:</em>\n\n"I absolutely loved how these gorgeous turquoise necklaces were worn over a placket-covered button up, perhaps unintended, but the minimalistic, clean and well tailored shirt in contrast to these classic, cool gems worked perfectly."\n\n<em>Laura Geddes'' Illustration Inspiration:</em>\n\n"The necklaces work so well together because they are a pair. So I drew sisters, friends, lovers... However you want to interpret their intimacy, they are a pair."\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/11/08/icu-exclusive-paris-street-style-fashion-illustration-3/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-7500" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/thumbnail_5.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="352" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/10/25/icu-exclusive-paris-street-style-fashion-illustration-2/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-7496" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/jpg1" alt="" width="200" height="459" /><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/10/11/paris-street-style-fashion-illustration/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-7499" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/thumbnail-21.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="459" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/09/27/icu-exclusive-paris-street-style-fashion-illustration/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-7498" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/thumbnail-11.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="276" /></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2011/09/13/an-exclusive-collaboration-of-inspired-inspiration/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-7501" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/thumbnail1.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="357" /></a></a>', 'ICU Exclusive: Paris Street Style &amp; Fashion Illustration', 'It''s time for another fabulous and exclusive ICU collaboration from our resident fashion illustrator, Laura Geddes and streel style photographer, Laura Wassermann.  Iconographic symbols, tarnished gunmetal silver and deep turquoise stones make for an interesting pairing captured so brilliantly by Laura W on the streets of Paris, and endearingly rendered by Laura G.  Scroll down to see what the artists themselves were thinking when they captured these beautiful necklaces.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'icu-exclusive-paris-street-style-fashion-illustration-4', '', '', '2011-11-22 11:13:56', '2011-11-22 10:13:56', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=7495', 0, 'post', '', 0);
