(7821, 9, '2012-01-12 12:54:02', '2012-01-12 11:54:02', '<p style="text-align: justify">We first set our sights on Alessandra Montani when she modeled for photographer <strong><a href="http://christiangeisselmann.com/" target="_blank">Christian Geisselmann</a></strong> in Cocoon Magazine''s "Paris Punk Deluxe".</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify">Drawn to her androgynous appeal and unique attitude, she was our top choice for <strong><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/" target="_blank">ICU''</a></strong>s latest photoshoot for <em><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/shop-independent-designer-accessories.html?style_4=135" target="_blank">Collection IV</a></em>.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify">Pleased with her humility behind the scenes and performance in front of the camera we instantly wanted to know more. Now back in her native Brazil, Alessandra took the time to answer a few of our questions, read below to see just why we fell for this Brazilian bombshell in the first place.\n\n-Christina Zervanos, Director of Media &amp; Press Relations, ICUinParis.com</p>\n<a title="ICUINPARIS.COM_NOOT_BIJOUX" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/lookbook" target="_blank"><img class="size-full wp-image-7830 aligncenter" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/ICUINPARIS_NOOT_BIJOUX.jpg" alt="ICUINPARIS_NOOT_BIJOUX" width="640" height="505" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CZ</strong>: <em><strong>An incredibly gifted model, you have been afforded the tremendous opportunity of world travel. Highlight your favorite destinations.</strong></em>\n\n<strong>Alessandra: </strong>Thank you for the incredible gifted model, lol! So my favorite destinations are Paris, New York and Hong Kong. They are different but all make me feel home, extremely happy being there-- a great vibe.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CZ: <em>From Brazil, you have traveled extensively in very differing cities (New York, Paris, Milan, etc.); Does one city speak to you more? Why?</em></strong>\n\n<strong>Alessandra: </strong>Wow, it''s hard to choose one... but I can say that Paris spoke to me more, that city is magical! There are always interesting places to go, something cool to do and everything is beautiful!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CZ: <em>Having modeled in print, runway and multimedia, is there one you prefer most? Why?</em></strong>\n\n<strong>Alessandra: </strong>Yeah for sure runway! It''s super exciting! I''m there seconds before walking and those butterflies in my stomach are unique. I love the feeling!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CZ: <em>What are the elements of a successful shooting for you?</em></strong>\n\n<strong>Alessandra: </strong>Photographer and model on the same wavelength, a good production, and music always helps!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CZ: <em>Share with us your most terrible shooting experience.</em></strong>\n\n<strong>Alessandra: </strong>It was an outside shooting for a wedding magazine, those super heavy dresses (which I had to play around with), under a killing sun (I bet it was 40 degrees), and the team was working so slowly you have no idea. Only eight looks but it took the whole day to get done and I was melting the whole time... I just know that was terrible!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>CZ: <em>Do other models inspire you, or is it strictly a personal art form for you?</em></strong>\n\n<strong>Alessandra: </strong>At the beginning yes, other models inspired me, which I think is normal. Nowadays I admire some. But for sure it''s a personal art, your own style, attitude...\n\n<a rel="https://www.icuinparis.com/lookbook" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/ICU_ALES.jpg" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-7827" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/ICU_ALES.jpg" alt="icuinparis.com " width="480" height="673" /></a>\n<p style="text-align: justify"><strong>CZ: <em>Can you articulate how you transform into a certain role or part when modeling?</em></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify"><strong>Alessandra:</strong> It''s like acting but being myself at the same time... like playing in front of the mirror when you are alone, I focus on the proposal and just go with the flow... music inspires me a lot and the power comes out. Lol!</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify"><strong>CZ: <em>Does fashion play a strong influence in your daily life, or is it solely a part of your work?</em></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify"><strong>Alessandra: </strong>It is solely a part of my work, although I like a lot of fashion it doesn''t influence much in my daily life.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify"><strong>CZ: <em>Tell us about your favorite shoot: theme, vibe, music if any, styling, energy of the photographer, location...</em></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify"><strong>Alessandra: </strong>I can say that was with you guys for <strong><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/" target="_blank">ICU</a></strong>! Seriously, I never got so excited like that during a shoot, it was an incredible vibe. The whole team was amazing! The photographer, <strong><a href="http://christiangeisselmann.com/" target="_blank">Christian Geisselmann</a></strong>-- that guy rocks and I always feel so free and comfortable with him, impossible not to absorb that energy. I love rock-n-roll and during this shooting there is one special song Kid Rock''s <em>Bawitdaba</em>!</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify"><strong>CZ:</strong> <em>A model for seven years, you have obviously modeled many different styles, some of which I am sure are very different from your own; Tell us about your personal style, and what it is like to often times step entirely away from that.</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify"><strong>Alessandra: </strong>Before having short hair 99% of the jobs weren''t at all my style which was great to learn how to interpret, pose, act-- to be a model! I can be whatever you guys want! Nowadays they pick me for stuff that is really my style, I guess because of the short hair and my personal style which is kind of boyish, rock-n-roll, trash, torn clothing...</p>\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com"><img class="size-full wp-image-7823 aligncenter" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/alessandra-montani.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="396" /></a>\n<p style="text-align: center">Click <strong><a title="icuinparis.com" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/lookbook" target="_blank">here</a></strong> to see more of Alessandra''s work for ICU.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center">Click <strong><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/category/notable-news-people/" target="_blank">here</a></strong> to read more ICU exclusive interviews.</p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n<div><strong>An<a title="http://ICUINPARIS.COM/" href="http://icuinparis.com/" target="_blank">ICUINPARIS.COM</a> Interview Production.</strong></div>\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>\n<div><a title="http://ICUINPARIS.COM/" href="http://icuinparis.com/" target="_blank">ICUINPARIS.COM</a> 2011 All Rights Reserved.</div>\n</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>', 'Alessandra Montani: ICU Exclusive Interview with the International Model', 'We first set our sights on Alessandra Montani when she modeled for photographer Christian Geisselmann in Cocoon Magazine''s "Paris Punk Deluxe".  Drawn to her androgynous appeal and unique attitude, she was our top choice for ICU''s latest photoshoot for Collection IV.  Pleased with her humility behind the scenes and performance in front of the camera we instantly wanted to know more.  Now back in her native Brazil, Alessandra took the time to answer a few of our questions, read below to see just why we fell in love with her in the first place.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'alessandra-montani-icu-exclusive-interview-with-the-international-model', '', '', '2012-01-12 12:54:02', '2012-01-12 11:54:02', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=7821', 0, 'post', '', 0),
