(7936, 9, '2012-02-06 11:59:49', '2012-02-06 10:59:49', '<a href="http://www.blackchapel.fr/"><img class="size-full wp-image-7938 aligncenter" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/Screen-shot-2012-02-06-at-10.30.03-AM.png" alt="" width="600" height="309" /></a>\n\nIn just one year, <strong>Anne-Clotilde Obeniche</strong>, the designer behind fashion label <strong><a href="www.blackchapel.fr" target="_blank">BlackChapel</a></strong>, has accomplished an impressive success. Coming from a family of artists and holding with her a degree from <em>LInstitut Suprieur des Arts Appliqus</em>, she creates a dark, complex and mysterious universe through her collections. With a breadth of influences from Pre-Raphaelite art and Christian iconography, <strong><a href="www.blackchapel.fr" target="_blank">BlackChapel </a></strong>explores a new spiritual and idealistic world within which people are free to lose themselves. We experience each collection as a real and complete existence with clothes, photos, videos and illustrations.\n<p style="text-align: left"><img class="size-full wp-image-7939 alignright" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/blackchapel1.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="425" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: left"><strong>Anne-Clotilde</strong> brings a style and personality to the <strong><a href="www.blackchapel.fr" target="_blank">BlackChapel </a></strong>woman, mixing straight lines and a range of deep colors to enhancethebeauty of the spiritual soul. By using an abundance of religious symbolism the prejudices of our society are questioned. Is this ambition to break the system of codes a way to stand out and attract more and more followers? Or is it simply a desire to assert personal opinions and bring a thoughtful awareness to fashion?</p>\nIt is <strong><a href="www.blackchapel.fr" target="_blank">BlackChapel''s</a></strong> genuine mystery that is so easy to fall in love with. We love the style of the collection, the inspirations behind it, and <strong>Anne-Clotilde''s</strong> desire and ambition to grow professionally. Recalling <strong><a href="www.blackchapel.fr" target="_blank">BlackChapel''s</a></strong> October 2011 Pop Up store exhibition in Paris, we wait with baited breath for the new collection and cross our fingers that an expansion into men''s clothing is somewhere in the future for this magical universe.\n\nThank you to <strong>Anne-Clotilde</strong> for this collaboration!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<em>- Erik Raynal</em>\n\n&nbsp;\n<p style="text-align: center"><a href="http://www.blackchapel.fr/"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center"><strong><a href="www.blackchapel.fr" target="_blank">www.blackchapel.fr</a></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center"><strong><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?s=erik+raynal&amp;submit.x=0&amp;submit.y=0" target="_blank">Read more contributions from Erik Raynal</a></strong></p>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'BLACKCHAPEL: Between Mystery &amp; Elegance the New Parisian Brand Creates a Buzz', 'BLACKCHAPEL: Between Mystery &amp; Elegance the New Parisian Brand Creates a Buzz', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'blackchapel-between-mystery-elegance-the-new-parisian-brand-creates-a-buzz', '', '', '2012-02-06 11:59:49', '2012-02-06 10:59:49', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=7936', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(7953, 9, '2012-02-06 12:09:01', '2012-02-06 11:09:01', '<a href="http://www.blackchapel.fr/"><img class="size-full wp-image-7938 aligncenter" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/Screen-shot-2012-02-06-at-10.30.03-AM.png" alt="" width="600" height="309" /></a>\n\n<!-- p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px ''Times New Roman''} -->Depuis maintenant plus dun an, <strong>Anne-Clotilde Obniche</strong> (cratrice de la marque <strong><a href="http://www.blackchapel.fr/" target="_blank">Blackchapel</a></strong>) connat un rel premier succs. La jeune cratrice, diplme de LISAA (Institut Suprieur des Arts Appliqus) et issue dune famille desthtes; explore et nous montre un univers sombre, recherch et pointubien plus donc quune simple ligne de vtement avant-gardiste. <em><strong><a href="http://www.blackchapel.fr/" target="_blank">Blackchapel</a></strong> </em>propose un monde spirituel et idaliste o la recherche dun monde inconnu et incompris fascine. Cest  travers des influences diverses comme le symbolisme, le pr-raphaeliste ou le christianismeque<em> <strong><a href="http://www.blackchapel.fr/" target="_blank">Blackchapel</a></strong></em> retient notre attention. Il est rare de voir tout un univers (habillement, photos, vidos, illustrations, inspirations) derrire,  premire vue, une collection de vtement nouvelle.\n<p style="text-align: left"><img class="size-full wp-image-7939 alignright" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/blackchapel1.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="425" />Anne-Clotilde apporte un style et une personnalit  ltre <em><strong><a href="http://www.blackchapel.fr/" target="_blank">Blackchapel</a></strong></em> (actuellement fminin) en misant sur des lignes bien dfinies, sur un mlange de couleurs affirm sublimant alors lme spirituel de la personne.</p>\nPlus prcisment, la marque joue sur les codes de la religion en les utilisant abondamment; volont premire pour la cratrice de rompre avec les prjugs sur la religion. Mais ceci est-il un moyen dattirer encore plus lattention? ou bien simple volont daffirmer un point de vue?\n<p style="text-align: left">Quoi quil en soit, le mystre <em><strong><a href="http://www.blackchapel.fr/" target="_blank">Blackchapel</a></strong></em> est entier et sest bien ce qui nous captive davantage. On aime le style en lui-mme de la collection, les inspirations mme de la cratrice et cette volont daller encore plus loin professionnellement.</p>\n\n<!-- p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px ''Times New Roman''} -->On retient aussi la fabuleuse exposition de la marque en octobre dernier au Popup Store dans le XIe arrondissement, on attend avec impatience la prochaine collection et on espre aussi voir se dessiner lhomme <em><strong><a href="http://www.blackchapel.fr/" target="_blank">Blackchapel</a></strong></em>.\n\nUn grand merci  <strong>Anne-Clotilde</strong> pour cette nime collaboration.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<em>- Erik Raynal</em>\n\n&nbsp;\n<p style="text-align: center"><a href="http://www.blackchapel.fr/"></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center"><strong><a href="www.blackchapel.fr" target="_blank">www.blackchapel.fr</a></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center"><strong><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?s=erik+raynal&amp;submit.x=0&amp;submit.y=0" target="_blank">Pour voir plus de Erik Raynal</a></strong></p>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'BLACKCHAPEL, entre mystre et lgance, la jeune marque en plein essor sur Paris', 'BLACKCHAPEL, entre mystre et lgance, la jeune marque en plein essor sur Paris', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'blackchapel-entre-mystere-et-elegance-la-jeune-marque-en-plein-essor-sur-paris', '', '', '2012-02-06 12:09:01', '2012-02-06 11:09:01', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=7953', 0, 'post', '', 0),
