(8099, 11, '2012-03-08 09:06:01', '2012-03-08 08:06:01', '&nbsp;\n\n<em><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/NDIDO-319-Custom-Name.jpg"></a></em>\n\n<em><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/NDIDO-319-Custom-Name.jpg"></a><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/NDIDI_O_ICUINPARIS.COM_.jpg"><img class="alignright" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/NDIDI_O_ICUINPARIS.COM_-1024x780.jpg" alt="" width="641" height="487" /></a></em>\n\n<em>I had the pleasure of meeting Ndidi O. socially this past year, unaware of her shining talent as a musician. </em><em>Immediately, however, it was clear Ndidi is a woman of depth, understanding, passion and humor.</em>\n\n<em>Now signed to <strong>Universal Music France</strong>, taking Europe and now America by storm, her style is often classified as jazz and blues, but she combines several musical genres in her songs including surf music, electric blues, gospel, and country. </em>\n\n<em>She is the absolute mix of pure intrigue on her own. To see her on stage is like watching the emergence of a star to be reckoned with. Magnetic in both inner and outer beauty, and most certainly personality, Ndidi undoubtedly creates music that moves you- lyrics often trickling into your soul catapulting personal reflection.</em>\n\n<em>A true great album is one you can listen to over and over, each time taken on a journey. Ndidi is that artist who is gifting listeners with an album difficult to escape.</em>\n\n- Christina Zervanos,<span style="color: #888888"><em>Director of Media &amp; PR, ICUinPARIS.com</em></span>\n<div style="text-align: center"></div>\n<p style="text-align: center"><span style="color: #888888"><em>\n</em></span></p>\n<span style="color: #888888"><em>____________________________________________</em></span>\n<!--more-->\n\n<strong>CZ: You have said your latest album, <em><a title="universal music, ndidi o" href="http://www.universalmusic.fr/ndidi-o/album/ndidi-o-the-escape/" target="_blank">The Escape</a></em>, is more of a ''projection of the future instead of a reaction to the past; how did you come to this outlook?</strong>\n\n<strong>Ndidi:</strong> Well I was traveling a lot while writing this record. I was living between Paris and Vancouver; a serious relationship I had been in for years was ending... so, while writing this I was really moving into my future.\n\n<strong>CZ: The songs on your last album were all ''born when moving somewhere: in a train, between planes, back in a train''; what is it about a nomadic lifestyle that inspires you?</strong>\n\n<strong>Ndidi:</strong> I am not sure, I have moved around my entire life, so really this sort of lifestyle is what I know. Something I do love about a nomadic life is that you are constantly meeting new people, and having wild experiences which for a writer are equivalent to gold.\n\n<strong>CZ: Have you written one lyric, song, or composition you think embodies you?</strong>\n\n<strong>Ndidi:</strong> Well, I have written a lot of songs about cats, well actually just one... but I happen to love those furry little creatures. They are so independent and mysterious. I can relate.\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n[caption id="attachment_8136" align="alignleft" width="434" caption="From left to rigtt: Ndidi O., Robin Foster &amp; Dave Pen"]<strong><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/ndidi-o-robin-foster-dave-pen.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-8136 " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/ndidi-o-robin-foster-dave-pen.jpg" alt="" width="434" height="289" /></a></strong>[/caption]\n\n<strong>CZ: You recently worked with <a title="robin foster interview for icuinparis.com" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2012/02/21/icus-exclusive-interview-with-robin-foster/" target="_blank">Robin Foster</a> on his last album; what do you gain from collaborating with other artists?</strong>\n\n<strong>Ndidi: </strong>I love , love, love collaborating with other artists. Working with others always enriches your knowledge of the craft. I wish I could collaborate more. (<em><a title="ndidi o, robin foster" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZgtT3HRdyW8" target="_blank">Listen to the collaboration between Ndidi O. &amp; Robin Foster here</a>)</em>\n\n<strong>CZ: Alive or dead, which artist would you most wish to work with? Why?</strong>\n\n<strong>Ndidi: </strong>I would love to work with Millie Jackson because she is one sarcastic, fabulous woman. Basically, I would love to sit next to her and hear all her stories.\n\n<strong>CZ: Given that you play the guitar and piano, when you are writing lyrics do you imagine which instrument(s) will compliment them?</strong>\n\n<strong>Ndidi: </strong>Not so much. I just write with whatever instrument is available.\n\n<strong>CZ: From Vancouver to NY, NY to Paris, and around Europe is there one performance that lit your world on fire? </strong>\n\n<strong>Ndidi:</strong> Hmm, that question''s is oh so hard :) Each performance lights my fire; I love performing more than anything, so every single show just makes my heart sing.\n\n<strong>CZ: Of your three albums, are you proudest of one particular song? Why?</strong>\n\n<strong>Ndidi:</strong> Hmm... I don''t have a particular favorite; I like different songs for different reasons.\n\n<strong>CZ: Do you sit down with the intention of song-writing, or is the process organic, often inspiring you to write at impromptu times?</strong>\n\n<strong>Ndidi:</strong> It''s a little of both. Sometimes I set up my writing "station" (it''s just my couch and I prop my guitar up against it) and I try and focus. Sometimes this works. Other times I will wake up in the middle of the night and have a song in my head - I''ll record it to my voicemail and work on it later.\n\n[caption id="attachment_8130" align="alignright" width="397" caption="Ndidi O. In Concert - European Tour"]<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/NdidiO2.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-8130" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/NdidiO2.jpg" alt="" width="397" height="265" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<strong>CZ: What do you want your listeners to take from your music?</strong>\n\n<strong>Ndidi:</strong> I hope that listeners can well, be entertained by my music, perhaps moved, and maybe, just maybe if the song is good enough feel some sort of emotional relief.\n\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/NDIDO-404_filter.jpg"></a><strong>CZ: What are the elements of a great album for you?</strong>\n\n<strong>Ndidi:</strong> Movement: a great album is a journey... one that changes over time.\n\n<strong>CZ: How does your everyday life intersect with your life as a performer? Similarly, how do they remain distant from one another and separately sacred?</strong>\n\n<strong>Ndidi:</strong> I am not sure, I tend to be a little quieter off of the stage, but that same sort of energy does tend to make an appearance after a few cocktails... I''m not going to lie! I think it''s impossible to truly separate the self, so I just try and stay quiet in the down times and be free in the up times... does that answer anything?? I think I need to stop drinking cocktails while answering interviews, ha.\n\n<strong>CZ: How do you want to be remembered as an artist?</strong>\n\n<strong>Ndidi:</strong> As a fun artist, and an original.\n<p style="text-align: center">For all tour dates visit the Ndidi O. website here:<a title="http://ndidio.net/" href="http://ndidio.net/" target="_blank">http://ndidio.net/</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center">Ndidi O.<strong>The Escape</strong> is on sale in all major music stores and Itunes.</p>\n<a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/big-collage-ndidi-o1.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-8150 aligncenter" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/big-collage-ndidi-o1.jpg" alt="" width="915" height="458" /></a>\n<p style="text-align: center">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: center">Photos:<a title="Christian Geisselmann" href="http://www.ChristianGeisselmann.com/" target="_blank">Christian Geisselmann</a></p>\n\n<div style="text-align: center"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?s=interview&amp;submit.x=0&amp;submit.y=0" target="_blank">Click<strong>here </strong>to read more exclusive ICU interviews.</a></div>\n<div style="text-align: center"><strong>An<a title="http://ICUINPARIS.COM/" href="http://icuinparis.com/" target="_blank">ICUINPARIS.COM</a> Interview Production.</strong></div>\n<p style="text-align: center"><strong> </strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center"><strong> </strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center"><strong> </strong></p>\n\n<div style="text-align: center"><strong><a title="http://ICUINPARIS.COM/" href="http://icuinparis.com/" target="_blank">ICUINPARIS.COM</a> 2011 All Rights Reserved.</strong></div>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'The Escape of Ndidi O. - Exclusive Interview', 'I had the pleasure of meeting Ndidi O socially this past year, unaware of her shining talent as a musician. Immediately, however, it was clear Ndidi is a woman of depth, understanding, passion and humor.\n\nNow signed to Universal Music France, taking Europe and now America by storm, she is the absolute mix of pure intrigue on her own. To see her on stage is like watching the emergence of a star to be reckoned with. Magnetic in both inner and outer beauty, and most certainly personality, Ndidi undoubtedly creates music that moves you- lyrics often trickling into your soul catapulting personal reflection.\n\nA true great album is one you can listen to over and over, each time taken on a journey. Ndidi is that artist who is gifting listeners with an album difficult to escape.\n\n- Christina Zervanos, Director of Media &amp; PR, 