(8209, 4, '2012-10-10 10:26:07', '2012-10-10 08:26:07', '<p style="text-align: left;">One of my absolute favorite places in Paris is a boutique/gallery dedicated to emerging French designers and artists called, <a title="la cour, paris" href="http://www.lacourparis.com/"><strong>La Cour</strong></a>. It is in fact where I discovered beloved <a title="http://www.icuinparis.com" href="http://www.icuinparis.com">ICU</a> designers such as <a title="charlotte martyr " href="https://www.icuinparis.com/shop-independent-designer-accessories.html?designer=29">Charlotte Martyr</a> and <a title="Laurent Desgrange" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/shop-independent-designer-accessories.html?designer=67">Laurent Desgrange</a>. Not to mention other <em>coup de coeurs</em> such as <strong>Galle Constanini, Ysterike, Dominique Denaive, Un Aprs Midi de Chien</strong>, and many others.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Yesterday was a real treat because I had the pleasure of making my visit with Charlotte Martyr and greeted by Martine, La Cour co-owner as well as one of the designers behind the brand, <strong>Un Aprs Midi de Chien.</strong>They have recently expanded the boutique which allows for larger installations of furniture and interior design work. Really great to see the boutique growing as well as the new designer additions. If you have never visited the boutique and love independent design, you absolutely should! Here is the address:</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><em>La Cour</em></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><em>60 Rue Tiquetonne</em></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><em>Paris, 75002</em></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">and the site:<a title="http://www.lacourparis.com/" href="http://www.lacourparis.com/">www.lacourparis.com</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">T''was a good day to take a stroll through Etienne Marcel.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1639.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8220" title="la cour paris" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1639-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="732" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1629.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8210" title="la cour paris" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1629-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="732" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1630.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8211" title="la cour paris" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1630-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="732" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1632.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8213" title="la cour paris, dominique denaive" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1632-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="732" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1633.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8214" title="la cour, paris" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1633-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="732" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1635.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8216" title="la cour, paris" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1635-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="732" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1636.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8217" title="la cour, paris - laurent desgrange" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1636-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="732" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1637.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8218" title="la cour, paris - laurent desgrange" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1637-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="732" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1638.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8219" title="la cour, paris - charlotte martyr" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1638-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="732" /></a></p>', 'Visit to La Cour, Paris', 'One of my absolute favorite places in Paris is a boutique/gallery dedicated to emerging French designers and artists called, La Cour. It is in fact where I discovered beloved ICU designers such as Charlotte Martyr and Laurent Desgrange. Not to mention other coup de coeurs  such as Galle Constanini, Ysterike, Dominique Denaive, Un Aprs Midi de Chien, and many others.\n\nYesterday was a real treat because I had the pleasure of making my visit with Charlotte Martyr and  greeted by Martine, La Cour co-owner as well as one of the designers behind the brand, Un Aprs Midi de Chien. They have recently expanded the boutique which allows for larger installations of furniture and interior design work. Really great to see the boutique growing as well as the new designer additions. If you have never visited the boutique and love independent design, you absolutely should! Here is the address:\n\nLa Cour\n\n60 Rue Tiquetonne\n\nParis, 75002\n\nand the site: http://www.lacourparis.com/\nT''was  a good day to take a stroll through Etienne Marcel.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'visit-to-la-cour-paris', '', '', '2012-10-10 10:26:07', '2012-10-10 08:26:07', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=8209', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(8234, 4, '2012-10-12 11:17:40', '2012-10-12 09:17:40', 'Tuesday night was the vernissage (expo) of<strong><a title="Lavignes Bastille Gallerie" href="http://www.lavignesbastille.com/expos-actuelle.php" target="_blank">"United Dead Artists" -- 400 dessins  vifs / 69 artistes</a></strong>at one of my favorite galleries in Paris, <a title="Lavignes, Bastille" href="http://www.lavignesbastille.com/index.html" target="_blank">Lavignes Bastille</a>. Friend and gallery owner Patrice Landau was present and full of exhaustion from the set-up ; )\n\nThe turn out was fantastic, the works were even more impressive.\n\n&nbsp;\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_16401.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8235" title="Lavignes Bastille Gallerie" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_16401-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="732" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_16411.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8236" title="Lavignes Bastille Gallerie" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_16411-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="732" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_16421.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8237" title="Lavignes Bastille Gallerie" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_16421-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="732" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_16431.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8238" title="Lavignes Bastille Gallerie" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_16431-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="732" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.