(8251, 4, '2012-10-23 12:39:32', '2012-10-23 10:39:32', 'My good friend and designer, Tania Petit, has moved to a brand new atelier at Metro Madeline in Paris. Her brand, NOOT has taken great strides over the past three years and now situated at Madeline, (those who have never visited Paris, Madeline is a beautiful part of the city and a great place for a designer to have her studio).\n\nLast week, I had a short visit at the new space before Tania and I went for lunch at a tiny Cambodian restaurant down the street. She never likes having her picture taken but I''ll keep trying.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1709.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8253" title="noot bijoux, icuinparis.com" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1709-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="732" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Tania, hiding from the camera.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1708.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8252" title="noot bijoux, icuinparis.com" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1708-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="732" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Tania''s new work station. I love seeing her things from the studio she was in before at Montreuil, it''s always surreal to see something in a new environment after you are so used to seeing it someplace else.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1710.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8254" title="noot bijoux, icuinparis.com" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1710-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="732" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Polishing tools.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1712.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8256" title="noot bijoux, icuinparis.com" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1712-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="732" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Tania shares the space with two other jewelry designers.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1713.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8257" title="noot bijoux, icuinparis.com" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1713-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="732" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1711.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8255" title="noot bijoux, icuinparis.com" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/IMG_1711-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="732" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">This is the entrance, it will be a great space for exhibits and vernissages.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">If you ever want to visit Tania I''m sure she would be happy to welcome you with an appointment.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">E-mail her directly at:noot.bijoux@gmail.com</p>', 'Visit to NOOT&#039;s new Atelier  Madeline', 'My good friend and designer, Tania Petit, has moved to a brand new atelier at Metro Madeline in Paris. Her brand, NOOT has taken great strides over the past three years and now situated at Madeline, (those who have never visited Paris, Madeline is a beautiful part of the city and a great place for a designer to have her studio).\n\nLast week, I had a short visit at the new space before Tania and I went for lunch at a tiny Cambodian restaurant down the street. She never likes having her picture taken but I''ll keep trying.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'visit-to-noots-new-atelier-at-metro-madeline', '', '', '2012-10-23 12:39:32', '2012-10-23 10:39:32', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=8251', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(8266, 4, '2012-11-01 18:16:35', '2012-11-01 17:16:35', 'Today was dedicated to brainstorming for <a title="NOOT" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/shop-independent-designer-accessories.html?designer=44" target="_blank">NOOT</a>''s next photo shoot for her FW/13 collection which will dbut in the United States this winter. A perfect time for a little refinement, <a title="Christan Summers" href="http://christansummers.com/" target="_blank">Christan Summers</a>, founder of icuinparis.com also works with designers on their brand positioning for particular markets.\n\nBelow, is a small visual re-cap of the day''s dedication to magazines, books, photographs, poems, sunshine and caf.\n\nYou can view a sneak of NOOT''s FW/13 photo shoot <a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/2012/12/04/noot-bijoux-fw13-14-photo-shoot/">here</a>\n\n[gallery link="file" orderby="rand"]', 'Inspiration Day  Chez NOOT', 'Today was dedicated to brainstorming for NOOT''s next photo shoot for her FW/13 collection which will dbut in the United States this winter. A perfect time for a little refinement, Christan Summers, founder of icuinparis.com also works with designers on their brand positioning for particular markets. ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'inspiration-day-a-chez-noot', '', '', '2012-11-01 18:16:35', '2012-11-01 17:16:35', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=8266', 0, 'post', '', 0),
