(8358, 4, '2009-09-24 13:12:43', '2009-09-24 11:12:43', '<p style="text-align: left;"><em>9.24.09</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em> </em></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-980" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/nylon-tv-and-magazine/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="nylon-tv-and-magazine" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/nylon-tv-and-magazine.jpg" alt="Nylon TV &amp; Magazine" width="480" height="250" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em><a href="http://www.threeasfour.com/" target="_blank">Three as Four</a></em><em> +</em><em><a href="http://www.yoko-ono.com/" target="_blank"> Yoko Ono</a></em></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Brought to us by, </em><em><a href="http://www.nylonmag.com/?section=section&amp;papid=9" target="_blank">Nylon TV</a></em></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Something a little different for a fashion show, and with music that was made made by ''an island''.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="660" height="405" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/Lfn_wv0Mj3s&amp;hl=en&amp;fs=1&amp;border=1" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="660" height="405" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/Lfn_wv0Mj3s&amp;hl=en&amp;fs=1&amp;border=1" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"> </embed></object>\n\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em><span style="font-style: normal;"> </span></em></p>\n<em> </em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<em>9.23.09</em>\n\n<em> </em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-973" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/september-2009/diane-a-shaded-view-on-fashion-film-festival/"><img class="size-full wp-image-973  aligncenter" title="diane-a-shaded-view-on-fashion-film-festival" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/09/diane-a-shaded-view-on-fashion-film-festival.jpg" alt="Diane, A Shaded View on Fashion" width="480" height="720" /></a></p>\n\n\n<a href="http://www.ashadedviewonfashion.com/" target="_blank">A Shaded View on Fashion</a>. An absolute favorite blog of mine is holding The World''s First Annual Fashion Beauty Style Film Festivalin Paris from the 25th-27th of September, 2009. With special guest <a href="http://www.rickowens.eu" target="_blank">Rick Owens</a> as well as artists and creators from all over the world, this is going to be a crazy, unbelievably eccentric and breathtaking experience.\n\nSpecial screenings, <a href="http://www.passagedudesir.com/">Passage Du Dsir</a>.\n\nThe Award Ceremony will be held on October 8th, at <a href="http://www.centrepompidou.fr/" target="_blank">Centre Pompidou</a>.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="480" height="326" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="src" value="http://blip.tv/play/gsQPgZfWCQI%2Em4v" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="480" height="326" src="http://blip.tv/play/gsQPgZfWCQI%2Em4v" allowfullscreen="true"> </embed></object>\n\n<em>9.14.09</em>\n\n<em><strong><a href="http://www.nature.fr/" target="_blank">Nature Bijoux</a></strong>, </em>a French concept and brand. Pulsating the Galeries Lafayette Hausmann in Paris (which may just be every jewelry designer''s dream location) and throughout France.\n\n<em><strong><a href="http://www.nature.fr/" target="_blank">Nature Bijoux</a></strong>, </em>innovative in design, stunning and on top of it all, eco-friendly.\n\n<em>Porter l''emotion...</em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.nature.fr/" target="_blank"><img class="size-full wp-image-895 aligncenter" title="Nature Bijoux, Bijoux, Paris bijoux" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/09/nature-Bijoux.jpg" alt="Nature Bijoux, Paris" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.nature.fr/" target="_blank"><img class="size-full wp-image-897 aligncenter" title="Nature Bijoux, Bijoux Paris, Bijoux" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/09/gal.jpg" alt="Nature Bijoux, Paris" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a title="Nature Bijoux" rel="http://www.nature.fr/" href="http://www.nature.fr/" target="_blank"><img class="size-medium wp-image-898 aligncenter" title="Nature Bijoux, Bijoux Paris, Paris" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/09/blp-300x244.jpg" alt="Nature Bijoux, Paris" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.nature.fr/" target="_blank"><img class="size-full wp-image-896 aligncenter" title="Nature Bijoux, Bijoux, Joaillerie Paris" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/09/pau.jpg" alt="Nature Paris, eco-friendly jewelry" width="194" height="270" /></a></p>\n\n\n<em>9.13.09</em>\n\nIt''s time for Fashion Week. Paris.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><object id="flashObj" classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="404" height="436" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="bgcolor" value="#FFFFFF" /><param name="flashVars" value="videoId=16729908001&amp;linkBaseURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.style.com%2Fvideo&amp;playerID=8558003001&amp;domain=embed&amp;" /><param name="base" value="http://admin.brightcove.com" /><param name="seamlesstabbing" value="false" /><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="swLiveConnect" value="true" /><param name="allowScriptAccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://c.brightcove.com/services/viewer/federated_f9/8558003001?isVid=1&amp;publisherID=1568114478" /><param name="name" value="flashObj" /><param name="flashvars" value="videoId=16729908001&amp;linkBaseURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.style.com%2Fvideo&amp;playerID=8558003001&amp;domain=embed&amp;" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed id="flashObj" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="404" height="436" src="http://c.brightcove.com/services/viewer/federated_f9/8558003001?isVid=1&amp;publisherID=1568114478" name="flashObj" allowscriptaccess="always" swliveconnect="true" allowfullscreen="true" seamlesstabbing="false" base="http://admin.brightcove.com" flashvars="videoId=16729908001&amp;linkBaseURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.style.com%2Fvideo&amp;playerID=8558003001&amp;domain=embed&amp;" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> </embed></object>\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>', 'SEPTEMBER UPDATES', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'september-updates', '', '', '2009-09-24 13:12:43', '2009-09-24 11:12:43', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=8358', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(8361, 4, '2009-07-22 13:13:44', '2009-07-22 11:13:44', '<em>7.22.09</em>\n\nAbsolutely love this.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img style="background-repeat: no-repeat; background-color: #ffffcc; background-image: url(https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/wp-includes/js/tinymce/plugins/media/img/flash.gif); background-position: 50% 50%; border: 1px dotted #cc0000;" title="&quot;allowFullScreen&quot;:&quot;true&quot;,&quot;allowScriptAccess&quot;:&quot;always&quot;,&quot;src&quot;:&quot;http://www.youtube.com/v/MkJHjpxJ9FM&amp;color1=0xb1b1b1&amp;color2=0xcfcfcf&amp;hl=en&amp;feature=player_embedded&amp;fs=1&quot;,&quot;allowfullscreen&quot;:&quot;true&quot;" src="https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/wp-includes/js/tinymce/plugins/media/img/trans.gif" alt="" width="425" height="344" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>7.21.09</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><a href="http://www.daphnasimon.com/" target="_blank">DAPHNA SIMON</a></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Now this is animalistic.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Yes. We wrote animalistic.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">And when you see these designs, you will of course understand. But before we get into show and tell, we must give some well-deserved respect to the creator, goldsmith and designer of each and every one of these pieces.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.daphnasimon.com/dynamic.asp?cid=11155" target="_blank">Daphna Simon</a>. Born in Israel, raised in New Jersey and now back in her home country this young craftswoman has an eye and a hand for incredible design. Carving each and every piece of jewelry out of solid 18k gold and/or silver, Daphna has already made a name for herself in the jewelry industry, and she only launched two years ago!</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Well, we think the hype is well deserved and we thank her for bringing something a little extra-ordinary into the forrest of the jewelry world (nopunintended).</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-466" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/11147-1/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Daphna Simon Signature Leopard Ring" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/11147-1.jpg" alt="Signature Leopard Ring $6900" width="339" height="303" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-467" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/attachment/11210/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Daphna Simon Signature Bear Ring" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/11210.jpg" alt="Signature Solid 18k Gold Bear Ring $6900" width="339" height="303" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-468" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/attachment/12001/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Daphna Simon Signature Bear Ring " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/12001.jpg" alt="Signature Bear Ring in Solid Silver $475" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-469" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/attachment/11146/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Daphna Simon Leopard Necklace" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/11146.jpg" alt="Leopard Necklace solid 18k Gold $2500" width="339" height="303" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<em>7.20.09</em>\n\n<strong><a href="http://www.atelierswarovski.com/Content.Node/autumn-winter/midnightnecklace.en.html#/collections/autumnwinter09" target="_blank">PHILIP CRANGI &amp; SWAROVSKI CRYSTAL</a></strong>\n\nA beloved designer on<a href="http://www.cinsummer.com" target="_blank">CinSummer.com</a>, we have been following Crangi from his<a href="http://shop.gilesandbrother.com/" target="_blank">Giles &amp; Brother collection</a>, to his<a href="https://www.cinsummer.com/index.php#/shop/set/2/37" target="_blank">Academie</a> collection, to<a href="http://www.verawangonweddings.com/Default.aspx" target="_blank">Vera Wang</a>,<a href="http://www.31philliplim.com/" target="_blank">3.1 Philip Lim</a> and now Swarovski Crystal.\n\n<a href="http://www.philipcrangi.com" target="_blank">Crangi</a> was recently quoted on his autumn/winter 2009 Art Deco-inspired Atelier Swarovski collection, "It was really fun to have that collaborative opportunity and explore the wealth of amazing ideas that dont really fit in with the thread of my collection that this gave me a new outlet for.\n\nThe collectionis slightly more sleek and streamlined than his edgy-refined namesake jewellery that has appeared in the recent runways shows or the custom pieces hes designed for 3.1 Phillip Lim, Vera Wang and Jason Wu.\n\nBut this is what Crangi lives for, out of the box designs, materials and shapes.\n\nAnd this is what we live for; unique, innovative designer jewelry. Thank you for feeding our creativepalate.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-455" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/swarovskicrangi_15jun09_pr_bt/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Swarovski &amp; Crangi Collaboration" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/SwarovskiCrangi_15jun09_PR_bt.jpg" alt="A New Kind of Bling: Crangi &amp; Swarovski" width="320" height="360" /></a></p>\nTo view more designs from the collaboration, kindly click<a href="http://www.atelierswarovski.com/Content.Node/autumn-winter/midnightnecklace.en.html#/collections/autumnwinter09" target="_blank">HERE</a>\n<p style="text-align: center;">-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<em>7.9.09</em>\n\n<strong><a href="http://www.christian-lacroix.fr/" target="_blank">CHRISTIAN LACROIX </a></strong>\n\nWhat do you think, is this the beginning of the end for couture fashion? Christian Lacroix isofficiallyclosing his doors this week. No rumors, friends on the inside who work for the man are officially out of a job today.\n\nIts sad. This is art. A form of something true is no longer valuable. I hate that. So, not to write too much, this is my salute, thank you and respect to Mr. Lacroix. A true artist, a pioneer and a man who worked his ass off to create something of his own. That is something to be proud of.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-409" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/article-1198301-059fb239000005dc-585_468x546/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Christian Lacroix" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/article-1198301-059FB239000005DC-585_468x546.jpg" alt="At his final couture show, Christian Lacroix" width="400" height="467" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>7.20.09</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><a href="http://www.ceramosdesign.com/index.htm" target="_blank">CECILIA E. RAMOS</a></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">It was her Snake Knot Necklace made of acrylic and transparent glass beads which initially caught our attention.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Then it was her Herribone Necklaces hand-made from Midori satin.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Then it was her hand painted acrylic cuff bracelets.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">I mean, really, could this woman be anymoreversatilelycreative?</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Trained as aartitectand painter, we can confidently say, she has got real talent.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-430" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/cecilia-ramos-nkl-3/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Cecilia Ramos Snake Knot Necklace" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/cecilia-ramos-nkl-3.jpg" alt="Snake Know Necklace $525" width="400" height="400" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-431" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/celcilia-ramos-nkl-2/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Cecilia Ramos Snake Knot Necklace" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/celcilia-ramos-nkl-2.jpg" alt="Snake Knot Necklace $525" /></a></p>\n<em> Below: </em>And in the daylight...\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-432" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/snakenecklace_glass3/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Cecilia Ramos Snake Know Necklace" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/SnakeNecklace_glass3.jpg" alt="Snake Knot Necklace $525" /></a></p>\n<em>Below: </em>And for the softer and more elegant side of us all, the Herringbone Necklace is a perfect fit.\n\nHand-made from midori satin ribbon, aluminum disks, and sterling silver closures. Measures 18" long.\n\nStriking yet soft, elegant yet bold, day yet night, sweet with a little bit of sexy. Oh, yeah, did we mention its also affordable?\n\nYep. We like it.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-442" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/herringbone_blue/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Cecilia Ramos Herringbone Blue" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/Herringbone_blue.jpg" alt="Herringbone Blue $75" width="460" height="330" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-443" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/herringbone_green/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Cecilia Ramos Herringbone Green" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/Herringbone_green.jpg" alt="Herringbone Green $130" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-444" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/herringbone_black/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Cecilia Ramos Herringbone Black" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/Herringbone_black.jpg" alt="Herringbone Black" /></a></p>\n<em>Below: </em>And to put her painting skills to work, using acrylic paint, ink, paper and collaged metal Ramos creates these cuff bracelets, one by one, by hand, with love and pure creativity.\n\nEach Cuff is finished with water resistant varnish and measure 3" wide. Yes, it will make a small statement. Innovative shall we say?\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-433" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/cecilia-ramos-cuff/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Cecilia Ramos Cuff" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/cecilia-ramos-cuff.jpg" alt="Kiss My Hand Cuff Bracelet $130" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-434" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/sowear_2058_9304574/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Cecilia Ramos, Cuff Bracelet" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/sowear_2058_9304574.jpg" alt="Venus of Milo Cuff Bracelet $130" /></a></p>\n\n</strong>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-441" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/cuffs_perfume/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Cecilia Ramos" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/Cuffs_Perfume.jpg" alt="A Drop of Perfume $130" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>7.16.09</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><a href="http://store.starsandinfinitedarkness.com/wearandtear.html" target="_blank">WEAR-AND-TEAR</a></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.starsandinfinitedarkness.com/">Stars and Infinite Darkness</a> is one of our favorite places to find new and rising indie designers. Overwhelming at times, but they house a good selection and most importantly a unique one.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">So, on the plate today is<a href="http://store.starsandinfinitedarkness.com/wearandtear.html" target="_blank">Wear-and-Tear</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The designer of wear-and-tear, Cheung Lik graduated from the Hong Kong Polytechnic University, Fashion Design. After her graduation, she works in a wide range of design field such as jewelry, costume, photography, art direction, web, cultural exhibitionetc.</p>\nWe like herbecauseshe plays with various materials and forms. She says, "We use an unusual juxtaposition to create the artistic wearing objects." And anyone who chooses to use the word ''juxtaposition'' when describing their design, I automatically love.\n\nView below, the wearable juxtaposition has now begun.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-426" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/wear-and-tera-brac/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="wear-and-tear Bracelet" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/wear-and-tera-brac.jpg" alt="Weaved Tape Bracelet $55" /></a></p>\n<em>Above:<span style="font-style: normal;">Black suede leather weaved into a bracelet with three plated brass chains. Measuring 12.5 cm long and 1 cm wide.</span></em>\n\n<em>Below:</em> Kind of an odd piece of jewelry, which is of course why we like it. But really, it is odd and will stand out and people will mostdefinitelycomment on on it.\n\nCrochet pouch Mixed with plated brass metal chains. Pendant measures, 4 x 2.5 cm and chain 50 cm long.\n\nInnovative, stylish and not so useful (I don''t think you can open the pouch), but it looks like you can ;)\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-427" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/wear-and-tear-crochet/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Wear-and-Tear Crochet Mix" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/wear-and-tear-crochet.jpg" alt="Crochet Mix $75" /></a></p>\n<em>Below:<span style="font-style: normal;">Squeezed Chains. Chains that have squeezed. I like the image of some super hero (yes, red panties and all) squeezing together some chains for me and handing it over with pleasure...yes, we are a bit imaginative over here. </span></em>\n\nPendant measures 8x2 cm. 48 cm of Faux suede holds the plate brass and antique gold chains.\n<p style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: #333333;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-428" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/wear-and-tear-nkl-2/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Wear-and-Tear Squeezed Chains" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/wear-and-tear-nkl-2.jpg" alt="Squeezed Chains, $85" /></a></p>\n<em>Below:</em>\n\n<em> </em><strong>The question of the day:</strong> "how do you make chaotic geometrics?"\n\n<strong>The answer of the day:</strong> Six gold plated alloy circular forms weaved with two plated brass chains chains to make a chaos of geometrics. 14cm in length and 1.5 in width.\n\nBetcha didn''t learn that one in honors geometry class.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-429" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/chaotic-gemetry/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Wear-and-Tear, Chaotic Geometry" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/chaotic-gemetry.jpg" alt="Chaotic Geometry $80" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>7.9.09</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><a href="http://www.katecusack.com/" target="_blank">KATE CUSACK</a></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Now this is innovative. Really, innovative. We first spotted her on Etsy, then on Refinery29, and now we are going to be followers, not because we like to be, butbecausethis woman deserves some more light.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Zipper Jewelry.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">I know, I know. How is that possible, why would you wear jewelry made of zippers? Well, view below my fellow fashionistas, her work is quite stunning.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Below: </em>From the bracelet collection and into ours, these two pieces will undoubtedly catch the attention of your onlookers...oh who''s kidding with all that cheesy fashion garb! ALL of these pieces will catch attention.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">People WILL DEFINITELY stop you in the street because they see any of Cusack''s pieces and ask you where you bought it.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Half of them will not have the guts to buy what she designs, some people just are too scared to pull it off, and that is why you will be the hero and on everyone''s radar for the day. Congratulations.<strong>You will be the jewelry superwoman.</strong> Make sure to tell us how you feel at the end of the day.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-400" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/bracelets_0003-1/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Kate Cusack " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/bracelets_0003-1.jpg" alt="Kate Cusack Zipper Bracelet, $300" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-401" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/bracelets_0008/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Kate Cusack" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/bracelets_0008.jpg" alt="For the Moulin Rouge in us...Cusack Bracelet" /></a></p>\n<em>Below:</em> Tell me from a quick glance this couldn''t pass for a diamond necklace? Just do that quickperipheralglance, you know what I''m talking about...It could pass.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-403" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/necklaces_0013-2/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Kate Cusack" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/necklaces_00131.jpg" alt="Kate Cusack Zipper Necklace" /></a></p>\n<em>Below: </em>And for the grande finale, a calamari, gold disc, cut tire, coral reef, flying saucer, however you want to see it, this necklace is amazing!!! Really, striking. We love this. We want one. Any other takers??\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-404" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/necklaces_0001/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Kate Cusack" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/necklaces_0001.jpg" alt="Kate Cusack Zippet Necklace" /></a></p>\nKate Cusack''s designs are available to view on her<strong><a href="http://www.katecusack.com/" target="_blank">website</a></strong> and you may buy her designs on her<strong><a href="http://www.etsy.com/shop.php?user_id=5175959" target="_blank">Etsy</a></strong> page.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.etsy.com/shop.php?user_id=5175959"></a>-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>7.8.09</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><a href="http://www.mykonos-net.com/en/accessories.html" target="_blank">MYKONOS</a></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">This woman is a dream, really. Her designs are those from a fantasy, but you can actually wear them. Designer, Akiko Kawayangi designs and inspires us from her studio in Tokyo, Japan.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Creating her vision with precious and semi-precious stones, both rough cut and precise molded in brass and solid gold, Ms. Kawayangi has found a solid place in the jewelry realm and in our hearts. :)</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-394" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/brass1/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Mykonos" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/brass1.jpg" alt="Brass Category" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-395" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/gold1/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Mykonos" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/gold1.jpg" alt="Gold Category" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-396" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/roughcut/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Mykonos " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/roughcut.jpg" alt="From the Rough Cut Collection" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-397" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/09ss-19ro/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Mykonos" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/09SS-19RO.jpg" alt="Earrings from the Rough Cut Collection" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n7.2.09\n\n<strong><a href="http://chronique-curiosite.over-blog.com/" target="_blank">CURIOSIT</a></strong>\n\nLast week we had the grand opportunity to visit a friend who is now assisting at the<a href="http://www.suzanne-tarasieve.com/" target="_blank">Galarie Suzanne Tarasieve </a>in the 20tharrondissement (<em>XXearrondissement</em>) of Paris. There was an exposition held named none other than "Jerk Off" with regards to Paris''s Pride weekend. The exposition was oddly fascinating, but the best part were the individuals we met.\n\nOne, Jol RIFF who stole our hearts with his gorgeous smile and fantastically chic and sophisticated blackensemble. Between the melange of French and English speaking we were able to communicate his work and mine. His work is the reason I write today.\n\nJol''s blog,<a href="http://chronique-curiosite.over-blog.com/" target="_blank">Curiosit</a> isundoubtedlyone of the most informative, creative and inspiring info portals for the world of contemporary art. With a keen eye and respected presence, Jol visits numerousexhibitions around Paris day after day<span style="color: #000000;"> and in return, writes about the ones which are worth his credibility, and yes, he has a lot of credibility. </span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;">The blog is in French, so if you don''t know the language, the pictures will do and if and when you make your way to Paris, take a visit to one of the exhibitionsJol claims on his<span style="color: #000000;"> is about the<a href="www.chronique-curiosite.over-blog.com" target="_blank">chronicle</a> blog where he is the redactor and through this he shares up to seven eventsaround a theme every week.</span></span>\n\n<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;">To say the least, we felt very Parisian, contemporary artsy.</span></span>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-368" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/pr-sentation-12/"><img class="aligncenter" style="display: block;" title="Jol RIFF" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/pr-sentation-12.jpg" alt="Jol RIFF" /></a></span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-369" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/portrait-blog-1/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Jol RIFF" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/portrait-blog-1.jpg" alt="Mr. Jol RIFF" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-370" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/attachment/15/"><img class="aligncenter" style="display: block;" title="Jol RIFF" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/15.jpg" alt="Jol RIFF" /></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-371" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/attachment/16/"><img class="aligncenter" style="display: block;" title="Jol RIFF" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/16.jpg" alt="Jol RIFF" /></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-372" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/attachment/17/"><img class="aligncenter" style="display: block;" title="Jol RIFF" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/17.jpg" alt="Jol RIFF" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><em>7.1.09</em></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">CinSummer.com July Design Feature: </span>AA Kinal</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a rel="attachment wp-att-356" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/july-2009/aa-kinal-for-cinsummer22/"><img class="aligncenter" style="display: block;" title="AA Kinal" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/aa-kinal-for-cinsummer22.jpg" alt="AA Kinal" width="440" height="564" /></a>\n</em></p>', 'JULY UPDATES', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'july-updates', '', '', '2009-07-22 13:13:44', '2009-07-22 11:13:44', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=8361', 0, 'post', '', 0);
