(8364, 4, '2012-06-30 13:15:00', '2012-06-30 11:15:00', '<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><em>6.30.09</em></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>HANDLE &amp; SPOUT</strong></p>\n<a href="http://handlespout.bigcartel.com/" target="_blank">Handle &amp; Spout.</a> Craft woman and designers,Corinne Gill and Blake Ramsey.Inspired by 30s and 40s glamour, the duo hand-makes the festive line of accessories and jewelry in their free time out of their New York apartments.\n\nHair pins adorned with silk flowers, disco headbands, leather link headbands and necklaces.\n\nAll of which are perfect for everyday living.\n\n<em>Below: </em>Headbands for the disco lady, for the funky lady, for the classy lady, well, for all the ladies! They are only $35 a pop! That is a good fashion deal.\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-321" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/bluedisco-headband/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Handle &amp; Spout" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/bluedisco-headband.jpg" alt="blue disco headband" width="546" height="410" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-322" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/discoflowers-headbands/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Handle &amp; Spout" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/discoflowers-headbands.jpg" alt="disco flower headbands" /></a></p>\n\n</em>\n\n<em>Below:</em> This is different. Necklaces made from leather links. The gold won''t tarnish.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-323" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/leather-link-nkl-gold/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Handle &amp; Spout" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/leather-link-nkl-gold.jpg" alt="Leather Link Necklace in Gold $75" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Below: </em>We are really lovin these.Flowers made of layered fabric &amp; tulle, attached to a 2" bobby pin.</p>\nSet includes 3 clips in coordinating hues &amp; a range of sizes, from 1.5-3".\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-324" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/hair-pins/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Handle &amp; Spout" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/hair-pins.jpg" alt="Hair Pins $35" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-325" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/whites-hair-pin-sets/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Handle &amp; Spout" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/whites-hair-pin-sets.jpg" alt="Hair Pin Set $35" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>6.18.09</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>ALLUMETTE</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">Natasha Leith Smith, of Allumer is launching a new diffusion line called Allumette exclusively to buy at<a href="http://www.kabiri.co.uk" target="_blank">Kabiri</a>. </span></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">The necklaces are fresh, funky and yes affordable. All 20 which is23.50 for our EU readers and $32.60 for our U.S. crew. </span></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">Something different and colorful to add to that layer look which seems to be sweeping the jewelry industry. </span></strong></p>\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-301" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/allumette_n_group/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Allumette Group Photo" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/allumette_n_group.jpg" alt="Allumette Group Photo" /></a></p>\n\n</strong>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-302" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/allumette_n_green/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Green Allumette" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/allumette_n_green.jpg" alt="Green Allumette" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-303" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/allumette_n_red/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Red Allumette" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/allumette_n_red.jpg" alt="Red Allumette" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">6.16.09</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>ALLY CAPELLINO</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>A bag should really be a bag for life.</strong></p>\nAlly Capellino. A designer we found after we found at<a href="http://www.capsuleshow.com/index.html" target="_blank">Capsule</a>. She will be in<a href="http://www.capsuleshow.com/paris_brandlist.html" target="_blank">Paris for the Capsule show</a>, perfect timing for a little Ally praise.\n\nAlly describes her bags as, "Timeless, but never boring, each piece is made from beautiful durable leathers and fabrics that only improve with age. Forget the idea of the statement bag  with their quiet branding they are meant to be worn, used and loved. People should add something of themselves, so that the bags become theirs not mine.\n\nWe chose a few that are a fit for the beach a few to fall into, and for a winter slide.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-288" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/kimma/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="kimma" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/kimma.jpg" alt="Kimma 168" /></a></p>\n<em>Above: </em><a href="http://allycapellino.co.uk/kimma.html" target="_blank">Kimma</a>.We think, summer sun and fun, no?\n\nLarge hand-knotted tote.Available in:black, blue, tan, yellow\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-289" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/kika/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="kika" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/kika.jpg" alt="Kika 146" /></a></p>\n<em>Above</em>:<a href="http://allycapellino.co.uk/kika.html" target="_blank">Kika</a>. Still thinking summer.\n\nSmall hand-knotted tote &amp; genuine leather. Available inblack, blue, tan &amp; yellow.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-292" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/caramel/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="caramel" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/caramel.jpg" alt="Caramel 154" /></a></p>\n<em>Above:</em> <a href="http://allycapellino.co.uk/caramel.html" target="_blank">Caramel</a>. Falling in to fall.\n\nGorgeous leather bag. Rectangular frame bag with adjustable narrow strap. Interior pocket. Availablein black, grey &amp; tan.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-293" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/dotty/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="dotty" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/dotty.jpg" alt="Dotty 190" /></a></p>\n<em>Above:</em> <a href="http://allycapellino.co.uk/dotty.html">Dotty</a>. Falling, falling cutely with dots.\n\nLarge shopper with fixed straps. Simple magnetic closure. Available inblack, rose.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-294" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/southend-1/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="southend" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/southend-1.jpg" alt="Southend 129" /></a></p>\n<em>Above</em>:<a href="http://allycapellino.co.uk/southend.html" target="_blank">Southend</a>. This bag has a special place in my heart. Those from the home hood, you understand. You also understand winter. Buy this, it will keep your iphone from freezing.\n\nBucket shaped bags with adjustable strap. A external pocket and sections of pockets inside.Available inblue &amp; brown. Genuine leather and canvas bag.\n<p style="text-align: center;">-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<em>6.15.09</em>\n\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="http://www.capsuleshow.com/index.html" target="_blank"><strong>CAPSULE: FASHION TRADE EVENT</strong></a></span>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-278" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/capsule-nk/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Capsule NYC" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/capsule-nk.jpg" alt="Capsule NYC" /></a></p>\nWe are so excited for this. Paris. June 26th - 28th Capsule fashion trade event will be in the Marais, Paris. and we will too.\n\nAnd those who are not on this side of the ocean, don''t worry. Capsule is coming to New York City July 20-21st and then Las Vegas 1-2 of September 2009.\n\nThis is the newest, funkiest, most innovative and out of this trendy fashion world, fashion trade show. Some of the most creative and rising independent designers are found here.\n\nJust check out the vendor list on the Capsule website<em><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> </span></em><a href="http://www.capsuleshow.com/index.html" target="_blank"><em>(</em></a><a style="text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.capsuleshow.com/index.html" target="_blank"><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">click here)</span></em></a><span style="text-decoration: none;"><a style="text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.capsuleshow.com/index.html" target="_blank">.</a> <span style="font-style: normal;"><span style="color: #000000;">The websites alone are an experience.</span></span></span>\n\n<span style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="font-style: normal;"><span style="color: #000000;">So, if you are in the area, and want some company, give us a shout. We will be there.</span></span></span>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-279" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/capsule-paris/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Casule, Paris" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/capsule-paris.jpg" alt="Capsule, Paris" /></a></p>\n\n</em>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">6.15.09</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>DANIELA JACOBS</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Emerging designer, 18 years old and yes. Very good.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Pictures please.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-273" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/daniela/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Daniela Jacobs" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/daniela.jpg" alt="Daniela Jacobs" /></a></p>\n<em>Above:</em> Smiling bright, Daniela Jacobs has reason. She is 18 years old, debuted her first collection under the name, Allora when she was 15 and she is on her way to study at Parson''s this fall. We will keep our eyes and ears open for this one.\n\n<em>Below: </em>Looks from Daniela''s 3rd collection which she recently shared in New York City at Tribeca''s own,<a href="http://roomonline.com/" target="_blank">Room</a>. We love the pallete. Calm yet myseious and sexy. Something for the natural beauty.\n\n<dt style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-274" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/dj2/"><img class="aligncenter" title="Daniela Jacobs 3rd collection" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/dj2.jpg" alt="Looks from Daniela''s 3rd Collection" /></a></dt>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-275" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/dj1/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Looks from Daniela''s 3rd Collection" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/dj1.jpg" alt="Looks from Daniela''s 3rd Collection" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">6.12.09</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>NELLE</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Perfect timing for summer weddings and warm nights on terrace restaurants.<em><a href="http://nellehandbags.com" target="_blank">Nelle</a></em> Handbags, found on Etsy.com have caught our eye and the interest of our pocketbooks, now envious pocketbooks ;)</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">In 2004 Laura Nelli started Nelle, a handbag company focused on creating luxurious handbags and clutches. By combining quality fabrics with her keen attention to detail Nelle handbags and clutches illustrate Lauras deep appreciation of vivid colors and textures. Respect for independent and slow design led Laura to develop a handbag label that prides itself on crafting well-constructed pieces that are produced locally.*</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">From luxurious to affordable, with prices ranging from $65 to $135 here are a few<a href="https://nellehandbags.com/about/" target="_blank">Nelle</a> treasures we saw fit to share.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-242" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/il_fullxfull55665296/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Cherub Clutch" src="https://www.cinsummer.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/il_fullxfull55665296.jpg" alt="Nelle''s Cherub Clutch, $95" /></a></p>\n<em>Above</em>:An envelope style silk charmeuse clutch which is the perfect gift for brides or their maids. Ruffled hand dyed silk ribbon detail with rich black ribbon center.Measures 8 x 5.5\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-213" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/il_fullxfull73214193/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Garden Party Clutch" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/il_fullxfull73214193.jpg" alt="Nelle, Garden Party Clutch $135.00" /></a></p>\n<em>Above</em>:<span style="font-style: normal;">Ribbon and silk organza blossoms combined with black swarovski crystals and wire gold balls make this the perfect piece for any look.Envelope style, measures 7" x 5"</span>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Below:</em> And of course, a post would not be complete without a highlight of jewelry.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The necklace is asymmetrical and adjustable on 14kt gold chain adorned by petersham ribbon and silk organza blooms with Swarovski crystal centers.The necklace is made to order and ships in a matter of 3 weeks, just more of a reason to appreciate designs custom made for you.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-224" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/model1/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Flora Bib Necklace" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/model1.jpg" alt="Nelle, Flora Bib Necklace, $166" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-225" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/necklace1/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Flora Bib Necklace" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/necklace1.jpg" alt="Nelle, Flora Bib Necklace $166" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">*textcreditwww.nellehandbags.com/about</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>6.11.09</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>BIJOU X</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">In honor of this weekend''s Art for the Cash Poor 10th annual event in Philadelphia, one participant we found exceptionally tasteful is jewelry designer, Bijou X.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The designer individually hand-makes each piece of bijou "X" jewelry. And says, "Each vintage or vintage-tooled stamping is lovingly restored, polished and lacquered to protect the finish and then combined with sterling silver or brass chain,crystals and sterling and gold-filled components. With pride, I pay homage to the past with a uniquely modern twist!"</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">We like her homage, so this is ours to her.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-180" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/bijoux-1/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Bijou &quot;X&quot; Laurel Wreath Frame Nkl" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/bijoux-1.jpg" alt="Laurel Wreath Frame Nkl $63" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-181" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/bijoux-2/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Bijou &quot;X&quot; Laurel Wreath Frame Nkl" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/bijoux-2.jpg" alt="Laurel Wreath Frame Necklace " /></a></p>\n<em>Above and Right: </em><a href="http://www.starsandinfinitedarkness.com/bixlawrfrne.html" target="_self">Bijou "X" Laurel Wreath Frame Necklace $63</a>\n\nVintage-tooled and raw brass laurel wreath frame (2 1/8" L)is attached to two sections of antiqued sterling silver chain. Draped in the center of the frame is an additional section of sterling chain, with a Swarovski briolette dangling from one side.\n\n<em>Below: </em><a href="http://www.starsandinfinitedarkness.com/bixvdicaea.html" target="_blank">Bijou "X" Cartouche Earrings $54</a>\n\n2 1/4" L cartouche earrings, suspended from antiqued sterling silver chains are 2" W, leafy shields. Dangling above are silver dagger drops of Czech glass. The cartouches are solid brass. The French earwires and components are gold-filled. The brass has been lacquered to protect the finish.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-182" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/bijou-x-4/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Bijou &quot;X'' Cartouche Earrings" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/bijou-x-4.jpg" alt="Cartouche Earrings $54" /></a></p>\n<em>Below:</em> <a href="http://www.starsandinfinitedarkness.com/bixvdiscea.html" target="_blank">Bijou "X" Victoria Digs $54</a>\n\nInterlacing, 1" L, vintage-tooled grills swing from 14k gold-filled chains. Stones of deep-blue sodalite and lime-green Swarovski crystal drops complete them. The grills are solid brass. The French earwires and components are gold-filled. The brass has been lacquered to protect the finish.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-183" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/june-2009/bijou-x-5/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Bijou &quot;X&quot; Victoria Digs" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/bijou-x-5.jpg" alt="Victoria Digs $54" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<em>\n</em>\n\n<strong><a href="http://www.husseinchalayan.com/#/current_collection.2009.aw09_earthbound/" target="_blank">HUSSEIN CHALAYAN AW09 EARTHBOUND</a></strong>\n\nA tyrant on the fashion scene, one who has always pushed the envelope yet continued to wear success.<a href="www.husseinchalayan.com/#/home/" target="_blank">Hussein Chalayan</a> is a beloved designer on our team and the news of his AW09 Earthbound womenswear collection made our hearts flutter, so here we are, fluttering.\n\nFor the Earthbound lookbook, Chalayan collaborated with photographer<a href="http://www.amytroost.com" target="_blank">Amy Troost</a>, who has worked with magazines like<a href="http://www.id-mag.com/GeneralMenu/" target="_blank">I-D</a> and brands like Rodarte and Balenciaga.The collection is sexy and suggestive, with bondage references and leather corsets hidden under exquisitely tailored creations.\n\nA few images may help to formulate this idea in your mind.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-249" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/cover/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Hussein Chalayan AW09 lookbook" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/cover.jpg" alt="Hussein Chalayan AW09 lookbook" width="435" height="580" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-250" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/3g/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Hussein Chalayan" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/3g.jpg" alt="Hussein Chalayan AW09" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-251" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/5g/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Hussein Chalayan" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/5g.jpg" alt="Hussein Chalayan AW09" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-252" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/4g/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Hussein Chalayan" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/4g.jpg" alt="Hussein Chalayan AW09" /></a></p>\n<em>Below:</em> Looks from the runway.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-257" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/attachment/43/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Hussein Chalayan" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/43.jpg" alt="Hussein Chalayan AW09 Runway" width="363" height="545" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-255" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/attachment/25/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Hussein Chalayan " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/25.jpg" alt="Hussein Chalayan AW09 Runway" width="363" height="545" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-256" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/attachment/40/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Hussein Chalayan" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/40.jpg" alt="Hussein Chalayan AW09 Runway" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n6.11.09\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-177" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/500x500/"><img class="aligncenter" style="display: block;" title="Art for the Cash Poor 10" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/500x500.jpg" alt="500x500" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\nPhiladelphia news!\n\nArt For the Cash Poor 10 annual event starts June 13 until the 14th, 2009.\n\n<a href="http://www.inliquid.com" target="_blank">InLiquid</a>s indoor/outdoor party and sale has more than 100 artisans selling their work for $199 and under. Plus, food, drinks, and music.\n\nA perfect fashion insight and one we love to promote, local designers that range from creators of jewelry, clothing, accessories, furniture, soap, paintings, murals, etc.\n\nThis is a hub for all that is original in the art world of Philadelphia. So, if you live in the neighborhood make a stop.\n\nSat. the 13th &amp; Sun. the 14th, 1-6 p.m.<a href="http://www.cranearts.com" target="_blank">Crane Arts</a> Building, 1400 N. American St. (215-235-3405).Click<a href="http://www.cranearts.com/?page_id=70" target="_blank">HERE</a> for a map and directions.\n<p style="text-align: center;">-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n6.10.09\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-123" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/sc_show-2009/"><img class="aligncenter" style="display: block;" title="SHOW RCA 2009" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/sc_show-2009.jpg" alt="SHOW RCA 2009" /></a></p>\n<a href="http://www.rca.ac.uk/Default.aspx?ContentID=504922&amp;GroupID=504922" target="_blank">SHOW RCA</a> Fashion 2009\n\nToday, the Royal College of Art''s renowned graduate Fashion Show will take place at the College in the Henry Moore Gallery.\n\nThe tickets are sold out, plus, we don''t live in London, but we cannot wait to see and hear about the results and the looks which steal the show.\n\nFinal collections by 36 postgraduate students will be showcased in a catwalk presentation that includes menswear, womenswear, knitwear and millinery, alongside static displays of footwear and accessory design.\n\nSHOW RCAis a way for the college to open their doors to the public while testing the art and talent of their graduating students. An unveiling, if you may.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/fashion-show-2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="SHOW RCA 2009" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/fashion-show-2.jpg" alt="SHOW RCA Graduate Soren Bach" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-118" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/daily-fashion-insight/fashion-show-1/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="SHOW RCA 2009" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/fashion-show-1.jpg" alt="SHOW RCA 2009 Womenswear, Eva Nip " /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n6.7.09\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.ristobimbiloski.com/collections.php"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Risto Bimbiloski spring/summer ''09" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/risto-lookbook-cs-blog-2.jpg" alt="Risto Bimbiloski spring/summer ''09" /></a></p>\nA light on fashion has begun to spread and the first stop is the beloved<a href="http://castorandpolluxstore.com" target="_blank">Castor &amp; Pollux boutique</a> in NY''s finest, West Village.<em>Burn Rubber 2009: Istok Showroom Great American Road Trip</em>, in collaboration with the NY Times blog,<a href="http://themoment.blogs.nytimes.com" target="_blank">the Moment </a>,a traveling documentary, will highlight different collections from Istok Showroom to boutiques and fashion aficionados across the country.\n\nWe love this.\n\nThe kick-off feature highlights up and comer,<a href="http://www.ristobimbiloski.com" target="_blank">Risto Bimbiloski</a>. The documentary will film the designer and his explanation of the collection, the process, the inspiration.\n\nLaunching in NY, stay tuned for news on when they land in your city.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.ristobimbiloski.com/collections.php"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Risto Bimbiloski spring/summer ''09" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/risto-lookbook-cs-blog.jpg" alt="Risto Bimbiloski spring/summer ''09" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"></p>\n<em>6.7.09 </em>\n\n<strong>ANDREA MAACK</strong>\n\nThis is something quite different. Icelandic artist. Andrea Maack. Clothing and sculpture designer. Perfume creator.\n\nMaack develops perfumes from drawings and sculptures.\n\nInspiring, rising, independent.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.andreamaack.com/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Andrea Maack" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/andrea-maack-cs-blog-1.jpg" alt="ANDREA MAACK " /></a></p>\nMaacks main focus is sculpture, mixing her background in\n\nfashion and design in her creative process. Her current\n\nseries of artworks display simple beauty items in original,\n\nunexpected ways, provoking questions about fashion,\n\nbeauty and consumerism.\n\nResulting in a diverse body of work that infuses the viewer\n\nto a sensory experience.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.andreamaack.com/"><img class="aligncenter" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;" title="Andrea Maack" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/andrea-maack-cs-blog-2.jpg" alt="ANDREA MAACK" /></a></p>\nMaack''s latest projects:\n\n<a href="http://www.andreamaack.com/page2/page2.html" target="_blank">CRAFT</a>\n\nC R A F T seeks inspiration from the world of<em>Haute Couture</em> with emphasis on the fabrics/materials and the work of the artisans.\n\nFor C R A F T Maack created her own fabric out of semi transparent acid stain paper with her signature drawing pattern, to create a one-off garment designed by collaborator Cedric Rivrain. The piece was custom fitted on an haute-couture mannequin.\n\n<a href="http://www.andreamaack.com/page0/page0.html" target="_blank">SMART</a>\n\nS M A R T is customized perfume made by artis Andrea Maack. The perfume comes in an edition of four 50 ml bottles, all hand carved with a matching boxes .\n\nS M A R T is a unisex perfume, a complex woody/oriental fragrance that starts out fresh, fruity and green. The base is musky and leathery with a hint of amber and the middle is warm and woody. The formula makes for an addictive, long lasting scent. Escorting the scent is a pencil drawing made up of 252 individual blotters, all signed and numbered.\n\n* Text credit:www.andreamaack.com\n<p style="text-align: center;">-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>', 'JUNE UPDATES', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'june-updates', '', '', '2012-06-30 13:15:00', '2012-06-30 11:15:00', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=8364', 0, 'post', '', 2),
