illiamsburg, AEA &amp; Beautiful Jewels', 'Back in New York and happy to see AEA Jewelry designer, Adrienne Emily this morning for breakfast in Williamsburg at Marlow & Sons. We chatted about the new collection... it''s BEAUTIFUL!! You will love it ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'coffee-williamsburg-aea-beautiful-jewels', '', '', '2012-11-29 04:32:20', '2012-11-29 03:32:20', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=8612', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(8620, 4, '2012-11-30 04:41:17', '2012-11-30 03:41:17', 'This evening I made a quick stop to <a title="open house gallery " href="http://openhouse.me/" target="_blank">OPEN HOUSE GALLERY</a> on Bowery in Manhattan''s Lower East Side to meet <a title="tipi thieves" href="http://tipithieves.com/" target="_blank">Tipi Thieves</a>(aka Felipa Merida), and visit his solo exhibit entitled POLAR. The pieces are truly impressive, the time and patience that must go into each is what really sets them apart. Literally, you see the hundreds upon thousands of lines drawn in order to create one part of a massive image. He uses water paint and ink and mixes the two for a balanced finish.\n\nThis was a treat as his work is rarely exhibited, as this for him is a side project, he makes his living by working in the fashion industry as a graphic designer.\n\nI was accompanied by Adrienne Alaimo, designer of <a title="aea jewelry, icuinparis.com" href="https://www.icuinparis.com/shop-independent-designer-accessories.html?designer=154" target="_blank">AEA Jewelry</a> - I snagged a photo of her wearing one of her new designs against a shirt that gave the impression Adrienne was not only naked but also covered in tatoos.\n\n&nbsp;\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/IMG_2195.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8621" title="open house gallery on bowery, tipi thieves" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/IMG_2195-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="604" height="604" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/IMG_2196.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8622" title="open house gallery on bowery, tipi thieves" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/IMG_2196-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="604" height="604" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/IMG_2198.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8624" title="open house gallery on bowery, tipi thieves" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/IMG_2198-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="604" height="604" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/IMG_2197.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8623" title="open house gallery on bowery, tipi thieves" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/IMG_2197-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="604" height="604" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/IMG_2199.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8625" title="open house gallery on bowery, tipi thieves" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/IMG_2199-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="604" height="604" /></a></p>', 'Tipi Thieves at Open House Gallery with AEA Jewelry &amp; Tatoo Shirts', 'This evening I made a quick stop to OPEN HOUSE GALLERY on Bowery in Manhattan''s Lower East Side to meet Tipi Thieves (aka Felipa Merida), and visit his solo exhibit entitled POLAR. The pieces are truly impressive, the time and patience that must go into each is what really sets them apart. Literally, you see the hundreds upon thousands of lines drawn in order to create a full head of hair on one of the pieces. ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'tipt-thieves-at-open-house-gallery-with-aea-jewelry-tatoo-shirts', '', '', '2012-11-30 04:41:17', '2012-11-30 03:41:17', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=8620', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(8632, 4, '2012-12-04 05:32:25', '2012-12-04 04:32:25', 'Very excited about the FW/13-14 <a title="Noot Bijoux" href="http://noot.fr/" target="_blank">Noot</a> collection and especially because the ICU team will present it to the US market this winter for the first time ever. icuinparis.com has developed into a virtual sales and consulting firm and we are lucky to have such a growing talent with us.\n\nBefore leaving Paris to return to New York we photographed Noot''s FW/13-14 Collection with photographer, <a title="Christian Geisselmann " href="http://www.ChristianGeisselmann.com" target="_blank">Christian Geisselmann</a> at <a title="light kitchen studio" href="http://lightkitchen.net/" target="_blank">Light Kitchen Studio</a>. Below a couple photos from the shoot and a couple sneak peaks of the results.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/IMG_2081.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8638" title="noot bijoux " src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/IMG_2081-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="604" height="604" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/IMG_2083.jpg"><img class=" wp-image-8637 aligncenter" title="christian geisselmann" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/IMG_2083-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="604" height="604" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/IMG_2082.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8636" title="noot bijoux" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/IMG_2082-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="612" height="612" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/IMG_2090.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8639" title="noot bjoux" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/IMG_2090-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="604" height="453" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>', 'Noot Bijoux FW/13-14 Photo Shoot', 'Very excited about the FW/13-14 Noot collection and especially because the ICU team will present Noot to the US market the winter for the first time ever. icuinparis.com has developed into a virtual sales and consulting firm and we are lucky to have Noot with us. ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'noot-bijoux-fw13-14-photo-shoot', '', '', '2012-12-04 05:32:25', '2012-12-04 04:32:25', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=8632', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(8644, 4, '2012-12-12 16:58:00', '2012-12-12 15:58:00', '<img class="wp-post-image" src="http://www.weheart.co.uk/upload-images/lachapelleburningbeauty1.jpg" alt="Burning Beauty, David LaChapelle" width="496px" />\n\n<em>Amanda As Andy Warhols Marilyn, 2002\n David LaChapelle,\ncourtesy of Fred Torres Collaborations,\nNew York</em>\n\n<strong>Until we have time to get there ourself, we will spread the word about this fantastic exhibit and of course give the below text credit to: <a title="weheart.co.uk" href="http://www.weheart.co.uk/2012/12/11/burning-beauty-david-lachapelle/?utm_source=MadMimi&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=We+Heart+List_+%2341&amp;utm_campaign=20121212_m114674850_We+Heart+List_+%2341&amp;utm_term=list41_lachapelle_jpg" target="_blank">www.weheart.co.uk</a></strong>\n\nWhen an artist is discovered and employed by Andy Warhol, their path to pop culture greatness is laid out before them, but first there has to be the talent and drive to succeed present in spades, and on those fronts there are few in the world of photography that can hold a light meter to<a href="http://www.davidlachapelle.com/">David LaChapelle</a>. His fashion work in the 1990s cemented his place in the photography hall of fame, but even when shooting supermodels, LaChapelles work had the ability to transcend the superficial, and in his most recent non-commercial work that exceptional eye for exposing hidden depths is beautifully, and often unsettlingly, evident.\n\nSpeaking of stellar starts to your career: Stockholm gallery<a href="http://fotografiska.eu/">Fotografiska</a>signed LaChapelle up as their first ever exhibitor, and he is back there with a new collection. Burning Beauty is the Americans largest ever exhibition, focused on his post-2005 independent work. In these images he turns a magnifying glass on the modern world and its inhabitants like a child torturing ants on a hot summer day  what he sees is all at once uncomfortable, even painful, yet darkly humorous. Catch this outstanding collection before 3rd March 2013.\n\n<img src="http://www.weheart.co.uk/upload-images/lachapelleburningbeauty2.jpg" alt="Burning Beauty, David LaChapelle" />\n\n<em>Death By Hamburger, 2002\n David LaChapelle,\ncourtesy of Fred Torres Collaborations,\nNew York</em>\n\n<img src="http://www.weheart.co.uk/upload-images/lachapelleburningbeauty3.jpg" alt="Burning Beauty, David LaChapelle" />\n\n<em>Sarah, 2007\n David LaChapelle,\ncourtesy of Fred Torres Collaborations,\nNew York</em>\n\n<img src="http://www.weheart.co.uk/upload-images/lachapelleburningbeauty4.jpg" alt="Burning Beauty, David LaChapelle" />\n\n<em>Aer the Deluge: Cathedral, 2007\n David LaChapelle,\ncourtesy of Fred Torres Collaborations,\nNew York</em>\n\n<img src="http://www.weheart.co.uk/upload-images/lachapelleburningbeauty5.jpg" alt="Burning Beauty, David LaChapelle" />\n\n<em>Uma Thurman: Gossip, 1997\n David LaChapelle,\ncourtesy of Fred Torres Collaborations,\nNew York</em>\n<div><em>\n</em></div>\n<img src="http://www.weheart.co.uk/upload-images/lachapelleburningbeauty6.jpg" alt="Burning Beauty, David LaChapelle" />\n\n<em>Icarus, 2012\n David LaChapelle,\ncourtesy of Fred Torres Collaborations,\nNew York</em>\n\n<img src="http://www.weheart.co.uk/upload-images/lachapelleburningbeauty7.jpg" alt="Burning Beauty, David LaChapelle" />\n\n<em>The Beatification: Ill Never Let You Part For Youre Always Part of My Heart, 2009\n David LaChapelle,\ncourtesy of Fred Torres Collaborations,\nNew York</em>', 'BURNING BEAUTY, DAVID LACHAPELLE', 'When an artist is discovered and employed by Andy Warhol, their path to pop culture greatness is laid out before them, but first there has to be the talent and drive to succeed present in spades, and on those fronts there are few in the world of photography that can hold a light meter to David LaChapelle. Text credit to:  www.weheart.co.uk', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'burning-beauty-david-lachapelle', '', '', '2012-12-12 16:58:00', '2012-12-12 15:58:00', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=8644', 0, 'post', '', 0),
