(8832, 4, '2013-02-22 14:09:51', '2013-02-22 13:09:51', '<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/IMG_3363.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-8840" title="Capsule NYC 2013" src="https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/IMG_3363-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="604" height="604" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">It''s that time of year again. Trade shows, expos, private appointments and sales. The question is always the same; which trade show is the best for me? Whether you are a designer or a buyer, this question, remains the same. The answer for the two parties can make or break you for the season - in two very different ways.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">As a seasoned trade show exhibitor and visitor, over the years I have watched them develop, sizzle, establish and grow. Therefore, my view on the fashion industries trade shows has changed over the years and continues to adapt to the ever changing market.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">This past week, I exhibited at Capsule NYC 2013 with Unearthen. A jewelry designer from Los Angeles whom I work with as a freelance sales rep.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>', 'Capsule NYC 2013', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2013-02-22 14:09:51', '2013-02-22 13:09:51', '', 0, 'https://www.icuinparis.com/blog/?p=8832', 0, 'post', '', 0),
